f: 1st Group Limited, formerly 1st Available Limited, is engaged in the provision of healthcare and corporate online search and appointment booking services. The Company operates 1stAvailable.com.au, a community Website portal and suite of business and consumer applications, including mobile applications. The Company allows patients to book their healthcare appointments with their preferred healthcare provider through its service online, around the clock, from any Internet-connected device, such as a smartphone, tablet or personal computer. It offers a range of products and services, including Self Checkin Kiosks and Applications, Patient Clipboard Applications, Advertising, Call Centre Applications, easyRECALL Application and easyFEEDBACK Application. Its customers include pharmacies, private practices (doctors, dentists, optometrists, allied services, specialists and natural therapists), radiology, veterinarian, and corporate and government agencies (state, federal and local).

Adslot Limited is engaged in providing trading technology, services and adserving. The Company's trading technology includes Adslot, a media trading technology, and Symphony, a workflow automation technology, which is purpose built for digital media agencies. The Company's Webfilm division offers marketing services to small and medium enterprise (SME) clients. The Company also offers project-based customization of trading technology. The Company's Adserving technology enables advertisers to deliver and measure the performance of inline display advertising, including impressions, clicks and online sales. The Company's geographical segments include APAC, including Australia, New Zealand and Asia; EMEA, including Europe, the Middle East and Africa, and the Americas, including North, Central and South America. The Company also offers Adslot publisher platform. Its Adslot Marketplace brings buyers and sellers together to create new market places and trading opportunities.

Australian Agricultural Projects Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the operation of the olive grove located in Boort, Victoria. The Company is also engaged in the operation of managed investment schemes. The Company serves Victorian Olive Oil Project, Victorian Olive Oil Project II and Peppercorn Estate Limited. The Victorian Olive Oil Project covers an area of approximately 290 hectares. The Victorian Olive Oil Project II covers an area of over 120 hectares. The Peppercorn Estate Limited occupies an area of 110 hectares. Its Victorian Olive Oil Project I has various tree types, including Barnea, Frantoio, Picual, Nevadillo Blanco and Picholine.

Atlas Iron Limited is an iron ore company. The Company's principal activities include the exploration, development, mining and sale of iron ore. It is involved in mining and exporting direct shipping ore (DSO) from its operations in the Northern Pilbara region of Western Australia. Its operations include Wodgina project, which is located approximately 100 kilometers south of Port Hedland through the Great Northern Highway; Abydos mine, which is located over 130 kilometers south-southeast of Port Hedland, and the Mt Webber mine, which is located approximately 230 kilometers south-southeast of Port Hedland. Its expansion projects include Corunna Downs project and McPhee Creek project. Its Davidson Creek Hub DSO Project is located approximately 100 kilometers east of Newman. Its Western Creek DSO Project is a group of tenements situated between 15 kilometers and 50 kilometers west of Newman in the Southeast Pilbara. Its Ridley Magnetite Project is located within the Pardoo project area.

4DS Memory Limited, formerly Fitzroy Resources Ltd., is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in the development of resistive random access memory (ReRAM), a non-volatile memory. In collaboration with HGST, the Company is developing a non-filamentary ReRAM, which is suitable for gigabyte (GB) silicon storage at smaller geometries. ReRAM is used for next generation storage in mobile and cloud. The Company owns Internet protocol portfolio developed to create high-density gigabyte storage. The Company's Interface Switching ReRAM is suitable for markets that require high-density memory and gigabyte silicon storage. The Company has non-volatile memory solution, which enables higher density memory to operate longer when compared to traditional storage technologies. The Company has its research and development facilities located in Fremont in Silicon Valley, the United States.

Austral Gold Limited is an Australia-based precious metals mining and exploration company, which is engaged in building a portfolio of assets in South America. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral properties, and gold and silver production. Its segments include Australia and South America. Its projects include Guanaco Project, Amancaya Project, Pinguino Project and 8 de Julio Project. It is also an operator of Casposo mine in San Juan, Argentina. Its Guanaco project is located approximately 220 kilometers South East of Antofagasta in Northern Chile. Its Amancaya Project is located approximately 60 kilometers south west of its Guanaco mine in northern Chile. Its Amancaya Project is a gold-silver deposit that consists of over eight mining exploration concessions covering over 1,775 hectares. The 8 de Julio site consists of approximately 30 mining properties over 67,000 hectares in the Deseado Massif corridor of the Province of Santa Cruz.

Admiralty Resources NL is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activities of the Company are the exploration for and development of economic mineral deposits. The Company operates through three segments: Australia, Chile and Hong Kong. Its exploration, appraisal, development and production activities for mineral resources take place in Chile. It has borrowing facility located in Hong Kong. The Company has mineral interests in Chile and in Australia. In Chile, the Company holds interest in iron ore districts, including Harper South, Pampa Tololo and El Cojin. The Harper South lies over 15 kilometers south west of the city of Vallenar in the Atacama Region of Chile. The Harper South covers an area of approximately 2,498 hectares. The Harper South includes three projects: Mariposa, Soberana and La Chulula. La Chulula is a project located approximately 15 kilometers south of the city of Vallenar, III Region, Chile.

Australia China Holdings Limited (AAK) is an investment holding company. The Company is engaged in providing property, agriculture, financial and advisory services. Its segments include Trading and Others, and Property Investment. The Trading and Others segment includes investments in businesses and trading. The Property Investment segment includes property holdings. It invests in various industries and businesses, including building material, resources, power and energy saving. The Company offers a range of energy related products, including power savers, electrical products, lights and controllers. The Company provides administration and restructuring services, including mergers and company acquisitions, sale of companies and businesses, corporate re-organization and insolvency. Its products include cast resin dry type eco transformers with range from 50 kilo volt amperes (kVA) to 2,500 kVA and replacement of traditional oil type transformers, among others.

Aruma Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company, which has various prospective project areas within the Eastern Goldfields and Ashburton regions of Western Australia. The Company's tenement package totals approximately 960 square kilometers covering structural and geochemical prospects. Its projects include Glandore Project, Clinker Hill Gold Project and Bulloo Downs Copper Project. The Glandore Project is situated approximately 40 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie-Boulder in the Eastern Goldfields Province of Western Australia. The Project consists of over three mining licenses and approximately 20 prospecting licenses covering over 40 square kilometers. The Clinker Hill Project is an-going gold exploration project situated over 40 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia and approximately six kilometers south from the Company's Glandore Project. The Bulloo Downs Copper Project covers an area of over 3,000 square kilometers with approximately 10 prospects identified.

APAC Coal Limited (APAC) is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the care and maintenance of a coal resource and reviewing further investment opportunities for the Company. The Company has a concession to explore for coal over a 23,124-hectare parcel of land in East Kalimantan, Indonesia. Its 68,360-hectare tenement is located in East Kalimantan on Borneo Island. Balikpapan, the provincial capital of East Kalimantan, lies approximately 110 kilometers due northeast of the tenement. The Company's subsidiaries include PT Deefu Chemical Indonesia and PT Batubara Selaras Sapta. APAC is a subsidiary of Magnus Energy Group Ltd (Magnus), which operates in the upstream petroleum and coal business.

Aguia Resources Limited is a fertilizer company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and development of resource projects in the resources sector. The Company's projects include Lucena Phosphate Project and Rio Grande Project. The Company's Rio Grande deposit consists of the Tres Estradas, Joca Tavares, and Porteira carbonatite-hosted phosphate and the Cerro Preto sediment-hosted phosphate. The Company's deposits are located in a farming region of approximately 350 kilometers from the state capital porto Alegre. The Company's Tres Estradas project is located in the state of Rio Grande do Sul. The Company's Lucena Phosphate Project (LPP) covers approximately 35,000 hectares, which is located within approximately 50 kilometers radius across the city of Joao Pessoa, Paraiba State in northeastern Brazil. The Company's LPP is located within the Pernambuco-Paraiba basin consisting of Cretaceous-Paleocene sediments covered by the Pleistocene Barreiras Group.

OneAll International Limited is an outdoor furniture designer, manufacturer and distributor. The Company operates in the segment of sales of self-produced and designed outdoor furniture. The Company operates under the brand name of Gardenart. The Company's products include chairs, tables, lounges, sunbeds and accessories. The chair product range includes dining chair, bar height chair and conversation chair. The table product range includes dining tables, extendable tables, bar tables, coffee tables, side tables, folding tables, as well as picnic tables. The lounges product range includes classicals, such as conversation sets with armchairs, loveseat and sofa, indoor-inspired like sectional modular sofa lounges. The sunbeds product range includes recliners of 4-5 positions. The accessories product range includes service tray, magazine shelf, serving trolley, table linen, flower pot and functional side table, among others.

Adherium Limited is principally engaged in the development, manufacture and supply of its Smartinhaler digital health technologies, which address sub-optimal medication use and improve health outcomes in chronic disease. It offers a range of smart devices for respiratory medications globally. Its Smartinhaler platform supports asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) medication adherence solution. The Bluetooth enabled Smartinhaler medication sensors wrap around patients existing inhalers and automatically send usage data to their smartphone. The Smartinhaler application enables patients and healthcare professionals to track medication adherence, set daily reminders, and discover insights into their medication usage. Its application also enables real-time reporting, monitoring, storing and analysis of inhaler use. The SmartinhalerLive platform uses wireless communications technology to provide real time data collection and reporting from the its Smartinhalers.

1-Page Limited offers a Sourcing solution to deliver candidate pools based on various open roles. The Company provides an Assessment solution, which offers companies a new system of engagement. The Company also offers an Innovation platform, which leverages automated scoring to filter and rank proposals, and runs reports and analytics to navigate through content. With its Assessment solution, the Company leverages natural language processing, auto-scoring and themed-based data management. The Company sells its solutions directly through its own sales force and indirectly through its channel partners. The Company operates in Australia and the United States. The Company's subsidiaries include The One-Page Company Inc., BranchOut Inc. and Marianas Labs Inc.

3P Learning Limited is engaged in developing, sale and marketing of online educational programs to schools and parents of school-aged students. The Company's geographical operating segments include Australia & New Zealand (ANZ); America, Canada and South America (Americas), and Europe, Middle-East and Africa (EMEA). The Company's programs cover mathematics, spelling, literacy, reading and science. The Company's programs include Mathletics, which covers mathematics for teachers and parents; Spellodrome, which covers spelling through an array of activities, games and challenges; Reading Eggs, which covers reading skills through online reading games and activities, and IntoScience, which covers science through three-dimensional environments, virtual experiments and digitally simulated environments. The Company also hosts a range of online educational events throughout the year, through World Education Games, which is a global online education event.

Automotive Holdings Group Limited is an automotive retailing company in Australasia. The Company's principal activities include automotive retail, refrigerated logistics and other logistics. The Company's segments include Automotive Retail, Refrigerated Logistics, Other Logistics and Property. Its Automotive Retail segment has approximately 190 motor vehicle franchises at over 110 dealership locations operating within the geographical areas of Australia and New Zealand. Its Refrigerated Logistics segment consists of the Company's cold storage and transport operations. The Other Logistics segment consists of the Company's automotive parts warehousing and distribution businesses, motorcycle distribution, bus and track distribution, and vehicle storage and engineering. Its Property segment consists of its direct property interests in land and buildings. The Company also operates national refrigerated transport and storage, and truck and trailer bodybuilding, among others.
Auto Vehicles, Parts & Service Retailers - NEC

Australian Ethical Investment Limited is engaged in acting as the responsible entity for a range of ethically managed investment schemes. The Company also acts as the Trustee of the Australian Ethical Retail Superannuation Fund. It operates through fund management segment. The Company's products include Super, Managed Funds and Pensions. The Company invests in clean energy solutions, such as solar and wind; energy efficiency, such as light emitting diode (LED) lighting, motors and smart energy management technologies; Other products and activities, such as recycling, insulation and battery storage; healthcare; medical research; communication; education; information technology; Responsible Banking; Aged Care, and sustainable products. Its managed fund is a managed investment portfolio and can include investments in shares, property and fixed interest. Its subsidiaries are Australian Ethical Superannuation Pty Limited and Australian Ethical Investment Limited Employee Share Plan Trust.

8I Holdings Limited is an investment holding company. The Company's segments include investment segment, which is involved in investments in listed securities; private equity segment, which is engaged in the provision of group-level corporate services, treasury functions and private investments in companies with initial public offering (IPO) potential; education and event segment, which is involved in financial education, training seminar and event organization business, and property segment, which is engaged in the business of constructing, developing and leasing out of residential and commercial properties. The Company, through its subsidiaries, includes a business intelligence and investment network made up of professionals, managers, executives and technicians (PMETs), entrepreneurs, and high-net-worth individuals (HNWIs) through its financial education and training hub. The Company has operations in Australia, China, Malaysia and Singapore.

Algae.Tec Limited is an Australia-based algae products company. The Company is engaged in the development of the technology for the production of algal oil and algal biomass for sale as feedstock to producers of biodiesel, jet fuel and ethanol. The Company operates in two geographical locations: Australia and the United States. The Company is also focused on developing the technology for the nutraceutical market. Its technology delivers algae products, such as proteins for consumption and biofuel oils for transportation and power generation. Algae and its byproducts can be used for various applications, including nutraceuticals, personal products, such as soap and face cream, protein food sources plus bio-polymers and fuels. The Company operates in the environmental energy industry.

Aurora Absolute Return Fund is an Australia-based registered managed investment scheme. The Fund's objective is to achieve an income return, whilst seeking to preserve the capital of the Fund over both rising and falling equity markets. The Fund invests in the unlisted Aurora Fortitude Absolute Return Fund (the Master Fund). The Master Fund invests in opportunities that it considers to offer attractive risk return characteristics with a focus on potential catalysts that seeks to generate a profitable return regardless of the market direction. The Master Fund uses derivatives for risk management. The Fund's investment manager is Aurora Funds Management Limited, which is engaged in managing funds that invest in Australian and global listed securities and derivatives.

Adcorp Australia Limited (Adcorp) is engaged in providing advertising agency services specializing in human resources, real estate, government, motor vehicle, education and retail; Website design, development and database support services; digital marketing services and consulting, including supply of Web-based products and strategic employment solutions, and video production and marketing solutions. The Company's segments include Australia and New Zealand. The Company's services include branding, creative/design, digital/social, events/public relation (PR), media planning, promotions, research, strategy and television/video. The Company has its offices located in Brisbane, Canberra, Darwin, Melbourne, Perth, Sydney, Auckland, Christchurch, Tauranga and Wellington. Adcorp's subsidiaries include Adcorp Australia (QLD) Pty. Limited, Adcorp Australia (VIC) Pty. Limited, Adcorp D&D Pty Ltd and Adcorp New Zealand Limited.

Australian Dairy Farms Group is a dairy company. The Company is engaged in operating dairy farms and dairy livestock for the production and sale of fresh raw milk to external processing factories for conversion to milk and milk products. The Company is also engaged in processing and sale of dairy products to domestic and export markets. The Company's segments are Dairy Farm and Dairy processing. The Company's initial focus was on aggregating dairy farms in Victoria, initially in the South Western region with particular emphasis initially, on the Dairy Golden Triangle region of South West Victoria between Warrnambool and Colac south of the Princes Highway to the coast around Port Campbell.

Alliance Resources Limited is engaged in the sale of its interest in the Four Mile Uranium Project in South Australia, exploring its projects in Chile and applying for additional mineral exploration tenements in Western Australia and New South Wales. The Company's Gundockerta South Nickel-Copper-Gold Project is located over 70 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie. Its Mt Pleasant Molybdenum-Tungsten-Copper Gold Project includes Exploration license 5277, which is located over 30 kilometers south of Mudgee and contains the Mt Pleasant porphyry style molybdenum-tungsten occurrence. Its Garema Gold Project is located over 30 kilometers south of Forbes. Its Bogan Gate West Gold-Base Metals Project is located in New South Wales. The Company also operates Chilean Copper-Gold-Silver-Uranium Projects and Western Australian Nickel-Copper-Gold Projects. It has completed a drilling program targeting copper and uranium at the Monardes project, located in Atamaca Region III in northern Chile.

9 Spokes International Limited is a holding company engaged in cloud services brokerage services. The Company is involved in the development of an online, software-as-a-service (SaaS) application platform and store allowing a business to access a range of online services made available on SaaS basis by third-party vendors. The 9 Spokes platform focuses on small medium enterprises and incorporates a dashboard, which takes data from third-party services and among other things, provides a graphical snapshot of the status of that business. Each business may allow access to the 9 Spokes platform for its employees and representatives, and in addition may grant access to third-party technical and business specialists, such as accountants. It also develops and licenses bespoke versions of the platform for third-party channels, which provides the features of the platform and store to channel customers. It makes the 9 Spokes platform directly available to customers through 9 Spokes Direct.

Animoca Brands Corporation Limited, formerly Black Fire Minerals Limited, is engaged in the development and marketing a portfolio of mobile games for smartphones and tablets. The Company's segment operates through the product development and marketing of mobile application games. The Company distributes its games on platforms, including the Apple App store, Google play and Amazon. The Company's brands develops and publishes a range of original games, and also serves as global or regional publisher for select games developed by third parties. The Company's brands include Garfield, Ben10, Doraemon, Astro Boy and Ultraman. The Company's products include Feed Garfield, Garfield Chef, Garfield Tycoon, Astro Boy Dash, Astro Boy Piano, Doraemon Gadget Rush, Doraemon Repair Shop Seasons, Ben 10 Ultimate Alien Xenodrome+, Ever After High Charmed Style, Norm of the North's Digit Dodge, Ultraman Galaxy, Cats vs Dragons, Robot Academy and Winter Wonderland.

Australian Careers Network Limited (ACN) is engaged in the provision of vocational educational and training services in Australia. The Company delivers training services and outcomes for students focusing on relevant course content. ACN has an education offering across a range of industry sectors, including trades, health and wellness, business, sport and recreation, and hospitality. It offers both funded and non-funded offerings ranging from short courses, nationally recognized certificate qualifications, diplomas and higher education degrees. ACN's services are distributed through three commercial streams: training and student services for individuals, consultancy and skills solutions for business, and employment and recruitment solutions for industry. The Company also partners with job seeking agencies and labor hire companies to provide employment pathway to students seeking employment upon completion of a course.

Auswide Bank Ltd is engaged in raising of funds and the provision of finance for housing, personal loans and business banking. The Company offers banking services, personal deposit accounts, business accounts, special entity deposit accounts, term deposits, home loans and line of credit access accounts and insurance, among others. The Company's personal offerings include home loans, personal loans, credit cards, term deposits, superannuation and insurance. Its loan portfolio includes home renovation loans, wedding loans, boat loans, holiday loans, motor home loans, and caravan or trailer loans. Its business offerings include business term loan, business overdraft, business line of credit and commercial vehicle and equipment finance, among others. Its Insurance range includes trades and services pack, office pack, farm insurance and travel insurance. It operates principally within the states of Queensland, New South Wales and Victoria.

Agricultural Land Trust (the Trust) is a registered managed investment scheme. The principal activity of the Trust is to operate as an agricultural land trust for the purpose of deriving income from agistment and cropping activities in the medium term. The Trust is focused on the ownership of rural property for the purpose of generating rental income and capital appreciation. The Trust owns approximately 8,937 hectares of rural property located in Western Australia. The Trust's subsidiaries include Kalgoorlie Apartment Hotel Syndicate, Murray Street Mall Property Trust and ALT No 1 Trust. The Responsible Entity of the Trust is One Managed Investment Funds Limited, which is a subsidiary of the One Investment Group Pty Limited. One Investment Group Pty Limited is a subsidiary of One Investment Group Holdings Pty Limited.

ADG Global Supply Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the provision of industrial and safety products, and global procurement and supply chain management services. The Company offers its services to clients across a range of industries in key regions of Africa, Asia and Australia. The Company's operating segments include Industrial Products, Global Procurement and Supply Chain. The Industrial Products segment includes products that are manufactured and/or distributed by the Company, including safety products; products for maintenance, repairs and operations (MRO), and off-the-road tires. The Global Procurement segment assists clients with purchasing and supply of a range of goods and capital equipment to site. The Supply Chain segment offers a range of logistics, in-country support, freight forwarding and project logistics services.

ADX Energy Ltd is an oil and gas exploration, and appraisal company. The Company operates over four oil and gas permits in North Africa and Europe, together with gold and base metal interests in Australia. Its segments are Tunisia Exploration and Evaluation, which includes assets and activities in Tunisia; Romania Exploration and Evaluation, which includes assets and activities in Romania, and Italy Exploration and Evaluation, which includes assets and activities in Italy. Its assets include Offshore Italy Pantelleria Permits and d 363 C.R-.AX Permit, Offshore Tunisia Kerkouane permit and Onshore Western Romania, Parta Concession. Its Sicily Channel Project incorporates the Kerkouane Permit, the Pantelleria License and d 364 C.R-.AX License (Italy). Its Dougga and Lambouka gas discoveries are located offshore Tunisia and Italy in the Sicily Channel. The Parta permit covers an area of over 1,220 square kilometers and is located in the southern Pannonian basin area of western Romania.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Ardent Leisure Group is an Australia-based company, which invests in and operates leisure and entertainment businesses in Australia, New Zealand and the United States. The Company operates Family entertainment centers in the United States; Dreamworld, a mobile phone recycling program continued to operating throughout the theme park; Bowling centers in Australia; Bowling centers in New Zealand; d'Albora Marinas; Goodlife Health Clubs, and Greenhouse gas and energy data reporting requirements. Its brands are categorized into Health Clubs, which include Goodlife Health Clubs and HYPOXI; Indoor Entertainment, which includes Kingpin Bowling and Main Event Entertainment; Attractions, which includes SkyPoint and SkyPoint Climb, and Marinas, which includes d'Albora Marina.

Abacus Property Group is a real estate investment. The principal activities of the Company include investment in office, retail and industrial properties, investment in self-storage facilities, participation in property ventures and developments, and property funds management. Its segments include Property, Storage, Property Ventures, Funds Management, AHF, ADIFII and AWLF. The Property segment is engaged in investing in ownership of commercial, retail and industrial properties. The segment also includes the equity accounting of material co-investments in property entities not engaged in development and construction projects. The Storage segment is engaged in investing in, and ownership of, self-storage facilities. The Property Ventures segment is engaged in providing lending and related property financing solutions and investment in joint venture developments and construction projects. The Funds Management segment includes development, and fund management revenues and expenses.

Aeeris Limited is a developer, operator and provider of the Early Warning Network (EWN). The Company is engaged in offering enterprise asset and people protection technologies. The Company operates through the segment of early warning notifications within Australia. EWN's geographic notification and information system (GNIS) platform ingests amounts of live data from a range of public and private sources on weather events, storms, bushfires, traffic incidents and other geospatial events, which impact the operations. The GNIS software offers the capabilities for businesses to put in place a range of mapping, monitoring, tracking and communication systems to prepare, secure and manage work forces and assets. The Company's services include custom forecast solutions, custom alert services, EWN all alerts, embargo services, situation room, severe weather incident manager (SWIM), EWN application for iPhone and Android, and EWN safe at work applications.

ABM Resources NL is an exploration company. The Company is engaged in open pit mining operations at the Old Private Gold Mine; treatment of ore from the Old Private Gold Mine at the Coyote processing plant to closure of the Old Private Gold Mine; substantial rehabilitation of the mine site, and exploration drilling and reconnaissance within the Tanami region. It operates through two segments: Mining and Processing, and Exploration. The Old Private Gold Deposit is a part of its Twin Bonanza Gold Project and consists of a series of gold-bearing quartz veins with a strike-length of approximately two kilometers. It is engaged in the development of open pits, including Western Limb, Old Pirate Central, Old Pirate South and Golden Hind. Its Tanami North includes Birrindudu, Bonanza and Suplejack. Its Tanami Regional includes South Tanami and Euro. Its Lake Mackay includes Tarawera and Lake Mackay North. It holds approximately 48,500 square kilometers of ground in the Central Desert region.

Australian Agricultural Company Limited is an Australia-based cattle and beef producer. The principal activities of the Company are ownership, operation and development of pastoral properties; production of beef, including breeding, backgrounding, feedlotting and processing of cattle, and sales and marketing of branded beef. The Company specializes in grassfed beef and grainfed beef production. It operates an integrated cattle production system across approximately 20 owned cattle stations, over two leased stations, approximately 10 agisted properties, over two owned feedlots, a beef processing facility and over two owned and an external farms located throughout Queensland, New South Wales, the Northern Territory and Western Australia. The Company runs herd of Wagyu cattle, producing Wagyu beef, which is exported to over 20 countries around the world. Its Northern Beef Processing Facility is located at Livingstone Valley.

Adelaide Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the exploration for gold, copper, uranium, and other economic mineral deposits. As on June 30, 2012, the Company has interests in 22 exploration licenses, covering over 7,800 square kilometers within South Australia, the Northern Territory and Queensland. The Company holds 100% of the majority of the Moonta Project on Yorke Peninsula in South Australia and a program of aircore and diamond drilling was completed in early 2012 to test a number of targets. The Companys projects include Rover, Eyre Peninsula, Eyre Peninsula Basement, Yalanda Hill JV, Corrobinnie Palaeochannel Project, Cleve, Anabama, Moonta and Glenroy. The Company subsidiaries include Adelaide Exploration Pty Ltd and Peninsula Resources Limited (formerly Eyre Energy Pty Ltd)

8Common Limited is engaged in the development and distribution of software solutions, which include Expense8, Realtors8 and Perform8. The Company's segments include Productivity and Performance, and Realtors8. The Productivity and Performance segment includes Expense8 and Perform8. Expense8 is a travel and management software solution that manages and streamlines the end-to-end processing of employee-generated expenses. Perform8 is a survey and action planning solution that diagnoses and prioritizes areas of improvement across the users business. The Realtors8 segment is a content management system (CMS) and customer relationship management (CRM) solution targeting realtors. Realtors8 provides personalized, Websites, integrated to multiple listing services (MLS), syndication and marketing tools, which enable the realtors to maintain relationship with customers. The Company's subsidiaries include Business Information Services (NSW) Pty Limited, Expense8 Pte Ltd and Realtors8 Pte Ltd.

Aeris Environmental Limited develops, manufactures and markets environmentally friendly technology solutions. The Company's principal activities include research, development, commercialization of technologies and global distribution of the AerisGuard range of products; provision of heating, ventilation, air conditioning and refrigeration (HVAC/R) hygiene and remediation technology, and provision of energy services. The Company's segments include Australia and International. The AerisGuard anti-microbial multi-enzyme technology cleans and removes contamination from coils, surfaces and ductwork and provides protection from recontamination. The SmartENERGY technology platform optimizes the compressor operation. Aeris Duct Sealant eliminates leaks in ductwork. AerisGuard Epicoat provides cleaning and removes cooking debris, oil and fats from commercial kitchen range hoods. It offers a range of solutions for commercial and residential applications.

Adairs Limited is engaged in the retailing of home wares and home furnishings in Australia. The Company is engaged in product design, development, sourcing, distribution and retail operations. Its product offering consists of two segments, being its core or staple product categories (Staple) and the fashion and decorator product categories (Fashion and Decorator). Its Staple product categories include plain bed linen, bedding (pillows, quilts, underlays, mattress protectors) and towelling products. The Staple range also includes seasonal products (Christmas trim, beach towels and flannelette bed linen). Its Fashion and Decorator product categories include fashion bed linen, soft furnishings, homewares, and occasional and bedroom furniture. The Company's products are sold under its own private brands. The Company has approximately 130 stores across Australia in five physical store formats: Adairs, Adairs Homemaker, Adairs Kids, urban home republic (UHR) and Adairs Outlets.

Ardiden Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral resources. The Company's segments include Canada (Manitouwadge), Canada (Hinton North), Canada (Seymour Lake), Canada (Root Lake) and Australia. The Company's projects include Seymour Lake Lithium Project, Root Lake Lithium Project, Manitouwadge Project and Yinchen Tin Project. The Seymour Lake Lithium Project consists of approximately 910 hectares of mining claims and is located in Ontario, Canada. The Root Lake Lithium Project consists of over 1,010 hectares of mining claims and is located in Ontario, Canada. The Root Bay lithium project consists of over 720 hectares and is located approximately 300 kilometers north-west of the regional center of Thunder Bay. The Manitouwadge Project consists of over 3,400 hectares and located north-east of the town of Manitouwadge in Ontario, Canada. The Yinchen Tin Project is located in Belitung, Indonesia.

AGL Energy Limited is engaged in buying and selling of gas and electricity and related products and services; construction and/or operation of power generation and energy processing infrastructure; operation of natural gas storage facilities; extraction, production and sale of natural gas, and sale of distributed generation technologies, including solar, digital meters, storage and other business and residential energy services. Its segments include energy markets, which sells electricity, natural gas, and energy related products and services to consumer market, business and wholesale customers; group operations, which is a diverse power generation portfolio spread across thermal and renewable generation, including hydro, wind and solar; new energy, which includes new energy services, distributed energy services, as well as digital meter installation and data provider business, and investments, which include equity accounted investments in various energy related business.

ApplyDirect Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in providing an online database and search platform that links employers and job candidates directly to live job opportunities on employer Websites. The Company offers database and search platform that facilitates direct recruitment by employers. The jobs are collated and advertised on the ApplyDirect platform using a search engine to enable access by job candidates. The Company is engaged in providing a central online database with a cataloguing system and search engine that is structured to enable job candidates to find and apply for their preferred jobs. ApplyDirect allows employers to reach a range of candidates without losing the benefits of the direct recruitment approach. For smaller employers without a careers page, the Company hosts an outsourced careers page on their behalf.

Australian Foundation Investment Company Limited (AFIC) is a closed-end investment company. The Company specializes in investing in Australian equities. The Company's investment objective is to provide shareholders with investment returns through access to a steam franked dividends and enhancement of capital invested. It has two portfolios of securities: the investment portfolio and the trading portfolio. The investment portfolio holds securities that the Company intends to retain on a long term basis. The trading portfolio consists of securities that are held for short term trading only, including call option contracts written over securities that are held in specific sub-component of the investment portfolio. It invests in a range of sectors, such as energy, materials, industrials, consumer staples, banks, property trusts, telecommunications, healthcare, information technology and utilities. Australian Investment Company Services Ltd is a subsidiary of the Company.

AFT Pharmaceuticals Limited is a pharmaceutical distributor and developer of pharmaceutical intellectual property. The Company's segments include New Zealand, Australia, Asia and Rest of World. The Company's products include Crystaderm, Maxigesic, Coco-scalp, Maxiclear, RestoraNail and Myconail, among others. The Company's NasoSURF Nebuliser is in pilot scale production. The Company is focused on conducting clinical for Maxigesic oral dose forms. The Company is also conducting clinical trials of Maxigesic intravenous (IV). Maxigesic PE is a cold and flu variant. Its subsidiary, AFT Pharmaceuticals (AU) Pty Ltd, is engaged in distribution of pharmaceuticals in Australia. Its subsidiary, AFT Pharmaceuticals Singapore Pte Ltd, is engaged in the registration of pharmaceuticals in Singapore. Its subsidiary, AFT Pharmaceuticals (S.E. Asia) Sdn Bhd, is engaged in the distribution of pharmaceuticals in Malaysia.

AdAlta Limited is an Australia-based drug discovery and development company. The Company is focused on using its technology platform to generate protein therapeutics, known as i-bodies, for treating a range of human diseases. The Company's principal activity is to develop its ibody platform with a focus on its lead candidate AD-114, a treatment for idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) and other fibrotic diseases. Its i-body AD-114 drug candidate is used for treatment in various fibrosis related eye diseases to support the pre-clinical development of the eye fibrosis indication. The Company's AD-114 has shown both anti-fibrotic and anti-inflammatory effects in various animal models. The Company's AD-114 is used in various therapeutic applications for fibrosis diseases of the liver, skin, kidney and heart. AD-114 has completed pre-clinical studies in vitro (in the lab) and in vivo (in animals) data obtained.

African Energy Resources Limited is engaged in evaluation and exploration of coal and energy projects in southern Africa. The Company's segments are development of power generation assets in Africa and Other. The Company focuses on the development of multiple integrated power projects in Botswana. It has a joint venture agreement to develop power generation capacity at the Sese coal project. The Sese integrated power project comprises a power station complex with its captive coal mine. The Sese coal license contains over five billion tons of low strip ratio coal providing potential for expansion of generation capacity. Its Mmamantswe coal project is approximately 1.25 billion tons project and is located approximately 20 kilometers from the international border with South Africa. Its Mmamabula West comprises approximately two 4 meters to 6 meters thick coal seams, with the upper K-Seam averaging over 105 meters depth below surface and the lower A-seam over 130 meters depth.

Adelaide Brighton Limited is an integrated construction materials and industrial lime producer. The Company's principal activities include the production, importation, distribution and marketing of clinker, cement, industrial lime, premixed concrete, construction aggregates and concrete products. The Company operates through two segments: Cement, Lime, Concrete and Aggregates, and Concrete Products. It supplies concrete bricks, blocks, pavers, retaining walls, erosion control products, architectural masonry and reconstituted stone veneers through locations in Queensland, New South Wales, Victoria, Tasmania and South Australia. The Company produces industrial lime in Australia, with production assets in Western Australia, South Australia and Northern Territory. The Company imports cement, clinker and slag products to customers in Australia. The Company serves building, residential and non-residential construction, engineering construction, alumina production and mining markets.

Alligator Energy Limited is principally engaged in the uranium mineral exploration. The Company is focused on the discovery of uranium deposits in the Alligator Rivers Uranium Province (ARUP) in western Arnhem Land. The ARUP is a uranium province, which is located approximately 250 kilometers east of Darwin, the capital city of the Northern Territory. The province hosts several uranium deposits, including the Ranger No 1 and No 3 deposits, which produce approximately 300 million pounds of U3O8 for export, and the Jabiluka deposit, which is a uranium deposit, having a resource of approximately 300 million pounds U3O8 at grades of approximately 5,000 parts per million (ppm) U3O8. The Company has approximately two active project areas covering over 650 square kilometers in the ARUP. These project areas, Tin Camp Creek and Beatrice, each contain known uranium, as well as the Caramal Resource.

Australian Finance Group Limited (AFG) is a mortgage broking company. The Company's principal activities are mortgage origination and management of home loans and commercial loans, and distribution of own branded home loan products, be they funded through traditional mortgage management products, while label or its residential mortgage backed securities program. Its segments include AFG Wholesale Mortgage Broking, AFG Home Loans and Other. The AFG Wholesale Mortgage Broking segment includes operating activities in which the Company acts as a wholesale mortgage broker that provides its broker members with administrative and infrastructure support, as well as access to a panel of lenders. The AFG Home Loans segment offers its branded mortgage products. It offers commercial finance, insurance products, and AFG-branded and securitized products. Its subsidiaries include Australian Finance Group (Commercial) Pty Ltd and Australian Finance Group Securities Pty Ltd, among others.

ASF Group Limited is an investment and trading company. The Company is engaged in identification, incubation and realization of opportunities in areas of synergy between China, Australia, the United Kingdom and Europe, including oil and gas, resources, property, infrastructure, travel and financial services sectors. It focuses on exploration and operation in the onshore opportunities that exist in Western Australia. It is engaged in real estate marketing and the provision of ancillary property services in Australia. The Company's property business consists of its subsidiary, ASF Properties Pty Ltd, which offers property marketing services to Chinese developers, including the sourcing of potential projects, preparing development feasibility studies and market analysis. Its investment business includes its subsidiary, ASF Capital pty Limited, which is a boutique investment banking firm that is engaged in mergers and acquisitions, and corporate advisory services.

CCP Technologies Limited, formerly Agenix Limited, specializes in Internet of Things (IoT) product development and product management. The Company assists customers to create IoT solutions by providing hardware, firmware and software development services. The Company is a turnkey solutions provider, which supports the entire product life-cycle process, from concept to creation, and ongoing product management. The Company has built its own business-to-business hardware and software solution, which provides customers with a critical control point monitoring platform. The Company's platform monitors control points, such as temperature and energy consumption. The Company's solution is being used to measure, monitor and report the temperature of fridges in hospitals, grocery stores, food wholesalers, food retailers and hotels.

Actinogen Medical Limited, formerly Actinogen Limited, is a clinical-stage biotechnology company. The Company focuses on the treatment of Alzheimer's disease and age-related neurodegenerative diseases. The Company is engaged in treating cognitive impairment in chronic neurodegenerative diseases through the inhibition of cortisol production. The Company's Xanamem is a drug under development for the treatment of Alzheimer's disease, which is designed to block the production of cortisol in the brain. Xanamem's mechanism of action is to block the activity of a specific enzyme in the brain, the 11B-HSD1 enzyme. It focuses on Xanamem in the clinical areas, including Diabetes-Cognitive dysfunction, Cognitive dysfunction in Parkinson's Disease, Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD), Cognitive dysfunction in schizophrenia and depression, and Cardiovascular disease-Post myocardial infarction. It focuses on Phase II XanADu efficacy and safety study with mild Alzheimer's disease patients.

Alterra Limited, formerly Carbon Conscious Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in managing its agri-forestry business. The Company has two segments: Plantations and Dairy. The Plantations segment includes the planting of mallee tree in the marginal wheat-belt land of Western Australia (WA) to produce carbon credits or Australian carbon credit units (ACCUs) on behalf of customers and the Company. The Dairy segment includes the running of dairy operations in WA. The Company focuses on Carbon Farming Initiative (CFI) projects in Australia. It focuses to manage over 18,000 hectares of agri-forestry projects in Western Australia on behalf of clients to generate carbon credits or ACCUs. It focuses on science and CFI project field work, which include tree measurement and monitoring. It focuses on building a herd suitable for System-5 operations. It focuses on developing System-5 farming operations to supply milk to local processors and the WA as a base camp.

AtCor Medical Holdings Ltd is engaged in the designing, manufacturing and marketing of medical devices for use in cardiovascular management. The Company operates through three segments: Americas, which includes global pharmaceutical trials business; Europe, which includes Middle East and Africa, and Asia Pacific, which includes Asia and Australia/New Zealand. The Company's clinical trial services, include study protocol assistance, study-specific user manual, operator training and certification, study-specific training materials, automated data transfer for expert over-read, quality assurance, ongoing data management, technical support and sponsor-defined data transfers. The Company also offers SphygmoCor technology, which is used in clinical trials for a range of therapeutic areas, including hypertension, renal disease, heart failure, inflammatory processes, diabetes and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

Aberdeen Leaders Limited is an investment company. The Company's investment objective is to invest primarily in companies within the S&P/Australian Securities Exchange (ASX) 200 Accumulation index. By investing primarily in companies within the S&P/ASX 200 index, it seeks to provide investors with high capital growth over the medium to long term. The Company is involved in making investments, and deriving revenue and investment income from listed securities and unit trusts in Australia. The Company invests in various sectors, such as materials, healthcare, property, utilities, energy, telecommunication services, consumer staples, consumer discretionary, industrials and information technology. The Company operates in Australia and in securities industry. The Company's investment manager is Aberdeen Asset Management Limited.

Aurora Labs Limited is engaged in the design, development and manufacture of three-dimensional (3D) metal printers and associated products and services. The Company also specializes in the development of printer software and the supply of associated consumable materials. It manufactures two models of small format printers (SFPs): the S-Titanium and S-Titanium Pro. Its SFPs are used in various markets, such as prototyping, jewelry, dental implants and appliances, medical implants and materials research businesses. Its printers can operate in three modes: Selective Laser Melting (SLM), Selective Laser Sintering (SLS) and Directed Energy Deposition (DED). Its SFP range is in a pre-production stage and Beta Units are undergoing Beta Testing. It also develops Europa medium format printer (MFP) and Titan large format printer (LFP), which are in the proof-of-concept phase. It procures and supplies consumable materials for use with 3D metal printers, such as metal and cermet powders.

Afterpay Holdings Limited is a holding company. The Company is a technology driven payments company with a focus on applying its technology to provide a retail centric, omni channel retail service, which facilitates commerce between retail merchants and their end-customers. The Company provides a platform, which allows its retail merchant clients to offer their end-customers the ability to buy products on a buy now, pay later basis. Its platform integrates directly into merchant Websites and retail environments. The Company offers installment plans for online shoppers, allowing a purchase to be paid for in approximately four equal instalments, due every fortnight. Its platform is integrated with over 300 Australian retailers. Its platform also includes in-store accessibility. Afterpay Pty Ltd is the subsidiary of the Company.

A-Cap Resources Ltd is a resources company. The Company's principal activities are the ongoing feasibility studies into the Letlhakane Uranium Project, continuing exploration of its tenement portfolio in Botswana and the evaluation of its coal discoveries. It also has coal resources and Greenfield base metals exploration tenements. The Letlhakane Uranium Project is located approximately 80 kilometers from Francistown. The Letlhakane uranium deposits has a joint ore reserves committee (JORC) resource of approximately 365.7 million pounds U3O8 with high grade resource of approximately 103.8 million tons at over 450 parts per million (ppm) U3O8. Its Mea coal deposit is located over 120 kilometers west of Francistown on PL134/2005. The deposit is located within the southern half of PL134/2005 and is hosted in Lower Ecca Group sediments of the Karoo Supergroup. The Mea Coal Project contains coal in Botswana and has a JORC compliant mineral resource of approximately 335 million tons coal.

Acrux Limited is a drug development company. The Company is engaged in developing and commercializing branded and generic transdermal and topical pharmaceuticals for global markets. The Company's transdermal or topical pharmaceutical product portfolio can be segregated into approximately two streams, such as generic pharmaceutical products and specialty pharmaceutical products. The Company's products include Axiron, Ellavie, Evamist and Lenzetto. Axiron (testosterone) topical solution CIII is a testosterone topical solution approved for application via an armpit (underarm) applicator. It has developed the estradiol spray for women, used to treat moderate to severe hot flushes commonly associated with menopause. In the United States, the Company's estradiol spray is branded Evamist. The Company has licensed its estradiol product to Gedeon Richter to commercialize in various territories, including Europe and Eurasia. Gedeon Richter has branded the estradiol spray as Lenzetto.

Aft Corporation Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the solar panel and light-emitting diode (LED) lighting business. The Company's principal activity includes marketing and sale of solar panel products through its subsidiary, Artemis Building Systems Pty Ltd, and supporting new developments with project finance under leasing and energy sale contracts through its subsidiary, Artemis Energy Solutions. The Company, through Artemis Building Systems Pty Ltd, offers solar products, including solar photovoltaic (PV) modules, building integrated photo-voltaics (BIPV), inverters and mounting systems, and lighting products, including LED lights and Optiled LED products. The Company, through Artemis Energy Solutions, offers solutions for solar PV integration (distributed power) for commercial and industrial applications with products, such as Clenergy Mounting System and SMA Inverters.

Abilene Oil and Gas Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in resource exploration and investment in Australia and overseas, with a focus on oil and gas. The Company operates in the exploration sector for oil and gas assets within the United States. It holds interest in Klick Oil Project, including Klick East Oil Field located in Section 22 of T29N-R14W, Woods County, Oklahoma; Welch-Bornholdt Wherry Project, including Welch-Bornholdt and Wherry Oil Fields located in Rice and McPherson Counties, Kansas; Mount Lookout Prospect, including Morrison Oil Fields located in the Clark County, Kansas; Kinsley Prospect, which is located in the Edwards County, Kansas; Central Kansas Uplift Project, including working interest in leases covering approximately 15,663 acres of the Russell, Rice, Ellsworth and Barton Counties located in Kansas; Pratt County Prospect Joint Venture, which is located in Pratt County, Kansas; Rawlins County Prospect Joint Venture, and Logan County Project.

Anglo Australian Resources NL is a gold/base metals exploration company with resource interests in Western Australia. Its projects include Feysville gold project, Mandilla gold project, Koongie Park zinc-rich Volcanogenic Massive Sulfide (VMS) base metals project, Koongie Park gold project and Leonora base metals project. The Feysville Project is located approximately 10 kilometers south of the Golden Mile deposit at Kalgoorlie. Its Koongie Park Copper-Zinc Project, with resources defined at Sandiego and Onedin, is located over 20 kilometers southwest of the regional Centre of Halls Creek in the Southern Eastern Kimberley Region of Western Australia. The Mandilla Gold Project, located 70 kilometers south of Kalgoorlie and 20 kilometers southeast of Kambalda, comprises two mining leases covering over 1819.2 hectares. The Leonora base metals project, with an 800-meter long bedrock electromagnetic conductor, lies to the south of and along strike from a producing mineralized VMS corridor.

Adacel Technologies Limited is engaged in developing simulation and control systems for aviation and defense. The Company's principal activities include air traffic management and air traffic control simulation and software applications and services in the global civil and military aerospace sector. The Company's segments include Systems and Services. The Systems segment represents various sales of integrated software systems and products covering operational air traffic management, as well as simulation and training applications. The Systems segment also includes various hardware and software upgrade sales. In Services segment, its activities include on-site simulator operators, field service representative services, system warranties services, air traffic control instructor services and long term software support contracts. The Company offers products and services, including voice activated cockpit (VAC), speech recognition, global services and support, and airport driver training.

Advanced Braking Technology Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the commercialization, research, development and manufacture of the Sealed Integrated Braking System (SIBS) braking systems, predominantly in Australia and through distribution arrangements to other countries. The Company supplies SIBS brakes for light commercial vehicles used in the mining sector. Its SIBS technology is used in concrete agitator trucks and explosive carrying vehicles in underground mines. It is also engaged in the development and commercialization of SIBS brakes for trailers and trucks. The SIBS system is a single rotor enclosed wet braking system. The Company also offers a polymer brake under the brand name, Terra Dura. Its manufacturing plant is located in Thailand.

Ainsworth Game Technology Limited is a gaming machine developer, designer and manufacturer. The Company is engaged in design, development, production, lease, sale and servicing of gaming machines, and other related equipment and services. Its segments include Australia, which comprises NSW, QLD, VIC/TAS and South Aust/N.T; Americas, which includes North America and South America; Asia; New Zealand, and Europe/Other. The Company's operations encompass the entire product development cycles, from conception through to installation, service and support. It designs and manufactures A560, Ambassador and Celebrity range of gaming products, along with various entertaining standalone progressives and linked games. It offers various cabinets, such as A600, A560x Dual Screen, A560xSL and A560XST. It offers various games, such as multi-games, including MultiPlay Big Time I and Double Shot King Spin; mystery jackpots, including Big Chief Mystery and Big Hit Jackpots, and linked, such as Frontier.

Alchemy Resources Limited is an Australia-based gold and base metal exploration company engaged in the exploration for copper and gold. The Company is engaged in the discovery and development of gold and base metal resources at its portfolio of projects within Australia. The Company's projects include Lachlan projects, Karonie project and Bryah Basin project. The Lachlan Projects consist of the Overflow Gold-Base Metal Project (Overflow), the Eurow Copper-Gold Project (Eurow) and the Girilambone Copper Project (Girilambone). Each of these projects contains identified gold and/or base metal targets, including drill-ready priority targets at Overflow. The Karonie Project, located over 100 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie, includes over 230 square kilometers of Archean greenstone belt in the Eastern Goldfields in Western Australia. Its Bryah Basin Project consists of over 500 square kilometers ground package, located over 130 kilometers northeast of Meekatharra, Western Australia.

Accent Resources NL is a mineral exploration company. The Company focuses on the identification of investment opportunities in the resources sector and development of existing projects. It is engaged in the discovery and development of iron ore, base metal and precious metal deposits at its project areas in Western Australia. Its projects include the Magnetite Range Project, the Norseman Gold Project and the Arcadia (Meekatharra) Gold Project. The Magnetite Range Project is an iron magnetite project and is located approximately 310 kilometers north northeast of Perth. The Norseman project comprises approximately five mining leases and eight prospecting licenses covering an area of approximately 256 hectares and is located approximately five kilometers south of Norseman in the Dundas Mineral Field. The Arcadia Meekatharra project (E51/1209) is located approximately 45 kilometers south west of Meekatharra in the Murchison District of the Murchison Mineral Field, Western Australia.

Allegiance Coal Limited is engaged in the acquisition and exploration of coal tenements. The Company's project, Back Creek, is located approximately 45 kilometers south-east of Wandoan in the Surat Basin covering an area of approximately 62 square kilometers and comprises exploration permit for coal (EPC) 1297 tenement. The Calen Project is located approximately 25 kilometers west of Mackay in the Calen Basin and covers an area of over 214 square kilometers. The Calen project consists of EPCs 1631 and 1820 tenements. The Mt Marrow Project is located near Ipswich in the West Moreton Coalfield covering an area of approximately 91 square kilometers, and consists of EPC 2374 tenement. The Townsville Project is located in the northern extension of the Bowen Basin covering an area of approximately 696 square kilometers and consists of EPCs 1492 and 1617. It also owns Telkwa coking coal project, which is located within the southern reaches of the Bowser basin.

Australian Bauxite Limited (ABx) is a bauxite explorer, producer and mining company. The Company's principal activities include bauxite exploration and development programs in Queensland, New South Wales and Tasmania. The Company operates in the mineral, exploration and development of resources in Australia. It holds approximately 30 bauxite tenements in Queensland, New South Wales and Tasmania exceeding over 5,000 square kilometers. Its projects include Binjour Project, Goulburn and Tasmanian Project. The Company is operating its first mine at the Bald Hill Bauxite project in Tasmania. It also focuses on mines, including Fingal Rail and DL130. Fingal Rail, the second planned ABx Tasmanian mine, which is close to Campbell Town (approximately 10 kilometers North). DL-130, the third planned ABx mine located in Tasmania, which is within approximately 70 kilometers of the Bell Bay Export Port.

Aconex Limited is engaged in the business of providing cloud collaboration software services for the construction industry. The Company is organized into four segments based on geographical locations: Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), Americas, Asia, and Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA). The Company's platform connects owners, contractors and their project teams in the construction, infrastructure, and energy and resources sectors, providing project-wide visibility and control between the various organizations collaborating across their projects. Its project-wide solutions include document management, building information modeling (BIM) collaboration, mail and forms, bidding and tenders, workflow management, interface management, packages and deliverables, field and inspection checklists, and data retention. Its cloud platform solutions include security and performance, integration, mobile and neutrality. Its services include implementation and setup, training and support.

88 Energy Limited is an Australia-based exploration and production company. The Company is engaged in oil and gas exploration. The Company has operations in Australia and the United States of America. The Company's project includes Project Icewine, which is located in Onshore Alaska. The Company has interests and operatorship in approximately 98,180 gross acre position onshore Alaska. The Company focuses on coring program HRZ shale & Upper Pebble Shale Unit (base seal). The Company has cut approximately two cores in the HRZ primary shale oil objective and the pebble shale unit (bottom shale) with recoveries. The Company focuses on1H 2016, which is a high resolution wide-azimuth three dimensional (3D) seismic acquisition. The Company has completed archaeological/cultural field work in its 1H 2016. The Company focuses on horizontal multi-stage frac and production test or vertical conventional test in its Icewine 2 project.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

AHAlife Holdings Limited, formerly INT Corporation Limited, is engaged in the sale of luxury and designer lifestyle products online. The Company is an online market place, which connects approximately 1.1 million users seeking items with over 3,800 independent designers and artisans in approximately 50 countries utilizing a network of over 70 curators across the world. The Company offers products under various categories, including women, men, home, beauty, dining and tech, among others. Its women products include jewelry, bags, accessories and apparel. The Company's men products include bags, accessories, jewelry, apparel and grooming products. Its home products include home accents, bed and bath, office, furniture, lighting and recreation. The Company's beauty products include hair care, face, cosmetics, skin and fragrance. Its dining products include dinnerware, drinkware, gourmet food and kitchen. Its tech products include mobiles, tablets, laptops, gadgets and cameras.

Ark Mines Ltd is engaged in exploration and development activities. The principal activity of the Company is the development of its Mt Porter project in preparation for the mining of gold, and the exploration and evaluation of surrounding tenements for gold. It holds interest in Mineral License (ML) 23839 (Mt Porter) and Frances Creek projects in the Northern Territory. Its projects include Mt Porter Anticline Projects, including 10400 Gold Deposit, 10800 Gold project and 10000 gold Project. It holds interest in the Glencoe Project, which is located in approximately three mineralized zones. It holds interest in Exploration License in Retention (ELR) 116, which immediately surrounds Mt Porter, and EL23237, which covers the northern extension of the Mt Porter anticline. It also holds interest in ML22839, which is located in the Northern Territory under the Pine Creek project; EL10137 under the Frances Creek project, and EL23237 under the Pine Creek South project, among others.

ActivEX Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company holds mineral exploration tenements in Queensland and Western Australia. The Company's focus is on exploration for gold and copper projects across its Queensland tenements. Its Gilberton Gold Project is located in the Georgetown Province in northeast Queensland, approximately 300 kilometers west-northwest of Townville. Its Ravenswood Gold Project is located in the Charters Towers Province in northeast Queensland, approximately 60 kilometers south of Charters Towers. Its Esk Copper and Gold Project consists of five exploration permits (EPM 14476, 14979, 16327, 18717 and part 16265) located approximately 100 kilometers west of Gympie in South East Queensland. Its Barambah Gold Project consists of three exploration permits (EPM 14937, 18732 and part 16265) located approximately 100 kilometers west of Gympie in South East Queensland. Its Cloncurry Copper and Gold Project consists of over 13 exploration permits.

AnaeCo Limited is a technology developer and designer of resource recovery and recycling systems. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of a process for the treatment of organic municipal solid waste (MSW) (the AnaeCo System). It provides engineering design and technical services to support the planning, design, development, implementation and operations of resource recovery and recycling solutions based on the AnaeCo System. The AnaeCo System is a technology that combines material recovery, anaerobic digestion and aerobic composting processes to recycle household waste into an organic fertilizer, renewable energy and recyclable plastics, metals and glass. The AnaeCo System is designed to process both mixed MSW and source separated organics. The Western Metropolitan Regional Council (WMRC) Project is involved in the design, construction and commissioning of a 60,000 tons per annum (tpa) AnaeCo Plant. The Company operates in the waste management sector.

Armstrong Jones Office Fund (the Fund) owns a portfolio of 17 office properties located throughout Australia. The portfolio has an average lease term of expiration of approximately 6.4 years. The Fund's properties, which are predominantly leased to investment-grade and blue chip tenants, are located across the major commercial markets within Australia, with 54% of the Fund located in New South Wales. Other properties are located in Victoria, Queensland, Western Australia and Australian Capital Territory. The Fund is managed by ING Real Estate Asset Management.

Anteo Diagnostics Limited is a nano-technology company. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of specialized surfaces used in life sciences, and the research and development of surfaces for specific binding of proteins (abiotics). It is engaged in offering products for sale into in-vitro diagnostics, point of care, medical devices and bioseparations markets. Its segments include Australia and Belgium. The Company offers nanoglue technology, called Mix&Go for healthcare markets. It also develops, manufactures and distributes products for the life sciences, clinical diagnostics and bio-separations markets and is creating new applications in the energy and medical devices sectors. It provides functional nanometer-thin coatings and binders across a range of industries and applications. Its subsidiaries include Anteo Technologies Pty Limited, Anteo Energy Pty. Limited, Aged Care Diagnostics Pty Limited, DIAsource Immunoassays SA and DIAsource IBERIA SL.

The a2 Milk Company Limited (a2MC) is engaged in the commercialization of a2MC branded milk and related products as supported by the ownership of intellectual property that enables the identification of cattle for the production of A1 protein-free milk products. The Company operates through four segments, which include Australia and New Zealand; China and other Asia; the United Kingdom and USA, Corporate and other. The Company's portfolio composition includes liquid milk, infant formula and other. The Australia and New Zealand segment includes sale of milk, cream, infant formula, whole milk powder and ice cream. The China and other Asia segment includes milk, infant formula, and whole milk powder sales. The China and other Asia segment is also responsible for the infant formula supply chain from New Zealand to all markets. The United Kingdom and USA segment includes milk and infant formula sales. The Company's brands include a2 Milk and a2 Platinum.

Activistic Limited is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in the further development and implementation of its micro-donation technology that enables regular payments or contributions using a mobile phone network, as well as the expansion of the user and beneficiary charities base. The Company's segments include Veterans Call and Ralli. The Company offers a product named White Label. The Company's applications include Veterans Call and Ralli. Veterans Call is a smartphone application for iPhone operating system (iOS) and Android. Veterans Call is the platform for people to find, connect with and contribute in a way to veterans' organizations. Ralli is also a smartphone application, which is offered for people of the United Kingdom. The Company is also focused on the Activistic applications platform, which intends to provide a consolidated view of data, visibility of user tracking and analytics, as well as a platform to manage Veterans Call and Ralli.

Pointerra Limited, formerly Soil Sub Technologies Limited, is an Australia-based company, which focuses on building an online Data as a Service (DaaS) solution for mapping the earth from three dimensional (3D) point clouds. The Company develops its 3D geospatial data technology. The Company builds DaaS solution for managing, distributing and visualizing point cloud data sets. The Company's technology offers real-time, dynamic Web viewing tools for providing access to user's data from any device in any location. It also enables users to upload raw data directly to its secure cloud servers, or process it on premise and upload a compressed stream of data. The technology also enables users to ship the data directly on a portable hard drive to skip the uploading step for big projects. The Company intends to be an online marketplace for 3D point cloud data by governments and commercial sector across the world. Pointerra Pty Ltd is a subsidiary of the Company.

Audalia Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in mineral exploration. The Company operates through two segments: Mineral Exploration, and Corporate and administrative. The Company's Medcalf vanadium-titanium Project is located approximately 470 kilometers east-southeast of Perth near Lake Johnston. The Project comprises two granted Exploration Licenses: E63/1133 and E63/1134. The Medcalf vanadium-titanium Project also includes three Prospecting Licenses: P63/1528, P63/1560 and P63/1561, as well as a mining lease, M63/656. These licenses cover an area of over 20 square kilometers. The Medcalf vanadium-titanium Project lies in the southern end of the Archean Lake Johnston greenstone belt. Its Gascoyne Project comprises tenements covering over 540 square kilometers that are prospective for Lead (Pb), Zinc (Zn) and Copper (Cu) deposits, located in the Gascoyne Region, Western Australia. The Gascoyne Project is located over 250 kilometers to the east of Carnarvon.

Adavale Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company is engaged in mining explorations and development in Australia and Indonesia. The Company is also involved in research and identifying coal projects across Indonesia. It is focused on exploration of its uranium project at Lake Surprise in South Australia, as well as evaluating other uranium and coal exploration opportunities. Its Tapan project lies approximately 120 kilometers south of the capital of Padang. Its Lake Surprise Project area contains the Jubilee and Mookwarinna Prospect areas, and these lie within a shallow and structural downwarp, known as the Clayton Basin. The Company's exploration licenses within northern part of the Lake Frome Embayment include EL 4949, EL 4950 and EL 5644. Its EL 4949 has an area of over 120 square kilometers. The Jubilee Prospect contains over 10 ore blocks. The Mookwarinna Prospect lies in the south-central part of EL 4950 and spaced drill-holes on a kilometer grid spacing.

Acorn Capital Investment Fund Ltd is an investment company. The Company's principal activity is to invest in a portfolio of listed and unlisted microcap companies. The Company's primary objective is to achieve after-fee returns on its investment portfolio in the long term that are higher than the Standard & Poor's (S&P)/Australian Securities Exchange (ASX) small ordinaries accumulation index, through long-term capital growth by way of investment in a portfolio of microcap companies. The Company invests in various sectors, such as consumer discretionary, consumer staples, energy, financials, healthcare, industrials, information technology, materials, telecommunication services and utilities. Acorn Capital Limited is the manager of the Company.

Argosy Minerals Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the development of exploration projects for graphite, copper, lithium, base metals and other mineral commodities. The Company holds an option agreement to purchase the Mt Paris Lithium Project, which includes an exploration license covering an area of approximately 110 square kilometers, located over 60 kilometers northeast of Launceston. It has farm-in joint venture agreement for the Wee MacGregor Copper-Gold Project, which includes approximately three mining licenses located over 60 kilometers southeast of Mount Isa. It focuses to identify and review project or asset acquisition opportunities. The Company's subsidiaries include Andover Resources NL, Argosy Energy Zambia Ltd, Rhino Mining and Exploration Close Company, Yucca Investment Sixty Three Corporation and Hallie Investments Number Three Thousand One Hundred and Seven Pty Ltd.

Aura Energy Limited is an Australia-based development company that has uranium projects in Europe and Africa also gold, lithium and soda ash in Africa. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of its projects in Sweden and Mauritania. Its segments include Sweden and Mauritania. Its projects include the Tiris project in Mauritania and the Haggan project. The Haggan project is a European uranium deposit located in Sweden. The Tiris Uranium Project is based on greenfields uranium discovery in Mauritania. Its portfolio also includes gold tenements in Mauritania just south of 21 million ounce Tasiast gold mine, and a soda ash and lithium prospects near the Tiris project. Its Tasiast South Gold Prospect tenements are located over 200 kilometers from Nouakchott, approximately 60 kilometers from the coast. The Soda Ash and Lithium Sabkha located over 165 kilometers from Hippolyte are large on a relative basis covering an area of approximately 85 square kilometers.

Avenira Limited, formerly Minemakers Limited, is engaged in the acquisition and development of the Baobab Phosphate Project in the Republic of Senegal (Baobab Phosphate Project). The Company's segments include exploration and development of the Wonarah Phosphate Project in the Northern Territory (Wonarah) located in Australia, and exploration and development of the Baobab Phosphate Project in the Republic of Senegal (Baobab) located in Africa.
