Its mineral tenure covers an area of over 1,000 square kilometers (100,000 hectares). The core of the mineral tenure with an area of approximately 148 square kilometers consists of over five east-west Reef Structures. Reef Structure 1 includes gold production from the approximately 10 mines, including the Brilliant, Day Dawn and Queen.

Dacian Gold Limited is a gold exploration and development company. The Company's principal activities include mineral exploration and development activities at its Mt Morgans Gold Project (MMGP) in Western Australia. MMGP is located over 20 kilometers west of Laverton, being approximately 850 kilometers northeast of Perth in Western Australia. The project area is a 520 square kilometer contiguous tenement package comprising granted mining licenses. MMGP includes various deposits, such as Westralia Deposit, Allanson Deposit, Beresford Deposit and Jupiter Deposit. The Jupiter Deposit occurs in the eastern half of the MMGP, being over 20 kilometers east-south-east of the Westralia Deposit. The Beresford mineralization is located at the south end of the Westralia ore system. The Cameron Well Prospect is located over five kilometers east of Westralia. The Callisto Prospect lies over six kilometers south of the Jupiter Deposit and over seven kilometers west of the Wallaby gold deposit.

Department 13 International Limited, formerly Kunene Resources Limited, is engaged in drone defense, cyber security and radio frequency (RF) software communications and networking. The Company develops software and communication systems for customers in both the public and private sectors. It offers Mesmer, a counter-drone system. Mesmer provides security measures to allow prison authorities to enforce perimeters to prevent the use of drones to deliver contraband. Mesmer prevents drones from penetrating perimeters, alerts the authorities and lands the drone in a secured space for subsequent recovery and investigation. In contrast to other systems, MESMER does not employ kinetic attacks or jamming. MESMER's detection stage occurs using cognitive techniques for blind signal detection and characterization to determine the existence of threats. MESMER's response stage is based on a technique called protocol manipulation.

Decmil Group Limited provides design, engineering and construction works for the oil and gas, resources, government and infrastructure sectors. The Company's principal activities include construction and engineering, property investment and accommodation services, and telecommunications. It operates through three segments: Construction and Engineering, Accommodation and Other. The Construction and Engineering segment is engaged in multi-discipline design, civil engineering and construction services; fabrication and installation of pipes, vessels and tanks, and delivery of study, project management, engineering and design consultancy services, among others. The Accommodation segment is engaged in building, owning and operating the Homeground Gladstone Accomodation Village located in Gladstone, Queensland. The Other segment owns and manages a commercial office building, and provides design, installation, commissioning and maintenance services.

Capilano Honey Limited is engaged in the packing of honey for domestic and export sales. The Company's segments include Domestic and Export. The Domestic segment's products are sold to customers with in Australia for Australian consumption and sale. The Export segment's products are sold to customers outside Australia for consumption outside of Australia. It offers classic honey, kids honey, premium selections, pure manuka honey, and creamed and pot set. Its classic honey is available in various forms, such as upside down, twist and squeeze, and jar. Its premium selections include yellow box, red box and macadamia. The Company sells Australian honey within Australian market under the Capilano brand. Its products are used in dessert, breakfast, main meals, sides, energy boost and healthy alternatives, among others. Its recipes include honey fruit smoothies, mango smoothie, honey lemonade, spring super food salad, strawberry shake, honey minted lamb, honey joys and honey fig puddings.

Cardinal Resources Limited is a gold exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in exploration of minerals in Ghana. The Company, through its subsidiary, Cardinal Resources Ghana Limited, holds approximately five tenements prospective for gold mineralization in Ghana in two northeast-southwest trending Paleo-Proterozoic granite-greenstone belts, the Bolgatanga and Namdini Projects located within the Nangodi and Bole-Bolgatanga Greenstone Belts in northeast Ghana, and the Subranum Project located within the Sefwi Greenstone Belt in southwest Ghana. The Namdini tenement is located approximately 12 kilometers southeast from its Ndongo East Prospect and approximately six kilometers southeast of the producing Shaanxi Gold Mine. The Bolgatanga Project area and the Subranum Project comprises approximately 734 square kilometers of granted tenements. It owns and operates two drill rigs.

Centaurus Metals Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in exploration and evaluation activities related to mineral resources. The Company operates through the exploration of minerals segment. Its projects include Aurora Copper Project; Mombuca Gold project; Conquista Direct Ship Ore (DSO) Iron Ore Project, and Jambreiro Iron Ore Project. Its Aurora Copper Project is located in the north-eastern region of Brazil in the State of Ceara, approximately 350 kilometers south of the State Capital Fortaleza. Its Mombuca Gold project focuses on gold and iron-ore mineralization, and is located in the State of Minas Gerais, Brazil. Its Conquista DSO Iron Ore Project consists of a portfolio of tenements located in the State of Minas Gerais, Brazil. Its Jambreiro Iron Ore Project, located in south-east Brazil, is a shovel-ready development project that is licensed for approximately three million tons per annum (Mtpa) of wet production.

Cleanaway Waste Management Limited, formerly Transpacific Industries Group Ltd., is a waste management company. The Company's segments include Solids and Liquids & Industrial Services. Its principal activities include offering commercial and industrial, municipal and residential collection services for all types of solid waste streams, including general waste, recyclables, and medical and washroom services; ownership and management of waste transfer stations, resource recovery and recycling facilities, secure product destruction, quarantine treatment operations and landfills; sale of recovered paper, cardboard, metals and plastics to the domestic and international marketplace; collection, treatment, processing and recycling of liquid and hazardous waste, including industrial waste, grease trap waste and used mineral and cooking oils, and providing industrial solutions, including industrial cleaning, site remediation, sludge management, parts washing and emergency response services.

DomaCom Australia Limited, formerly DomaCom Limited, is an Australia-based operator of an investment platform. The Company is the Australian Financial Services Licence holder and investment manager of the DomaCom Fund. The Company is engaged in management and platform services that it provides to the DomaCom Fund. Its investment platform offered through an Australian Securities and Investments Commission (ASIC) registered Managed Investment Scheme, the DomaCom Fund. The Companys online platform supports property listing management, which facilitates trading, unit registry and book build processing for existing properties and proposed developments. The DomaCom Funds customers are retail investors introduced to the DomaCom Fund through DomaCom Australias primary distribution channel. The DomaCom Fund offers a range of crowdfunding opportunities to retail investors directly, such as the Kidman Station campaign.

Carbon Energy Limited is an Australia-based gas business using its keyseam underground coal gasification (UCG) technology. The Company's principal activities include proving and improving its UCG technology, keyseam; progressing the China JinHong New Energy joint venture; licensing keyseam technology internationally, and establishing keyseam as the UCG technology of choice for UCG projects around the world. The Company operates through the development of clean energy and chemical feedstock from UCG syngas segment. Its keyseam technology transforms solid coal into gas underground and optimizes the amount of energy extracted from otherwise stranded coal resources. The Company provides UCG services from site selection through to rehabilitation. Its projects include Bloodwood Creek in Australia, Claromeco Coal Basin in Argentina and Mulpun Project in Chile. It also holds a UCG project located at Haoqin Coal Field in Xiwuqi in Inner Mongolia, China.

Dampier Gold Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in exploration and evaluation activities in Australia. The Company was involved in the exploration and evaluation of its mining tenements at the Plutonic Dome Gold Project. The Company is focused on search for a new resource project or other business opportunities.

Cyclopharm Limited is engaged in the manufacture and sale of medical equipment and radiopharmaceuticals, including associated research and development. The Company operates in two business segments: Technegas segment and Molecular imaging segment. The Technegas segment is a supplier of diagnostic equipment and consumables used by physicians in the detection of pulmonary embolism. The Molecular Imaging segment produces radiopharmaceuticals used by physicians in the detection of cancer, neurological disorders and cardiac diseases. The Company offers Technegas for lung imaging, and Molecular Imaging/Positron Emission Tomography radiopharmaceuticals, which are used in cancer, brain and cardiac imaging. The Company formed a joint venture with Alfred Health Solutions and Macquarie University Hospital to provide various imaging services on-site at the hospital. The Company's Ultralute is a device that extends the useful life of Molybdenum-99 (Mo-99) generators.

Dark Horse Resources Limited, formerly Navaho Gold Ltd, is an exploration company. The Company holds interests in gold projects in the United States, numerous mineral licenses in Australia, oil and gas projects in Australia (held through NavGas Pty Ltd), and coal and lithium projects in Argentina. It operates in the mining exploration and evaluation segment, and two geographic locations, including Australia and the Americas. The Company is primarily focused on the development of the coal assets in Argentina. The Company's project portfolio consists of energy resource and mineral projects. Its projects include Coal projects, Lithium projects, Oil and Gas Projects and Gold Projects. Its Coal projects include Pico Quemado Coal Project and Marayes Coal Project. Its Lithium projects are located in San Luis and Cordoba Provinces. Its Oil and Gas Projects include Pirie Torrens Basin Oil & Gas Project and Roma Shelf Oil & Gas Project. The Company's Gold Project includes New Mexico Project.

Dongfang Modern Agriculture Holding Group Limited is an Australia-based citrus company. The Company is engaged in the business of cultivation and sales of various agricultural produce, including the citrus fruits, such as tangerine, pomelo and navel oranges, and also camellia fruit and related products. It operates through four segments: Tangerine, Camellia, Pomelo and Orange. It sources tangerines primarily from orchards located at the source of Xunwu County, Ganzhou City. Its navel oranges orchards are located at the source of Special Citrus Zone, in Ganzhou City of Jiangxi Province. Its pomelos are sourced from plantations in the Nankang District, south west of Ganzhou, China. It harvests camellia fruit from various plantations in the Ganzhou City region, including in Xingguo County. Its products are pressed and processed to become camellia (or tea) oil, which is used in food preparation and other vegetable oil applications. Its total plantation area spans over 8,600 hectares.

DataDot Technology Limited is an Australia-based company, which provides asset identification, management, protection and authentication solutions. The principal activities of the Company include manufacturing and distributing asset identification solutions that include DataDotDNA and Asset Registers; manufacturing and distributing high security DataTraceDNA authentication solutions, and developing and distributing customized solutions combining DataDotDNA, DataTraceDNA and asset registration. The Company's segments include DataDotDNA and DataTraceDNA. DataDotDNA are polymer and metallic microdots containing etched data. DataTraceDNA is a machine readable system for authenticating materials, products and assets. Its authentication solutions include DataTraceSPECTRO, DataTrace CONSUMER and DataTrace CONSULT. Its theft deterrence solutions include ToolMate and PartMate. The DataDotDNA National Register allows users to verify the original owner of assets protected by DataDotDNA.

DGO Gold Limited is engaged in evaluation and exploration of mineral deposits in sediment hosted gold deposits in Australia. The Company is involved in acquiring exploration tenements on gold, copper and zinc exploration. The Company has applied for approximately three sediment hosted gold target areas in the Eastern Goldfields of Western Australia at Mt Edwards, Black Flag and Ora Banda South West. The Mt Edwards is an exploration license application, consisting of over nine contiguous sub blocks, located to the east of the Coolgardie-Norseman highway, approximately 15 kilometers north of the township of Widgiemooltha. The Black Flag is an exploration license application, consisting of over six contiguous sub blocks, to the west of the Kalgoorlie-Menzies highway, approximately 20 kilometers North West of Kalgoorlie. The Ora Banda South West consists of over 10 contiguous prospecting licenses, approximately seven kilometers south west of the township of Ora Banda.

Connexion Media Limited is an Australia-based Internet of Things (IoT) technology company. The principal activities of the Company consist of carrying out its endeavor to realize revenue streams from its two products, miRoamer and Flex. The Company operates in the segment of specializing in developing global information technology solutions for automotive industry in Australia. The Company offers software as a service (SaaS) products for the automotive industry. The Company offers various products, which include Flex, Commercial link, Wex Motorpass, miRoamer and Customisation. Flex is a cloud-based, integrated vehicle management system that gives control over fleet of cars, trucks and other vehicles from a central control point. miRoamer is an Internet Car Radio. miRoamer is a multi-platform application. The miRoamer application is available on iPhone operating system (iOS), Android, Blackberry and Desktop.

Duketon Mining Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral resources. The Company's projects include Duketon project, Eastern Goldfields projects and minority interest projects. The Duketon project consists of landholding over the Duketon Greenstone Belt. The Duketon project consists of over 2,000 square kilometers of contiguous granted and pending tenure located 80 kilometers to 120 kilometers north of Laverton in Western Australia. The Company holds tenements, such as the Diorite Hill Project, within the Eastern Goldfields project. The Diorite Hill project tenement is located over 20 kilometers east of Laverton and consists of an exploration license application over the eastern margin of the Merolia Greenstone Belt of the Eastern Goldfields Mineral Province. The Company's minority interest projects include Cardabia project in the western Gascoyne, and Pilgangoora and Western Shaw projects in the northern Pilbara.

Dakota Minerals Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration and project development company. The Company is engaged in exploration of mineral deposits. The Company's projects are located in Portugal and Western Australia. Its Lynas Find Lithium project is located in the Pilbara region of Western Australia, approximately 100 kilometers south of the regional center of Port Headland. It is located on and in the vicinity of Pilgangoora lithium-tantalum bearing pegmatitic dyke swarm. Its Sepeda Lithium Project is located in Barroso-Alvao district, Northern Portugal. The swarm area of Sepeda Lithium Project swarm area is over 1,500 meters long by over 500 meters wide. Its Lusidakota Lithium projects, located in Northern Portugal, are located over three districts of pegmatitic dyke swarms, which contain spodumene and petalite-bearing pegmatites. The Lusidakota tenement package consists of eight exploration licenses (one granted and seven under application).

DirectMoney Limited, formerly Basper Limited, is a marketplace lender that originates personal loans through its online lending platform. The Company's principal activities include writing unsecured personal loans for 3 to 5 year maturities to Australian consumers, then on-selling these loans to either the DirectMoney Personal Loan Fund (the Fund) or to institutional and wholesale investors. The Fund provides exposure to a portfolio of fixed rate, unsecured personal loans made to Australian borrowers. The Fund is a registered managed investment scheme. It offers interest rates and terms on personal loans for borrowers and provides structures for retail and institutional investors to invest in these loans. The Responsible Entity for the Fund is One Managed Investment Funds Limited. Its subsidiaries include DirectMoney Finance Pty Ltd, DirectMoney Investment Management Pty Ltd, DirectMoney Loans Servicing Pty Ltd, DirectMoney Credit Management Pty Ltd and DirectMoney Marketplace Limited.

DGR Global Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the business of resource-project generation and discovery across a range of commodities, including copper, gold, nickel, tin, iron ore, titanium, bauxite, coal, oil and gas. Its segments include DGR Global, Archer, IronRidge and Others. It generates and develops independently funded and managed resource companies. Its portfolio includes Armour Energy Ltd, which holds prospective whole basin oil and gas positions in Northern Territory and North West Queensland; SolGold plc, which focuses on discovery of a high grade copper gold porphyry system at Cascabel in Ecuador; IronRidge Resources Ltd, which includes prospective hematite rich iron targets evident in Tchibanga and Belinga Sud licence areas in Gabon; Aus Tin Mining Ltd, which is focused on the discovery and development of tin and nickel projects, and Dark Horse Resources Ltd, which focuses on Nirihuau Coal Project in Rio Negro province in Argentina.

DigitalX Limited, formerly Digital CC Limited, is an Australia-based software solutions company developing products and services. The Company is involved in the activities, which include development of software for retail-based consumer applications; Bitcoin trading and the operation of a liquidity desk, and Bitcoin mining. The Company operates through two segments: Software Development and Trading. The Company offers AirPocket, which is a short message service (SMS)-enabled, international mobile bill payments platform and mobile money remittance application. The application supports international Airtime transfers for the United States consumers to approximately 10 countries in Latin American in a partnership. The application is available on Google Play and the Apple App store. The Company also offers DigitalX Direct, which is a business-to-business liquidity platform that is designed to provide real time liquidity to institutional investors and commercial operators.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

3D Resources Limited is a mineral explorer. The Company focuses on commodities, including gold, copper, lead, zinc, nickel, coal, manganese, uranium, thorium and rare earth minerals. The Company operates in four segments, which include 3D Resource, Platquest, Alltower and Croydon Coal. The Company's projects include Mt Angelo Porphyry, Mt Angelo North and Koongie Park VMS, which are located at East Kimberly; Cosmo Newbery, located at Eastern Goldfields; Mt Padbury, located at Glengarry Proterozoic Basin, and Mt Agnes, located at Ashburton Proterozoic Basin. Its Western Australian projects are located in the Proterozoic Lamboo Complex of the East Kimberley, the Paleoproterozoic Glengarry Basin, in the Peak Hill Goldfield and the Archaean Cosmo Newbery area, in the Eastern Goldfields. It is evaluating coal projects in Indonesia and also assesses manganese in Timor and Kalimantan, iron ore projects in Kalimantan and Sulawesi, as well as gold resource projects in Australia.

Diversified United Investment Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company is engaged in taking medium to long term view and investing in Australian equities, listed property trusts, and short-term investments, and international equities through exchange traded index funds. The Company's objective in managing capital is to continue to provide shareholders with dividends and capital appreciation over the longer term within acceptable levels of risk. The Company invests in cash management units with the MF Cash Management Fund and cash deposits with Australian banks, with a direct or underlying AA-credit rating assigned by Standard & Poor's. The Company invests in Australian equities operating in a range of sectors, including banks, building materials, energy, healthcare, infrastructure and utilities, insurance, mining, mining service, other financials, property, retailers, transportation and telecommunications services.

Dicker Data Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the wholesale distribution of computer hardware, software and related products. The Company operates through two segments, which include Australian and New Zealand operations. The Company sells its products to over 3,000 resellers. The Company's product portfolio comprises of technology vendors, including APC, arcserve, AudioCodes, Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HP), ASUS, CISCO, SONY, LG, Kensington, Lenovo, Microsoft, Novell, Symantec, Targus, Ruckus, SONY, Kingston, Wyse, Plantronics, belkin, Motion, DELL, imation, intel, Trustwave, WatchGuard, cloudrecover, ShoreTel, NETGEAR and FUJIFILM, among others. The Company's subsidiaries include Express Data Holdings Pty Limited, Dicker Data New Zealand Ltd and Simms International Pty Ltd.

Dateline Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration and development company. The Company has exploration projects in the Republic of Fiji and Australia. The Company focuses on the exploration and development of Udu and Mt. Augustus projects. The Company also focuses on pursuing base metal opportunities in Australia and the South Pacific. The Company is focused on acquiring, exploring, evaluating and exploiting gold and copper-zinc deposits and exploring prospective tenements for other minerals. The Udu deposit includes the mineralization that consists of a cluster of Volcanogenic Massive Sulfide (VMS) lenses with an overprint of epithermal base metal mineralization. The Mt. Augustus sedimentary copper project is located in the Gascoyne region of Western Australia.

Consolidated Zinc Limited is an Australia-based minerals exploration company holding projects in Mexico, Australia and Sweden. The Company's principal activities are to acquire exploration tenements holding potential for mineral commodities, explore those tenements, discover mineral deposits and proceed to upgrade and develop those deposits. Its projects cover a commodity mix that includes zinc, lead, silver, uranium and copper. The Company is focused on the Plomosas Zinc-Lead-Silver Project. The Plomosas project is located in the northern Mexican state of Chihuahua, approximately 350 kilometers from the border with the United States state of Texas. The Company has interests in over 10 exploration and exploitation concessions in northern Mexico totaling approximately 3,020 hectares in area. The Plomosas project comprises zinc and lead mineralization of approximately 15%-25% combined, with significant silver credits of over two ounces per ton.

East Energy Resources Limited (EER) is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's east energy resources hold an exploration permits for coal (EPC 1149) in the Eromanga Basins in Central Queensland, approximately 65 kilometers south of the township of blackall. The Blackall Project is secured by tenement EPC 1149, EPC 1398 and EPC 1399, covering over 2,500 square kilometers just to the south of the township of Blackall, a rural community within central western Queensland, located on the Barcoo River. Its other tenements include EPC 1400, EPC 1403, EPC 1407 and MDL 464. The MDL464 tenement covers approximately 37,000 acres over the central portion of the main coal resources within EPC 1149. With a resource strike length of approximately 95 kilometers and an average width of approximately six kilometer, the three EPC's host an exploration target of over six billion tons of open cut mineable coal-one of the coal deposits in Australia. The Company's subsidiary is Idalia Coal Pty Ltd.

Diploma Group Limited is a construction and property development company. The Company is undertaking a portfolio of commercial, retail and residential projects. The Company's projects include Capri Coastal Apartments, Rockingham and QUEST East Perth. The Company's Capri Coastal Apartments, Rockingham is located within the Rockingham Beach Waterfront Village Precinct. The Company offers commercial construction and residential apartments, including multi-level residential, hotels, hospitality and tourism, commercial offices, retail, industrial offices, health and aged care, and sports and recreation. The Company offers a range of construction services, including design, construction project management, site management, construction management, construction supervision and contracting services. Its property development services include project identification, finance solutions, site acquisition and sales, marketing and property management services.

Dreamscape Networks Limited is an Australia-based provider of domain name, hosting and online services and solutions that enable businesses and consumers to find, establish and manage their online presence. The Company offers approximately 30 products and services across its three core segments: Domains, Hosting and Solutions. The Domains segment includes Domain Names, Domain Backorder, Domain Transfers, Domain Certification, Private Registration, Domain Services and Directory Listing. The Hosting segment includes Website Hosting, domain name system (DNS) Hosting, Servers, E-mail Exchange, Hosting Services and secured sockets layer (SSL) Certificates. The Solutions segment includes Website Builder, Traffic Booster, E-mail Marketing, Web Design, Logo Design, E-mail Protection, Site Protection, Web Analytics and Fax to E-mail. The Company's brands include Crazy Domains, Cheap Domains and Aust Domains. Its packages include Online Startup, Business Builder and Ultimate Empire.

Downer EDI Limited provides services to customers in markets, including transport services, technology and communications services, utility services, rail, mining, and engineering, construction and maintenance. The Company's segments include Transport Services, which includes its road, rail infrastructure, bridge, airport and port businesses, and provides a range of transport infrastructure services, such as maintenance and earth works; Technology and Communications Services, including services, such as civil construction, network construction, commissioning and testing; Utility Services, including water lifecycle solutions for municipal and industrial water users and sugar cane waste fired cogeneration plants; Rail, including rail asset solutions, such as passenger and freight build; Engineering, Construction and Maintenance, which includes services, such as engineering design and civil works for projects, and Mining, including blasting services and exploration drilling services.

Convergent Minerals Limited is engaged in mining and exploration operations. The Company's principal business activity is resources mineral exploration. The Company's projects include MT HOLLAND PROJECT, which is located in Western Australia (WA) and ESMERALDA PROJECT, which is located in Queensland (QLD). The Company's tenements at MT HOLLAND PROJECT include M77/1065, M77/1066, M77/1067, M77/1068, M77/1080, E77/1772, E77/1773, E77/1775, E77/1776, E77/2011, E77/2080, E77/2097, E77/2137, E77/2162, E77/2167, P77/4082, P77/4115 and P77/4220. The Company's tenements at ESMERALDA PROJECT is EPM18050. The Company's general purpose and miscellaneous licenses at MT HOLLAND PROJECT include G77/37, G77/38, G77/45, G77/47, G77/48, G77/49, G77/50, G77/68, G77/70, G77/71, G77/72, L77/199 and L77/200.

Eclipx Group Limited is a financial services company, which provides complete fleet management services, corporate and consumer asset backed finance and medium term vehicle rentals to the Australian and New Zealand market. The Company's segments include Australia Commercial, Australia Consumer and New Zealand Commercial. The Australia Commercial segment is engaged in vehicle fleet leasing and management business; commercial equipment finance and leasing, and has a diversified funding structure, which includes multiple funding parties. The Australia Consumer segment is engaged in online broker facilitating consumer financing for vehicles in Australia; consumer novated leasing business in Australia, and medium term rental to not at fault drivers. The New Zealand Commercial is engaged in vehicle fleet leasing and management business in New Zealand; used vehicle retail sales, and medium term rental to not at fault drivers. It brands include FleetPlus, Right2Drive and AutoSelect.

Draig Resources Limited is an Australia-based coal exploration company. The Company's principal activities are the exploration of coal resources in Mongolia and the evaluation of new business opportunities. The Company holds interests in approximately two exploration licenses in Mongolia. The Company holds an interest in Bellevue Gold Project, which is located approximately 157 kilometers north west of Laverton in Western Australia. The Bellevue Gold Project covers an area of approximately 27 square kilometers over three granted mining leases and one exploration license (tenementsM36/24, M36/25, M36/299, E36/535). The Company's subsidiaries include Draig Investments (Singapore) Pte. Ltd. and BDBL LLC.

Corazon Mining Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration for nickel, copper and gold, and development of mining activities. The Company operates through two segments: Australia and Canada. It is engaged in the mineral resource and exploration activities in Australia and Canada. The Company is exploring and developing the Lynn Lake Nickel-Copper-Sulphide (Lynn Lake) project in Canada and Mount Gilmore Cobalt-Copper-Gold project in Australia. The Lynn Lake project area is situated immediately adjacent to the Lynn Lake township. The Mount Gilmore Cobalt-Copper-Gold project is located approximately 35 kilometers from the center of Grafton in north-eastern New South Wales. The Mount Gilmore Cobalt-Copper-Gold project tenure includes one granted Exploration License (EL8379-one year old), covering an area of approximately 25 kilometers by 15 kilometers. The Company's subsidiaries include Resource Investment Group Pty Ltd, Manitoba Nickel Pty Ltd and Manitoba Nickel Inc.

Asia Pacific Digital Limited is engaged in digital strategy, creative and technology solutions: ADP Interact; digital market research, lead generation and performance marketing: ADP Acquire, and customer engagement and retention: ADP Engage. The Company's segments include APD Interact, which provides digital strategy, creative and technology services; APD Acquire, which provides performance-based digital marketing services that focus on customer acquisition and lead generation, such as search engine optimization, paid research and affiliate marketing services; APD Engage, which provides e-mail marketing, messaging and campaign management services, and APD Venture, which provides e-commerce services. The Company's services include customer relationship management, conversion rate optimization, data and insights, design and usability, development and technology, display advertising, lead generation, pay-per-click, social media marketing, SmartMail Pro and short message service.

Ding Sheng Xin Finance Co. Limited is an Australia-based holding company. The Company is a parent company for China Ding Sheng Xin Holdings Limited, Guizhou Ding Sheng Xin Long Asset Management Co., Ltd and Ding Sheng Xin Financing Guarantee Co., Ltd. The Company is engaged in providing financing and non-financing guarantee services to its customers. The Company's non-financing guarantee services include performance guarantees, which includes the guarantee of a party's obligations under a contract and litigation guarantees, which includes the guarantee of a party's obligations to court during litigation. The Company offers two guarantee services Working Capital Guarantee, which is branded as Ze Wu Pang Dai is a guarantee service for small and medium enterprises (SME) to assist them with obtaining finance from banks and Home Decoration Guarantee, which is branded as Gai Chao Huan Dai to assist individuals with obtaining bank loans to fund the decoration of their homes.

Dyesol Limited is engaged in the up-scale and commercialization of perovskite solar cells (PSC), through the provision of a range of products and services, including materials, consulting, research and development (R&D), collaborative product development, licensing, training, and turnkey manufacturing and laboratory facilities. The Company operates through three segments: Glass and Equipment, Metal Strip and R&D Materials. The Glass and Equipment business unit has three activities, including partner and customer business development, glass application development, and equipment engineering. The Metal Strip business unit facilitates the development of PSC on coil steel. The R&D Materials business unit undertakes core PSC material technology research and development of a generic nature, which is applicable to a range of PSC device product forms. It operates in Australia, Asia, Europe and North America.

CSG Limited (CSG) is an Australia-based company, which is a technology as a service provider. The Company is engaged in the print and business technology solutions in Australia and New Zealand. The Company's business segments include Business Solutions, Finance Solutions and Other. The business solutions segment provides the sale, support, service and financing of print and business technology equipment to customers across Australia and New Zealand. The Company's Enterprise Solutions provide managed service based print and technology solutions for enterprise, education and government customers in Australia and New Zealand. The finance solutions segment is a specialist service provider of lease and rental products for business technology assets sold and serviced by CSG in both Australia and New Zealand. The Company offers various products, including Photocopiers, Monitors, Large Format Displays and Mobile Devices.

Ensogo Limited is an Australia-based mobile shopping company. The principal activity of the Company is the provision of an e-commerce business. The Company's segments are Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Indonesia and Philippines. With operations in Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Philippines, Indonesia and Thailand, the Company provides products and services for sale to customers in South East Asia and Hong Kong through its e-commerce Websites. The Company connects over 140 customers to retailers by providing volume discounts on a range of goods. The Company's subsidiaries include iBuy Group Pte Ltd, Buy Together Hong Kong Ltd, Buy Together Retail Ltd, Buy Together Technology (Shenzhen) Ltd, Dealmates Sdn Bhd, Dealguru Holdings Pte Ltd, Deal Travel Pte Ltd, Mydeal Sdn Bhd, My Deal Travel & Lifestyle Sdn Bhd, Ensogo Holdings Limited, Living Social Malaysia Sdn Bhd, Ensogo Company Limited, Ensogo Inc and PT Living Social.

Doray Minerals Limited is a gold mining company. The Company's projects include Andy Well Gold Project, Deflector Gold Project (Deflector) and other exploration projects, such as Horse Well Gold Project. The Andy Well Gold Project is located approximately 50 kilometers north of Meekatharra, in the Murchison region of Western Australia (WA). Deflector is a gold-copper deposit located in the southern Murchison region of WA, approximately 450 kilometers north of Perth and over 160 kilometers east of the Western Australian regional city of Geraldton. Deflector's ore is located in approximately three separate lodes, including the West, Central and Contact lodes. It has an exploration tenement portfolio in both WA and South Australia (SA). The Deflector Project has a mine life of approximately six years. It is engaged in exploring gold mineralization at various WA regional projects, including the Gnaweeda Project. The Horse Well Gold Project is located near Wiluna.

Crossland Strategic Metals Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the exploration for rare earth elements (REE) and uranium in the Northern Territory and economic hard rock gold deposits. The Company's Charley Creek Project lies on pastoral leases to the west-north west of Alice Springs. In addition to Charley Creek Project, the Company has long-standing applications on the Aboriginal Land Trust in the southern Tanami region (Highland Rocks Project), which is a perspective for gold and copper.

Dragon Mining Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in gold mining and refining in Finland and Sweden. The Company is involved in exploration, evaluation and development of gold projects in the Nordic region. The Company operates various gold mines and processing facilities. It operates through two segments: Sweden and Finland. In Finland, the Vammala Production Centre (Vammala) consists of a converted approximately 300,000 tons per annum nickel flotation plant, the Orivesi Gold Mine (Orivesi) and the Jokisivu Gold Mine (Jokisivu). In Sweden, the processing operation is known as the Svartliden Production Centre (Svartliden), consisting of an over 300,000 tons per annum carbon in leach (CIL) processing plant and the Svartliden Gold Mine. Faboliden is a gold project located over 30 kilometers by road, southeast of its operational Svartliden Plant and over 750 kilometers north of the Swedish capital Stockholm. Its Kaapelinkulma Gold Project is an exploration project.

eCargo Holdings Ltd. provides eCommerce enabling and operation outsourcing services. The Company offers a range of services, such as fulfilment; operating online sales channels; warehousing; customer delivery, and marketing, among others. It provides eCommerce solutions to designer brands, retailers and branded manufacturers. The Companys services include eCommerce information technology (IT), eSupport, eMarketing, eOperation and eFulfillment, which are enabled by its eCoreOS eCommerce technology platform. eCommerce IT offers solutions, including eCoreOS, Web Design and Enrich. eSupport offers eStudio, call centre and copywriting. eMarketing provides brand strategy, Weibo and Wechat, among others. eOperation solutions include brand site development, TMALL Development and JD.com Development, among others. eFulfillment provides eDC, Express and QC facilitation, among others. The Company has its operations in Australia, South Africa and the United Kingdom, as well as other countries.

Delecta Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the wholesale distribution of adult products, investment in gold exploration company, and investment in oil and gas operation. The Company's segments include wholesale, and oil and gas. The wholesale segment sells wholesale products directly to the wholesale customers in Australia and New Zealand. The Company entered the oil and gas industry through the acquisition of an interest in an oil and gas field development project in the United States. Its geographical segments include Australia, New Zealand and United States. The Company's subsidiaries include Calvista Australia Pty Ltd, Calvista New Zealand Limited and Canadian River Inc.

Donaco International Limited is engaged in operating leisure and entertainment businesses across the Asia Pacific region. The Company's segments are Casino operations-Vietnam, Casino operations-Cambodia and Corporate operations. Its Casino operations-Vietnam segment consists of the Aristo International Hotel operating in Vietnam, hotel accommodation, and gaming and leisure facilities. Its Casino operations-Cambodia segment consists of the Star Vegas Resort and Club operating in Cambodia, hotel accommodation, and gaming and leisure facilities. Its Corporate operations segment consists of the development and implementation of corporate strategy, commercial negotiations, corporate finance, treasury, management accounting, corporate governance and investor relations functions. The Star Vegas Resort and Club has over 100 gaming tables, more than 1,400 slot machines, and 385 hotel rooms. The Aristo International Hotel has approximately 400 hotel rooms.

DroneShield Limited is a drone detection technology company. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of hardware and software acoustic technology for drone detection. It has developed drone detection solution that protects people, organizations and critical infrastructure from intrusion from drones. Its products include omnidirectional sensor, long-range sensor, dronegun, on-site processor and DroneShield user interface. It designs detection systems, which uses specialized technology. The Company's technology uses software and hardware, to detect drones approximately a kilometer away that would usually be invisible to radar, camera and radio frequency-based systems, and alert users in real-time through multiple channels ensuring any potential threats can be addressed. It utilizes audio/acoustic signatures to detect drones. The Company offers solutions for airports, prisons, government, commercial venues, critical infrastructure and executive protection.

DUET Group owns and operates energy utility assets in Australia, the United States, the United Kingdom and Europe. The Company's segments include Dampier Bunbury Pipeline (DBP), which owns the Dampier to Bunbury Natural Gas Pipeline (DBNGP), which is the only pipeline connecting the natural gas reserves of the Carnarvon and Browse basins; DBP Development Group (DDG), Wheatstone Ashburton West Pipeline which is a gas transmission pipeline that connects the domestic Wheatstone Liquefied natural gas (LNG) plant to the DBNGP; Energy Developments Limited (EDL), which is a provider of low greenhouse gas emissions energy and remote energy solutions, and manages an international portfolio of over 900 mega watt of power generation facilities; Utility Energy (UE), which operates a distribution network covers approximately 1,470 square kilometers of south-east Melbourne and Mornington Peninsula, and Multinet Gas (MG), which is a Victorian gas distribution company.

Decimal Software Limited provides digital advice solutions. It has developed Decimal, an omni-channel, cloud-based automated digital advice platform. The service platform is accessible directly from any smart device. The software-as-a-service-based platform enables enterprises to provide consumer-driven automated financial advice and execution to the consumer market with global application. It offers digital advice across various topics, such as savings, superannuation, insurance and retirement, as well as investments. Its Decimal platform features Decimal Advisor Console, Decimal Compliance Console, Decimal Marketing Console and Decimal Configuration Console. It offers Eqilize, a pre-configured digital advice (robo) solution built on the Decimal platform. The package caters to the small to medium sized superannuation and Non-Bank Financial Institution (NBFI) market. It offers its solutions to financial Institutions, such as banks, superfunds, credit and unions, among others.

Digimatic Group Ltd, formerly CPA Digital Media Group Ltd., is an investment holding company. The Company is engaged in the development of other software and programming activities. The Company operates through two segments: media and solutions. The Company's media segment specializes in online performance-based marketing and provides online marketing campaign planning and execution services. The media segment also manages a training academy that provides businesses and individuals with the opportunity to achieve financial stability through performance-based marketing. The Company's solutions segment is the platform and technology provider for brands to market and manage their products and services to a global audience. The solutions segment offers for brands a range of online and offline platforms and solutions to reach out to their targeted audiences with products or services.

Easton Investments Limited is a financial services company. The Company is engaged in the provision of wealth and asset management services, distribution services, and accounting and taxation services. The Company's segments include Wealth and Asset Management, which consists of Easton Asset Management Pty Ltd, Easton Wealth Protection Pty Ltd and First Financial Pty Ltd, and is engaged in providing financial planning, risk insurance advice and broking, self-managed superannuation administration and a distribution platform for managed funds; Distribution Services, which includes Knowledge Shop Pty Ltd, Merit Wealth Pty Ltd, Hayes Knight Referral Services Pty Ltd and Law Central Co. Pty Ltd, and provides professional support services and dealer group services primarily to the accounting profession; Accounting and Tax, which consists of Hayes Knight NSW, and is a traditional accounting practice, and Corporate, which comprises Easton Investments Limited.

DEXUS Office Trust is engaged in owning, managing and developing real estate assets and managing real estate funds. The Company offers space solutions for offices, industrial or retail property needs. The Company's segments include Office, which consists of domestic office space with any associated retail space, as well as car parks and office developments; Industrial, which consists of domestic industrial properties, industrial estates and industrial developments; Property management, which consists of property management services for third party clients and owned assets; Funds management, which consists of funds management of third party client assets; Development and trading, which consists of revenue earned and costs incurred by the Company on developments and inventory, and All other segments, which comprises corporate expenses associated with maintaining and operating the Company and it also includes the centralized treasury function.

Dubber Corporation Limited is engaged in the provision of call recording and audio asset management in the cloud. The Company offers Dubber, which is a technology that operates from a cloud platform. Its segments include SaaS and Corporate. It provides a call recording, management and access service. Its global reach allows recordings to be captured, managed and accessed from anywhere in the world. Its products include Call Recording, Call Playback, Call Recording Intelligence, Dubber Lab and Call Recording API. It offers Call-recording software as a service. With its Playback activated as a service through the service provider, end users can rewind, replay and save their conversations immediately after the call. Call Recording Intelligence is a collection of call recording analytics tools, products and services. Dubber API enables an access to recordings within user's existing business applications. Its Dubber Lab provides a platform for testing all of its services.

Empire Energy Group Limited is engaged in the acquisition, development, production, exploration and sale of oil and natural gas in the United States. The Company's segments include Oil and Gas operations, Investments, and Other. Its Oil and Gas operations segment includes all oil and gas operations in the United States. Its Investments segment includes all investments in listed and unlisted entities, including the investment in Empire Energy Group USA. The Company manages the oil and gas production operations through its subsidiary, Empire Energy E&P, LLC (Empire E&P). The Company sells its oil and gas products to owners of domestic pipelines and refiners located in Pennsylvania, New York and Kansas. The Company holds two exploration licenses and five license applications over 14.6 million acres in McArthur Basin, in the Northern Territory. The exploration program in the McArthur Basin, Northern Territory, is operated through its subsidiary, Imperial Oil & Gas Pty Ltd.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Ebos Group Limited is a marketer, wholesaler and distributor of healthcare, medical and pharmaceutical products. The Company is also an animal care products marketer and distributor. Its segments include Healthcare, Animal care and Corporate. The Healthcare segment incorporates the sale of healthcare products in a range of sectors, own brands, retail healthcare, wholesale activities and logistics. The Animal care segment incorporates the sale of animal care products in a range of sectors, own brands, retail and wholesale activities. Its businesses include Community Pharmacy, Institutional Healthcare, Contract Logistics and Animal Care. Community Pharmacy includes Symbion, Endeavour Consumer Health, ProPharma, DoseAid and Intellipharm. Institutional Healthcare includes EBOS Healthcare, Onelink, Clinect and Zest. Contract Logistics comprises Healthcare Logistics, Symbion Contract Logistics and Symbion Clinical Trials. Animal Care includes Masterpet, Lyppard, Animates and Vitapet.

Coziron Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company has exploration focused primarily on feed-stock material for the steel-making business but investigates any opportunities for gold, copper and other base metal mineralization on the tenements controlled by the Company. Its Yarraloola Project consists of over eight exploration licenses and approximately three prospecting licenses with a total area of over 850 square kilometers. In the southern part of the tenements palaeo-channels of the Robe River host deposits of pisolitic iron-ore. The Shepherds Well is approximately 192.2 square kilometers exploration license (E08/2361) located over 50 kilometers southwest of Karratha. The Yarrie tenements are located approximately 150 kilometers to the east of Pt Hedland. The Buddadoo Project is located over 200 kilometers east of the port of Geraldton. The KingX Manganese project includes over four granted exploration licenses in the Earaheedy basin.

DEXUS Property Group is a real estate investment trust. The principal activity of the Company is to own, manage and develop real estate assets, and manage real estate funds on behalf of third-party investors. The Company's segments include Office, which consists of domestic office space with any associated retail space, as well as car parks and office developments; Industrial, which includes domestic industrial properties, industrial estates and industrial developments; Property management, which includes property management services for third-party clients and owned assets; Funds management, which consists of funds management of third-party client assets; Development and trading, which includes revenue earned and costs incurred by the Company on developments and inventory, and All other segments. The owned portfolio consists primarily of central business district office properties. The Company's leasing includes office, industrial, retail, search for space and casual leasing.

Danakali Limited, formerly South Boulder Mines Limited, is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral resources. The Company is involved in the development of Colluli Potash Project in Eritrea. It operates through the exploration of minerals in Eritrea segment. Its Colluli Potash Project is located in the Danakil region of Eritrea, East Africa. Its Colluli Potash Project is located approximately 180 kilometers south-east of the capital, Asmara and over 180 kilometers from the port of Massawa. The Colluli Potash resource consists of over three potassium bearing salts, such as sylvinite, carnallitite and kainitite. The Colluli Potash project consists of over 1.3 billion tons of potassium bearing salts used for the production of potash fertilizers and approximately 350 million tons of rock salt. Its potassium bearing salts produces a range of potash types, including muriate of potash (MOP), sulfide of potash (SOP) and sulfide of potash magnesia (SOP-M).
Dotz Nano Limited, formerly Northern Iron Limited, is a technology company. The Company is focusing on the development, manufacture and commercialization of graphene quantum dots.

Dimerix Limited, formerly Sun Biomedical Limited, is clinical-stage biotechnology company, which is focused on developing therapeutics discovered using its drug development platform, Receptor-Heteromer Investigation Technology (HIT). The Company's principal activity is the development of its DMX-200 clinical asset for the treatment of chronic kidney disease and the commercialization of its underlying drug discovery technology. The Company's business segments are the development of occupational drug testing devices and new therapeutic agents in Australia, and clinical-stage drug discovery and development in Australia. Its DMX-200 is a combination of two existing drugs: irbesartan and propagermanium. DMX-200 is in Phase II clinical trials. It also has additional programs in its pipeline, including therapeutic candidates for treatment of Nonalcoholic Steatohepatitis (NASH) (fatty liver disease), Ocular diseases, Cancer fatigue and Multiple sclerosis.

Desane Group Holdings Limited is a property investment company. The Company's principal activities include property investment, property development (residential, commercial and industrial), property project management and resale, and property services. Its segments include Property Investment, Property Development, Property Project Management and Resale, Property Services, Plant and Equipment, and Other. The Property Investment segment includes rental income from prime real estate investments. The Property Development segment includes development projects, such as residential, commercial and industrial. The Property Project Management and Resale segment is engaged in property project management and resale of commercial, industrial and residential properties, principally in Sydney. The Property Services segment includes property and related services. Its geographical segment is New South Wales, Australia. Its properties include 7-9 Orion Road, Lane Cove, and 7 Sirius Road, Lane Cove.

De Grey Mining Limited is a mining company. The Company is engaged in exploration activities in Australia. The Company's principal activity is minerals exploration at its Turner River Project, located approximately 50 kilometers south of Port Hedland in the Pilbara region of Western Australia. The Turner River Project covers an area of approximately 980 square kilometers. The Turner River Project consists of over 900 square kilometers of gold and base metals tenure covering various portions of the Tabba Tabba Thrust and Mallina Shear Zone, host to approximately three gold and two base metal deposits, with various exploration targets. The Company's tenements include E47/891, E45/2533, E45/2364, E45/2995, E45/3390, E45/3391 and E45/3392. The Company's subsidiaries include Beyondie Gold Pty Ltd, Domain Mining Pty Ltd, Winterwhite Resources Pty Ltd and Last Crusade Pty Ltd.

Dome Gold Mines Limited is a mining company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of its projects in Fiji. It focuses on gold, copper and mineral sands in Fiji. Through its subsidiaries, Dome Mines Ltd and Magma Mines Ltd, it holds interests in three special prospecting licenses (SPLs) in Fiji: SPL 1495 (Sigatoka Iron Sand Project), SPL 1451 (Kadavu Island Project) and SPL 1452 (Nadrau Project). The SPL 1495 Sigatoka Iron Sand Project covers an area of approximately 2,522.69 hectares on the south coast of Viti Levu, and is located approximately 80 kilometers south of Nadi and over 120 kilometers west of the capital, Suva. The SPL 1451 Kadavu Island Project covers over 3,030 hectares and is located in the southern part of Fiji on Ono Island. The SPL 1452 Nadrau Project covers over 33,210 hectares on the main island of Viti Levu, Fiji. The SPL 1452 Nadrau Project contains two copper-gold-silver ionic leach geochemical anomalies (Namoli and Wainivau prospects).

DuluxGroup Limited is engaged in the manufacturing, marketing, selling and distributing of paint, coatings, adhesives, garden care and other building products. The Company's segments include Paints and Coatings Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), which offers Dulux decorative paints, woodcare, texture, protective, powder and industrial coatings; Consumer and Construction Products ANZ, which offers Selleys adhesives, sealants, and other household repair and maintenance products, and Parchem construction chemicals, decorative concrete solutions and related equipment; Garage Doors and Openers, which offers B&D garage doors and electronic openers; Cabinet and Architectural Hardware, which includes Lincoln Sentry, a specialist trade distributor of cabinet hardware and architectural hardware, and Other businesses, which includes Yates garden care and home improvement products, specialty coatings and adhesives businesses, coatings business, Craig & Rose paints business, and DGL Camel business.

Delta SBD Limited is a contracting company servicing the underground coal mining industry. The Company is engaged in the provision of contract mine services, which include mine operation, roadway development, board and pillar extraction, conveyor installations, total mine care and maintenance, equipment rental, mining products and other specialized mine services. It operates in the Mining contracting segment, which offers various services, such as mine care and maintenance, mine service, secondary support installation, excavation, ventilation device installation, service/utility installation/recovery, long wall relocations and support, conveyor installations and maintenance, plant hire and maintenance, mining products and supplementary labor. It offers DeltaGRID, which is a knitted polyester mesh used in underground coal mines as roof protection. It also provides mining services in the Illawarra, Hunter Valley, the Western regions of New South Wales and the Bowen Basin in Queensland.

Empire Energy Group Limited is engaged in the acquisition, development, production, exploration and sale of oil and natural gas in the United States. The Company's segments include Oil and Gas operations, Investments, and Other. Its Oil and Gas operations segment includes all oil and gas operations in the United States. Its Investments segment includes all investments in listed and unlisted entities, including the investment in Empire Energy Group USA. The Company manages the oil and gas production operations through its subsidiary, Empire Energy E&P, LLC (Empire E&P). The Company sells its oil and gas products to owners of domestic pipelines and refiners located in Pennsylvania, New York and Kansas. The Company holds two exploration licenses and five license applications over 14.6 million acres in McArthur Basin, in the Northern Territory. The exploration program in the McArthur Basin, Northern Territory, is operated through its subsidiary, Imperial Oil & Gas Pty Ltd.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Djerriwarrh Investments Limited is a closed end investment company. The Company is engaged in investing in Australian equities with a focus on stocks where there is an active options market. The Company's investment objective is to provide attractive total returns including capital growth over the medium to long term, and to pay an enhanced level of dividends. The Company invests in a range of sectors, including Energy, materials, industrials, consumer staples, banks, other financials (including property trusts), telecommunications, healthcare, other sectors, such as consumer discretionary, information technology and utilities, and cash. The Company uses exchange-traded options to enhance income return to investors. It holds a portfolio of approximately 50 companies.

Deep Yellow Limited is an advanced-stage uranium exploration and development company. The Company's principal activities include the core Namibian projects, which include pre-development activities to progress the Tumas Project and reassessment of the Omahola Project, and Other, which includes uranium mineral exploration in Namibia and activities associated with the divestment of non-core projects in Namibia and Australia. The Company's segments include Australia and Namibia. The Omahola Project consists of three relatively shallow open pitable hard rock deposits: the Ongolo and MS7 Alaskite deposits, and the INCA deposit. Its Tubas Sand Project consists primarily of low-grade secondary uranium mineralization (carnotite) in well-sorted aeolian (windblown) sand, which occurs immediately south of the Tubas palaeochannel located on Exclusive Prospecting License (EPL) 3496. The Tumas (Palaeochannel) Project straddles EPLs 3496 and 3497.

DateTix Group Ltd, formerly Enverro Limited, is a provider of social and dating products and services. The Company is engaged in the provision of software solutions, including implementation and training support services; development and marketing of its on-demand dating platform, and the provision of social and dating product and services, including the Datetix application, personalized matchmaking services and member events. Its segments include Dating services, Enterprise Services and Corporate. The Dating services segment includes online, events and matchmaking services in China, Hong Kong and Singapore. The Enterprise Services segment offers license and support services in Australia. It offers DateTix application, which facilitates offline dates; the Lovestruck platform, which is an online dating platform; the Noonswoon application, which is a dating application in Thailand. It operates in Hong Kong, China, Singapore, Thailand and the United Kingdom.

Eden Innovations Ltd, formerly Eden Energy Limited, is a clean energy company. The Company produces and sells a concrete admixture, EdenCrete and retrofit dual fuel technology, OptiBlend, developed for diesel generator sets. The Company's segments include Eden Innovations LLC and Eden Energy (India) Pvt Ltd. The Eden Innovations LLC segment is engaged in Optiblend sales, service and manufacturing in the United States, and EdenCrete sales and development. The Eden Energy (India) Pvt Ltd segment is engaged in Hythane and Optiblend sales, service and manufacturing in India. The Company has interests in carbon nanotube and carbon fiber production, nanomaterial concrete admixtures, hydrogen production, storage and transport fuel systems, including the low emission Hythane hydrogen-methane blend. Through the Company's pyrolysis process, methane (natural gas) is broken down into its constituents of hydrogen gas and carbon, without the production of carbon dioxide.

Domino's Pizza Enterprises Limited is engaged in the operation of retail food outlets and the operation of franchise services. The Company's segments include Australia/New Zealand, Europe and Japan. The Company is a franchisee for the Domino's Pizza brand across the world. The Company's menu consists of Domino's Pizzas, including Chicken and Prawn Pizzas, Traditional Pizzas, Pizza Mogul, Pizza Chef, Crusts, Extra Value Pizzas, Gluten Free and Chef's Best; Sides, including Breads and Chips, and Chicken and Dipping Sauce; Drinks, including Coca-Cola, Fanta and Mount Franklin, and Desserts, including Oven Baked Churros, Belgian Choc Fudge Brownies, Chunky Choc Chip Cookie, Mini Dutch Pancakes, Chocolate Dipping Sauce and Dessert Sampler Pack. In addition, the Company allows its customers to order Pizzas online. The Company operates in approximately seven countries, with over 2,000 stores. It has presence in Australia, New Zealand, Belgium, France, the Netherlands, Japan and Germany.

Data#3 Limited is engaged in providing information technology solutions. The Company operates through two segments: Product, which is engaged in providing hardware and software licenses for its customers' desktop, network and data center infrastructure, and Services, which is engaged in providing consulting, project, managed and maintenance contracts, as well as workforce recruitment and contracting services, in relation to the design, implementation, operation, and support of information and communication technologies (ICT) solutions. Its technology offerings cover various areas, including consulting; which offers solutions to align people, processes and technology; data and analytics for business decisions; hybrid Information technology (IT)/cloud, which offers secure data center solutions; IT lifecycle management, which offers solutions to optimize customers' IT landscape; mobility, which connects to business networks and information, and security to manage cyber security.

DEXUS Industrial Trust is an Australia-based trust that owns, manages and develops real estate assets and manages real estate funds on behalf of third party investors. The Trust's segments include Office, Industrial, Property management, Funds management, Development and trading, and All other segments. The Office segment is engaged in offering office space with any associated retail space, as well as car parks and office developments in Australia and New Zealand. The Industrial segment offers domestic industrial properties, industrial estates and industrial developments. The Property management segment is engaged in offering property management services for third party clients and owned assets. The Funds management segment is engaged in the funds management of third party client assets. The All other segment includes the centralized treasury function.

Eumundi Group Limited is engaged in the operation of the Ashmore and Aspley Central Taverns, and the holding of investment properties. The Company's segments include Hotel operations and Investment property operations. The hotel operations segment sells packaged alcoholic beverages through its retail outlets, sells food and alcoholic beverages on-premise through bars and restaurants and operates licensed gaming venues. The investment segment owns and leases investment property assets to retail tenants. The Company holds portfolio of properties in high growth areas in Queensland. Its places of business include Ashmore Tavern; Aspley Shopping Centre (including Aspley Central Tavern); Aspley Arcade Shopping Centre, and Level 15, 10 Market Street. The Company's subsidiaries include Eumundi Property Group Pty Ltd, Eumundi Group Hotels Pty Ltd and Airlie Beach Lagoon Hotel Pty Ltd.

Diatreme Resources Limited is focused on development activities and mineral exploration within Australia. The principal activity of the Company is exploration of mineral sands, copper and gold. Its projects include Cyclone Zircon Project, Eucla Basin, Cape Bedford, Clermont, Grays Hill and Tick Hill. Its Cyclone Zircon Project is situated in Western Australia on the Barton shoreline along the northern margin of the Eucla Basin, approximately 20 kilometers west of the South Australia border and over 300 kilometers north of Eucla. Eucla Basin is an onshore-offshore basin on the southern Australian passive margin. The Grays Hill project is located approximately 40 kilometers northeast of Rockhampton. The Clermont Project consists of over three exploration permits and covers various prospects, including Rosevale Project and the Peak Downs Copper Mine. The Tick Hill Gold Project consists of over three granted mining lease numbers 7094, 7096 and 7097, totaling approximately 390 hectares.

Dart Mining NL is an Australia-based company engaged in exploring, evaluating and developing Orogenic Gold, Porphyry Gold and Lithium opportunities in North East Victoria. The Company's gold prospects include Mountain View, Rushworth, Fairley's, New Discovery, Onslow and Empress Lodes. The Mountain View prospect is located approximately 35 kilometers southwest of Corryong within the Company's Dart Goldfield. The Fairleys prospect is located approximately 17 kilometers southwest of Bright within EL4724. The Empress Gold Lodes at Granite Flat are hosted within the Banimboola Quartz Monzodiorite approximately nine kilometers southeast of Mitta Mitta. The Onslow Reef workings are made up of a small isolated cluster of workings, located approximately eight kilometers south of Unicorn within EL4726. The mineralization at Onslow Reef is generally narrow and composed of quartz-sulfide lodes with true widths between 0.7 and 1.5 meters.

dorsaVi Ltd is engaged in the distribution of motion analysis technologies. These technologies are commercialized through license, sale or fixed fee consultancy. The Company's segments include Australia, Europe and the United States of America. The Company's wireless technology consists of Muscle Sensor and Movement Sensor. It offers wearable sensors, software and algorithms that objectively measure movement and muscle activation at over 200 frames per second. Its products include ViSafe, ViMove and ViPerform. ViSafe is a wireless sensor technology that tracks and measures how people move in real-time work situations. It offers ViSafe Wearable Sensors and ViSafe Compliance. ViMove is a wireless sensor technology that objectively measures human movement and turns it into actionable data. ViPerform provides objective data to accurately assess and prevent risk of injury, guide training programs, and help determine when it is safe to return to play.

Drake Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of its projects in Scandinavia, Africa, and Australia. The Company focuses on exploration and evaluation of nickel, gold, silver and base metals projects. The Company operates through three segments: Australian Exploration, Scandinavian Exploration and African Exploration. The Company's projects include Guinea Projects, Mauritania Projects, Norway Projects and Swedish Projects. The Company's Norway Projects include JOMA project and Sulitjelma Joint Venture project. The Company's JOMA project covers approximately 50 square kilometers, including the historic Gjersvik mine and Exploration and Exploitation (Mining) Agreement over the Joma mine. The Company's Sulitjelma Joint Venture project covers approximately 70 kilometers at Sulitjelma. The Company's Swedish Granmuren Nickel project has its greenfield nickel, copper, cobalt discovery in the Bergslagen district of Sweden.

Echo Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration for mineral resources. The Company is focused on Gold in the Yandal Belt region of Western Australia. The Yandal Gold Project is located in the northern part of the Eastern Goldfields, and hosts the Julius Gold Project, as well as a range of prospective targets. The Company holds approximately 915 square kilometers tenement package across the Yandal Gold Province. The Julius Gold Project is located approximately 450 kilometers north of Kalgoorlie and over 70 kilometers east of Wiluna. The Zaphod Prospect is located within the southern part of the tenement package and within approximately 10 kilometers of multi-million ounce Gold deposits. The Company has also identified a range of regional targets at the Yandal Project. The regional prospects include Tipperary, Wimbledon, Bill's Find, Orpheus and Shady Well.

Dragon Mountain Gold Limited is engaged in examining opportunities with a view to identifying a new project. The Company operates primarily in the minerals exploration and evaluation industry. Xinjiang Pan Pacific Mining Co Ltd. (XPPM) is the Company's subsidiary. The Company is maintaining the XPPM licenses held at Urumqi in North Eastern China. The Company is primarily operating in China.

Dragontail Systems Limited is an Australia-based technology company. The Company has developed Algo Dispatching System. The Algo Dispatching System is an algorithm, which streamlines, optimizes and manages the entire restaurant order and delivery transaction, including order receipt, kitchen prioritization for meal preparation, dispatch and route management, and customer delivery. Its Algo Dispatching System automates the kitchen flow of restaurants, as well as the process of dispatching drivers. The Algo Dispatching System components include Kitchen station, dispatch station, driver's unit and Customer tracking. Its Algo Dispatching System is based on a field tested mathematical algorithm, which manages both ends of a quick services restaurants (QSR). The Algo Dispatching System uses a proxy server outside the restaurant to communicate between restaurant management, delivery drivers and customers. The Algo Dispatching System also enables customers to track their order online.

Dempsey Minerals Limited is an Australia-based mineral and oil exploration company. The Company is engaged in mineral exploration, acquisition and evaluation. The Company's segments include Exploration and Unallocated. The Company's minerals portfolio includes the Greenbushes South project and The Socrates project in Western Australia. The Greenbushes South project comprises one exploration License application (E70/4629) covering a total area of approximately 43 square kilometers. The Greenbushes South project is prospective for lithium, tin and tantalum. The Socrates Gold Project is located approximately 155 kilometers southeast of Kalgoorlie and comprises underexplored Archaean Greenstones of the Eastern Goldfields Province, as well as Proterozoic metamorphic rocks of the Tropicana Gold Province.

Egan Street Resources Limited, formerly Auricup Resources Limited, is engaged in the evaluation of opportunities to acquire and develop mineral tenements in Western Australia and Mexico. The Company's geographical segments include Mexico and Australia. The Company holds tenements, which includes the Rothsay Gold Project and Victoria Bore in Western Australia and the Mazocahui Project in Mexico. The Rothsay Gold Project is located approximately 300 kilometers north-north east of Perth, in the Southern Murchison region of Western Australia and covers an area of approximately 69.4 square kilometers, including the Rothsay tenements. The Company's subsidiaries include Auricup International Pty Ltd, Auricup (Rothsay) Pty Ltd, Minera Auricup de R.L. de C. V, Recursos Auricup de R.L. de C.V., Auricup Baviacora Pty Ltd and Auricup Victoria Bore Pty Ltd.

DWS Limited is an information technology (IT) services company. The Company provides information technology services to a range of corporations and government bodies. The Company offers a suite of integrated solutions spanning IT consulting services, including IT strategy and architecture advice, program and project management, business and technical analysis, custom application development, systems integration and solution testing; digital solutions incorporating data automation and capture systems, customer-led innovation, digital strategy and design services; business intelligence, including advanced analytics, Power business intelligence (BI) and data warehouse as a service; strategic sourcing and productivity services, and managed application services using a mix of offshore, on-site, off-site and high-security models depending on client requirements. The Company has its operations in Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Coolangatta, Adelaide, Canberra and Perth.

Eastern Goldfields Limited, formerly Swan Gold Mining Limited, is engaged in mineral exploration and evaluation, and the care and maintenance of its gold producing mines. The Company's segments include ongoing care and maintenance and mine development work segment and exploration segment. The Company holds interests in the Davyhurst Gold Project and Mt Ida Project. The Davyhurst Gold Project is located approximately 120 kilometers north-west of Kalgoorlie, and the Mt Ida Project is located over 200 kilometers north-west of Kalgoorlie. It also holds a tenement position, covering approximately 1,420 square kilometers. Its other projects include the Golden Eagle project Area; Lights of Israel Complex; Waihi Project Area; Mulline Project Area, including Foxtrot Prospect and Lady Gladys Offset Prospect; Callison/Glasson Project Area, and Siberia Project Area, including Sandking and Missouri Project Area, Camperdown Project Area, Black Rabbit Deposit, Pole Prospect and South Pole Prospect.

Energy Action Limited is an energy management, technology and services company. The Company's principal activities are providing integrated energy management services to a range of commercial and industrial customers. The Company provides electricity and gas procurement services, energy monitoring services and sustainability services in Australia. Its services include energy procurement: specialized in buying and negotiation strategies, utilizing reverse auctions, bespoke tender models and advising on structured products; energy monitoring, assessment and contract management (Energy Metrics), and energy efficiency and sustainability, and projects and advisory services (PAS). Its projects and advisory services include compliancy reporting, demand management solutions, embedded networks feasibility and management, energy audits and assessments, grants and funding, independent commissioning agent, and measurement and verification and metering systems.

E&A Limited is an investment company. The principal activities of the Company consist of provision of engineering and maintenance services to the oil and gas, mining and resources, water, defense, and power and energy industries, and financial advisory services to the corporate sector. Its segments include Investment & Corporate Advisory, which provides a range of corporate advisory services; Water & Fluid Solutions, which provides geomembrane liners and floating covers, and supplies and designs stainless steel drainage and pressure systems, among others; Heavy Mechanical and Electrical Engineering, which operates pipe fabrication and installation business, and provides a range of steel fabrication and structural engineering services, and electrical engineering consultancy and project management services, among others, and Maintenance Engineering & Plant Construction, which provides electrical and instrumentation services, and supplies breakdown and repair services, among others.
