Empire Oil and Gas NL is an Australia-based company engaged in oil and gas exploration and production. The Company is an onshore conventional gas and condensate producer and explorer. The Company has assets in Perth Basin in Western Australia. The Company's oil and gas producing assets are located in Red Gully Gas and Condensate Processing Facility (Red Gully Processing Facility) is in the Perth Basin. The Company's producing assets at Red Gully are located approximately 150 kilometers from the city of Perth. The Red Gully Processing Facility has produced and delivered over 7,800 Terrajoules (TJ) of gas. It is the holder of the onshore acreage in the prospective Perth Basin with its production licenses and permits covering approximately 9,000 square kilometers. The Red Gully Processing Facility is located in the Shire of Gingin, approximately 150 kilometers from the city of Perth. It holds nine exploration permits and two production licenses in the Perth Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Eureka Group Holdings Limited is engaged in the ownership and property management of senior independent living communities. The Company is principally engaged in providing specialist property asset management through property ownership and caretaking and infrastructure management; providing accommodation and tailored services to a range of market of aged residents with discretionary and nondiscretionary spend characteristics, and project management. The Company operates in two segments, which include Rental Villages, which includes ownership of senior's rental villages and Property Management, which includes management of senior's independent living communities. The Company's senior's accommodation villages include Alexam Place, Amber Lodge, Avenell Village and Cascade Gardens. The Company provides specialist management services under the brand names of Eureka Care Communities, Eureka Cascade Gardens, Village Life and SunnyCove.

Sigma Pharmaceuticals Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution business. The Company delivers pharmacies across Australia. The Company also manages and promotes a range of over-the-counter private and exclusive label products made available to brand member customers, as well as a generic range of private label products under the Pharmacy Care range. The Company, through its subsidiary, Central Healthcare Services (CHS), operates in the hospital pharmaceutical distribution market. The Company has pharmacy-led network in Australia, including over 700 retail brand members representing various brands, such as Amcal, Guardian, PharmaSave, Chemist King and Discount Drugstores (DDS). It offers third party logistics (3PL) and fourth party logistics (4PL) services, which include inventory management, centralized and decentralized warehousing, debtor management and customer service facilities.

Enero Group Limited is engaged in providing marketing and communication services, including strategy, market research, advertising, public relations, communications planning, graphic design, events management, direct marketing and corporate communications. The Company consists of approximately 10 marketing and communication services businesses across over eight countries. The Company has three hubs: Sydney, London and New York. It has two cash generating units (CGUs): the Operating Brands CGU and the Search Marketing CGU. Its Operating Brands business includes International and Australian marketing and communication services. It has offices or affiliates in Auckland, Amsterdam, Frankfurt, Glasgow, Houston, Madrid, Melbourne, Milan, Munich, Paris, San Francisco, Tokyo and other markets. The Company's subsidiaries include Enero Group UK Holdings Pty Limited, Enero Group UK Limited, BMF Holdco Pty Limited and Brigade Pty Limited.

Devine Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in community development and creation, home building, and apartment and mixed use projects. In addition, the Company is engaged in construction business. The Company's segments include Communities, Development, Construction and Corporate. The Communities segment includes land development and integrated housing. The Development segment includes apartment and mixed use projects. The Construction segment includes residential apartment construction. The Company's subsidiaries include Devine Homes Pty Ltd, Devine Constructions Pty Ltd, Pioneer Homes Australia Pty Ltd, Devine Funds Unit Trust, 111 Margaret Street Pty Ltd, Victoria Point Docklands Pty Ltd, Riverstone Rise Gladstone Unit Trust and DoubleOne 3 Pty Ltd.

Dropsuite Limited, formerly Excalibur Mining Corporation Limited, offers Dropsuite, a Cloud-based software platform that enables small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) to backup, recover and protect their digital assets. The Company's products include Dropmysite, Dropmyemail, Dropmymobile and DSE Server Backup. Dropmysite is a cloud-based Website backup and monitoring service that Website owners can use independently to schedule automatic backups, monitor Website availability and performance, and restore lost or corrupted data in a single click. Dropmyemail is a cloud e-mail backup and archiving service that helps businesses and consumers backup, manage, recover and protect all of their critical data. Dropmymobile provides automatic backups of users' mobile phone contacts, short message service (SMS), pictures, videos, call logs and much more in the cloud. DSE Server Backup is a file-based backup solution ideal for virtual private server (VPS), dedicated and cloud servers.

The Environmental Group Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the design, application and servicing of gas and vapor emission control systems, inlet and exhaust systems for gas turbines and engineering services to a range of industries. The Company's segments include Products and Corporate. The Products segment incorporates the operations related to the supply, design, construction and installation services to industry and includes activities related to air pollution control, pressure sewer systems and design and manufacture of gas turbine equipment and solutions, which incorporates the Total Air Pollution Control Pty Limited (TAPC) pollution control dust and fume (electrostatic precipitators and filtration businesses) and gas vapor business units and the Baltec IES Pty Ltd (Baltec) design and manufacture business. Its subsidiaries include The Environmental Group Share Plans Pty Limited, Environmental Group (Operations) Pty Limited and Mint Assist Mechanical Pty Limited.

Emu NL is an Australia-based junior resource company. The Company is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's principal activities are to explore its mineral interests in Western Australia and the United States; to assess and pursue mineral property acquisition opportunities globally, and to invest in shares in listed mining entities. The Company has an agreement to explore the Speedway project located on the Utah/Nevada border. The Company's subsidiaries include Emu Blue Pty Ltd and American Emu Inc.

Eastern Iron Limited is principally engaged in the exploration and delineation of iron ore, precious and base metals resources in Australia/Asia Pacific region and the development of those resources into economic, cash flow generating mines. The Company's projects include Nowa Nowa Iron and Nowa Nowa Copper. Its Nowa Nowa Iron Project is located over 250 kilometers (km) east of Melbourne, which is close to the Princes Highway. Its mineral exploration license in Victoria, EL5545, covers an area of approximately 110 square kilometers near Buchan. Its mineral exploration license in Victoria, EL006183, covers an area of approximately 60 square kilometers just north of Nowa Nowa. It also holds the Eulogie and Hawkwood magnetite projects in Central Queensland. Gippsland Iron Pty Ltd is the subsidiary of the Company.

DTI Group Ltd provides integrated surveillance, passenger communication systems and fleet management solutions for the global mass transit industry and other related markets. The Company operates through three segments: Australasia, EMEA and Americas. Its products and services include Advanced surveillance solutions, which include specialized hardware systems, incorporating video, audio, global positioning system (GPS) tracking, communications and recording technology supported by device and data management software to provide fleet-wide, closed-circuit television (CCTV) and vehicle management solutions; Passenger communication solutions, which includes specialized hardware systems, incorporating real time passenger information through graphical and high brightness displays, as well as public address and hearing aid loop communications and passenger emergency communications, and Managed Services, which includes back-end control room communications and infrastructure.

Energy Metals Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company's principal activity includes uranium exploration. The Company's segments include uranium exploration, uranium trading and corporate. The Company holds a portfolio of approximately eight exploration projects, which cover over 3,500 square kilometers, located in the Northern Territory and Western Australia. Its projects include Bigrlyi and Ngalia, Macallan, Mopoke Well, Lake Mason, Anketell, Manyingee and Lakeside. Its Manyingee exploration license (E08/1480) is located approximately 85 kilometers south of the port of Onslow; Mopoke Well project is located approximately 55 kilometers west of Leonara; Lakeside project is located in the Murchison district, approximately 20 kilometers west of Cue; Anketell project is located 50 kilometers of Sandstone, and Lake Mason project is located approximately 25 kilometers north of Sandstone.

Ellex Medical Lasers Limited designs and manufactures lasers and ultrasound systems. The Company is also engaged in the distribution and service of medical devices to ophthalmologists to diagnose and treat eye disease, and manufacture and distribution of lasers and ultrasound. Its segments include Distributors, which sells ophthalmic medical equipment to independent third-party distributors across the globe and Direct, which sells ophthalmic medical equipment to the end user customer in various markets around the world. Its products include ultra Q, Solo, Tango, iTrack, ultra Q reflex, solitaire, integer pro scan, integer pro and 2RT. Selective Laser Trabeculoplasty with Tango and Solo addresses early-stage glaucoma. Its iTrack addresses late-stage glaucoma. Its ultra Q and ultra Q reflex addresses cataracts and vitreous floaters. Its integer pro and integer pro scan addresses diabetic disease of retina. Its 2RT addresses early-stage age-related macular degeneration and macula edema.

Elders Limited is engaged in the provision of livestock, real estate and wool agency services; services and farm inputs; financial services; real estate franchise; live export operations; feedlotting of cattle; grain trading, and red meat supply chains. The Company's segments include Network, which includes the provision of agricultural retail products; Feed and Processing, which includes the Australian cattle feedlot near Tamworth in New South Wales (Killara Feedlot), the Indonesian cattle feedlot near Lampung (PT Elders Indonesia), and Elders Fine Foods, which is involved in the importation and distribution of Australian and New Zealand food products throughout China; Live Export, which facilitates the trades of dairy, beef feeder, beef slaughter and breeding cattle, and sheep from Australia and New Zealand to international markets by sea or air freight, and Other, which includes the general investment activities and the administrative corporate office activities.

Emu NL is an Australia-based junior resource company. The Company is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's principal activities are to explore its mineral interests in Western Australia and the United States; to assess and pursue mineral property acquisition opportunities globally, and to invest in shares in listed mining entities. The Company has an agreement to explore the Speedway project located on the Utah/Nevada border. The Company's subsidiaries include Emu Blue Pty Ltd and American Emu Inc.

Elk Petroleum Limited is an oil and gas producer and developer. The principal activities of the Company include development of a carbon dioxide (CO2) enhanced oil recovery (EOR) project at the Grieve oil field in Wyoming, the United States; continuation of operations at the Singleton Unit in Nebraska in anticipation of future implementation of an EOR project in the Singleton Unit, and acquisition of the Singleton South oil field in Nebraska focusing on development of potential by-passed oil pool on the southern flank of the Singleton Unit. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and US. Its subsidiaries are based in Casper, Wyoming, and their activities comprise administration, production, exploration, evaluation and development of oil and gas fields and ownership of pipelines. The Grieve oil pipeline is an approximately 30-mile-long (eight-inch diameter) steel pipeline that extends from the Grieve CO2 EOR Project to a receiving station located in Casper, Wyoming.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Ensurance Ltd, formerly Parker Resources Limited, is engaged in sale of insurance products and underwriting, and development of industry information technology (IT). The Company's segments include insurance, information technology and Treasury. It operates three businesses, including a Sydney-based insurance brokerage, insurance underwriting agency and an IT company. Its insurance brokerage, Savill Hicks Corp Pty Ltd (SHC), is a national insurance brokerage and operates complementary underwriting agency. Its IT business, Ensurance IT Pty Ltd, offers an online platform, which enables businesses to execute real-time insurance sales online. Its online insurance products include general insurance, such as home and contents insurance; SHC Insurance Brokers, which include owner builder insurance, trades insurance and transit insurance, and Ensurance Underwriting, which includes licensed builder annual construction, plant and liability insurance and specified construction insurance.

Emerchants Limited is a payments solutions provider of prepaid financial card products and services. The Company's segments include Australia Reloadable, Australia Non-Reloadable, Europe and North America. By using its payments software and processing platform, the Company provides its clients with financial service payment solutions for reloadable and non-reloadable prepaid card programs, in Australia, the United Kingdom and Europe, the United States and Canada. It offers various solutions, such as consumer lending, EachWay cash load solution, disaster recovery and commercial solutions. It provides prepaid solutions, such as treasury, risk, and compliance and fraud management. EachWay cash load solution allows customers to convert cash to value in their gaming account, and to deposit cash at a retailer for instant value in the gaming account. It delivers general purpose reloadable (GPR) and non-reloadable prepaid card based solutions for clients across various industries.

Dynasty Resources Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company is principally engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral licenses. The Company also holds interest in Shanghai Chen Mao

Finance Lease Co., Ltd, which is financial leasing company operating in mainland China. The Company operates through two geographical segments: mineral exploration in Australia and financial leasing in China. The Company holds interest in the North Shaw Project. The Company owns tenement E 45/2728-I that sits adjacent to lithium resources in the Pilgangoora Area of the East Pilbara region in Western Australia. The Company holds interest in Tropicana tenement, which is a 48 square kilometers tenement. Tropicana tenement is located in the Mt Margaret Mineral Field approximately 370 kilometers North East of Kalgoorlie. The Company also holds interest in two tenements in the Bulloo Downs project area, including E52/2024 and E52/2464.

Elementos Limited is engaged in project development in Australia. The Company operates through the segment of exploration of mineral assets in Australian. The Company is developing the Cleveland tin-copper-tungsten project. The Cleveland tin-copper-tungsten project is located in northwest Tasmania, Australia. The Company progresses the mine in three stages: tailings reprocessing, open pit mining and the redevelopment of the existing underground mine. The Company's mineral resource projects include Tailings Project, Open Pit Project, Underground Tin and Copper, and Underground Tungsten. The Company's subsidiaries include Rockwell Minerals Pty Ltd, Rockwell Minerals (Tasmania) Pty Ltd, Elementos Minerales S.A. and Elementos Chile Limitada.

Embelton Limited is a wholesale distributor of hard floor covering. The Company's principal activities consist of manufacture and distribution of flooring products, structural noise and vibration control systems, metal fabrication, rubber and cork sheeting, and other industrial products. Its segments include Merchandising-Victoria, Tasmania and South Australia, which comprises the sale of flooring and accessory products, various vibration control devices, building materials, industrial cork, rubber products and metal fabrications in the States of Victoria, Tasmania and South Australia; Merchandising-Rest of Australia and Overseas, which comprises the sale of flooring and accessory products, various vibration control devices, building materials, industrial cork, rubber products and metal fabrications in the rest of Australia and overseas, and Manufacturing, which includes manufacturing operations supply to Victoria, Tasmania, South Australia, rest of Australia and overseas markets.

Enice Holding Company Limited is an Australia-based holding company. The Company is an integrated wireless telecommunications technology company, which provides services to the Chinese mobile carriers. It provides wireless telecommunications solutions, from supply and implementation of wireless telecommunications technology to ongoing management and monitoring of their wireless networks. Its operations include technology development, product assembly, product supply, network engineering, network management and maintenance services. It offers Antenna Alignment Tool; omni-directional and directional distributed antenna systems (DAS) antennas with ultra-low passive intermodulation (PIM); long term evolution (LTE) dual polarization DAS antennas with ultra-low PIM, and LTE dual polarization spotlight antennas with low PIM. Its products in the research and development phase include EpinpointRT, Antennet, LTE Base Station antennas and bionic antennas.

Eneabba Gas Limited is an energy company. The Company operates through three segments: energy and electricity generation; petroleum exploration, and mineral exploration. The Company is focused on the development of the 168-megawatt gas-fired Centauri 1 power station on Company-owned land over eight kilometers east of Dongara in the Mid-West of Western Australia. It is involved in the development of its onshore Perth Basin gas assets, which include the Ocean Hill Project and Exploration Permit (EP) 447. The Ocean Hill application and Oil and Gas rights consist of approximately 297 square kilometers and is located over 225 kilometers north of Perth and approximately 90 kilometers southeast of Dongara and the Centauri-1 Power station site. EP 447 covers approximately 1,108 square kilometers and is located over 20 kilometers south-east of its Ocean Hill Gas Project. The Company's subsidiaries include Eneabba Energy Pty Ltd and Eneabba Mining Pty Ltd, among others.

Energy Technologies Limited is an Australia-based manufacturer and seller of specialist industrial cables. Bambach Wires and Cables Pty Limited (Bambach Wires and Cables) and Cogenic Pty Limited are the Company's wholly owned subsidiaries. The Company owns a stake in Dulhunty Ploes Pty Limited (DPPL), a manufacturer and seller of glass fiber reinforced cement composite power poles. The Company manufactures specialist and industrial cables through Bambach Wires and Cables, which produces braids and terminated braids, control cable, data and instruments, marine cables, microphone cables, mining cables, pump cables, power cables, speaker cables, among others.

European Metals Holdings Limited is a mineral exploration and development company engaged in the exploration of tin and base metals. The Company is primarily involved in the development of a lithium and tin project in the Czech Republic. The Company's segments include Australia, Congo and Czech. The Company's project includes Cinovec Lithium/Tin Project. The Cinovec project is located approximately 100 kilometers north west from Prague on the border with Germany. It is located in Cinovec-Zinnwald mining district. The Inferred Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC)-compliant resource based on approximately 846 diamond drillholes for over 83,466 meters, and approximately 21.5 kilometers of underground development tunnels is 28 metric tons (Mt) at 0.4% tin (Sn) (28 Mt at 0.6% Sn equivalent-allowing for lithium and tungsten credits), and over 37 Mt at 0.38% lithium (Li). The Company's subsidiaries include European Metals UK Limited and Geomet S.R.O.

Ennox Group Limited, formerly AG Financial Limited, is an Australia-based diversified financials company. The Company is engaged in stockbroking, funds management and investment management. The Company's segments include investment management, which comprises the management of an investment portfolio; funds management, which includes the provision of a multi-manager approach using sector specialists, and stockbroking. The Company focuses on undertaking corporate advisory activities, such as advising on cross border mergers and acquisitions, initial public offerings, capital raising (equity/debt/hybrid), underwriting, private equity investments and managed investment schemes. The Company's subsidiaries include AGF Funds Management Pty Ltd, AG Stockbroking Ltd, AGF Management Pty Ltd. and Ennox Capital Pty Ltd.

Evolution Mining Limited is a gold company. The Company is engaged in operating, identifying and developing gold related mining projects in Australia and New Zealand. Its segments are Cowal, Mungari, Mt Carlton, Mt Rawdon, Edna May, Cracow, Pajingo, Exploration and Corporate. It owns and operates approximately seven gold mines, including Cowal in New South Wales; Cracow, Pajingo, Mt Carlton and Mt Rawdon in Queensland, and Mungari and Edna May in Western Australia. The Cowal operation is an open pit mining operation with production from a range of different faces within the single pit. The Edna May gold mineralization consists of high-grade reef structures and associated stockwork veining hosted within approximately three en-echelon tonalitic gneiss intrusions (Edna May, Greenfinch and Golden Point). The Mt Carlton project is a high-sulfidation epithermal style deposit with mineralization occurring within felsic volcanic rocks on the northern margin of the Permian Bowen Basin.

Enerji Limited is an Australia-based company, which is primarily involved in the marketing of energy recovery and clean energy generation solutions. The Company's principal activities are the design and development of systems to produce electricity from heat. The Company's technology includes Accretive Thermal Energy Node (ATEN) technology, which is a heat-to-power conversion technology. Its ATEN technology takes the waste heat from power generation and industrial processes and turns it into zero emission electricity. The Company's ATEN technology also recovers waste heat from silicon production processes. The Company's projects include mining, paper milling, steel refineries and smelting. The Company has applications for its ATEN technology in a range of heavy industries. The Company's subsidiaries include ATEN Operations Pty Ltd, Enerji Holding Pty Ltd, Enerji Research Pty Ltd, Enerji PE Management Pty Ltd and Enerji GMRL SPV Pty Ltd.

Emeco Holdings Limited (Emeco) provides heavy earthmoving equipment rental solutions to mining companies and contractors. The Company's segments include Australia, Canada and Chile. The Australia segment provides a range of earthmoving equipment and maintenance services to customers in Australia. The Canada segment provides a range of earthmoving equipment and maintenance services to customers primarily in Canada. The Chile segment provides a range of earthmoving equipment and maintenance services to customers in Chile. Its rental fleet includes Caterpillar and Komatsu rear dump trucks of 50 to 240 tons; Komatsu, Hitachi, Liebherr and Caterpillar excavators of 40 to 400 tons; Caterpillar articulated trucks of 30 to 40 tons; Caterpillar dozers of D8 to D11; Caterpillar and Komatsu loaders of 966 to 994H; Caterpillar graders of 14H to 24M, and ancillary equipment, including water carts, service trucks, compactors, integrated tool carriers and tire handlers.

Ephraim Resources Limited is engaged in the business of agricultural biogenetics research and experimentation, licensing and consultancy. The Company focuses on nipah palm breeding, tissue culture, cultivation and plantation, and the conversion of sap from the nipah palm to sugar and ethanol. The Company operates through two segments: Australia and Indonesia. It has developed a methodology to develop nipah palm fit for cropping on an industrial scale and optimize the use of degraded land for nipah palm plantations in Indonesia, and to produce sugar. The Company, through its subsidiary, PT First Flower (PTFF), has completed plantation trials and has rights over 11,800 hectares of land for nipah palm cultivation. PTFF has land use rights in the Meranti District, Riau province for over 8,000 hectares for non-wood products; in the Tanah Laut District, South Kalimantan province for over 1,200 hectares, and in the Kota Baru District, South Kalimantan province for over 2,600 hectares.

Energex Limited, formerly Enegex NL, is an Australia-based natural resource exploration company. The Company is focused on exploration for petroleum. The Company is focused on its interest in the Cornea Retention Lease, WA-54R, in which it holds approximately 14.875% participating interest.

EVENT Hospitality and Entertainment Limited, formerly Amalgamated Holdings Limited, is engaged in cinema exhibition operations; ownership, operation and management of hotels and resorts in Australia and Overseas, and property development. The Company's principal activities include cinema exhibition operations in Australia, including technology equipment supply and servicing, and the State Theatre; cinema exhibition operations in New Zealand and Fiji; cinema exhibition operations in Germany; operation of the Thredbo resort, including property development activities, and investment properties and investment in shares in listed and unlisted companies. The Company's segments include Entertainment Australia, Entertainment New Zealand, Entertainment Germany, Hotels and Resorts, Thredbo Alpine Resort, and Property and Other Investments. The Company has operations in Australia, New Zealand, Fiji and Germany.

Empired Limited is an information technology (IT) services provider. The Company is engaged in design, development and integration of business knowledge, information technology and creativity. The Company operates through two segments: Australia and New Zealand. The Company's business solutions include Cloud Services, Identity and Access Management, Systems Integration, Data Insights and Business Intelligence, Internet of Things, Spatial Services, Mobile Solutions, Digital and Experience Design, Enterprise Content Management (ECM), Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP), Customer Relationship Management (CRM), Digital and Experience Design, Infrastructure Transformation Services, Managed Infrastructure Services, Project Management Office (PMO) and Unified Communications. The Company operates in various industries, including retail and manufacturing, public sector, financial services and insurance, health, mining, oil and gas, utilities, transport and education.

Enhanced Oil & Gas Recovery Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration and development in the energy resources sector. The Company is focused on securing an interest in Wailawi Oil & Gas project in Indonesia.

FAR Limited (FAR) is an oil and gas exploration company. The Company focuses on exploration for oil and gas in Australia and Africa. The principal activities of the Company include conducting exploration for oil and gas deposits; conducting activities to identify and evaluate new exploration projects, and monetization of oil exploration and production interests. Its segments include AGC, Australia, Guinea-Bissau, Kenya, Senegal, Other and Corporate. It has a portfolio of exploration licenses in approximately 10 blocks in Africa and Australia. The Company in West Africa has a portfolio of exploration permits, including offshore Senegal, which consists of FAN-1 and SNE-1 exploration wells, and Guinea-Bissau, which consists of Sinapa (Block 2) and Esperanca (Blocks 4A and 5A) offshore licenses. It has interest in over two Kenya permits, including Block L6 and Block L9. It holds interest in offshore Western Australia exploration permits, including WA-457-P and WA-458-P.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

ERM Power Limited is an energy company. The Company operates electricity sales, generation and energy solutions businesses. The Company's segments include Business Energy Australia, Business Energy US, Generation Assets and Other. The Business Energy Australia segment includes electricity sales to business customers in Australia. The Business Energy US segment includes electricity sales to business and residential customers in the United States. The Generation Assets segment includes gas-fired power generation assets and delivery of power generation solutions, from the initial concept through to development and operations. The Other segment includes gas, metering, data analytics, lighting solutions and corporate. The Company designs, supplies, installs and supports energy efficient technical solutions, including demand response programs, load control, power factor correction, embedded generation, and sensing and controlling systems (Greensense sustainability and energy monitoring).

FairStar Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the mining and exploration of uranium and gold properties. The Company is focused on the development of its properties, which include Steeple Hill Iron Project and Kurnalpi-Randalls Project. The Steeple Hill Iron Project is located approximately 100 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia. At the Steeple Hill Iron Project, the Company has undertaken various exploration programs, such as rock chip sampling, geological mapping, aero-magnetic survey and drill programs. The Kurnalpi-Randals Project is located south east of the old Kurnalpi mine workings approximately 90 kilometers north east of Kalgoorlie, in the Coolgardie Mineral Field in Western Australia. The Kurnalpi-Randals project area consists of Kurnalpi East (Colour Dam-Anti Dam), Kurnalpi North (Halfway Hill), Kurnalpi South, Jones Find and Duchess of York prospects.

Elixir Petroleum Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas exploration company. The Company is focused on conventional oil and gas exploration in the United States and Europe. The Company operates through two segments: oil and gas exploration in France and oil and gas exploration in the United States of America (USA). The Company's portfolio includes Petra Project in Colorado, the United States. The Petra Project is an oil and gas field, and exploration project. The Company, through its subsidiary Elixir Petroleum (Petra) LLC, owns a 50% working interest across all leases in over 30,000 net acres in Washington County, Colorado, the United States. The Company's Pompano Project is also an oil and gas field, and exploration project. The Moselle Permit is located in north-eastern France in the Saar-Lorraine Basin. The Company's subsidiaries include Elixir Petroleum (Australia) Pty Ltd, Elixir Petroleum (Moselle) Ltd, Cottesloe Oil & Gas LLC and Cottesloe Oil & Gas Inc.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Emefcy Group Limited offers a commercially-proven wastewater treatment solution. Its initial technology, SABRE-The Spiral Aerobic Biofilm Reactor is a modular decentralized wastewater treatment solution using 90% less energy than conventional technology. Future generation SABRE2 and SUBRE are higher capacity solutions being developed for broader markets. The Companys future technology under development, EBR - The Electrogenic Bioreactor is being designed to harvest electricity from highly-loaded industrial wastewater.

Exterra Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activities of the Company are the acquisition of mining tenements, and exploration of these tenements with the objective of identifying economic mineral deposits. The Company's gold projects lie within the Archaean Yilgarn Craton in Western Australia. Its Linden Gold project lies at the southern end of the Laverton Tectonic Zone, on the eastern margin of the Norseman-Wiluna belt. Its Moolyella Lihium Project is located at Moolyella in the Pilbara region of Western Australia. Its Grass Flat Gold project is located north east of the Diemals Mining Center, over 150 kilometers north of Southern Cross in Western Australia. The Company's Zelica project is located over 20 kilometers to the northwest of the Linden project. The Company's Malcolm Project consists of granted Mining Lease, M37/1164 (over 105 hectares), over two kilometers in strike, and contains the North Star and Richmond Gem gold mines.

eServGlobal Limited offers mobile money solutions that covers the spectrum of mobile money, mobile wallet, mobile commerce, recharge, remittance, promotions and agent management. The Company operates in provision of telecommunications software solutions to mobile and financial service providers segment. It develops and implements technology solutions enabling financial inclusion, through the mobile phone for people across the world. Its PayMobile platform is a mobile money solution offering a suite of services in both an operator centric mode or integrated with the open financial ecosystem. It includes a featured prepaid account recharge solution. The operators can centralize their recharge needs for both their electronic and physical scratch cards. Its Remittance enables both cross-border and domestic transfer between mobile money accounts, payment cards, bank accounts or cash outlets. It offers international money transfer through an interface with the HomeSend remittance hub.

Enzumo limited is a financial services advisory and implementation company. The Company is a provider of software services and research to the financial planning and superannuation industries. The Company's segments include XPLAN and eLMS-Enzumo and Superannuation Services-Chant West. The Company offers financial planning advisory services. Enzumo Paraplanning is the Company's outsourced paraplanning service. The Company focuses on producing Advice Documents on a needs only basis, using XPLAN financial planning software. The Company offers financial planning solution built on the Xplan platform, including Statements of Advice, review documents, complete business process solutions, fully managed Xplan solutions, Xplan site administration and Xplan datafeed assistance. The Company offers Master Xplan learning platform, which includes over 200 training simulations to guide its users through the Xplan system.

Estia Health Limited is engaged in operating and developing owned and leased residential aged care facilities throughout Australia. The Company's homes offer a range of care services, from providing semi-independent living, to specific and comprehensive care for those with memory or cognitive support needs. The Company offers services, including personal assistance, meals, therapies and lifestyle activities. It offers residents with general activities, such as gardening, reading, movies, music, parties, cultural celebrations, art sessions or daytrips and lifestyle coordinators, and can also cater for many specialist interests. It offers clinical care that includes regular reviews and includes daily medication; pain management program; medical services, such as physiotherapy, pharmacy, podiatry, optometry and dental; specialist dementia care, and personal care. It operates homes in Victoria, South Australia, New South Wales and Queensland.

Fastbrick Robotics Limited, formerly DMY Capital Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in developing technology to build an automated robotic machine. The Company is engaged in research and development of construction industry automation solutions and robotic bricklaying technology. The Company has conducted proof of concept study for technology demonstrator Hadrian 105. Hadrian X is the Company's commercial bricklaying machine. The Company is engaged in the design of Hadrian 109 Commercial Prototype. Fastbrick Robotics Engineering Pty Ltd is the Company's subsidiary.

eSports Mogul Asia Pacific Limited, formerly Volta Mining Limited, is an Australia-based eSports media company. The Company is a provider of eSports content. The Company's business is to provide an integrated eSports-focused online media platform, called ESM Media Hub. The Company provide its services online through the ESM Media Hub, which includes mobile applications. ESM Media Hub provides an accessible online platform for eSports enthusiasts, and also offers a range of eSports products and services. The ESM Media Hub offers subscribers' access to ESM Academy, which is an eSports learning academy; ESM Digital Products, an online shop offering various gaming titles for purchase; ESH Tournament Platform, which is an online eSports tournament platform, and ESM Productions, an eSports content. The Company offers eSports Hero Tournament Platform, which is available in Australia and Singapore. The Company offers digital games and video contents.

Pacific Environment Limited is engaged in environmental consulting and technology services. The Company focuses on providing environmental consulting, monitoring, predictive management and automated reporting solutions from Australasia to the Americas and Europe. The Company's EnviroSuite is a proactive environmental management system that combines real-time monitoring and predictive modelling with high-resolution weather forecasting and automated data analysis. EnviroSuite gathers real-time data from multiple sources into a single repository, providing display, instant analysis, automated reporting and alerts. The Company's services include Air Quality and Meteorology, Ambient and Fugitive Monitoring, Auditing Services and Carbon Management, Groundwater Monitoring and Assessment, Landfill Gas Monitoring and Assessment, Acoustic Consulting, Odour Assessment, Phytocapping Landfill Technology, Solid Waste Management, Contaminated Land Assessment.

Energy Resources of Australia Ltd (ERA) is an Australia-based uranium producer. The Company operates the Ranger uranium mine in Northern Territory of Australia. It operates through the Uranium segment. ERA sells its product to international power utilities. The Company's Ranger mine is located approximately eight kilometers east of Jabiru and over 260 kilometers east of Darwin. The mine lies within the 79-square kilometer Ranger Project Area. Its Ranger mine produces approximately 120,000 tons of uranium oxide (U3O8). The Company also holds interest in Jabiluka Mineral Lease, which is approximately 20 kilometers north of the existing Ranger facilities. The Ranger 3 Deeps project involved the construction of a 2,710-meter Exploration Decline and an associated underground exploration-drilling programmer designed to pave the way to a potential underground mine. The Company's operations rely on the processing of uranium ore stockpiles following cessation of open pit mining of Pit 3.

Engenco Limited provides a range of engineering services and products through two business steams: power and propulsion, and rail and road. The Company operates through six segments: Drivetrain Power and Propulsion, which provides technical sales and services to the mining, oil and gas, rail, transport, defense, marine and power generation industries; Centre for Excellence in Rail Training (CERT), which provides specialist rail training; Convair Engineering, which manufactures pneumatic road tankers and mobile silos for the carriage and storage of construction materials, grains and other dry bulk materials; Total Momentum, which is a provider of personnel and project management services to freight rail and mining rail infrastructure managers; Gemco Rail, which is engaged in the remanufacture and repair of locomotives, wagons, bearings and other rail products for rail operators and maintainers, and Greentrains, which leases rolling stock to freight rail operators throughout Australia.

Empire Resources Limited is principally engaged in the mineral exploration and evaluation of properties in Australia. The Company is a gold and copper focused explorer and mine developer. The Company's projects include Penny's Find gold project and Yuinmery copper-gold project. Penny's Find gold project is a near surface, gold deposit located in the Eastern Goldfields of Western Australia, within the gold mining centers of Kalgoorlie and Kanowna Belle. The gold mineralization at Penny's Find gold project is associated with quartz veining developed at the sheared contact between mafic volcanics and sediments. The Yuinmery copper-gold project is located near the town of Sandstone approximately 475 kilometers northeast of Perth in Western Australia. The Yuinmery copper-gold project lies within the Archaean Youanmi greenstone belt and covers a synclinal sequence of chloritised felsic tuffaceous rocks, sulfide bearing chert horizons, gabbro, basalt and ultramafics.

Equity Trustees Limited (EQT) is an Australia-based company engaged in the provision of a range of financial services to clients of the Trustee & Wealth Services (TWS) and Corporate Trustee Services (CTS). Trustee & Wealth Services (TWS) includes provision of personal financial and superannuation services, including in relation to personal estates and trusts, wealth management, asset management, aged care services, and portfolio services. Corporate Trustee Services (CTS) includes responsible entity trustee services for managed funds on behalf of local and international managers and sponsors. CTS also manage and coordinate the distribution and marketing of equity trustees co-branded retail and wholesale funds.

Enviromission Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the development of Solar Tower renewable energy technology in the United States and global markets. The Company's geographical segments are Australia and United States of America. The Company's subsidiaries include SolarMission Limited, Pure Solar Power (IP) Pty Ltd, SolarMission Technologies, Inc., EnviroMission, Inc., EnviroMission Capital, LLC, EnviroMission Management, LLC and La Paz Solar Tower, LLC.

European Lithium Limited, formerly Paynes Find Gold Limited, is a mining exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in the lithium exploration and development in Austria. The Company owns the Wolfsberg lithium project, which is located in Carinthia, approximately 270 kilometers south of Vienna, Austria. The Company focuses on the development of the Wolfsberg Lithium Project, which is located approximately 20 kilometers east of Wolfsberg. The Wolfsberg Lithium Project includes approximately 22 original and over 32 overlapping exploration licenses, and a mining license in approximately 11 mining areas. It also holds interest in the Paynes Find Gold Prospect. Paynes Find is a gold producing region located approximately 420 kilometers Northeast of Perth, Western Australia. It holds interest in mineral tenements, including M59/2, M59/10, M59/235, M59/244, M59/396, M59/662, M59/663, P59/1907, P59/1908, P59/1909, P59/1924, P59/1941, P59/1942 and P59/1956.

Euroz Limited is a financial services company. The Company is involved in various activities, such as stockbroking, fund management, investing and wealth management. Its segments include Stockbroking & Corporate Activities, Principal Trading, Fund Management, Investments and Wealth Management. The Stockbroking & Corporate Activities segment offers trading of Australian securities, corporate finance opportunities and provision of company research. The Principal Trading segment is engaged in the purchase and sale of securities. The Fund Management segment provides advice and the execution of mandates in relation to fund management. The Investments segment invests in listed and unlisted securities from which it derives dividends. The Wealth Management segment provides wealth management services, including the administration of funds under management. Its stockbroking operation comprises four divisions: equities research, institutional sales, private clients and corporate finance.

Equatorial Resources Limited is an iron ore exploration and development company. The Company is focused on exploration of mining tenements; investing cash assets in interest bearing bank accounts, and general administration. It operates in the mineral exploration industry segment. It is focused on the exploration and development of approximately two owned large-scale iron ore projects, which are located in the Republic of Congo (ROC). Its projects include Mayoko-Moussondji Iron Project (Mayoko-Moussondji) and Badondo Iron Project. The Mayoko-Moussondji Project is located in the southwest region of the ROC. Its Mayoko-Moussondji project hosts a Hematite Resource Estimate of approximately 180 million tons at over 35.7% Iron (Fe) as part of a total Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) Mineral Resource Estimate of approximately 920 million tons at over 31.4% Fe. Its Badondo Iron Project (Badondo) is located within the Congo craton iron projects in the northwest region of the ROC.

Frontier Capital Group Limited, formerly Precious Metal Resources Limited, conducts graphic design and mineral exploration programs. The Company operates through mineral, exploration, development and geological surveys of resources in Australia, and graphic design business in Malaysia segment. Its projects include Casablanca Casino, Stotsenberg Hotel, CK Graphic, Broken Hill and Peel Fault. It holds exploration license 6648 that covers various gold workings in Crow Mountain goldfield. Its Stotsenberg Leisure & Hotel Corporation, which includes the Hotel Stotsenberg and Casablanca Casino, is located at Clark. The Stotsenberg Hotel consists of three-story buildings with over 240 hotel rooms, including two Presidential Suites; 39 Executive Rooms, 28 Deluxe Queen Bedrooms, 163 Deluxe Twin Bedrooms, and seven Studio rooms. It also holds exploration license 8024, which covers various gold workings in Panama Hat goldfield. Its subsidiaries include PMR3 Pty Ltd and Peel Gold Pty Ltd.

EPAT Technologies Limited, formerly Minquest Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in developing mobile medical application that provide pain assessment for individuals that are unable to communicate with their carers. The Company's mobile medical application, ePAT, uses the facial recognition software to facilitate and improve pain assessment in patients. The Company intends to develop, and has rolled out its mobile medical applications in two phases, which include patients with dementia and lost the ability to communicate with their carers and for young children not yet speaking. The data captured through the mobile medical applications is combined with non-facial pain cues, including vocalizations, movements and behaviors to automatically calculate a pain severity score. The Company has completed pilot validation studies of ePAT.

Environmental Clean Technologies Ltd. is engaged in the business of commercializing energy and resource technologies. The Company's principal activities are investment, research, development and commercialization of environmentally cleaner technologies and processes capable of reducing carbon emissions and environmental damage in the energy and resource sectors. Its activities include development of a large-scale demonstration project for the Coldry Process; advancement of the Matmor Process toward pilot scale, and managing the development of, and extracting value from, its intellectual property. The Company is focused on advancing a portfolio of technologies: Coldry and MATMOR. The Coldry beneficiation process produces a black coal equivalent (BCE) in the form of pellets, when applied to lignite and some sub-bituminous coals. The MATMOR is a production technology, which enables the use of cheaper feedstock to produce primary iron.

Excelsior Gold Limited is engaged in gold mining and exploration at its Kalgoorlie North Gold Project. The Kalgoorlie North Gold Project is located between 30 and 55 kilometers north of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia. The Project covers approximately 96.4 square kilometers of granted mining leases and prospecting licenses over 25 kilometers of strike of the Bardoc Tectonic Zone greenstone belt. The Project is located at the convergence of approximately two gold mineralizing structural systems, the Bardoc Tectonic Zone and the Black Flag Fault. Its mining operations include Castlereagh Pit, Big Blow South Pit, Zoroastrian Extended Pit and Zoroastrian Central Pit. Its Castlereagh Pit is centered on the southern extensions of the Excelsior Shear Zone. The Zoroastrian gold mineralization is hosted in quartz veins and stockwork zones within the differentiated Zoroastrian Dolerite. The Central Pit is centered on the easterly Royal Mint structure and the westerly Birthday Dream structure.

Elanor Retail Property Fund (the Fund), formerly Manning Mall Syndicate, is a multi-asset retail property fund. The principal activity of the Fund is its investment in real estate property. The Fund is a managed investment scheme. The strategy of the Fund is to acquire and hold the properties to provide investors with real estate investment; to implement leasing and active asset management, and to acquire high investment quality Future Assets over the next two years in line with the Fund's investment criteria. The Companys portfolio includes Auburn Central, Manning Mall and Tweed Mall Shopping Centre, which are sub-regional shopping center; Glenorchy Plaza, which is a shopping center, and Northway Plaza Shopping Centre, which is a neighborhood shopping center. The Fund has sub-regional shopping centers in Taree, New South Wales and Glenorchy, Tasmania.

EVZ Limited operates in the energy and engineering services sectors. The Company's segments include engineering, energy, water and corporate. Its engineering segment designs, manufactures and installs steel tanks, silos, cooling towers, pipe spooling, pressure vessels and fabricates structural steel. It is also involved in the installation process and provides ongoing support and maintenance for its products. The energy segment designs and installs constant load power stations, back-up power generation equipment and sustainable energy solutions. It services, maintains and hires all types of generators and associated equipment. The water segment designs syfonic roof drainage systems for roof structures, supplies and installs fiberglass panel tanks, and prefabricated hydraulic systems. The Company is also involved in designing, installing and maintaining clean energy solutions, communications equipment, marine installations and provision of mobile generation solutions.

Fletcher Building Limited is a holding company. The Company is involved in the manufacturing and distribution of building materials, and residential and commercial construction. Its segments include Building Products, International, Distribution, Residential and Land Development, and Construction. The Building Products segment is a manufacturer, distributor and marketer of building products used both commercially and in residential markets. The International segment includes laminates and panels businesses that manufacture and distribute decorative surface laminates, and roof tiling businesses. The Distribution segment consists of building, plumbing, pipeline and steel distribution businesses in Australia and New Zealand. The Residential and Land Development segment develops land holdings for both residential and commercial use, and is a residential home builder. The Construction segment includes Fletcher Construction, a general contractor in New Zealand and the South Pacific.

Energia Minerals Limited is engaged in mineral exploration and development. The Company is engaged in exploration of a suite of tenements located throughout Italy and Australia. Its geographical segments include Western Australia, Italy and Other. Its flagship projects are the Gorno Zinc-Lead-Silver project in Northern Italy and the Carley Bore uranium project in north Western Australia. Its projects include Northern Territory projects, including McArthur River Project, which covers an area of over 1,610 square kilometers and Novazza-Val Vedello Uranium project, which includes its two uranium Exploration License applications, at Val Vedello and Novazza in the Lombardia region of Italy. Its Australian projects include Nyang Project and the Carley Bore Project, which consist of three Exploration Licenses E08/1644, E08/1645 and E08/1646, and its three tenements cover an area of over 1,536 square kilometers. Its other projects include Paterson Project and Nabberu Project.

Dropsuite Limited, formerly Excalibur Mining Corporation Limited, offers Dropsuite, a Cloud-based software platform that enables small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) to backup, recover and protect their digital assets. The Company's products include Dropmysite, Dropmyemail, Dropmymobile and DSE Server Backup. Dropmysite is a cloud-based Website backup and monitoring service that Website owners can use independently to schedule automatic backups, monitor Website availability and performance, and restore lost or corrupted data in a single click. Dropmyemail is a cloud e-mail backup and archiving service that helps businesses and consumers backup, manage, recover and protect all of their critical data. Dropmymobile provides automatic backups of users' mobile phone contacts, short message service (SMS), pictures, videos, call logs and much more in the cloud. DSE Server Backup is a file-based backup solution ideal for virtual private server (VPS), dedicated and cloud servers.

Emerald Resources NL is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in exploring and developing gold projects. The Company's principal activities include the exploration and development of the Okvau Gold.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

EVE Investments Limited, formerly Energy Ventures Limited, is an Australia-based investment company that invests in technology companies. The Company has an interest in Wayland Copper, which holds the Ballek copper-gold in Northern Sweden. It also holds an interest in Agricola Resources Plc, which is focusing on undergoing a corporate restructure and is seeking a new project. The Company owns an interest in Omni Innovation, a medical nutrition company focused on creating products, tools and technologies for foods for special medical purposes. Omni Innovation is developing dietary interventions for common chronic diseases, such type II diabetes and low blood pressure (hypotension). Omni Innovation's product, GlucoControl, is a pre-meal drink for people with pre-diabetes or type II diabetes.

Electro Optic Systems Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the space and defense system business. The Company's segments include Space and Defence Systems. Space segment includes laser-based space surveillance systems and also manufactures and sells telescopes and dome enclosures for space projects. Defence Systems segment develops, manufactures and markets fire control, surveillance and weapon systems military customers. The Company has developed space tracking sensors. The Company, through its subsidiary, offers observatories, telescopes, space surveillance products, detector systems and laser products. The Company's product range includes EOS R-400 and EOS R-600. It offers repair services and sensor units for military and security application.

Eclipse Metals Limited is an exploration company. The Company's principal activity includes mineral exploration. The Company holds portfolio of tenements covering an area of approximately 11,300 square kilometers in the Northern Territory and Queensland. The Company has a multi-commodity portfolio, including gold, uranium, iron, manganese and base metals. The Company's projects include Uranium projects, Gold projects, Manganese projects and Iron projects. The Uranium project includes the Liverpool project, the Gumadeer project, the Flying Fox project, the Mount Poiziers Uranium project and the South Alligator group, the North Arunta Uranium project and Eclipse Uranium project. The Gold project includes Mt Wells project. The Manganese project includes the Mary Valley Manganese Project and the West McArthur River Project. The Iron project includes the West Bachelor Iron Project and the Moonford Iron project.

Explaurum Limited is an Australia-based gold exploration company. The Company is a mineral exploration and development company with land holdings in Western Australia. The Company holds the Tampia Gold project located in the wheat belt of Western Australia. The Company is engaged in multi metal exploration and development. The Tampia Gold Project is located approximately 300 kilometers east of Perth in the wheat belt of Western Australia. The Company holds over three tenements on the Tampia Gold Project.

Enterprise Metals Limited is engaged in the exploration of various gold, copper, uranium and iron ore tenements in Western Australia. The Company is exploring approximately five gold and base metals projects targeting volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) and stratabound base metals, and Archaean vein/lode hosted gold. The Doolgunna Project covers approximately 1,100 square kilometers and is located over 110 kilometers northeast of Meekatharra. The Doolgunna Project is considered prospective for VMS and stratabound base metals, and mesothermal stockwork gold. The Fraser Range Project covers over 594 square kilometers and is located approximately 100 kilometers east of Norseman and over 650 kilometers east of Perth within the Albany-Fraser province. The Darlot Project covers approximately 897 square kilometers and is located over 40 kilometers east northeast of Leinster. The Darlot Project is considered prospective for orogenic gold deposits and VMS style copper/zinc base metal deposits.

Esperance Minerals Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in investigating new business opportunities both within and outside the mining exploration sector. The Company is focused on diversifying its exploration activities into prospective mineral tenements. The Company's subsidiaries include Dingo Resources Pty Limited and Yampi Sound Pty Limited. The Company was engaged in mineral exploration primarily in the Kimberly Region Western Australia.

Equus Mining Limited is focused on exploring for and developing thermal coal resources in Chile, South America. The Company's principal activity includes mineral exploration in the Magallanes Basin. The Company's segments include Mineral Exploration and Investing. The Company's geographical segments include Australia, Chile, Ghana and Kyrgyz Republic. The Company controls a package of exploration licenses centered on the coal bearing Loreto Formation, located in Chile's coalfield, the Magallanes Basin. These licenses are situated in project areas, including Rubens, Perez and Mina Rica. The Mina Rica Coal Project covers an area of approximately 88 square kilometers of the Loreto Formation. The Rubens Coal Project covers an area of over 54 square kilometers. The Perez Coal Project covers an area of approximately 140 square kilometers.

Elysium Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company's Burraga project consists of EL 6463, EL 6874 and EL 7975 tenements. The Company's EL6463 tenement has an area of approximately 80 square kilometers. The Company's Lucky Draw Gold Mine is located in the north-east sector of the EL 6463 tenement. The Company's EL 6874 tenement has an area of approximately 20 square kilometers and is located to the east of EL6463. Its EL 7975 tenement consists of an area of over 75 square kilometers and is located to the east of EL6874. Its western portion of EL 7975 covers the eastern portion of the Burraga Granite and Rockley Volcanic intrusions. Its Malang project in East Java is located approximately 60 kilometers to the southeast of the city of Malang. Its Horseshoe South E52/2569 tenement covers approximately five square kilometers and lies over four kilometers to the south of the Horseshoe Lights Mine in Western Australia.

Emergent Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in exploration for iron, base metals and precious metals in Western Australia. The Company holds interest in the Beyondie Project in the mid-west region of Western Australia. The Company's Beyondie Iron Project is located adjacent to the Great Northern Highway and Goldfields Gas Pipeline in the northern part of Western Australia's mid-west iron ore precinct. The Company is engaged in developing iron-ore tenement, E52/2215, in the Beyondie Iron Project. The Company's E52/2215 ((iron ore, vanadium and manganese) covers approximately 142 square kilometers and includes over 46 blocks.

Firstwave Cloud Technology Limited, formerly Crestal Petroleum Limited, is an Australia-based company, which operates in the cloud security services industry and delivers a range of cloud content security services to enterprises and government customers through a telecommunications company in Australia. The Company offers a range of products, including cloud content security gateway (CCSG), Cloud Email Security, Cloud Web Security, cloud Next Generation firewalls and cloud integration services. CCSG integrates firewall, intelligent e-mail inspection and Web content filtering. Cloud Email Security is a fully-configurable cloud Mail security service for businesses and enterprises. Cloud Web Security is a cloud based Web scanning, threat prevention and content security technology. cloud Next Generation firewalls is a managed solution that allow companies to control over applications and also detect and block malicious threats.

F.F.I. Holdings Limited is a food processing company. The Company's principal activities include processing, manufacture, packaging and distribution of food products for the Australian food industry, and property investment/leasing. Its segments include Bakery Segment, which manufactures a range of bakery and home cooking needs food products for distribution to customer base; Smallgoods Segment, which manufactures a range of smallgoods products for distribution to customer base, and Investment Property, which manages its industrial/commercial land which is held for investment purposes. The Company is a manufacturer of a range of food products for the Australian industrial, wholesale and retail markets. The food operations include the manufacture of chocolate and confectionery products; the manufacture of bakers jam fillings and processed apple products; the processing and packing of home cooking needs products, and the production of fresh sausages, bacon and other small goods.

First Graphite Limited, formerly MRL Corporation Limited, focuses on mineral exploration. Its segments include Mining and exploration activities, and Corporate services. It is engaged in the exploration and development of high-grade projects in Sri Lanka. It is a developer and producer of high technology graphene materials. Its geographical segments include Australia and Sri Lanka. It holds 13 exploration licenses over 39,500 hectares together with two granted industrial Mining licenses, one at Pandeniya and the other at Aluketiya. The exploration license areas are situated across the areas of Warakapola, Pujapitiya, Palinda Nuwara and Hikkaduwa. The Warakapola project area consists of six licenses covering 8,300 hectares of granted exploration concessions. The Aluketiya Project Area is located in Meegahatenna. The Palinda Nuwara Project Area consists of 54 square kilometers of exploration grids. The Hikkaduwa Project Area consists of 10 square kilometers of exploration grids.

Emmerson Resources Limited (Emmerson) is engaged in exploration and evaluation of mineral interests. The Company's projects include the Tennant Creek Mineral Field (TCMF) in the Northern Territory (NT) and the Lachlan Fold Belt (LFB) in New South Wales (NSW). It holds approximately 2,500 square kilometers (km2) of ground in the TCMF. The TCMF is located approximately 500 kilometers north of Alice Springs. Its TCMF consists of gold and copper fields producing over 5.5 million ounces (Mozs) of gold and approximately 470,000 tons of copper from a range of deposits, including Gecko, Orlando, Warrego, White Devil, Chariot and Golden Forty, which are within Emmerson Resources portfolio. Its NSW project includes Wellington Project, which covers an area of approximately 390 km2; Fifield Project, which covers an area of approximately 66 km2; Temora Project, which covers an area of approximately 203 km2, and Parkes Project, which covers an area of approximately 109 km2.

Fe Limited is a mineral resources company engaged in the management of iron ore, precious and base metal tenements in Western Australia. The Company operates through mineral exploration segment. It holds, or has rights or interests in several tenements prospective for iron, nickel, copper and gold. Its projects include Bryah Basin Joint Venture Projects, Grosvenor Project, Bryah Basin Project, Mt Ida Gold and Evanston Iron Ore Royalty. It has interest in a mine consisting of approximately 10 tenements covering an area of over 840 square kilometers in the Bryah Basin. It has interest in a mine consisting of approximately six exploration licenses covering an area of over 610 square kilometers. The Bryah Basin Project covers approximately 40 kilometers strike of the prospective sequence in the Bryah Basin. The Mt Ida Gold is located over 80 kilometers northwest of the railway at Menzies. The Evanston Iron Ore Project is located in the Southern Yilgarn Iron Province of Western Australia.

Flinders Mines Limited is an iron ore mining company. The Company has various exploration operations of iron mineralization, gold and base metals. The Company's principal activity is the mineral exploration and development. The Company operates in three segments, which include Pilbara Iron Ore, Canegrass Magnetite and Other Minerals. The Company's projects include Pilbara Iron Ore project and Canegrass project. The Pilbara Iron Ore project is located in the Pilbara region of Western Australia, approximately 60 kilometers north-west of the town of Tom Price. The Pilbara Iron Ore project consists of the Blacksmith and Anvil tenements. The Anvil tenement is located approximately 10 kilometers to the south-west of Blacksmith. The Company's Canegrass project is located near located near Mount Magnet, Western Australia. The Canegrass projects tenement package consists of over six granted exploration licenses.

Estrella Resources Limited is an exploration company, which is focused on copper exploration in Chile. The Company is engaged in maintaining mining/mineral exploration rights/assets in Chile and is looking for new opportunities. The Company operates through the segment of mineral exploration in South America. The Company owns two tenements, Saturno and Mecurio, in a Chile copper project. The Company is reviewing project opportunities. The Company primarily operates in Australia.

Finders Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in operation of an approximately 3,000 tons per annum solvent extraction-electrowinning (SX-EW) plant at the Wetar Copper Project; construction and development activities at the Wetar Copper Project to expand its copper production capacity from 3,000 tons per annum to 28,000 tons per annum, and exploration for copper and gold in Indonesia. The Company operates through copper mining segment. Its projects include the Wetar Copper Project and the Ojolali Gold-Silver Project. The Wetar Copper Project is located on the island of Wetar in eastern Indonesia and comprises the development, mining and processing of sulfide deposits (Kali Kuning and Lerokis) located at or near the northern coastline of the island. The Ojolali Gold-Silver Project is a goldsilver project in Lampung Province of southern Sumatra covering an approximately 10 square kilometers system. The project has a defined oxide gold resource at Jambi.

Elanor Investors Group is engaged in the management of investment funds and syndicates, and the investment in, and operation of, a portfolio of investment assets and businesses. The Company's segments include Funds Management, Hotels, Tourism and Leisure, Real Estate and Special Situation Investments. The Funds Management division manages third-party owned investment funds and syndicates. The Hotel, Tourism and Leisure division originates investment and fund management assets. Its investment portfolio includes Featherdale Wildlife Park and Ibis Styles Canberra Eaglehawk Hotel. The Real Estate division originates investment and fund management assets. Its investment portfolio comprises an investment in Auburn Central syndicate, Elanor Retail Property Fund and Limestone Street Centre syndicate. The Special Situations Investments division contains the John Cootes Furniture business and the property associated with John Cootes Furniture business at Merrylands, New South Wales.

Entek Energy Limited is engaged in oil and gas exploration, development and production, and investment in the resources industry. The Company's geographical segments include Australasia and North America. The Company focuses on acquiring and exploring oil and gas opportunities, including conventional and unconventional resources in proven and producing areas. The Company's projects are located in the Green River Basin, the United States. The Company's interest covers approximately 163,680 gross acres of prospective leasehold. The primary focus of the Company is the appraisal of its Niobrara Oil Resource Play. The Company owns leases based in the states of Colorado and Wyoming, the United States, in the Niobrara Oil Resource play with ownership interests in approximately 55,390 net acres across over 149,460 gross acres.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Etherstack plc is a holding company. The principal activities of the Company are design, development and deployment of wireless communications software and products. The Company specializes in wireless technology. It develops software for use in transceivers, which enables the transceiver to communicate with a radio network and other transceivers. The Company licenses its software and designs to companies that manufacture telecommunication equipment primarily for government public safety agencies and utilities. The Company operates in the United Kingdom, the United States, Japan and Australia. The Company also provides ongoing warranty and support services to its customers. Its subsidiaries include Etherstack London Limited, Indian Pacific Nederland BV, Etherstack Inc., Etherstack Pty Limited, Auria Wireless Pty Limited, Etherstack Japan Limited and Etherstack Pte Limited. These subsidiaries develop and sell wireless software communications products.

Frontier Digital Ventures Limited is an operator of online classified businesses in underdeveloped, emerging countries or regions. The Company focuses on property and automotive verticals and general classifieds Websites. The Company provides an integrated support system to help entrepreneurs build online classifieds businesses in frontier markets. The Company provides funding to accelerate the growth of online classifieds businesses. The Company provides operational guidance to maximize the implementation of the strategy. The Company's portfolio consists of approximately 15 companies, operating businesses across over 19 markets, ranging from Pakistan and Myanmar to Nigeria, Ghana and Morocco.

Freedom Oil & Gas Company, formerly Maverick Drilling & Exploration Limited, is a development-stage company. The Company is focused on oil and gas exploration and production. The Company is engaged in evaluating the acquisition of producing assets and undeveloped acreage. The Company is involved in in the development of undeveloped acreage in the United States unconventional shale plays. It is focused on acquiring approximately 6,000 acres of undeveloped land in the heart of the Eagle Ford shale play in South Texas.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

EZA Corporation Limited is an Australia-based company, which is evaluating new projects. The Company is seeking opportunities in the mining sector. The Company's focus is precious metals with a bias towards gold exploration and development. The Company has no revenue.

Fiducian Group Limited is a specialist financial services company. The Company provides financial planning, funds management, investment platform administration, information technology and accounting/accountancy resourcing services. The Company's segments include Superannuation, which includes the operates of Fiducian Portfolio Services Ltd, a registrable superannuation entity (RSE) for a public offer superannuation fund, Fiducian Superannuation Service; Funds Management, which includes the operations of Fiducian Investment Management Services Ltd, which acts an operator of an Investor Directed Portfolio Service, Fiducian Investment Service and as Responsible Entity for managed investment scheme; Financial Planning, which includes its specialist financial planning operations; Administration, which provides administration and professional services, and Business Services, which provides accountancy resource services through its subsidiary, Fiducian Business Services Pty Ltd.

Freedom Insurance Group Limited designs, distributes and administers life insurance products. The Company is also engaged in the distribution of life insurance products, and ongoing administration and management of the life insurance products that it distributes. It distributes a range of life insurance products through the direct channel, including final expenses, accidental death, accidental injury and term life. Its products also include mortgage protection and direct life. In addition, the Company distributes a range of other third-party life insurance products through the indirect channel. It undertakes a range of services and life insurance functions in respect of its products, including policy administration, customer service, fulfillment, administration and information technology (IT); legal and compliance and quality assurance, product development, marketing and lead generation, learning and development, human resources, finance and actuarial and claims administration.

Energy One Limited is a supplier of software products and services to wholesale energy, environmental and carbon trading markets. The Company's principal activities include supply and development of software and services to energy companies and utilities. It operates through the energy software industry segment. The Company's products include EnergyFlow, EnergyOffer, EnergyOne Trading, and Business Intelligence & Energy data. The EnergyFlow platform is a solution that allows customers to automate their energy business operations from logistics and nominations in energy, through specialist tasks, such as environmental transactions, to settlements and position reporting. Energy One is a local provider of enterprise bidding systems that enable energy producers to bid their energy into spot or pool markets. Energy One Trading is an energy trading and risk management (ETRM) system that is out-of-the-box ready for energy, carbon and environmental certificate trading needs.

Freedom Foods Group Limited is engaged in sourcing, manufacturing, sale, marketing and distribution of cereal and snacks; sourcing, manufacturing, selling, marketing and distributing plant and dairy based beverages; selling, marketing and distributing canned seafood, and investment in dairy farming operations. The Company operates through five segments: Freedom Foods, which includes cereal, snacks and branded plant-based beverages; Pactum, which offers a range of ultra-high temperature processing (UHT) food and beverage products, including liquid stocks, soy, rice, almond and dairy milk beverages; Pactum Dairy Group, which offers a range of UHT dairy milk beverage products; Specialty Seafood, which offers a range of canned seafood, such as sardines, salmon and specialty seafood, and Freedom Foods North America, which offers a range of products for consumers, including allergen free, low sugar, or salt, or fortified or functional.
Eagle Nickel Limited is an Australia-based company. The Company is engaged in mineral prospecting and exploration.

Fatfish Internet Group Limited is an Australia-based Internet venture investment firm. The principal activity of the Company is the investment in technology and Internet companies. The Company operates through two business divisions: Direct Ventures Division and Digital Incubator Division. Its Venture Capital Division is a growth-stage ventures builder. The Company offers various opportunities to investors to invest in diversified portfolio of early-stage and growth-stage Internet businesses. The Company operates in Australia, Singapore and Malaysia. The Company's subsidiaries include Fatfish Internet Pte Ltd, AutoDirect Corporation, Vdancer Pte Ltd, Fatfish Vnetures Sdn Bhd and PT Dragon Commerce Indonesia.

Encounter Resources Limited is an Australia-based exploration and resource development company. The Company's principal activity is mineral exploration. The Company's Yeneena project covers over 1,800 square kilometers tenement package in the Paterson Province of Western Australia located between the Nifty copper mine, the Woodie Woodie manganese mine, the Telfer gold-copper mine and the Kintyre uranium deposit. The Yeneena Project includes the BM1, BM7 and BM8 copper prospects. The Yeneena Project Gold Claw-back relates to various exploration licenses: E45/2500, E45/2501, E45/2502, E45/2503, E45/2561, E45/2657, E45/2658, E45/2805 and E45/2806. Its Millennium zinc project consists of exploration licenses, which include EL45/2501, EL45/2561 and over four blocks of EL45/2500 in the Paterson Province of Western Australia. The Company's subsidiaries include Encounter Operations Pty Ltd, Hamelin Resources Pty Ltd and Encounter Yeneena Pty Ltd.
