FarmaForce Limited is engaged in the provision of services as a contract sales organization. The Company provides its pharma clients with contract sales services to general practitioners (GPs), specialists and pharmacists. The Company's services include sales teams to service both hospital and private-based specialists; sales teams to service pharmacists, including pharmacy assistants, and third-party healthcare professional relationship management. The Company operates in Australia.

Equatorial Resources Limited is an iron ore exploration and development company. The Company's iron ore projects are located in Republic of Congo (ROC). The Company focuses on advancing its existing mineral resource assets in Africa, as well as searching for opportunities in the resources sector. It operates Badondo Iron Project through a subsidiary, Congo Mining Exploration Ltd SARL (CME). The Badondo Iron Project is located in the northwest region of Republic of Congo. It focuses on targeting direct shipping ore (DSO) hematite at Badondo. It has approximately 10 drill holes, which intersects hematite mineralization over 50% Iron (Fe). The near surface down hole intersections include 41.9 meters at 62.9% Iron (Fe) in BADDD0001; 40.4 meters at 65.6% Iron (Fe) in BADDD0002; 26.4 meters at 61.9% Iron (Fe) in BADDD0003, and 13.5 meters at 61.5% Iron (Fe) in BADDD0004.

Energy World Corporation Ltd (EWC) is an independent energy company engaged in the production and sale of power and natural gas. The Company's principal activities include development, design, construction, operation and maintenance of power stations; development of liquefied natural gas (LNG), design, construction, operation and maintenance of LNG plants and road transport of LNG, and design and development of LNG receiving terminals, and exploration, development and production of gas and oil, design, construction, operation and maintenance of gas, processing plants and gas pipelines. The Company's segments include Oil & Gas, and Power. The Company operates in Australia and Indonesia. The Company is focused on the development of LNG facilities using mid-sized modular LNG trains and regasification facilities. The Company has primary gas and power operations located at Sengkang, South Sulawesi in Indonesia and it also produces gas, power and LNG in Australia.

Ferrum Crescent Limited is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in the exploration for minerals. The Company's geographic segments include Australia and South Africa. The Company is focused on capitalizing on the demand for iron products by producing material, which can be used in the manufacture of steel in electric arc furnaces. The Company's primary focus is the Moonlight Iron Ore Project, which is based on Moonlight Deposit, a magnetite deposit located on the farms Moonlight, Gouda Fontein and Julietta in Limpopo Province in the north of South Africa. The Company also owns the Lead-Zinc Exploration Projects in Spain. The Lead-Zinc Exploration Project is located in the provinces of Len and Galicia, in Spanish mining areas. Its subsidiaries include Ferrum Metals Pty Ltd, Batavia Ltd, Ferrum South Africa (Pty) Ltd, Ferrum Iron Ore (Pty) Ltd and Mkhombi Investments (Pty) Ltd.

Frontier Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in exploration and evaluation of gold and base metal projects in Papua New Guinea. Its segments include Australia and Papua New Guinea. The Company is focused on discovering copper-gold-molybdenum porphyry, high grade and bulk mineable gold/silver epithermal and gold and base metal skarn deposits in the mineralized Pacific Rim of Fire in Papua New Guinea. The Company has interest in two exploration Licenses in Papua New Guinea: Bulago Exploration License and Muller Range. The Company has conducted exploration program at the Swit Kai Prospect, EL 1595, Bulago, and has undertaken diamond drilling program on the eastern strike extensions of the Upper Zone. Muller project consists of exploration license 2356, which has been granted exploration license. The Fold Belt contains the Ok Tedi porphyry copper-gold Mine; Porgera intrusive/ epithermal related gold Mine, and Kili Teke porphyry copper-gold Deposit.

Folkestone Education Trust (the Trust), formerly Australian Education Trust, is a real estate investment trust (REIT). The objectives of the Trust are to provide secure long-term cash-flows with minimal risk and the potential for capital growth to its investors; to provide access to sector specific real estate investment that invests in early learning property; to provide a stable, growing income stream supported by secure lease covenants; to provide geographical diversification through asset selection, and to provide an attractive income yield with growing underlying property values. The Trust operates in the Asia Pacific geographic segment. The Trust owns approximately 390 early learning properties in its portfolio, a medical center and a portfolio of property securities. Its tenants include Goodstart Early Learning Limited, BestStart Educare Limited and G8 Education Limited. Folkestone Investment Management Limited is the Responsible Entity of the Trust.

Future Generation Investment Company Limited is engaged in investing in funds managed by various Australian equity fund managers. The Company invests in unlisted unit trusts and cash and/or cash equivalents. The Company's investment objectives are to provide franked dividends, to achieve capital growth, and preserve shareholder capital. By investing through the initial fund managers, its initial portfolio will consists of investments in funds that have a focus on long only, long/short and alternative investment strategies. Once fully invested, the Company will provide investors with diversified exposure to selected Australian fund managers, investment styles and strategies. It invests its capital with fund managers that have agreed to provide their services. The pro bono support of these fund managers, as well as the pro bono support of various service providers allows the Company to donate 1% of its average monthly net tangible assets each year to Australian charities.

Faster Enterprises Ltd is engaged in residential property development, commercial property development, and hotel and serviced apartment development. The Company's business comprises of three areas: Property development, Hotel development and Property leasing. The Property development business is engaged in development of residential, commercial and apartment hotel properties for leasing for leasing of for sale. The Hotel development business is engaged in development of hotel properties for long-term leasing. The Property leasing business consists of leasing of retail properties held for investment. The Company's services include acquisition, disposition, management, valuation, consulting and financial. It projects include 78 Albion Road to 46, 48 and 50 Barkly Street Box Hill; an office site property; a two-levels office property, which comprises over seven shops, and 1032 Dandenong Road, Carnegie.

Food Revolution Group Limited, formerly Crest Minerals Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in the manufacture of a range of functional juices, fibers, infused fruits, fruit waters, infused waters and bio-actives for sale as branded products and/or ingredients. The Company is engaged in the provision of co-packing and logistics services to third parties, and the research and development of various food related technologies to develop functional food products and ingredients. The Company offers pressed fruits, vegetable juices and smoothies under the brand Juice Lab; fruit-based fiber supplements under the brand Hi-Fi, and drinking alternatives under the brand Badu. The Company operates fruit and vegetable processing facilities in Victoria and New Zealand. It serves food, beverage and nutraceutical markets. The Company's subsidiaries include LangTech International Pty Ltd, Roxdale Foods Limited, LangTech Citrus Pty Ltd and LangTech Bottling Pty Ltd, among others.

Focus Minerals Limited (Focus) is engaged in gold exploration in Western Australia. The Company operates in three segments: Coolgardie, Laverton and Corporate. It operates exploration and development projects in two goldfields: The Laverton Gold Project and Coolgardie Gold Project. The projects have a combined mineral resource of over 50.1Metric tons at 2.4grams/tons for 3.8 million ounce of gold with a mixture of existing underground and open pit developments, mills on care and maintenance central to both operations, and a combination of brownfields and greenfields exploration. Its other project is Nepean Project, which is located at the southernmost end of the Company's Coolgardie tenement package. The Nepean ore body consists of over two lodes of nickel sulfide intersected by almost horizontal pegmatite sills that offset the mineralization. Austminex Pty Ltd, Focus Operation Pty Ltd and Focus Minerals (Laverton) Pty Ltd. are the subsidiaries of the Company.

Foy Group Limited is engaged in mining exploration in Papua New Guinea. The Company's segments include exploration areas and corporate activities. The exploration areas segment undertakes exploration and evaluation activities. Exploration and evaluation activities are being undertaken in the geographical segment of Papua New Guinea. The Corporate activities segment includes the corporate functions of the Company, including regulatory activities and the development of markets and business opportunities. It is based in the geographical segment of Australia. Its Amazon Bay project is located approximately 270 kilometers southeast of Port Moresby and runs along the southern coastline of Papua New Guinea east of Port Moresby for approximately 140 kilometers. The Company's subsidiaries include New Guinea Iron Pty Limited, GAMAS Magnesium Technology Pty Limited, Titan Metals Limited, Magnesium Holdings Pty Ltd and Magnesium Developments Pty Limited.

Fonterra Shareholders' Fund is a New Zealand-based unit trust established to be the authorized fund. The principal activity of the Fund is to acquire economic rights and issue units to investors. It allows investors in the Fund an opportunity to earn returns based on the financial performance of Fonterra Co-operative Group Limited (Fonterra), New Zealand-based Co-operative. Under the Trust Deed, the Fund may invest only in authorized investments, which are economic rights of Fonterra shares (Economic Rights), and issue units to investors. It may not invest directly in Fonterra shares (shares). FSF Management Company Limited is the manager of the Fund, whose objective is to manage the Fund and its property as a passive investment vehicle under the Trust Deed.

Fisher & Paykel Healthcare Corporation Limited designs, manufactures and markets medical device products and systems for use in respiratory care, acute care and the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea. The Company's segments include New Zealand, which includes all activities controlled by entities or employees based in New Zealand; North America, which includes all activities controlled by entities or employees based in the United States and Canada; Europe, which includes all activities controlled by entities or employees based in the United Kingdom, France, Germany, Sweden, Turkey and Russia, and Asia-Pacific, which includes all activities controlled by entities or employees based in Australia, Japan, India, China, South Korea, Taiwan and Hong Kong. Its products include respiratory humidifiers, single-use and reusable chambers and breathing circuits, infant resuscitators, infant warmers and accessories. In addition, the Company offers hardware and consumables.

Flight Centre Travel Group Limited is engaged in travel retailing in both the leisure and corporate travel sector, and wholesaling. The Company's segments include Australia, United States, Europe, Rest of World and Other. The Europe segment includes businesses in the United Kingdom, Ireland and Netherlands. The United States segment includes businesses in the United States and Mexico. The Rest of world segment includes the aggregation of a range of geographic businesses. The Other segment includes Brisbane-based support businesses that support the global network. It operates retail, corporate and wholesale brands in Australia. Its leisure travel brands include Flight Centre, Escape Travel, Student Flights, Travel Associates and Cruiseabout. Its corporate business includes brands, such as Travel Money, Campus Travel and 4th Dimension. Its wholesale brands include Infinity Holidays and Explore Holidays. It is also engaged in activities, such as recruitment marketing and bike retailing.

Eumeralla Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in acquiring and exploring mining projects in Mongolia and Myanmar. Its segments include Mineral Exploration (in Mongolia and Myanmar) and Other. The Company, through its subsidiary, Eumeralla Resources Pte Ltd, holds interest in Centreville LLC, which holds Mongolian minerals exploration license XV-015591 for tungsten and other metals (License). The License covers over 12,660 hectares and is located in north-eastern Mongolia approximately 20 kilometers north of the town of Dashbalbar, over 850 kilometers north-east of Ulaanbaatar and approximately 85 kilometers north-west of the Solowevsk-Choibalsan railway. Its projects in Myanmar include Mawchi Tin and Tungsten Project, Southern World Mining and Two Palms Mining Project. It has a joint venture with Myanmar Energy Resource Group for an exploration lease of an approximately 400 square kilometers tin and tungsten concession in Kayah State, Myanmar.

iShares Global Consumer Staples ETF (the Fund), formerly The iShares S&P Global Consumer Staples Index Fund, is an exchange-traded fund (ETF). The Fund seeks investment results that correspond to the price and yield performance of the S&P Global 1200 Consumer Staples Sector Index (the Index). The Index is a subset of the Standard & Poors Global 1200 Index. Components primarily include consumer discretionary, consumer goods and consumer staples companies. The Index includes manufacturers and distributors of food, producers of non-durable household goods, and food and drug retailing companies. The Fund will concentrate its investments (that is hold 25% or more of its total assets) in a particular industry or group of industries, which may include large-, mid- or small-capitalization companies. The Funds investment advisor is BlackRock Fund Advisors (BFA).

Global Construction Services Limited is engaged in delivering a range of products and services to a diverse set of customers in the commercial; residential, and resource, industrial, oil and gas sectors of the construction and maintenance industries. The Company's segments include Commercial, Residential, and Resource, Industrial, Oil & Gas. Its activities include provision of equipment and on site specialized labor services, such as scaffolding, formwork, material hoists, temporary site accommodation, general plant hire, temporary fencing, concrete pumping, concrete placement, and related engineering and design services. Its products and services include equipment solutions, such as access equipment and air power tools; scaffold and access solutions, such as modular scaffold and scaffold accessories; site accommodation solutions, such as lunch rooms and site offices, and specialized site services, such as traffic management and security services. It operates in Western Australia.

Grand Gulf Energy Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in oil and gas production, exploration and evaluation operations. The Company has its production and exploration operations in Louisiana, United States. The company's portfolio of projects includes Desiree Field and Dugas & Leblanc Field in Assumption Parish, Abita in Plaquemines Parish and West Klondike Development in Iberville Parish, Louisiana.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Folkestone Limited is a real estate funds management and developer providing real estate wealth solutions for private clients and select institutions. Its funds management platform offers listed and unlisted funds to private clients and select institutional investors. Its segments include Funds Management and Development. Its on-balance sheet activities focus on value-add and opportunistic real estate investments. It manages a real estate investment trust, Folkestone Education Trust. The Folkestone Education Trust invests in early learning properties within Australia and New Zealand. Its Private Funds offer unlisted income, value-add and opportunistic (development) funds and mandates for private client and select institutions. Its Private Funds are able to offer clients investment strategies across the real estate spectrum. Its Australian real estate investment trust (A-REIT) Securities Funds include Folkestone Maxim A-REIT Securities Fund and Folkestone Maxim A-REIT Securities SMA.

GDI Property Group Limited is an integrated, internally managed property and funds management company. The Company is engaged in ownership, management, refurbishment, leasing and syndication of office and industrial properties. It operates through two segments: property investment and funds management. The property investment segment is engaged in the investment and management of income producing properties. The funds management segment is engaged in the establishment and management of property investment vehicles. The Company owns a funds business (Funds Business) which, in addition to managing the GDI Property Trust (the Trust), manages unlisted and unregistered managed investment schemes with assets under management (AUM) of approximately $356.1 million. The Trust is engaged in the property investment business and internally manages and owns a portfolio of office properties across Australia, which includes approximately five properties in central business district (CBD) locations.

Family Zone Cyber Safety Limited is an Australian operated technology company focused on the cyber safety market. The Company is engaged in the development, technical assessment and trials of the Family Zone platform, a universal parental control platform that works in the home, outside, within carrier networks, public hotspots and schools. The Company operates in two segments: Cyber Safe Technology (Box Services) and corporate undertakings (Corporate). Family Zone platform is a cloud-based parental control platform, which incorporates networking and application technologies, which allow parental controls to be embedded within home, enterprise, public and telecommunications carrier networks and installed on mobile devices. This platform allows users to block porn and adult content; restrict access to social networks; set access and sleep times; limit application downloads and in-application purchases; restrict access to mobile games and applications, and restrict YouTube content.

GoConnect Limited is a media communications company. The Company engages in online delivery of interactive audio and video content through its technologies. It is focused on the development and delivery of Internet Protocol television (IPTV) products. The Company offers JJ5TV; Undercover, which is an interactive music magazine, featuring news, reviews, profiles and interviews from around the world; uctv.fm, which is an entertainment IPTV channel that streams programming on users television, personal computer or smart phone; Soundcheck, which is an online talent discovery network across a range of platforms, and The Business Show, which is an investor relations solution designed to assist companies communicate with investors. It also provides SharpEye, which allows users to view photos online on their television; Free WiFi Marketing Platform, and iCheckWeather, which provides the weather forecast, weather reports and weather conditions. The Company's subsidiary is Uctv.fm Pty Ltd.

Grandbridge Limited is an investment company. The Company is engaged in the development of its investments in investees, BPH Energy Limited, MEC Resources Ltd and Advent Energy Ltd. The Company's operating segments include Consulting services, Investing and Corporate. It is engaged in the development of products and services within the private and public equity markets in Australia, the United States, Europe and Asia. The Company also provides corporate advisory services to businesses, including assisting with corporate structuring/restructuring, development funding and initial public offerings (IPOs), corporate recognition and strategic development. It provides clients seeking market expansion, strategic partnerships or investment funding with a range of services and also provides corporate advisory services to sectors, including biotechnology, oil and gas, agriculture, technology and mining. Its subsidiaries include Grandbridge Securities Pty Limited and e-Shares.com.au Pty Limited.

Golden Deeps Limited is a mineral exploration and investment company. The Company operates projects in the Republic of Namibia and in Western Australia and Victoria. Its Grootfontein Base Metal Project (GBMP) is located the Otavi Mountain Land (OML), in north-east Namibia. The GBMP landholding stands at 632 square kilometers (Sq. Kms.), with a further 331 Sq. Kms. under application. There are four recognized base metal trends located within the package: Askevold, Abenab, Pavian and Khusib. The Askevold trend is a copper trend hosting the Deblin copper mine. The Abenab trend is a copper-lead-zinc-vandium trend hosting the Abenab and Abenab West mines in the east and the Nosib Block copper mine in the west. The Pavian trend is a lead-zinc mineralized trend, while the Khusib trend is a copper-silver trend.

Great Boulder Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company, with a primary focus on exploration, discovery and delineation of gold deposits. The Company's Balagundi Project is located approximately 20 kilometers east of the Kalgoorlie Super Pit and the township of Kalgoorlie in the Eastern Goldfields District of Western Australia. Its Broadwood Project is located between the historical Binduli gold mining center and the Golden Mile/Kalgoorlie Super Pit alongside the township of Kalgoorlie. Its Jundee South Project is located east of Wiluna in the Eastern Goldfields district of Western Australia, approximately 10 kilometers along strike from the Jundee Gold Mine operated by Northern Star Resources Limited. Its Tarmoola Project is located over 40 kilometers north-west of Leonora. Its Yamarna project is located approximately 130 kilometers east of Laverton, and over 30 kilometers west of the Gruyere gold deposit in the Eastern Goldfields District of Western Australia.

Grays eCommerce Group Limited is engaged in the provision of online auctioneering and valuation services in the business to business (B2B) sector. The Company's segments are B2B, which is an auction site catering to business customers, working closely with corporates, banks and insolvency practitioners to auction fixed and mobile plant and equipment through its Website graysonline.com and this division also provides valuation and workplace health and safety consulting service to business customers, and B2C, which comprises both auction and buy now sales of wine, homewares, electronics, jewelry, brown goods and white goods through the Websites graysonline.com and grayswine.com.au. It operates in every state in mainland Australia, in the Northern Territory and New Zealand. GraysOnline offers over 80 categories in consumer, industrial and commercial goods direct from the manufacturer and distributors. GraysWine offers over 2,000 wines from winemakers from Australia and abroad.

Gale Pacific Limited is a manufacturer and marketer of commercial and do it yourself (DIY) products. The Company operates through branded shading, screening and home improvement products segment. Its operating segments include Australasia, which includes manufacturing and distribution facilities located in Australia, and distribution facilities located in New Zealand; China Manuf. and EurAsia, which includes manufacturing facilities located in Beilun and China, which supplies to the Company's sales and marketing operations across the world; Americas, which includes sales offices located in Florida and custom blind assembly and distribution facilities located in California, and Middle East and North Africa (MENA), which includes sales office and distribution facility located in the United Arab Emirates. Its products include architectural shade fabrics, shade sails and a range of commercial fabrics. Its brands include Coolaroo, ZONE Interiors, EVERTON and GALE Pacific.
Home Improvement Products & Services Retailers - NEC

XPD Soccer Gear Group Limited is engaged the designing, developing, manufacturing, distributing and marketing sportswear with a focus on soccer wear under the XPD brand. The Company operates through two segments: Own-brand sales (XPD brand) and Contract third-party sales (OEM). It offers a range of products, consisting of sports footwear, sports apparel, soccer kits and soccer accessories. It also manufactures sports footwear on an original equipment manufacturer (OEM) or original design manufacturer (ODM) basis for international footwear brands. It sells its XPD brand products to independent third-party distributors on a wholesale basis. Through distributors, its distribution network reaches over 1,900 retail outlets throughout China. These retail outlets are either specialty stores, such as shoe stores and sporting goods stores, or concessions in department stores and shopping malls. Its products are also sold through online platforms. It operates in People's Republic of China.

Globe Metals & Mining Limited is a resources company. The Company's principal activities are to explore, develop and invest in the resource sector. It operates through two segments: Africa-Kanyika and Africa Exploration. The Africa-Kanyika segment includes the Kanyika Niobium project in Malawi. The Kanyika Niobium project is in evaluation stage. The AfricaExploration segment consist of exploration-stage projects, including Chiziro Graphite project in Malawi. The Chiziro Graphite project includes approximately 2,020 square kilometers. The Chiziro Graphite project includes Chimutu Prospect and the Katengeza Prospect. The Kanyika Niobium Project focuses to produce niobium pentoxide and tantalum pentoxide powders. The Company holds interest in the EPL0421/15 tenement in Malawi under Kanyika Exploration project. It holds interest in EPL0299/10R tenement in Malawi under the Chiziro Graphite project. The Company operates in Australia and Africa.

Glennon Small Companies Limited is an investing company. The Company is engaged in making investments in, and deriving revenue and investment income from listed companies outside the Standard & Poor's/Australian Securities Exchange 100 (S&P/ASX 100). The Company operates in Australia. It provides investors with an opportunity to invest in a small and micro-cap investment portfolio, targeting over 60 equity securities through an ASX listed investment company. The Company's investment objective is to provide investors over the medium to long term with capital growth in excess of the S&P/ASX Small Ordinaries Accumulation Index before fees, costs and taxes. The Company invests in a range of securities, including information technology, financial services, energy, healthcare, consumer staples, industrials, consumer discretionary, utilities, materials and telecommunications services. Glennon Capital Pty Ltd. is the investment manager of the Company.

Greenearth Energy Ltd is engaged in investment of energy efficiency technologies along with other renewable energy research and development projects. The Company operates through three segments: Industrial Energy Efficiency, Technology Investment and Other Investments. The industrial energy efficiency segment provides lighting solutions to industrial and infrastructure businesses in Australia and the Pacific Rim. The technology investment segment includes technology investments or projects, which it has either invested in but have not been expanded into a distinct business segment, or technologies or projects that are being developed or considered. This segment also includes the consolidated entity's investment in NCF Global Pty Ltd and NewCO2Fuels Ltd. It has interests in technology-focused solutions in the industrial energy efficiency and carbon dioxide (CO2)-to-fuel conversion markets, as well as conventional geothermal resources.

Fleetwood Corporation Limited is a provider of accommodation solutions, and recreational vehicles, parts and accessories. The Company's principal activities include design, manufacture and sale of manufactured accommodation; manufacture of caravans and vehicle parts and accessories; manufacture and distribution of vehicle parts and accessories, and operation of accommodation villages. The Company's segments include RV Manufacturing, Parts and Accessories, Manufactured Accommodation, Village Operations and Unallocated. The RV Manufacturing segment includes manufacture of caravans and vehicle parts and accessories. The Parts and Accessories segment manufactures and distributes vehicle parts and accessories. The Manufactured Accommodation segment is engaged in the design, manufacture and sale of manufactured accommodation. The Village Operations segment includes operation of accommodation villages. The Company operates in Australia and New Zealand.

First Growth Funds Limited is an investment company. The Company's investment objective is to acquire 100% of, or to invest in listed or unlisted companies or operating businesses where there are suitable growth opportunities. The Company manages a portfolio of investments covering small and medium companies that are listed on Australian Stock Exchange or seeking investment ahead of initial public offering (IPO). The Company has also invested in recapitalization. The Company is seeking suitable investments that will deliver beneficial returns over both short and longer terms to complement its investment. The Company's subsidiaries include Whifzone Pte Ltd and Whizfone (Singapore) Pte Ltd, which are located in Singapore, and AM Communications Joint Stock Corporation, which is located in Vietnam.

Freshtel Holdings Limited is an Australia-based Internet communications company. The principal activities of the Company include the operation of the sub-contracted voice over Internet protocol (VoIP) business, and the search for an appropriate investment opportunity. The Company is engaged in the business of development and marketing of VoIP telephony products and services. The Company's Freshtel Internet phone allows the user to make free phone calls to other people also running Freshtel Internet phone (or any other service running on the Voicedot network, such as Tesco Internet phone users) on their computers. Its VoIP plans include Freshtel 29.95, Freshtel 14.95, Freshtel 9.95, Freshtel 4.95, Freshtel National, Freshtel World and Freshtel Mobile. The Company offers Firefly SoftPhone, which offers features, such as conference calling, call transfer and instant messaging, among others.

Fairfax Media Limited is a multi-platform media, marketing services and real estate services company. The Company's principal activities include the publishing of news, information and entertainment, advertising sales in print and digital formats, and radio broadcasting. Its segments include Domain Group, which provides residential, commercial and rural property marketing solutions and search tools, as well as information for buyers, investors, sellers, renters and agents; Metropolitan Media, which provides metropolitan news, sport, lifestyle and business media across various platforms, including print, online, tablet and mobile; Australian Community Media, including newspaper publishing and online for Australian regional, community and agricultural media; New Zealand Media, which includes newspaper, magazine and general publishing, and online for all New Zealand media; Radio, including metropolitan radio networks in Australia, and Other, including corporate and other entities.

Factor Therapeutics Limited, formerly Tissue Therapies Limited, is a biotechnology company. The Company's principal activities include the development and commercialization of its intellectual property in wound care. The Company's lead program, VF-001, is a biologic product for wound care. VF-001 can be used in conjunction with standard care compression bandaging in the community setting. VF-001 is a fusion protein between a truncated vitronectin peptide and Insulin-like growth factor 1(IGF-1). The initial indication for VF-001 is for Venous Leg Ulcers (VLUs). The Company also has other programs in early development to address other wound applications, as well as new products in the ocular wound care space. Its pipeline includes VF-002, a viscous product to assess burn potential, particularly mucosal burns from radiation therapy, and VF-003 and VF-004, for growth in eye procedures/use of glaucoma stents, reduction of fibrosis and minimization of negative effects of ocular surgery.

Gascoyne Resources Limited is a mineral exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in the exploration for gold and evaluation of the development options for its Australian gold projects. The Company holds mining leases and exploration licenses and applications totaling approximately 4,000 square kilometers in the Gascoyne and Murchison regions of Western Australia. Its Dalgaranga gold project is located approximately 70 kilometers Northwest of Mt Magnet in the Murchison gold mining region of Western Australia. Its Glenburgh gold project is located in the Southern Gascoyne Province of Western Australia approximately 250 kilometers east of Carnarvon. The Glenburgh gold project consists of a gold mineralized system hosted in interpreted remnants of Archaean terrain in a Proterozoic mobile belt. Its Egerton project consists of approximately two granted mining leases and over three granted exploration licenses.

Finbar Group Limited is engaged in property development and investment. The Company focuses on the development of medium to high-density residential buildings and commercial developments in Western Australia by way of direct ownership, ownership through subsidiaries or by equity accounted investees. Its segments include Residential apartment development, Commercial office/retail development, Rental of property and Corporate. The Residential apartment development segment is engaged in residential apartment development in Western Australia. The Commercial office/retail development segment is engaged in commercial office/retail development in Western Australia. The Rental of property segment is engaged in renting of property in Western Australia. Its projects include Norwood-280 Lord Street, Perth; Ecco-262 Lord Street, Perth, and Unison on Tenth-241 Railway Avenue, Maylands. It holds rental properties through its subsidiaries, 175 Adelaide Terrace Pty Ltd and Finbar Karratha Pty Ltd.

Fitzroy River Corporation Ltd is an oil and gas investment holding company. The Company focuses on nonoperational assets, such as royalties, free carried interests and minority equity positions. Its investments consist of Royalty agreements centered around oil and gas production in the onshore Canning Basin in far north Western Australia. Its focus is on Western Australia, specifically the Canning Superbasin where the Company holds royalty interests in various permits in the Canning Superbasin through two separate Royalty Deeds: the Canning Basin Royalty Deed and the Lennard Shelf Royalty Deed. The Canning Basin Royalty deed consists of EP 391, EP 371, EP 428, EP 431, EP 436, R 1 and L 15 1. The Lennard Shelf Royalty deed consists of EP 129, which includes an area of over 652.99 square kilometers and eight blocks; L 6, which includes an area of approximately 407.9 square kilometers and five blocks, and L 8, which includes an area of over 326.3 square kilometers and four blocks.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Woolworths Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in retail operations. The Company's segments include Australian Food and Petrol, New Zealand Supermarkets, Endeavour Drinks Group, BIGW and Hotels. The Australian Food and Petrol segment is engaged in the procurement of food and petroleum products for resale to customers in Australia. The New Zealand Supermarkets segment is engaged in the procurement of food and liquor products for resale to customers in New Zealand. The Endeavour Drinks Group segment is involved in the procurement of liquor products for resale to customers in Australia. The BIGW segment is engaged in the procurement of discount general merchandise products for resale to customers in Australia. The Hotels segment is engaged in the provision of a range of leisure and hospitality services, including food and alcohol, accommodation, entertainment and gaming in Australia. The Company's brands include Essentials, Woolworths, Dan Murphy's and BWS.

GBM Gold Limited is focused on becoming a gold production company and building a gold production base in Central Victoria. The Company targets low-cost open pit gold projects to develop mining operation in Central Victoria, Australia. Its projects include Bendigo Goldfield, Goldsborough, Fiddlers Creek, Avoca and Beavis/ISG. The Bendigo Goldfield project consists of Greater Bendigo, which inlcludes the MIN 5344 tenement; Whip & Jersey, which includes MIN 4878 tenement; Woodvale, which consists of the MIN 5364 tenement; Bendigo Urban, which includes the EL 3327 tenement; West Bendigo, which consists of EL 5035 tenement, and Wilson Hill, which includes EL 5527 tenement. The Wilsons Hill project covers the Wilsons Hill Goldfield, approximately 20 kilometers west of Bendigo. The Goldsborough project consists of the Harvest home JV (MIN 5510) and Queen's Birthday (EL 5528). The Beavis-ISG project is centered on an Alluvial gold deposit at Beavis, and it consists of WA 1395 tenement.

FYI Resources Limited is a resources company. The Company is a potash explorer focused on the exploration and development of potash projects in Southeast Asia. The Company has two principal target project areas being Thailand and Laos. The Company's segments include mineral exploration and evaluation of properties in Australia and Asia. It has various project areas that it is intending to explore and develop in Thailand. The portfolio of projects focuses on the Khorat Basin, North-eastern Thailand. Its project areas in Thailand covers over six Special Prospecting Licenses (SPL's) under the name of West Mekong Minerals project (WMM) and another six SPL's under the East Siam Minerals project (ESM). The Lao target project areas are located approximately 220 kilometers Southeast of the Vientiane. The Company is conducting due diligence reviews on projects, including database assessments, field inspections, confirmation drilling, down-hole geophysics and laboratory analysis.

Farm Pride Foods Limited is engaged in the business of production, processing, manufacturing and sale of egg and egg products. The Company grades, packs, processes, supplies and markets shell eggs and process egg products within Australia, and exports to Asia. The Company sources eggs from Farm Pride farms and other local suppliers to process and pack approximately eight million eggs every week. The Company's grading and processing facilities are located at Keysborough and Lethbridge in Victoria, Greendale in New South Wales, Australia. The Company offers egg varieties, including freshly laid cage eggs, barn laid eggs and free range egg varieties. The Keysborough site has egg processing plants, turning shell eggs into value-added egg products for supply into the food service industry. The Company operates approximately 10 farms. The Company offers egg products, such as whole egg, egg white, egg yolk, scrambled eggs, peeled boiled eggs, fried eggs, crepes and omeletts.

Global Petroleum Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas, upstream exploration company, which focuses on Africa and the Mediterranean. The principal activities of the Company consist of oil and gas exploration, development and production. The Company's principal assets are two exploration blocks located offshore Namibia. The Company's project includes Namibian Project. The Namibian Project holds interest in petroleum exploration license number 29 (License) covering Offshore Blocks 1910B and 2010A in the Republic of Namibia. The License covers approximately 11,730 square kilometers and it is located offshore Namibia in water depths ranging from 1,300 meters to 3,000 meters. It intends to seek license positions in frontier exploration areas in Africa and the Mediterranean, and potentially other frontier basins, either directly through license rounds, joint venture arrangements or acquisition. Its subsidiaries include Global Petroleum UK Limited and Jupiter Petroleum Limited.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Fraser Range Metals Group Limited is a mineral exploration company operating with early stage nickel, copper and gold exploration tenements in Western Australia's Fraser range region. The Company focuses on exploration of its Fraser Range tenements. Its Dundas project-ELA 63/1792 covers an area of approximately 202 square kilometers. The Company's Fraser range project, situated within the Albany-Fraser Orogen, is divided into a Western set of tenements, which include E28/2390 and E28/2392, and an Eastern tenement, which includes E28/2385. The Western tenements are located on, or adjacent to, Harris Lake Shear Zone, which hosts Segue Resources Limited's Corvette gold prospect, approximately 140 kilometers to the North of the project. The Fraser range project has over four geochemical anomalies, including approximately one nickel and over two gold anomalies on E28/2385 and a gold anomaly on E28/2392, which sits within the Harris Lake Shear Zone.

Flexiroam Limited is an Australia-based telecommunications company. The Company is a mobile virtual network operator offering voice and data roaming services across the world through various technologies. It offers FLEXIROAM APP and FLEXIROAM X. Its FLEXIROAM X is a thin, microchip-embedded film that, once applied to a user's existing subscriber entity module (SIM) card, provides data roaming in approximately 100 countries. The FLEXIROAM Voice App has an Over The Top (OTT) application that provides voice, messaging and video functionalities for iPhone Operating System (iOS) and Android devices. It is an intuitive smartphone application that offers a range of services, including international voice calls and international number rental. The Company has approximately 815,230 subscribers and over 100 travel industry partners, including airlines. The Company's subsidiaries include Super Bonus Profit Sdn Bhd and Flexiroam Sdn Bhd.

Global Fortune Investment Limited, formerly China Mining Limited, is engaged in exploration for gold in the Kalgoorlie area located in Western Australia. The Company operates through two business segments, including mineral exploration and food, and beverage and agricultural products trade sector. The Company focuses on its Horse Rock Project, which consists of exploration licenses, including E31/859 and E31/887. Its E31/859 and E31/887 have an area of over 90 square kilometers, and are located in the Goldfields of Western Australia. The Horse Rock Project is located approximately 170 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie. The Horse Rock Project is located within the Archaean aged murrin domain of the Kurnalpi Terrrance. The Company's exploration consists of geographical mapping, targeted rock chip sampling, geochemical sampling and analysis, and aircore drilling. It focuses on becoming a multi-tiered investment vehicle through its interests in its Australian exploration assets.

Genesis Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration for and evaluation of gold, manganese and base metals. It segments include Australia, which consists of copper, iron, gold, manganese and other base metal exploration projects, and Macedonia, which consists of a base metal and gold exploration project. The Company's projects include Plavica Project, Arltunga Project, Alice Springs Project, Gladstone-Mount Miller Project, Pioneer Project, Mcarthur River Project, Laura River Au-Pt Project and Fenn Gap Mn-Fe Project. The Arltunga Gold Project consists of exploration license EL25238. The Gladstone-Mount Miller Project consists of exploration license EPM15771. The Pioneer Project consists of one granted Exploration Permit Mineral (EPM15619). The McArthur River project consists of exploration license EL24814. The Laura River project consists of exploration license EPM15242. The Fenn Gap project consists of one exploration license, EL24839.

GARDA Diversified Property Fund (GDF) is a real estate investment trust (REIT). The Fund's objective is to provide sustainable and growing distributable income derived from investments in commercial offices in city and suburban markets, as well as industrial facilities along the eastern seaboard of Australia. The Fund invests in commercial and industrial properties, and other assets in accordance with the provision of the Fund's constitution. The Fund holds eight established property assets: B2, 747 Lytton Road, Murarrie; Land at 26-30 Grafton Street, Cairns; 7-19 Lake Street, Cairns; 142-150 Benjamin Place, Lytton; 12-14 The Circuit, Brisbane Airport; 436 Elgar Rd, Box Hill; 154 Varsity Parade, Varsity Lakes, and 572-576 Swan Street, Richmond.

Forte Consolidated Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activities of the Company are exploration for and evaluation of economic deposits for gold and other minerals. The Company's primary focus is on Johnnycake (EPM 18986) project, which is located approximately 40 kilometers north west of Collinsville. The Johnnycake (EPM 18986) project has over two prospects within the tenement, such as Sledgehammer and Szarbs. The Sledgehammer prospect produces high grade rock chip assays from an outcrop of silicified hydrothermal breccia, including a single sample yielding approximately 50 grams per ton (g/t) gold and over 40 g/t silver. The Szarbs prospect is located within a prospective trachyte host unit interpreted to be part of the Mount Toussaint Trachyte, which hosts the Mount Carlton series of deposits approximately 20 kilometers to the north.

GB Energy Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company that focuses on uranium and Iron Oxide-Copper-Gold-Uranium (IOCGU) mineralization in South Australia. The Company operates through segments, including Exploration and evaluation-South Australia and Other sector. The Exploration and evaluation-South Australia segment includes approximately five exploration licenses (ELs) held by the Company. The Company holds interest in these licenses through its subsidiary, GBE Exploration Pty Ltd., which include EL 5231, EL 5255, EL 5302, EL 5391 and EL 5778. The Company operates Stuart Shelf Copper-Gold-Uranium project and Mount Denison Uranium project. The Stuart Shelf Copper-Gold-Uranium project hosts Olympic Dam, Prominent Hill, Carrapateena and Hillside discoveries. Its other subsidiary is Namib Pty Ltd.

Global Gold Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the money lending business under its money lending license. The Company's money lending license is held by its subsidiary, G-Vest Corporation Sdn Bhd. The Company is also engaged in investments in gold equities and gold related entities. The Company operates its money lending activities predominantly in Malaysia. The Company's subsidiaries include Rimbun Teratai Sdn Bhd and Global Gold Holdings (HK) Limited.

GBST Holdings Limited is engaged in client accounting and securities transaction technology solutions for the finance, banking and capital markets industry globally, and funds administration and registry software for the wealth management industry in Australia and the United Kingdom. The Company is a gateway technology provider to the superannuation industry. It is also a provider of data and quantitative services offering after tax measurement of portfolio performance in Australia. It also provides Website and mobile platform design and digital agency services focused on e-commerce and the financial services industry in Australia and Europe. The Company's segments are Capital Markets Australia; Capital Markets International; Wealth Management Australia, and Wealth Management International. The Company's divisions include GBST Wealth Management and GBST Capital Markets.

Genera Biosystems Limited is engaged in the development and commercialization of a portfolio of molecular diagnostic test technologies in Australia. The Company is developing a suite of molecular diagnostic testing products based on its AmpaSand bead-based technology. The Company's AmpaSand beads are utilized in its PapType and RTIplex molecular diagnostic tests. It has approximately three additional AmpaSand bead-based multiplexed tests in its development pipeline. PapType is a molecular diagnostic test for the simultaneous detection and genotyping of approximately 14 high-risk and over two low-risk types of human papillomavirus (HPV), the viruses that cause cervical cancer in women and genital warts. RTIplex is an automated assay for the simultaneous detection of approximately 12 viral and over three bacterial respiratory pathogens. The RTIplex kit is used for the detection and identification of over 15 respiratory analytes from nasopharyngeal swab specimens.

Generation Healthcare REIT (the Fund) is a real estate investment trust. The principal activity of the Fund is investment in healthcare real estate. The Fund's portfolio of approximately 20 properties include hospitals, medical centers, laboratories, residential aged care and other purpose-built healthcare facilities. The Fund's property portfolio includes Epworth Freemasons Private Hospital and Medical Centre; Harvester Centre; Epworth Freemasons Private Hospital (Clarendon Street); Frankston Private; Frankston Specialist Centre; Casey Specialist Centre; Australian Red Cross Blood Service Facility; Spring Hill, Pacific Private Clinic; RSL Care Tantula Rise Aged Care Facility; RSL Care Baycrest Aged Care Facility; RSL Care Darlington Aged Care Facility; Waratah Private Hospital Ground Floor Suites, and Westmead Rehabilitation Hospital. The Fund's investments are located in Victoria, New South Wales and Queensland. The Fund's responsible entity is APN Funds Management Limited.

Globe International Limited is engaged in the specialized production and distribution of purpose-built apparel, footwear and hardgoods for the board sports, street fashion and workwear markets globally. The Company's segments include Australasia, North America and Europe. The Company's divisions include Globe, Dwindle Distribution, Hardcore Distribution, 4Front and FXD. The Company's brands include Globe, Dwindle Distribution, Enjoi, Blind, Almost, Cliche, Darkstar, Tensor, Dusters, FXD and Sample. The Company also maintains diverse licensing and distribution of various third-party brands for the Australian and New Zealand markets through its Hardcore Distribution and 4Front divisions. The Company offers various products of third-party brands, such as Stussy, OBEY, KOMONO, Misfit Shapes, X-Large, Zero, Andale Bearings and Kryptonics Wheels. The Hardcore Distribution division is a distributor of over 30 skateboard brands, including Girl, Flip, Chocolate and Thrasher.

Gladiator Resources Limited is an Australia-based company focused on the Zapucay Project conducting further exploration and reviews of past economic and pre-feasibility studies. The Company's segments include Australia and Uruguay. The Company's subsidiaries include Ecochar Pty Ltd, Ion Resources Pty Ltd, Ferrous Resources Pty Ltd, Ferrominas Sociedad Anonima, Floniler Sociedad Anonima, Joutes Sociedad Anonima, Hamfu Sociedad Anonima, Kyntu Sociedad Anonima and Rolben Sociedad Anonima.

Galilee Energy Limited is an energy company, which is engaged in the oil and gas exploration and production. The Company has tenement interests located in Australia, the United States and Chile. Its segments consist of Australia, including Qld; United States, including Illinois, Texas and Kansas, and South America, including Chile. The Company is engaged in the development of coal seam gas (CSG) in the Galilee Basin near Longreach in Queensland. The Company holds interest in the Glenaras Gas Project, which is located within the ATP529 permit, in western Queensland's Galilee Basin. The permit covers an area of approximately 4,000 square kilometers. The Glenaras Gas Project contains CSG contingent resource position in the Betts Creek coals. In the Unites States, the Company holds interest in the Hoffer Extension Area, including over 1,500 acres under lease covering a range of prospects. The Company focuses on the CSG potential in the Southern Magallanes Basin in Chile.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Goodman Group is a global integrated property company. The Company is engaged in owning, developing and managing industrial property and business space in the markets across the world. The principal activities of the Company are investment in directly and indirectly held industrial property, property services, property development (including development management) and fund management. The Company's segments include Australia and New Zealand, Asia, Continental Europe, United Kingdom and Americas. The Company's stapled entities include Goodman Limited, Goodman Industrial Trust and Goodman Logistics (HK) Limited. The Company's portfolio consists of approximately 190 properties located in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Adelaide, Canberra and Perth. The Company is an investor in four property funds: Goodman Australia Industrial Partnership (GAIP), Goodman Australia Partnership (GAP), Goodman Australia Development Partnership (GADP) and KWASA-Goodman Industrial Partnership (KGIP).

Genworth Mortgage Insurance Australia Limited (Genworth Australia) is an Australia-based company, which provides lenders mortgage insurance (LMI). The Company operates through one geographical segment conducting loan mortgage insurance business in Australia. Genworth Australia has commercial relationships with over 105 lenders across Australia. The Company has supply and service contract with over 10 of its lender customers. It offers over three products, including Standard LMI, Homebuyer Plus and Business Select/Low Doc. The Company underwrites LMI through flow and portfolio channels. The Company's subsidiaries include Genworth Financial Mortgage Insurance Pty Limited, Genworth Financial New Holdings Pty Ltd, Genworth Financial Australia Holdings, LLC and Genworth Financial Services Pty Ltd.

GrainCorp Limited is an Australia-based food ingredients and agribusiness company. The Company focuses its activities on approximately three grains, including wheat, barley and canola. The Company has four segments: GrainCorp Storage & Logistics, GrainCorp Marketing, GrainCorp Malt and GrainCorp Oils. The GrainCorp Storage & Logistics segment includes services, such as CropConnect, which is an online cash marketplace, and GrainTransact, which is the Company's grain stock system. The GainCorp Marketing segment includes the buying and selling of grain products. GrainCorp Malt segment supplies malt to global brewers, craft brewers and distillers. GrainCorp Oils sources, supplies and refines edible oils that are used in food and animal feed products, as well as non-food industrial production, such as biofuel. CropConnect allows users to manage, sell and buy warehoused grain. It allows growers to set the cash price for their warehoused grain.

Gold Mountain Limited is an exploration company operating in Australia and Papua New Guinea to acquire, explore and develop areas that are highly prospective for gold and other precious and base metals and minerals. The Company's geographical segments include Australia, Papua New Guinea and Peru. Its projects include Papua New Guinea Project, Peruvian Project and Australian Projects. The Papua New Guinea Project comprises Wabag, PNG (EL1966, EL1967, EL1968, EL2426, & EL2430), Crown Ridge Prospect EL1968 and Sak Creek Prospect EL1966. The Peruvian Project comprises Goldsmith Resources SAC, which holds three Peruvian gold projects: Mollehuaca Gold Processing Plant, Eladium project and third project at Saulito. Its Australian Projects include Cowarra gold project, Grenfell, NSW (EL8263) and Dalton, NSW (EL6922). The Wabag Gold Project is situated in Enga Province of Papua New Guinea, immediately to the north of Wabag township, the provincial capital.

Gateway Mining Limited is a mineral exploration company, engaged in the exploration for gold and base metals. The Company holds interests in approximately 140 square kilometers of tenements in the Gidgee area, located over 600 kilometers northeast of Perth. These tenements are located over a mineral deposit setting, Volcanic Arc Extensional Basin in the Gum Creek Greenstone Belt of the Archean Yilgarn Craton. Its Gidgee area includes Airport Area Gold, Bungarra Project, Gossans Galore, Gravel Pit, The Cup and JV Tenement and Victory Creek. Airport Gold Trend includes approximately four mining leases over the Montague Granodiorite and margins. Its Bungarra Project comprises the northern portion of Gateway's ground in Gidgee. The Cup area has copper/base metal deposit. Its Cup is host to volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) mineralization, which occurs close to the tenement boundary with tenement M57/633. Its Gossans Galore area has numerous mafic/bi-modal mafic VMS mineralized deposits.

GTN Limited is engaged in the provision of an advertising platform to advertisers. The Company's segments include Australia, the United Kingdom, Canada and Brazil. It offers advertising spots on television and radio networks, adjacent to information reports that listeners are engaged with, such as traffic and news. It is a supplier of traffic information reports to radio stations in Australia, United Kingdom, Canada and Brazil. In exchange for providing these reports, and in certain cases monetary compensation, it receives commercial advertising spots adjacent to traffic, news and information reports from its network of affiliates. These spots are bundled together by the Company and sold to advertisers on a national, regional or specific market basis. The Company's advertising spots are short in duration, and are read live on the air by radio and television personalities during peak audience hours. Its subsidiaries include GTCR Gridlock Management, Inc. and Global Alert Network, Inc.

Newcrest Mining Limited is a gold mining company. The Company is engaged in exploration, mine development, mine operations, and the sale of gold and gold/copper concentrate. It owns and operates a portfolio of mines and a pipeline of brownfield and greenfield exploration projects. Its operating segments include Cadia, Australia; Telfer, Australia; Lihir, Papua New Guinea; Gosowong, Indonesia; Hidden Valley JV, Papua New Guinea; Bonikro, Cote d'Ivoire, and Exploration and Other. Its mines are located in Australia, Papua New Guinea, Indonesia, and in Cote d'Ivoire, West Africa. Cadia Valley Operation is located approximately 30 kilometers from the city of Orange in central west New South Wales and is over 250 kilometers west of Sydney. The Lihir operation is on Niolam Island in the New Ireland Province of Papua New Guinea. The Telfer gold-copper mines are located in the Great Sandy Desert in the East Pilbara region. Hidden Valley is located in the Morobe province in Papua New Guinea.

GPS Alliance Holdings Limited (GPS) is an Australia-based company engaged in the provision of services as real-estate agency, provision of real estate consultancy and investment and trading of building materials and interior design and fit-out work businesses. The Company holds the issued capital of the Singapore investment holding company, GPS Alliance Holdings Pte. Ltd. The Company segments include Property Development, and Interior designing and fit-out work (ID & fit-out work). The Company's Property Development business is conducted by GPS Alliance Development and Investment (GPSDI). The Company's fit-out solutions business is conducted by GPS Alliance Home Solutions (GPSHS). The Company's international projects include Grove House, Manchester; The Bay, Phnom Penh, Cambodia; Angelgate, Manchester; Spectrum Apartments, Sheffield; The Quadrant, Liverpool, and City Center Residence, Pattaya. Its local projects include The Terrace EC (Punggol) and Waterwoods EC (Punggol).

Golden Rim Resources Ltd is engaged in the mineral exploration and investment. The Company is engaged in the business of exploration for mineral resources in various geographical regions. Its geographical segments include Australia, South America and Africa. It has a pipeline of gold projects covering over 1,015 square kilometers in the Birimian greenstone belts of Burkina Faso. The Company has three projects in Burkina Faso for a total landholding of approximately 632 square kilometers, which include Korongou, Yako and Babonga projects in Burkina Faso. The Korongou Project covers part of the Lower Proterozoic Birimian Samira Hill greenstone belt in Burkina Faso. The Korongou Project covers an area of approximately 65 square kilometers and is located approximately 230 kilometers north-east of Ouagadougou. The Babonga project covers single license area of approximately 102 square kilometers. Its subsidiaries include Golden Rim Chile Pty Ltd and Golden Rim SAR Exploration SARL.

Greenpower Energy Limited is engaged in the development of its Coal to Liquid project, and maintaining core exploration licenses with the potential to supply feedstock and integrate with the Coal to Liquid project. The Company is engaged in the exploration activities throughout Australia. The Company has licenses in Victoria. The Company holds three mineral exploration licenses in the Gippsland Basin, including EL 4500 (Korumburra), EL 5227 (Athlone) and EL 4877 (Mirboo). The Company, through its subsidiary, Greenpower Natural Gas Pty Ltd, holds interest in EL 4500 (Korumburra) and EL 5227 (Athlone). The Company, through its subsidiary, Sawells Pty Ltd, holds interest in EL 4877 (Mirboo). The Company's subsidiaries include GCC Asset Holdings Pty Ltd and Greenpower Energy Limited.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Growthpoint Properties Australia Limited is a real estate investment trust (REIT). The Company invests in Australian property in the industrial, office and retail sectors. Its segments include Office and Industrial. It acquires properties leased to tenants and holds these assets for a medium-long term. It owns approximately 20 central business district and metro office properties. Its office portfolio includes 1 Charles Street, 75 Dorcas Street, 333 Ann Street, 10-12 Mort Street, 255 London Circuit, 89 Cambridge Park Drive and 7 Laffer Drive. Its tenants include government, resources, infrastructure and construction, information technology, media and telecommunications, education and health. Its industrial portfolio includes 70 Distribution Street, 20 Colquhoun Road, 120 Northcorp Boulevard, 599 Main North Road, 28 Bilston Drive, 9-11 Drake Boulevard, 130 Sharps Road and 1-3 Pope Court. Its tenants include retail, logistics, manufacturing, and other consumer and business services.

Genetic Technologies Limited is a molecular diagnostics company. The Company is engaged in the provision of molecular risk assessment for cancer. The Company offers predictive testing and assessment tools for physicians to manage women's health. The Company's lead product, BREVAGenplus, is a clinically validated risk assessment test for non-hereditary breast cancer. The Company markets BREVAGenplus to healthcare professionals in breast healthcare and imaging centers, as well as to obstetricians/gynecologists (OBGYNs) and breast cancer risk assessment specialists, such as breast surgeons. The Company operates in Australia, the United States and Switzerland. The Company's subsidiaries include Genetic Technologies Corporation Pty. Ltd. and Phenogen Sciences Inc. Genetic Technologies Corporation Pty. Ltd. is engaged in genetic testing. The Company has launched the BREVAGen test across the United States through Phenogen Sciences Inc.

Grange Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in production of magnetite. The Company is involved in the mining, processing and sale of iron ore, and the ongoing exploration, evaluation and development of mineral resources particularly, the Southdown Magnetite and associated Pellet Plant Projects. It operates through the exploration, evaluation and development of mineral resources and iron ore mining operations segment. The Company produces iron ore products from its Savage River and Port Latta operations in Tasmania. The Savage River mine and concentrator plant are located approximately 100 kilometers south west from Burni. The pelletizing plant and dedicated port facilities at Port Latta are located approximately 70 kilometers north west of Burnie. In addition, the Company is involved in the development of an iron ore project, Southdown Magnetite Project, located approximately 90 kilometers northeast of Albany on the South coast of Western Australia.

Hot Chili Limited is an Australia-based company that acquires and develops copper multi-commodity projects within Chile. The Company is principally engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's geographical regions include Australia and Chile. The Company's project include Productora copper project. The Productora copper project is located 15 kilometers south of the town of Vallenar, at low altitude, in Chile's Region III. The Company is focused on achieving growth and development at its Productora copper project, and in expanding the Company's project portfolio to ensure future copper production hub.

GetSwift Limited is a logistics management software company. The Company provides a cloud-based software-as-as-service (SaaS) platform that streamlines delivery and logistic channels for businesses. The Company's delivery tracking software platform optimizes routes for businesses to deliver their products to end customers automates the delivery dispatch process. It provides real-time tracking and alerts to both the sender and the receiver via mobile devices. The Company's algorithm chooses the appropriate driver based on the location, mode of transport and distance to drop-off. It increases customer loyalty. It monitors the driver's service and performance. It monitors the customer feedback in real-time. It allows clients to place new delivery bookings via their own white labelled booking form. It captures photos, delivery notes and digital signature as proof of delivery on the driver application.

Gazal Corporation Limited is engaged in the design, manufacture, importation, wholesale and retail of branded apparel and accessories. The Company operates through Wholesale Group segment, which operates as an apparel supplier of corporate uniforms and workwear sold under the Bisley brand. The Company is engaged in supplying apparel, such as casualwear, men's business shirts, and intimate apparel sold under various brand names. The Company's outwear brands include Van Heusen, Calvin Klein, pierre cardin, Bisley and Bracks. Its intimates' brands include Nancy Ganz, hold me tight, Tommy Hilfiger and Spanx. The PVH Brands Australia joint venture has a mix of wholesale and retail activities across various brands. Its subsidiaries include Gazal Apparel Pty Limited, Gazal Clothing Company Pty Limited, Manline Clothing Company Pty Limited, M. Graphics Pty Limited, Coronet Corporate Pty Limited, E-Commerce Apparel Pty Limited, Gazal (NZ) Limited and Gazal Hong Kong Limited.

Hunter Hall International Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in investment management business. The Company's segments include Investment management business and Investing activities. Its subsidiary, Hunter Hall Investment Management Limited (HHIML) manages five retail equity funds (Hunter Hall Equity Trusts): the Hunter Hall Value Growth Trust (VGT), the Hunter Hall Australian Value Trust (AVT), the Hunter Hall Global Equities Trust (GET), the Hunter Hall Global Deep Green Trust (GDG) and the Hunter Hall High Conviction Equities Trust (HCT), and a wholesale equity fund, the Hunter Hall Australian Equities Fund (AEF). HHIML is also the investment manager for the Hunter Hall Global Value Limited (HHV). Its subsidiary, Hunter Hall International (UK) Limited, provides international investment research to the Company and its controlled entities. It provides investment advisory, managing and dealing services.

Gowing Bros. Limited is an Australia-based investment company, which is engaged in wealth management and investment. The Company maintains and manages a diversified portfolio of assets, including long-term equity and similar securities, investment properties, managed private equity, property development projects and cash. The Company's segments include cash and fixed interest, equities, private equities, investment properties, development properties and others. The Company's investment objective is to focus on preserving and growing the value of its underlying financial and real assets, and to grow net income from ordinary activities as the principal source of income to pay ordinary dividends.

Hills Limited is focused on delivering technology products and service solutions. The Company has four segments, which include Hills Building Technologies, Hills Health Solutions, Home and Corporate. The Hills Building Technologies segment is a distributor of electronic security systems, closed circuit television systems, home and commercial automation and control systems, audio products, consumer electronic equipment, communications related products and services, domestic and commercial antennas, master antenna television systems, communications antennas and amplifiers. The Hills Health Solutions segment consist of the supply and installation of health technology solutions, Nursecall and patient entertainment systems to hospitals, aged care facilities and similar institutions. The Home segment consists of the Hills Home Living business. Its products include integrated access, card access, intruder alert, cameras, home hub, locks and analytics software.

GTI Resources Ltd is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of mineral and energy resources. The Company's projects include Henry River project, Silver King project and Mount Jackson. The Company's tenements include E08/2381, E08/2446, E08/2447 and E77/2199. The Company operates in Australia.

Helloworld Limited is a travel service provider offering retail, wholesale, corporate, inbound and tour operating businesses in Australia, New Zealand, the South Pacific and Asia. The Company is engaged in selling of international and domestic travel products and services, and the operation of a franchised network of travel agents. It operates through three segments: Retail, Wholesale and Travel Management. The Retail segment is engaged in acting as a franchisor of retail travel agency networks, including Helloworld branded Network, Helloworld Associate Network, Helloworld for Business, the My Travel Group and Mobile Travel Australia (MTA). The primary purpose of the Wholesale segment is to procure air, cruise and land product for packaging and sale through retail travel networks and other third-party retailers. The Travel Management is engaged in providing travel management services to corporate and government customers, including the booking of flights and accommodation.

Holista CollTech Limited is an Australia-based biotech company. The Company researches, develops, manufactures and markets health-style products. The Company focuses on three areas: Healthy Food Ingredients, Dietary Supplements and Collagen, including marketing PANATURA GI globally and upgrading the collagen plant in Perth to produce food-grade sheep collagen. It is primarily involved in development and commercialization of food ingredients and ovine collagen. Its products and services by segment include Supplements, Sheep collagen and Food ingredients. The Supplements segment is involved in the manufacture and wholesale distribution of dietary supplements. The Sheep collagen segment is involved in the manufacture and distribution of cosmetic grade collagen. The Food ingredients segment is involved in the manufacture and wholesale distribution of healthy food ingredients. It delivers natural ingredients and wellness products, and leads in research on herbs and food ingredients.

Global Geoscience Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in exploration for economic deposits of minerals. It has assets in the United States, Peru and Australia. The Company holds interest in various projects, such as Tokop Gold Project, which is an Intrusion Related Gold System (IRGS) located approximately 330 kilometers southeast of Reno in southern Nevada, the United States, including its interest covering an area of approximately 4.82 square kilometers. The Company's Lone Mt gold-silver-base metal project is located approximately 35 kilometers northwest of Elko and over 35 kilometers from the Carlin Trend in northern Nevada. Its Towers Mountain Porphyry Copper Project is located approximately 2 kilometers west of Crown King and over 90 kilometers north of Phoenix in Central Arizona, including its interest covering an area of approximately 2.54 square kilometers. It holds various other projects in Nevada (Bartlett and Orovada) and Arizona (New Morenci).

HUB24 Limited is a financial services company. The Company is engaged in providing investment and superannuation portfolio administration services, and licensee services. It operates the HUB24 investment and superannuation platform. Its segments include Platform, Licensee and Corporate. The Platform segment is engaged in the development and provision of investment and superannuation platform services to financial advisors, stockbrokers, accountants and their clients. The Licensee Services segment provides financial advice to clients through financial advisors. The Licensee Services segment provides compliance, software, education and business support to advisor practices enabling advisors to provide clients with financial advice over a range of products. The Corporate segment provides corporate services to other segments. Its platform offers a range of investment options for various types of investors, such as individuals, companies, trusts, associations or self-managed super funds.

Highfield Resources Limited (Highfield) is an Australia-based company engaged in mineral exploration. The Company has around four potash projects. The Company's Muga, Vipasca, Izaga, Pintanos and Sierra del Perdon potash projects are located in the Ebro potash producing basin in northern Spain covering a project area of over 550 square kilometers. The Muga project targets the shallow sylvinite beds to the south east of the project area. The Muga project is located approximately 50 kilometers to the southeast of Pamplona. The Sierra del Perdon project is located approximately 10 kilometers from Pamplona. The Vipasca project area includes the Vipasca permit, the Borneau permit and the Osquia permit. The Pintanos project covers an area of around 125 square kilometers abutting the Muga-Vipasca project. The Izaga project is located in a syncline structure abutting the northern extent of the expanded Vipasca project.

Hansen Technologies Limited is a global customer care and billing solutions provider that develops, implements and supports software, and delivers data center, application and implementation services for the energy, pay television and telecommunications industries. The Company's segments include Billing, which represents the sale of billing applications and the provision of consulting services in regard to billing systems; IT outsourcing, which represents the provision of various information technology (IT) outsourced services covering facilities management, systems and operations support, network services and business continuity support, and Other, which represents software and service provision in superannuation administration. Its geographical segments include APAC, which includes sales and services across Australia and Asia; Americas, which includes sales and services across the Americas, and EMEA, which includes sales and services across Europe, the Middle East and Africa.

Ironbark Capital Limited is an investment company. The Company is engaged in making investment and deriving revenue and investment income from listed securities and unit trusts in Australia. It operates primarily in Australia and in the securities industry, deriving revenue from dividend, distribution and interest income, and from the sale of its trading portfolio. Its investment objective is to provide a positive investment return averaging the one year swap rate plus 6% over time with an emphasis on income generation. It is focused on delivering consistent returns and a franked dividend yield from the portfolio. Its portfolio includes investments in sectors, such as banks; hybrids and corporate bonds; large industrial; materials and energy; property trusts; small industrial, and utilities and infrastructure. Its portfolio is focused on income through yield orientated securities, and buy and write positions. Kaplan Funds Management Pty Limited is its investment manager.

High Peak Royalties Limited is engaged in acquisition of royalty and exploration interests in oil and gas assets predominately in Australia and the United States. The Company has royalties on approximately 23 oil and gas projects, including two royalty areas that are in production, located in Australia and the United States. Its portfolio of royalty interests includes PL 171 and ATP 574P; ATP 299P, including the petroleum leases PL29, PL38, PL39, PL52, PL57, PL95, PL169, PL170, PL293, PL294, PL295 and PL298; Pet Gas Field (PL101); Surprise Oil Field (PL6); Longtom Gas Field (VIC/L29 and VIC/P54); WA-314P; WA-315P; EP115NM; PEL512; WA-482-P; EP156, and East Texas, Permian and Texas Gulf Coast Basins in the United States. Its royalty portfolio has access to projects in main oil and gas basins in Australia. Its portfolio spans producing royalties, potential development royalties and exploration royalties.

Heemskirk Consolidated Limited is engaged in the development of the Moberly Frac Sand Project and resource equity investments. The principal activities of the Company are mining, development and processing of industrial minerals and resource equity investments. The Company's segments include Canada, Portfolio and Corporate. The Company's Canada segment covers operations owned by the Company concerned with the mining and processing of industrial mineral products, including the development of the Moberly Frac Sand Project. The Portfolio segment covers the investment in listed and unlisted resource equities. The Moberly plant is located on the Trans-Canada Highway near Golden, British Columbia.
