The Company also offers various insurance products, such as home and contents insurance, Prestige insurance, motor vehicle insurance and landlord insurance. The Company offers fixed and variable rates across its product suite. The Company's products offer a range of features, such as redraw, offset accounts and early repayment facilities.

Indiana Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in exploration for minerals. The Company's activities are focused on its tenement package located in southeast Tanzania. The tenement package lies in the Mozambique Belt, which is prospective for nickel, gold, copper and graphite mineralization. Its projects include the Kishugu and Naujombo Gold targets and the Ntaka Hill Nickel Project. The Kishugu Gold target, a gold-in-soil anomaly, covers six kilometers by 600 meters, with approximately 900 pounds per barrel (ppb) assessment unit (Au), and the Naujombo Gold Target measures greater than 9.5 kilometers by 600 meters with values of approximately 810 ppb Au. The Naujombo Gold Target is located over 30 kilometers northeast of the Kishugu Gold Target. The two gold targets exhibit multi-element anomalism including arsenic, bismuth and silver. The Ntaka Hill Nickel Project comprises two tenements, is located in the north-eastern area of the Nachingwea Property.

Gage Roads Brewing Co Limited is engaged in brewing, packaging, marketing and selling craft brewed beer, cider and other beverages. The Company operates through two segments: proprietary brand brewing and contract brewing. The Company offers a range of ales and lagers, which are crafted in Western Australia. The Company offers dry-hopped and unfiltered beers. The Company's beers include Little Dove, which is a new world-style pale ale; Sleeping Giant, which is an India pale ale; Single Fin, which is a summer ale; Narrow Neck, which is an American-style pale ale; Break Water, which is an Australian-style pale ale; Atomic, which is an American-style pale ale; Small Batch Lager, which is a European lager, and Premium Mid Pils, which is a Czech Pilsener.

GME Resources Limited is a nickel exploration company. The Company is engaged in the mineral exploration and mining of gold. The Company owns a range of gold projects in the Leonora-Laverton region. The Company's projects include NiWest Nickel Laterite Project and Devon Gold Mine. The Company's Murrin Murrin Project is located within the northeastern Goldfields of Western Australia. The project includes approximately 20 contiguous tenements covering over 50.3 square kilometers. The NiWest Nickel Laterite Project located at Murrin Murrin. The project land holding is in excess 500 square kilometers hosting laterized ultramafic structures. The project contains a nickel resource. It has total metal content of over 1,000,000 tons of nickel. The Company focuses on pursuing other opportunities within the northeastern Goldfields of Western Australia.

GWA Group Limited is engaged in the research, design, manufacture, import and marketing of building fixtures and fittings to residential and commercial premises, and the distribution of these various products through a range of distribution channels in Australia, New Zealand and selected international markets. The Company's segments include Bathrooms & Kitchens, and Door & Access Systems. The Bathrooms & Kitchens segment includes the sale of vitreous china toilet suites, basins, plastic cisterns, tapware, baths, kitchen sinks, laundry tubs and bathroom accessories. The Door & Access Systems segment includes the sale of door locks and levers, and supply and maintenance of commercial door systems. It owns a range of brands, including Caroma, Dorf, Fowler, Stylus, Clark, Austral Lock, Gainsborough and API Locksmiths, and is a distributor of other brands, including Cristina tapware. Its subsidiaries include API Services and Solutions Pty Limited and Caroma Holdings Limited.

Haoma Mining NL is engaged in mineral exploration, and research and development within its areas of interest in the Pilbara district of Western Australia and in the Ravenswood district in North Queensland. The principal activity of the Company is gold mining, including the exploration and evaluation of its areas of interest in relation to discovery of gold and other precious metals. The Company's research and development activities at the Bamboo Creek Pilot Plant conducted in conjunction with The University of Melbourne are focused on developing processes for the assaying and extraction of gold and other precious metals when processing Bamboo Creek Tailings concentrate and mineral ores from various Pilbara locations including Mt Webber. All the Company's exploration and evaluation assets are held in Australia.

iCollege Limited is an Australia-based training company. The Company's principal business activity is a vocational training focused mainly on three areas: Allied Health and Community Services, Sports and Fitness, and General Services training. The Company's segments include Financing, Research and Development, and Education Services. The Company's Financing segment includes capital raisings, which is used to provide funding for acquisitions and working capital. The Company's Research and Development segment includes iCollege Holdings Pty Ltd, which conducts all activities in relation to development of the iCollege education platform. The Company's Education Services segment includes education services businesses. The Company offers learning management system that offers a range of accredited and non-accredited courses and units. The Company's subsidiaries include Bookkeeping School Pty Ltd, Mathisi Pty Ltd and Management Institute of Australia Pty Ltd.

iBosses Corporation Limited is an entrepreneurship training and consultancy provider. The Company focuses on offering advice, support and solutions to entrepreneurs and start-ups. The Company supports entrepreneurship and assists entrepreneurs from early-stage of idea creation, through to the final stages of commercialization and exits. The Company's services include Entrepreneur Training, Entrepreneurship Mentorship, Entrepreneurship Licensing and an Entrepreneurship Digital Platform. The Company's e-system on cloud is a digital platform that displays start-ups from all over the world to investors, customers and other entrepreneurs. The Company employs the eight-level entrepreneurship acceleration process, including passion, ideation, validation, implementation, commercialization, replication, fruition and actualization, to mentor entrepreneurs whose businesses focus on regional markets. The Company's subsidiaries include iBosses Pte Ltd and iBosses International Investment Limited.

Gold Road Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration and development in Western Australia. The Company is involved in the development of the Yamarna greenstone Belt, which is located approximately 150 kilometers east of Laverton in Western Australia. It holds interests in tenements, covering approximately 5,000 square kilometers in the Yamarna greenstone Belt. Its tenements contain a gold resource of approximately 6.6 million ounces, including approximately 6.2 million ounces at the Gruyere deposit. Its projects include the Gruyere project, Yamarna Belt-Central Bore Trend, Yamarna Belt-Attila Trend and Gold Road. Gruyere project has width that ranges from 7 meters (m) to 190 m with an average width of 90 m. The Gruyere project's mineral resource amounts to approximately 96.93 million tons at approximately 1.23 gram per ton (g/t), and is based on a total of over 38,000 m of drilling, which includes approximately 11,600 m of diamond and over 26,400 m of Reverse Circulation.

Intrepid Mines Limited is an Australia-based minerals exploration and mining company. The Company's principal activity is exploration and development of base metals with a focus on assets held in Zambia. Its principal exploration project is in Zambia, where the Company is exploring and developing various mineralized zones. The Company's Mumbwa Project is located in west-central Zambia, approximately 200 kilometers west of Lusaka. The Mumbwa Project includes over five contiguous prospecting licenses with a total area of approximately 1,000 square kilometers, including the Mumbwa license (8589-HQ-LPL) that hosts its Kitumba Copper Project. The Mumbwa Project lies within the southern end of a fold and thrust belt, Lufilian Arc, which also hosts the Zambian copper belt deposits. Its assets in Zambia target copper and gold. Its other Mumbwa targets include Kakozhi and Tasmania targets. It focuses on advancing the Kitumba Copper Project and exploration on its Mumbwa Project tenements.

Hunter Hall Global Value Limited is listed investment company (LIC). The Company's investment objective is to generate positive absolute returns in excess of the investment portfolio's benchmark over an investment horizon of approximately five years. The Company operates through investment in securities segment. The Company's portfolio is invested in equities. The Company invests in a range of sectors, such as consumer staples, financials, healthcare, industrials, information technology, materials, telecom services and consumer discretionary. The Company operates through various countries, such as Italy, Brazil, Australia, Japan, South Korea, the United Kingdom and the United States. The Company gives investors easy access to a portfolio of global equities, including a strategic allocation to Australian equities. The Company's investment manager is Hunter Hall Investment Management Limited.
Goldsearch Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the business of analysis of prospective investments in the healthcare industry. The Company was a mineral exploration company.

Hannans Ltd, formerly Hannans Reward Limited, is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of minerals in Sweden and Australia. The Company has a portfolio of greenfields exploration projects in the Yilgarn and Pilbara regions of Western Australia. The Company's projects include Pahtohavare Copper-Gold Project, Lapland Project, Queen Victorias Rock Project, Rakkuri (Iron) Project, Lannavaara Iron Project and The Forrestania project. The Company's Forrestania project is located over 120 kilometer (km) to the south of Southern Cross and approximately 80 km east of Hyden in Western Australia. The Forrestania project area is prospective for gold mineralization with various one million-ounce gold deposits existing proximal to the project area. Its subsidiaries include HR Subsidiary Pyt Ltd, HR Forrestania Pyt Ltd, HR Equities Pyt Ltd, Corporate Board Services Pyt Ltd, Critical Metals Ltd and Scandinavian Resources AB.

Harris Technology Group Limited, formerly Shoply Limited, is engaged in the business of online retailing. The Company is engaged in online e-commerce destination in Australia. The Company owns online shopping destinations, such as YourHomeDepot.com.au, ht.com.au, WowBaby.com.au and Anyware.com.au. Your Home Depot offers dining and kitchenware brands to retail customers. Anyware is an importer and distributor of computer accessories to information technology retailers. WowBaby is an Australian online retailer engaged in offering Australian families a range of baby and mother care products. The Company's subsidiaries include AdEffective Business Networks Pty Ltd and AER Group Pty Ltd.

Heron Resources Limited is engaged in the base and precious metal mineral exploration and development in Australia through sole funded and joint venture activities. The Company's segments include Woodlawn, which consists of tenements related to the Woodlawn Underground Project (WUP), Woodlawn Retreatment Project (WRP) and Woodlawn Exploration Project (WEP); Lewis Ponds, which includes tenements relating to the Lewis Ponds Project; KNP, which includes tenements related to the Kalgoorlie Nickel Project Exploration, and Corporate, which includes corporate activity. It focuses on the development of the Woodlawn Project, which is located approximately 250 kilometers southwest of Sydney in New South Wales. The Kalgoorlie Nickel Project is located north of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia, and holds a range of other base metal and copper-gold exploration properties located in the Lachlan Fold Belt of New South Wales. Its mineral properties are at the exploration and pre-development stage.

Hudson Investment Group Limited (HGL) is an industrial and commercial property company. The Company is engaged in the principal activities of investment and development of properties in Australia. HGL operates through three segments: Property investment & development, engaged in the development and administration of industrial property in eastern Australia; Investment services, involved in equity investment in listed entities and providing corporate finance services, and Exploration and processing of minerals, engaged in the processing and distribution of attapulgite, which is an industrial clay material used in the domestic and industrial absorbent, industrial oil refining, agricultural and horticultural industries. In addition, it is involved in the exploration and development of coal mining leases. Its Warnervale property is an over 44.5-hectare site consisting of factory and office complex occupying over five hectares of land adjacent Sparks/Mountain Roads Warnervale.

Hillgrove Resources Limited is an Australia-based mining company. The Company is focused on copper production from the Kanmantoo Copper Mine in South Australia. The Kanmantoo Copper Mine is located approximately 50 kilometers from Adelaide in South Australia. The Company also has Indonesian projects, including Bird's Head Project, which is located in north-western West Papua in the Indonesian province of Papua Barat, and the Sumba Project, a gold prospect located on the island of Sumba, west of Timor.

Innate Immunotherapeutics Limited is engaged in research and development of its lead drug candidate (MIS416) to treat secondary progressive multiple sclerosis (SPMS). The Company's segments include Australia and New Zealand. It has designed and manufactured an immunomodulator micro particle technology. Its drug candidate, MIS416, is a construct of the micro particle and naturally occurring, non-immunogenic, cytosolically active Toll-like receptors 9 (TLR-9) and Nucleotide-binding oligomerization domain-containing protein 2 (NOD-2) ligands. MIS416 has specific immunomodulatory effects on dendritic cell, monocyte and macrophage, Natural Killer (NK) and Natural killer T (NKT) cell cytokine secretion patterns, in parallel with enhancement of a range of soluble and cellular tumouricidal mechanisms, such as granule, Fas, tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF-a) and TNF related apoptosis-inducing ligand (TRAIL). MIS416 is in Phase IIB study focused on the treatment of multiple sclerosis.

IDT Australia Limited is engaged in the supply of products and provision of research and development and other technical services for the pharmaceutical and allied industries. The Company's segments include CMAX, Boronia and Corporate/Unallocated. Its CMAX is a clinical trial facility in Adelaide, South Australia. It has an integrated manufacturing, development and corporate facility at Boronia, Victoria. The Company specializes in manufacture of active pharmaceutical ingredients (API) and finished dose products, including beta lactams; microbiological and analytical testing; clinical packaging, and Phase I and first time in man clinical trials research and pharmacy services. Its IDT Pharma specializes in the development, scale-up and current goods manufacturing practices (cGMP) clinical and commercial manufacture of cytotoxic API and finished drug product. The Company also offers a range of clinical trial labelling, packaging and dispensing services.

Greenland Minerals and Energy Limited (GMEL) is an Australia-based company engaged in mineral exploration and project evaluation. The Company's projects include Northern Ilimaussaq Specialty Metal; Kvanefjeld-REEs, uranium, zinc; Sorensen; Zone 3, and Steenstrupfjeld. The Northern Ilimaussaq Specialty Metal project consists of resources, such as rare earth elements and resources of uranium and zinc. The Kvanefjeld-REEs, uranium, zinc project is located at the northwest corner of the Ilimaussaq complex. The Sorensen project consists of lujavrite. The Zone 3 project is located along the northeastern margin of the Ilimaussaq Complex and features outcropping lujavrite. Steenstrupfjeld project consists of lujavrite. Steenstrupfjeld occurs at the top of the Narsaq valley, to the immediate east of Kvanefjeld. The Kvanefjeld Project exploration license (EL) 2010/02 is held by the Company's subsidiary, Greenland Minerals and Energy (Trading) A/S.

ICS Global Limited is an investment holding company, which is engaged in the provision of medical billing services, specifically in the United Kingdom. The Company's primary operating business is Medical Billing and Collections (MBC), which is owned and managed by it. The Company provides billing services to the United Kingdom medical consultants and specialists. The MBC service is tailored for both the individual consultant and group practices and is based on its software. MBC caters to all consultants, including those just starting out in private practice, the independent consultants of varying sizes and any specialties, and group practices with multiple providers and clinics. The Company is seeking new investment opportunities. The Company's subsidiaries include Thelma Pty Ltd and Thelma-EU Limited.

Hammer Metals Limited is engaged in the exploration and extraction of mineral resources. The Company is focused on the discovery and production of metals. It is focused on the discovery of copper-gold deposits. The Company's segments include Gold exploration, Iron ore exploration, Base Metals exploration and Copper-Gold exploration. The Company operates primarily in the exploration and evaluation phase. Its projects include Mount Isa Region Projects and Mount Morgan Region Projects. The Company holds 2,600 square kilometers tenement position in the center of the Mount Isa Inlier in North West (NW) Queensland. It holds interest in over five Mining Leases that cover the Millennium cobalt-copper-gold prospect located over 16 kilometers to the northwest of the Rocklands copper-cobalt mine near Cloncurry. Mount Morgan Region Projects include the Golden Peaks Project, which is situated in coastal central Queensland near the gold and copper mine of Mount Morgan.

Intra Energy Corporation Limited is a mining and energy company. The Company is principally engaged in coal exploration, production and power generation in Eastern Africa. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and Africa. The Company holds interest in the Tancoal Mine, which is a coal mine in Tanzania. The Company's coal-fired energy projects include Project Pamodzi and Project Ngaka. The Project Pamodzi is a 120 megawatt power project. The Project Ngaka is a 270 megawatt coal-fired power mine moth project located near the Tancoal Mine in Tanzania. The Company holds interest in Tancoal Energy Limited, which is engaged in mining and supply of coal to domestic and regional industrial customers in Tanzania, Kenya, Uganda, Zambia and Malawi. The Company's mining tenements tenements include ML439/2011, PL7391/2011, PL7620/2012, PL7713/2012, PL5756/2009, PL5903/2009, ML0143/2005, EPL 377/2013, EPL0392/2013 and EPL376/2013.

HotCopper Holdings Limited is a stock trading and investment Internet discussion forum. The Company provides a FREE forum for investors to comment on a range of topics, including listed companies and initial public offerings (IPOs); stocks to buy and sell; share market trading; futures, derivatives, managed funds and foreign currency trading; Australian Securities Exchange (ASX) stock markets; foreign stock markets, and politics, sport, betting. The Company's user and membership base comprises a range of investors, including Australian retail investors and self-managed superannuation funds. It is also used by Australian listed companies as an investor relations tool and to monitor investor perception. The Company derives its revenue through advertising, which is divided into two streams of customers, including commercial advertisers and corporate advertisers.

iCar Asia Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the development and operation of Internet-based automotive portals, and the advertising, publication and distribution of automotive magazines in South East Asia. The Company operates in the advertising segment. The Company has operations in Malaysia, Thailand and Indonesia. The Company's classified sites include carlist.my, one2Car.com and mobil123.com. The Company's combined audience for its sites includes approximately 5,123,000. The Company also offers a Response Management System (RMS). Carlist.my and mobil123.com offers mobile applications for both iPhone Operating System (iOS) and Android. The Company's subsidiaries include iCar Asia Pte Ltd, Netyield Sdn Bhd, iCar Asia Sdn Bhd, PT Mobil Satu Asia, iCar Asia (Thailand) Limited, DQBP Sdn Bhd, O2C Holdings (Thailand) Co. Ltd, Perfect Scenery Ventures Limited and One2Car Co., Ltd.

Genetic Signatures Limited is a molecular diagnostics company. The Company is engaged in the research and commercialization of identifying individual genetic signature to identify diseases and disabilities, and the sale of associated products into diagnostic and research market place. It is focused on the development and commercialization of its platform technology, 3Base. The Company has a suite of polymerase chain reaction (PCR)-based products for the detection of infectious diseases under the EasyScreen brand. Its product portfolio includes EasyScreen detection kits and MethylEasy research kits. The Company's 3base technology forms the basis of its EasyScreen Pathogen Detection Kits. Its EasyScreen products provide hospital and pathology laboratories with the molecular tools to screen for an array of infectious pathogens. Its MethylEasy research kits include Methyl Easy Xceed, which is a bisulfite modification research kit for the detection of methylation patterns in genes.

HearMeOut Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in offering audio social media platform. The Company offers HearMeOut application. The HearMeOut application is a mobile application (iPhone operating system (iOS) and Android) that enables users to record approximately 42 seconds of audio, add description, category and speak, share their thoughts, and listen to others on the go, hands-free (in drive mode). The Company offers social communicating in the private cars. The drivers can listen and record posts while driving through voice control features.

International Equities Corporation Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in Property Development; Tourism, which includes Hotel Management, and Others, which include Real Estate Sales and Management. The Company's segments include Property Development, Tourism and Leasing. The Property Development and re-sale segment is responsible for identifying, costing and financing potential development opportunities, developing acquisitions and finding buyers for completed developments. The Tourism segment relates to the Company's own hotel operations and to leasing and operating a hotel cum serviced apartment for a fee. The Leasing segment relates to the operations of a licensed real estate agency, which includes sale and/or leasing of apartments for a management fee. Its properties include Uropa and Seasons Residential Apartments, Seasons Heritage Melbourne Service Apartments and Tate Penthouse Suites, Seasons of Perth hotel and Seasons Heritage Melbourne.

Icon Energy Limited is an oil and gas company. The Company is engaged in exploration, appraisal and development of oil and gas properties. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and USA. The Company has a portfolio in the Cooper/Eromanga, Surat and Gippsland Basins. Its tenements include ATP 855, which is located in the Cooper-Eromanga Basin on the eastern side of the Queensland and South Australian border; PRL's 33-49, which covers the area in the South Australian side of the Nappamerri Trough; ATP 626, which is located north of the town of Goondiwindi in the Surat Basin in Queensland; ATP 594, located near the township of Quilpie; ATP 794, which is located north west of the town of Quilpie and lies directly north of ATP 594; ATP 549 West, which is located inside the boundaries of the Cooper Basin in Queensland; PEP 170, which is located in Victoria's Gippsland Basin; PEP 172, which is located in Gippsland Basin, and PEP 173, which is located in Gippsland Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

HGL Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the importation and distribution of branded products. The Company's segments include Retail marketing segment, Homewares segment, Collectables segment, Building products segment and Health & beauty segment. The Retail marketing segment (SPOS) provides customized shelving product solutions to brand owners and retailers. The Homewares segment (Leutenegger and Nido) distributes homewares and traditional sewing and craft supplies. The Collectables segment (Biante) distributes collectable model cars. The Building product segment (JSB Lighting) distributes architectural lighting for the commercial market. The Health & beauty segment (BLC Cosmetics) distributes cosmetics and skincare products through salon, spa and retail markets. Through Mountcastle Pty Ltd, the Company manufactures and distributes uniforms, headwear and bags to public and private schools, and various clients.

iBuyNew Group Ltd, formerly Disruptive Investment Group Limited, is a technology investment company. The Company operates as an owner, developer and operator of retail, franchise and e-commerce brands. Its segments include Corporate Entity, Online Real Estate Services and Online Travel/Online Booking. The Online Real Estate Services segment includes Find Solutions Australia (FSA), which is an owner and operator of iBuyNew.com.au (iBuyNew). iBuyNew is an online, off-the-plan property platform operating in Australia's eastern states. The Travel/Online Booking Services segment includes Professional Performance Systems (PPS), which is an owner and operator of BYOjet, which is an Australian owned and operated online travel agency and technology platform encompassing various travel Websites offering travel and accommodation booking and services. BYOjet operates in the business-to-customer markets through its Australia, New Zealand and Singapore Websites.

Inca Minerals Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in conducting exploration and evaluation work on existing and newly acquired tenements. The Company is a Peruvian and Western Australian focused exploration company, which focuses on finding, developing and/or demonstrating the potential of projects to others. Its projects include the Riqueza and Cerro Rayas zinc-silver-lead (Zn-Ag-Pb) projects. The Riqueza Project is located in Peru. The Riqueza property comprises the centrally located Nueva Santa Rita concession (1,000 hectares (ha)) and approximately four surrounding new concessions, including Antacocha (1,300 ha), Rita Maria (500 ha), Uchpanga (1,000 ha) and Picuy (800 ha). The Riqueza project hosts the Humaspuco prospect. The Cerro Rayas project is located approximately 15 kilometers (km) of northeast (NE) of Riqueza. The Cerro Rayas project hosts over three groups of old mine workings, including Wari, Torrepata and Vilapuqueo.

Ikwezi Mining Limited is an Australia-based resource exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and development of coal. The Company is focused on advancing the development of coal projects in the KwaZulu Natal, Limpopo and Mpumalanga regions of South Africa. The Company holds an interest in Ntendeka Colliery, which is located in Northern KwaZulu Natal. The Ntendeka Colliery covers an area of approximately 12,182 hectares. The Company's coal wash plant has a monthly design capacity of over 170,000 tons run of mine (ROM) per month, expandable to approximately 340,000 tons ROM with the addition of a second module. It contains primary and secondary crushers, which are designed to process approximately 400,000 tons ROM per month. Its subsidiaries include Naledi Holding Ltd, Naledi Investments Ltd, Ikwezi Mining Services Pty Ltd and Ikwezi Mining (Pty) Ltd.

HFA Holdings Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in the provision of investment management products and services to investors globally via Lighthouse Investment Partners, LLC (Lighthouse). The Company has one segment, being the United States-based Lighthouse Group, which operates as a global absolute return funds manager for the United States and Cayman Island-based investment vehicles. Lighthouse is an investment manager dedicated to managing multi-manager hedge funds for diversification and absolute return. Lighthouse has offices in New York, Chicago, Palm Beach Gardens, London and Hong Kong. Lighthouse has an investor base that spans North America, Europe and Asia, and includes high net worth individuals, family offices, endowments, foundations, trusts, investment banks, benefit plans, pension funds, healthcare and insurance companies.

Insurance Australia Group Limited is engaged in the underwriting of general insurance and related corporate services and investing activities. The Company's segments include Consumer division (Australia), which provides general insurance products to individuals and families throughout Australia; Business division (Australia), which provides commercial insurance to businesses of all sizes throughout Australia under CGU, WFI and Swann Insurance brands; New Zealand, which provides general insurance business underwritten in New Zealand; Asia, which provides direct and intermediated insurance business underwritten through subsidiaries in Thailand, Vietnam and Indonesia, and Corporate and other, which comprises other activities, including corporate services, capital management activity and others. The consumer insurance products are sold under the brands, including NRMA Insurance, SGIO, SGIC and CGU. The Consumer division also includes travel insurance, life insurance and funeral products.
Hughes Drilling Limited is an Australia-based company. The Company is a coal production and delineation drilling specialist with a client base consisting of Australian mine operators and owners.

Intiger Group Limited, formerly Star Striker Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in investigating investment opportunities across various sectors. The Company's segments include Australia and Malawi (Africa). The Company operates an Australian software development house and offshore processing platform. The Company's software platform, LiLLY is designed to digitize and automate core components of the financial planning process, including the production of automated statements of advice. In conjunction with LiLLY, the Company presents the online practice management system KLIP, which tracks performance indicators of a financial planning practice and delivers oversight and control to both licensors and financial planning practices across the nation. In addition, the Company is a provider of offshore processing solutions built for the financial planning sector. The Company's subsidiaries include Orion Exploration Pty Ltd and Eastbourne Exploration Pty Ltd.

Independence Group NL is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in non-operator gold mining from the Company's interests in the Tropicana Gold Mine, nickel mining at the Long Operation, zinc and by-product mining at the Jaguar Operations, development of the Nova Project and ongoing mineral exploration. The Company's segments include the Tropicana Operation, the Long Operation, the Jaguar Operation, the Nova Project, and New Business and Regional Exploration Activities (New Business). The Tropicana Operation represents the Company's 30% joint venture interest in the Tropicana Gold Mine. The Long Operation produces primarily nickel, together with copper, from which its revenue is derived. The Jaguar Operation primarily produces copper and zinc concentrate. The Nova Project comprises the construction and development of the Nova nickel, copper and cobalt mine, located east of Norseman in Western Australia.

Indago Energy Limited, formerly Pryme Energy Limited, is an Australia-based oil and gas company. The Company is engaged in acquiring, exploring and developing oil and gas prospects in the United States. The Company holds interest in Newkirk Project located in Kay and Noble Counties, Oklahoma. The Company holds approximately 4,050 acres located in Kay County, Oklahoma near Ponca City. Oil and gas leases held by the Company are contiguous with an additional approximately 4,940 acres held by Empire Energy Group. The Newkirk Project has approximately 100 wells, over 2,500 thousand barrels (MBBL) oil, over 15,965 million cubic feet (MMCF) natural gas and over 5,115 barrels of equivalents (MBOE) oil equivalent. Its subsidiaries include Pryme Energy LLC, Trident Minerals LLC, Pryme Royalty Holdings LLC, Pryme Mineral Holdings LLC, Pryme Oil and Gas LLC, and Trimissco LLC.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Iluka Resources Limited is engaged in mineral sands exploration, project development, operations and marketing. It is the producer of zircon and titanium dioxide products. The Company offers products of rutile and synthetic rutile. The Company's segments include Australia (AUS), United States (US) and Mining Area C (MAC). The AUS segment includes the integrated mineral sands mining and processing operations in Victoria, Western Australia and South Australia. The material is mined from various deposits in western Australia (Perth Basin), together with the Jacinth-Ambrosia deposit in south Australia (Eucla Basin) and several deposits in Victoria (Murray Basin). The US segment includes the mineral sands mining and processing operations in Virginia and rehabilitation obligations in Florida. The MAC segment includes iron ore royalty interest over certain mining tenements in Australia operated by BHP Billiton Iron Ore.

Indus Energy NL is an oil and gas exploration company. The Company is engaged in pursuing acquisition opportunities in the resource sector. The Company operates through Australia segment. The Company's subsidiaries include Nuenco LLC, Anzoil (Asia) Pte ltd, Enercal Ltd and Merric Capital Pty Ltd.

Integrated Research Limited is a provider of performance monitoring, diagnostics and management software solutions for business-critical computing environments. The Company's principal activities are the design, development, implementation and sale of systems and applications management computer software for business-critical computing, unified communication (UC) network and payment networks. Its geographical segments include the Americas, which operates from the United States with responsibility for the countries in North, Central and South America; Europe, which operates from the United Kingdom with responsibility for the countries in Europe; Asia Pacific, which operates from the Australia and Singapore with responsibility for the countries in the rest of the world, and Corporate Australia. It is focused on three markets: Infrastructure, which includes users of computing systems; Communications, which includes users of Internet Protocol telephony and UC applications, and Payments.

IM Medical Limited is an Australia-based company that uses technology to promote the health. The Company was engaged in medical research and development in advancement of human health. The Company's subsidiaries include Intelliheart Pty Ltd, IMI Zinc Exploration Pty Ltd and eHealth Imaging Pty Ltd.

Inghams Group Limited is an integrated poultry producer. The Company has two operations: poultry, which is engaged in the production and sale of chicken and turkey products across various categories, such as primary, free range, value-enhanced, further processed and ingredients, and stockfeed, which is engaged in the production of stockfeed for use by the poultry, pig, dairy and equine industries. The Company operates through two geographic segments: Australia and New Zealand. The Company's operations include approximately one quarantine facility, over 10 feedmills, approximately 74 breeder farms, over 11 hatcheries, approximately 225 predominantly contracted broiler farms, as well as over seven primary processing plants, approximately seven further processing plants, over one protein conversion plant and approximately nine distribution centers across Australia and New Zealand. The Company's brands include Ingham's and Waitoa.

Imdex Limited is a mining technology provider. The Company is engaged in providing drilling fluid products, downhole instrumentation, data solutions and geo-analytics services to exploration, development and production companies in the minerals and oil and gas sectors around the world. Its Minerals segment comprises the manufacture, sale and rental of down hole instrumentation, the manufacture and sale of drilling fluids and chemicals and related equipment and the provision of cloud-based data management solutions to the mining and mineral exploration industry. Its geographic segments are Asia Pacific, Europe, Africa/Middle East and Americas, which are engaged in the manufacture and sale/rental of products to the mining and mineral exploration industry. Its subsidiaries include Australian Mud Company Pty Ltd, Samchem Drilling Fluids & Chemicals (Pty) Ltd, Imdex International Pty Ltd, Imdex Sweden AB, Reflex Instrument AB, Reflex Instrument Asia Pacific Pty Ltd and AMC Chile S.A.

IRESS Limited is engaged in the provision of information, trading, compliance, order management, portfolio and wealth management, and enterprise lending systems and related tools. The Company operates through three segments: Financial Market Services, Wealth Management Services and Enterprise Lending. Its Financial Market Services segment provides information, trading, compliance, order management, portfolio systems and related tools to cash equity participants in Australia, New Zealand, Canada, Asia, South Africa and the United Kingdom. Its Wealth Management Services segment provides financial planning systems and related tools to wealth management professionals located in Australia and New Zealand. Its Enterprise Lending segment operates in the United Kingdom to provide enterprise mortgage origination software and associated consulting services. Its subsidiaries include IRESS (NZ) Limited, IRESS Wealth Management Pty Ltd, Apollo I Australia Pty Ltd and IRESS Asia Holdings Limited.

IOT Group Limited, formerly Ardent Resources Limited, is an Australia-based company, which develops technology and consumer products in the Internet of things industry, and delivers Internet protocol (IP) television services. The Company has developed a range of Smart Watches and a flying selfie, and is engaged in releasing and marketing these products internationally. The Company's flying selfie stick product is known as ROAM-e. The Company is also developing other products, such as holographic systems, home automation, augmented reality, virtual reality and a range of flying selfie drones. The ROAM brand focuses on a range of consumer technology products, both software and hardware. Outdoor Konnect is focused on designing and developing a range of wearable devices, accessories and outdoor products.

Imperial Pacific Limited is engaged in the management of the London City Equities Limited portfolio, the depositing of funds and sale of the MainstreamBPO Pty Limited investment. The Company's segments include Investment and Financial Services. London City Equities Limited owns interests in companies in the financial sector. Together with that indirect interest, the Company has its own interests in the same sector. The Company's subsidiaries include Imperial Pacific Asset Management Pty Limited, Imperial Pacific Fund Managers Pty Limited and Imperial Pacific Resources Pty Limited.

ikeGPS Group Limited is engaged in producing end-to-end measurement solutions targeted at customers in specific vertical industries, such as electric utilities in need to measure and model their distribution assets, such as power poles and wires. The Company's products include IKE 3, IKE 4 and Spike. Spike is a smart laser measurement solution that enables the user to measure an object by taking a photo with smartphone or tablet, and take real-time measurements, including height, width, area, length and target location. The Company offers Spike device, Spike mobile application and Spike Cloud. IKE 3 is a customizable and verifiable pole data collection solution that consists of a laser rangefinder, digital camera and compass along with global positioning system (GPS) and a mobile computer. IKE 4 is a field data collection product used for outside plant (OSP) design and new attachment permitting, and pole replacement, new construction, and post construction as-built audits.

ImpediMed Limited is an Australia-based company, which is a global provider of medical technology to measure, monitor and manage fluid status and body composition. The principal activities of the Company consist of the development, manufacture and sale of bioimpedance instruments and consumables, and the sale of electronic test and measurement devices. The Company's operating segments include Medical, and Test & Measurement. The Medical segment is a supplier of non-invasive medical devices to over two underserved markets: aiding in the subclinical assessment of individuals at risk of secondary lymphedema, and the monitoring of body composition and hydration. The medical cash-generating unit (CGU) is the core business of the Company. The Test & Measurement segment is a supplier of power precision testing and measuring equipment (T&M). The Company's geographical locations include Australia/rest of world (ROW) and North America.

Imugene Limited is an immuno-oncology focused biopharmaceutical company. The Company is engaged in the research and development of human epidermal growth factor receptor 2 positive (HER2 +ve), and gastric and breast cancer vaccines. The Company is also engaged in the research, development and commercialization of health technologies. HER-Vaxx is a cancer immunotherapy designed to treat tumors that over-express the HER-2/neu receptor, such as gastric, breast, ovarian, lung and pancreatic cancers. HER-Vaxx has completed a Phase I clinical trial with over 10 HER-2 positive patients with metastatic breast cancer. It was shown in pre-clinical studies and in one Phase 1 study to stimulate a potent polyclonal antibody response to HER-2/neu. HER-Vaxx has stimulated the production of HER-2 antibodies in early-stage cancer patients enrolled in the initial clinical trial. The Company is also developing mimotope-based immunotherapies against validated and oncology targets.

Incremental Oil and Gas Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas exploration and production (E&P) company. The Company is focused on identification, appraisal, exploitation and acquisition of natural gas and crude oil in the United States. The Company has operating oilfields located in the states of Wyoming, Colorado and California, the United States. Its projects include Silvertip Oil and Gas Field, which is located in the Bighorn Basin, Wyoming, and leases cover an area of approximately 5,500 acres; Florence Oilfield, which is located in the southern Denver Julesburg Basin; Sheep Springs Field, which is situated adjacent to the Cymric Oil Field in the San Joaquin Basin, west of Bakersfield and produces both oil and gas, and Round Mountain Oilfield, which is situated in the San Joaquin Basin north east of Bakersfield, and produces hydrocarbons from four formations: the Freeman-Jewett, Pyramid Hill, Vedder and Walker.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Intermin Resources Limited is an exploration and development company, which is focused on Australian resource projects. It has interests in approximately seven separate gold projects located in Western Australia. It operates gold projects in the Kalgoorlie Region, and it has entered in earn-in joint ventures at the Binduli North gold project and the Nanadie Well copper-nickel project. Its Binduli North project also comprises the Teal gold mine development project. It has interest in the Richmond oil shale, vanadium and molybdenum project located in Queensland. Its gold acquisitions to expand the Kalgoorlie area portfolio include the Goongarrie, Windanya, Blister Dam and Bullabulling projects. The Menzies Gold Project is located over 130 kilometers north of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia, on the Kalgoorlie-Leonora Highway. The Lehmans Gold joint venture is located over 40 kilometers south of Leinster in Western Australia. The Nanadie Well Project covers an area of 145 square kilometers.

Ingenia Communities Group owns, manages and develops a portfolio of retirement and lifestyle communities across Australia. The Company invests in rental properties located in Australia with three segments: Ingenia Garden Villages, Ingenia Settlers and Ingenia Lifestyle & Holidays. The Ingenia Garden Villages segment comprises 31 rental communities located across the eastern seaboard and Western Australia. The Ingenia Settlers segment includes eight deferred management fee communities, which are located in Queensland, New South Wales and Western Australia. The Ingenia Lifestyle & Holidays segment includes 27 lifestyle communities comprising permanent and tourism accommodation, and the development and sale of manufactured homes. Its properties include Lakeside, Ravenswood, Western Australia (WA); Meadow Springs, Mandurah, WA; Brooklyn, Brookfield, Victoria (VIC); Horsham, Horsham, VIC; Carey Park, Bunbury, WA; The Grange, Morisset, New South Wales (NSW), and Albury, Lavington, NSW.

Investa Office Fund is an externally managed real estate investment trust. The Company is an owner of investment grade office buildings. It consists of Armstrong Jones Office Fund and Prime Credit Property Trust (Trusts). The principal activity of the Trusts is to own investment grade office buildings, generating rental and other property income. These properties are either owned directly or indirectly through the ownership of interests in unlisted entities. It invests in office property and office property under redevelopment and construction. Its portfolio of properties include in geographic locations, such as New South Wales, Queensland, Australian Capital Territory, Victoria and Western Australia. Its portfolio includes in banking, finance, insurance, government, legal, car parking, energy and property sectors. It holds over 25 investments located in Central Business District (CBD) markets throughout Australia. The Company is managed by Investa Listed Funds Management Limited.

Image Resources NL is a mineral sands producer focused on the development of its Boonanarring Project in the North Perth Basin. The Company's principal activity is to develop the Boonanarring and Atlas deposits comprising part of Company's North Perth Basin Heavy Mineral Sands Project (Project) in Western Australia. All of the Company's mineral sands tenements and resources are located in Western Australia. The Company has a landholding and an expanding resource base in both the North Perth Basin in Western Australia. The Company also holds North Perth Basin High Grade Resources and North Perth Basin Large Scale Resources. The north perth basin high grade resources include Cooljarloo North, Hyperion and Helene, Gingin South, Gingin North and Red Gully. The Company's north perth basin large scale resources include Bidaminna and Cooljarloo. The Company's exploration projects include Winooka and Atlas South.

Iron Mountain Inc. is a holding company, which stores records, primarily physical records and data backup media, and provides information management services. The Company operates through five segments: North American Records and Information Management Business, North American Data Management Business, Western European Business, Other International Business and Corporate and Other Business. The Company offers records and information management services, and data management services. The Company provides storage and information management services to legal, financial, healthcare, insurance, life sciences, energy, businesses services and government organizations. Its other services include information destruction services (primarily secure shredding), document management solutions (DMS), compliant records management and consulting services, health information storage and management solutions, entertainment services, energy data services, discovery services and other ancillary services.

Intec Ltd is engaged in the treatment of industrial waste, including the manufacture and supply of chemicals for the treatment of wastewater. The Company's principal activity is its ownership in Science Developments Pty Ltd (SciDev). SciDev develops, manufactures and supplies coagulants and flocculants for wastewater treatment and sludge dewatering. Its products are categorized into three groups: Aqueous cationic coagulants, Aqueous flocculent concentrates, and Polyacrylamide powders and emulsions. It operates under DairyFlox, MaxiFlox and OptiFlox brand names. DairyFlox is used in dairy processing business and MaxiFlox is used by industry participants for the treatment of wastewater streams. The OptiFlox system and associated coagulants is designed for turbid water flowing from a thickener in a coal handling and preparation plant. Its OptiFlox System enables coal productivity and OptiFlox Skid houses all instrumentations to provide measurements of particle characteristics.

Intueri Education Group Limited is engaged in investment in private training establishments. The Company's principal activity is the provision of both physical and online private training tuition. The Company's segments are online vocational training and in-class vocational training. The online vocational training segment is operated in Australia and the in-class vocational training segment is operated in New Zealand. The Company offers a range of study options, from foundation courses through to Certificate, Diploma, Bachelor's Degree and Graduate Diploma level qualifications. It is a non-public vocational provider in New Zealand, with approximately 5,000 domestic students studying for qualifications across its New Zealand schools. The Company's subsidiaries include Elite Education Holdings Limited, D&A Education Holdings Limited, Commercial Diver Training Limited, and Design and Arts College of New Zealand Limited.

iQ3Corp Ltd is engaged in the provision of capital raising and corporate advisory services to listed and unlisted companies in the life science industry. The Company provides general financial product advice in respect of certain financial products; deals in a financial product by applying for, acquiring, varying or disposing of certain financial products on behalf of another person, and provides underwriting services. Its services include initial public offerings, listings, private equity, sell-side advisory, buy-side advisory and structured finance. It is also engaged in asset management. iQ Capital USA LLC is the subsidiary of the Company, which operates as an investment bank.

Jindalee Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company holds interests in tenements in Tasmania prospective for magnesite and in Western Australia for gold, diamonds, base metals and iron ore. The Company also holds indirect interests in uranium, gold and base metals through investee companies. The Company's projects include Aries Project, Arthur River Project and Joyners project. The Aries Project is located in the Kimberley region of Western Australia, approximately 270 kilometers east of Derby and over 230 kilometers west of the Argyle diamond mine. The Joyners project is located approximately 40 kilometers west of Wiluna in Western Australia and covers the eastern part of the Joyners Find greenstone belt. The Company's subsidiaries include Eastmin Pty Limited and Awesomous Pty Ltd.

Jupiter Energy Limited is engaged in exploration for oil and gas in Kazakhstan, and appraisal, development and production of oil and gas properties in Kazakhstan. The Company owns an exploration permit known as Block 31 in the Mangistau Basin, West Kazakhstan. Its Block 31 is approximately 120 square kilometers (km2) in size and covers an area of oil production. The Company has its operations based in the port city of Aktau, which is located approximately 80 kilometers (km) from Block 31. The Company also holds approximately eight drilling wells, which include J-51, J-52, J-58, J-59 and Well 19, among others. Its Kazakhstan property has over three oil refineries located in Pavlodar (northern region), Atyrau (western region) and Shymkent (the South) with an estimated total refining capacity standing at approximately 430,000 barrels of oil per day. Its Mangistau Sub-basin is located in western Kazakhstan bordering the Caspian Sea.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Jayex Healthcare Limited is engaged in the development and provision of healthcare industry service technologies, and the development of integrated dispensing automation systems for the pharmaceutical and healthcare sectors. The Company's segments are Australia and United Kingdom. The Company's products include Appointuit, which is a patient engagement solution; Enlighten Patient Workflow Platform, which is a software platform supported by a suite of hardware devices, such as patient self check-in, patient call, patient way find and patient survey tool; Pharmacy Delivery 2 You (p2u), which is a service that acts as an intermediary between pharmacists and patients, facilitating improved access and convenience to prescription medicines by click and collect or delivery services, and BluePoint Remote Dispensing Terminal (RDT), which is a kiosk vending system for remote processing of prescriptions and physical dispensing of pharmaceutical products.

Jervois Mining Limited is engaged in mineral exploration and evaluation, including associated metallurgical test work, and research and development activities. The Company has exploration tenements in New South Wales and Western Australia. Its assets include nickel, cobalt and scandium. The Company's tenement list includes Summervale; Syerston, New South Wales; Young, New South Wales, and Khartoum Project. The Company's Exploration License (EL) 7281, Summervale, is located approximately 25 kilometers north west of Nyngan, New South Wales, straddling the Mitchell Highway. Its EL 7805, Syerston, is situated approximately 9.4 kilometer south east of the platinum mining town of Fifield and over 160 kilometer south of its scandium resource in Nyngan. Its nickel/cobalt laterite project near Young in New South Wales contains 167 million tons at 0.72% nickel and 0.07% cobalt. Its Khartoum Project includes EPM 14797 Khartoum, EPM 15570 Khartoum North and EPM 19112 Khartoum East.

Investigator Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is focused on the opportunities for Greenfields silver-lead, copper-gold and nickel discoveries offered by the minerals frontier of the southern Gawler Craton on South Australia's northern Eyre and Yorke Peninsulas. It holds a portfolio of exploration tenements in South Australia and is focused on advancing the shallow Paris silver deposit to an indicated mineral resource. Its projects include Paris-Nankivel area for further epithermal silver and associated skarn and conceptual porphyry copper-gold targets in the mineral system; Diomedes with Archaean ultramafic and nickel intersected in the underlying basement geology near Paris; Thurlga JV containing silver, gold and copper targets on the tenement adjacent to Paris; Uno/Morgans epithermal silver copper and nickel in the basement of probable Archaean age approximately 100 kilometers east of Paris, and Maslins Project.

JV Global Limited is engaged in the manufacture, sale and utilization of steel building products; global marketing and sale of computer numerically controlled (CNC) roll forming production lines, and associated technologies transfer and joint ventures utilizing the use of and the manufacture of steel building products. The Company supplies machinery to produce a range of steel building products. The Company's operating segments include manufacture of steel framing housing (MSFH) and Corporate. The MSFH segment is engaged in the manufacturing of steel framed housing within Australia. The Corporate segment is engaged in holding of equity investments in businesses engaged in manufacturing and sale of steel building products, together with machinery leased to those businesses. The Company's product range includes steel door frames, metal decking, roofing, wall cladding, steel framed housing, structural, pallet racking, shelving and channel sections.

Jacka Resources Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas exploration company. The Company is engaged in oil and gas exploration in the Bargou Block in Tunisia, Odewayne Block in Somaliland and Ruhuhu Block in Tanzania, with Phase I development of the Aje Project in OML113 Nigeria. The Company has two segments, being oil and gas exploration in Australia and Africa. The Bargou Permit is located in the Gulf of Hammamet, offshore northern Tunisia and covers an area of approximately 4,616 square kilometers. The Ruhuhu license is located in southwest Tanzania and covers an area of approximately 10,343 square kilometers. The Aje Field is located in OML113, approximately 20 kilometers offshore western Nigeria. Its focus areas are North Africa, West African Transform Margin and East Africa rift basins. Its subsidiaries include Exmouth Energy Pty Ltd, Jacka Resources Africa Limited BVI AND Jacka Resources Tanzania Limited BVI.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

James Hardie Industries Plc is a manufacturer of fiber cement products and systems for internal and external building construction applications in the United States, Australia, New Zealand, and the Philippines. The Company's operating segments are North America and Europe Fiber Cement, and Asia Pacific Fiber Cement. The North America and Europe Fiber Cement manufactures fiber cement interior linings, exterior siding products and related accessories in the United States. The Asia Pacific Fiber Cement includes fiber cement manufactured in Australia, New Zealand and the Philippines, and sold in Australia, New Zealand, Asia, the Middle East (Israel, Saudi Arabia, Lebanon and the United Arab Emirates) and various Pacific Islands. The Company offers a range of fiber-cement building materials for both internal and external use across a range of applications, including external siding, internal walls, floors, ceilings, trim, fencing and facades.

Iron Road Limited is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of iron ore interests at its principal project, the Central Eyre Iron Project (CEIP) in South Australia. The Company's Central Eyre Iron Project is located on the Eyre Peninsula of South Australia and is a collection of three iron occurrences, which include Warramboo, Kopi and Hambidge. The Company's other project is Gawler Iron Project (GIP), which is located approximately 25 kilometers north of the standard gauge Trans-Australian Railway that connects to the Central Australia Railway at Tarcoola. The Gawler Iron Project covers approximately 3,380 square kilometers and includes over 10 areas of known iron occurrences, including the Mt Christie deposit. The Company's subsidiaries include IRD Corporate Services Pty Ltd, IRD Group Finance Pty Ltd, IRD Port Assets Midco Pty Ltd, IRD Port Assets Holdings Pty Ltd and IRD Rail Assets Holdings Pty Ltd, among others.

IPB Petroleum Limited is an oil and gas exploration company. The Company's principal activities consist of conventional hydrocarbon exploration and associated activities in relation to its approximately three exploration permits along the southern margin of the Browse Basin offshore North West Australia. The Company has an interest in approximately three petroleum exploration permits located in the Browse Basin, including WA-424-P, WA-471-P and WA-485-P. The WA-424-P permit contains over three wells, such as Gwydion-1, Caspar-1A and Pryderi-1. The WA-471-P permit lies immediately north of the WA-424-P permit, which contains the Gwydion oil discovery. The WA-485-P permit lies immediately east of the Company's WA-471-P permit, between the oil discoveries at Gwydion and Cornea to the northeast.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Integrated Media Technology Ltd, formerly China Integrated Media Corporation Limited (CIMC), is an Australia-based investment holding company. The Company is engaged in the development, sale and distribution of autostereoscopic three dimensional (3D) displays, 3D conversion equipment and software; provision of 3D consultancy services, and sale and distribution of audio products. The Company has three segments: the development, sale and distribution of autostereoscopic 3D displays; sale and distribution of audio products, and provision of consultancy services. The Company focuses on 3D (autostereoscopic) digital advertising, and the gaming and entertainment market sectors. The Company and its subsidiaries have presence in Australia, China and Hong Kong. The Company, through its subsidiary, CIMC Marketing Pty. Limited, is engaged in providing management services. Its subsidiary, China Media Limited, is engaged in the provision of advertising and media services.

Invitrocue Limited is engaged in research and experimental development on biotechnology, life and medical science. The Company offers a three dimension (3D) cell-based scaffolding technology, which mimics a human for Tropical Diseases to investigate the lifecycle of Plasmodium cynomolgi (monkey malaria) and helps in evaluating new drug targets to malaria infection using in vitro hepatocyte culture systems. It is engaged in developing non-small cell lung cancer organoids and for drug testing programs using approved drugs. It is also engaged in range of activities, including in vitro cell-based assays, patient-derived organoids, digital pathology and medical imaging, while providing access to industry networks. It also offers an in vitro screening of experimental drug compounds for anti-leishmanial activity. It intends to develop an in vitro 3D perfused liver model to expedite and facilitate new application notes in infectious liver diseases.

Impact Minerals Limited is engaged in the exploration for deposits of uranium, nickel, gold and platinum group elements. The Company operates through three segments: Australia, Africa and Turkey. The Company's project in Africa is Botswana Uranium Project, and in Australia includes the Mulga Tank Project, the Broken Hill Project, the Commonwealth Project and Clermont Project. The Botswana Uranium Project consists of over two prospecting licenses covering an area of approximately 1,390.6 square kilometers within the uranium province of central Botswana. The Mulga Tank Project covers an area of over 425 square kilometers in the emerging nickel province of southwest Western Australia. The Broken Hill Project is located approximately 20 kilometers east of the Broken Hill silver-lead-zinc mine in New South Wales. The Commonwealth Project is located approximately 95 kilometers north of Orange in New South Wales. The Clermont Project is located over 20 kilometers south east of Clermont.

Incitec Pivot Limited is engaged in the manufacture and distribution of industrial explosives, industrial chemicals and fertilizers, and the provision of related services. The Company segments include Asia Pacific, Americas and Corporate. Its Asia Pacific segment includes Incitec Pivot Fertilizers (IPF), Southern Cross International (SCI) and Dyno Nobel Asia Pacific (DNAP). IPF manufactures and distributes fertilizers in Eastern Australia. SCI manufactures ammonium phosphates and is a distributor of its manufactured fertilizer product to wholesalers in Australia and the export market. DNAP manufactures and sells industrial explosives and related products and services to the mining industry in the Asia Pacific region and Turkey. Its Americas segment includes Dyno Nobel Americas (DNA), which manufactures and sells industrial explosives and related products and services to the mining, quarrying and construction industries in the Americas (the United States, Canada, Mexico and Chile).

IMF Bentham Limited is engaged in investigation, management and funding of litigation claims. The Company's services include funding for factual investigations preliminary to litigation; appeal funding; payment of adverse costs orders; strategic planning, monitoring and managing of litigation, and assistance in facilitating settlements. It offers funding for commercial litigation, insolvency, arbitrations, lawyers, class actions and public interest. It funds single party and multi-party claims and proceedings at the appeal stage. It can provide funding for all legal and other costs associated with pursuing the arbitration, including disbursements, such as tribunal fees and expert reports. As part of the funding arrangements, the Company may cover adverse costs and security for costs orders. The Company can provide initial funding for costs associated with assessing the commercial viability and merits of a claim. The Company operates in Australia, the United Statas and Canada.

JCurve Solutions Limited offers software development and software solutions. The Company is engaged in the sale of a cloud-based business management solution focused on the small business market in Australia and New Zealand, together with associated consulting services (JCurve Business Software) and the development and marketing of telecommunications expense management solutions (JTEL and Full Circle Group). Its solutions include JCurve, which offers accounting and payroll, customer relationship management (CRM), inventory management and e-commerce, among others; Full Circle, which offers a telecom expense management (TEM) software and analytics creating insights into telco spend, and JTel, which enables to manage telecom costs and usage. Its services include enterprise resource planning (ERP) implementation and management, training, support, accounting and consulting services. It serves a range of industries, such as food and beverage, natural products and consumer electronics.

Kairos Minerals Limited, formerly Mining Projects Group Limited, is a resource exploration and investment company. The Company operates through three segments: Investments, Exploration and Corporate. The Investments segment invests in a portfolio of listed investments for short-term gains and liquidity purposes and unlisted equities for the purpose of long-term results. The Exploration segment invests in exploration activities in areas of interest in order to identify mineral deposits for exploration through sale of rights or mining activities. The Company owns interests in exploration assets and financials assets that are based in Australia. Its portfolio includes the Mt York Lithium-Gold project in the Pilbara region, the Wodgina East Lithium-Tantalum project, the Roe Hills Gold-Nickel project, the Fraser Range project, and the Dingo Range project.

IPH Limited is a holding company. The Company offers a range of intellectual property (IP) services and products to a client base of Fortune Global 500 companies, multinationals, public sector research organizations, small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and professional services firms around the world. The Company operates through the segments, including Intellectual Property Services Australia, Intellectual Property Services Asia, and Data and Analytics Software. The Company's Intellectual Property Services Australia segment is engaged in providing filing, prosecution, enforcement and management of patents, designs, trademarks and other IP in Australia. The Company's Intellectual Property Services Asia segment is engaged in providing filing, prosecution, enforcement and management of patents, designs, trademarks and other IP in Asia. The Company's Data and Analytics Software segment develops and provides IP data and analytics software under a subscription license model.

IODM Limited, formerly Paradigm Metals Limited (Paradigm), is an Australia-based cloud-based Software as a Service provider. The Company, through The Debtor Management Hub Pty Ltd, develops an automated debtor management solution that provides business accounts receivable monitoring and collection management tool through a central cloud-based platform. The Company's platform schedules and sends out reminder letters, short message service (SMS) reminders and collection letters. The Company's subsidiaries include The Innovative Online Debt Management Trust, Paradigm NSW Pty Limited, Paradigm Queensland Pty Limited and Tungsten NSW Pty Limited.

ITL Limited is engaged in manufacturing and supplying of products into the Australian and global healthcare markets. The Company's principal activities are development, manufacture, distribution and sale of medical devices, and manufacture, distribution and sale of medical procedure packs. Its segments include ITL BioMedical (BioMed), Healthcare Australia (HCA), MyHealthTest Pty Ltd (MHT), and Corporate and other. The BioMed segment designs, manufactures, markets and distributes a range of biological safety sampling devices and hospital single use devices for the global human healthcare market. The HCA segment is a healthcare company that provides medical and surgical solutions to suit the individual needs of both public and private hospitals. The HCA segment has three product areas: Customized Procedure Packs, Catheter Laboratory kits and Invasive Pressure Monitoring kits. The MHT segment is a medical biotechnology company, which provides direct to consumer pathology testing.

Kaboko Mining Limited is a high grade manganese mining and exploration company based in Perth, Western Australia. The Companys principal activity is the exploration and development of high Grade Manganese projects in Zambia. The Companys projects include Zambia projects, which include Emmanuel project, Chowa open pit project, Peco project and Kanona project; and the United States of America projects, which include Grants ridge joint venture and Kit carson and northern projects. The Company holds about 51% interest in five large scale prospecting licenses and around three small scale mining licenses in manganese mining districts in Zambia, which extends over around 2,700 square kilometers. The company carries out exploration and resource definition drilling across its large license holdings and is focused on increasing production and exports of a manganese ore from its other projects throughout Zambia.

Joyce Corporation Limited is engaged in foam manufacturing. The Company holds interests in Bedshed Franchising & Company Stores (Bedshed). The Company's segments include Franchising, Company owned stores and The operation of Retail kitchen stores. The Franchising segment includes the operation of Bedshed retail bedding franchise operations. The Company owned stores segment includes the operation of Bedshed stores. The Company holds interests in KWB Group Pty Ltd (KWB). KWB operates Kitchen Connection, a retailer of custom design kitchens and wardrobes. Bedshed is a specialist bedding and bedroom furniture retailer with stores in Western Australia, South Australia, Victoria and Queensland. Kitchen Connection offers a range of products based on various European design concepts, including glass splash backs, stone benches and appliances.

Jatenergy Limited (Jat) is an Australia-based company engaged in undertaking trading activities with China, including the development of a JAT product range specifically for China, and marketing technology with TTG Mineral Processing and Coalplus conversion. The Company's product range includes milk powder, wine, cosmetics, skin/face creams, nutraceuticals, cereals, oats, biscuits, cleaning products and organic oils.

iSignthis Ltd provides identification and payment authentication services. The Company is engaged in anti-money laundering (AML)/counter terrorist funding (CTF) know your customer (KYC) identity proofing. It provides online payment security, Internet identity, e-mandates and e-contract validation services to e-Commerce operators, and assists AML and CTF. The Company's solutions include Evidence of Identity (EOI), e-Know Your Customer (eKYC) and Strong Customer Authentication (SCA). Its Paydentity solution incorporates real time electronic verification to converge remote payment authentication and KYC identification. Its eKYC offers a range of online services, including digital banking, card issuers, loan providers, insurance, bitcoin and crypto currency exchange, financial services, and person to person remittance/money service businesses. It also has partnerships with various card schemes and payment processors, as well as direct connect to a number of acquiring institutions.

iSelect Limited operates in the online product comparison sector. The Company's principal activities include health, life and car insurance policy sales, mortgage brokerage, energy, broadband and financial referral services. Its segments include Health Insurance, Life and General Insurance, Energy and Telecommunications, and Other. The Health Insurance segment offers comparison and referral services across the private health insurance category. The Life and General Insurance segment offers comparison, purchase and referral services across a range of life insurance, car insurance and other general insurance products. The Energy and Telecommunications segment offers comparison, purchase and referral services across a range of household utilities, including electricity, gas and broadband products. The Other segment includes comparison, purchase and referral services, and offers financial service products, including home loans. Its brands include iSelect, InfoChoice and Energy Watch.

JB Hi-Fi Limited (JB Hi-Fi) is engaged in the retailing of home consumer products. The Company has two segments: Australia and New Zealand. It is involved in the sale of consumer electronics products and services, including televisions, audio equipment, computers and cameras; software, including Compact Discs (CDs), Digital Versatile Discs (DVDs), Blu-ray discs and game; whitegoods, cooking products and small appliances; telecommunication products and services; musical instruments, and digital video content. The Company also offers information technology and consulting services. The Company has approximately 60 JB Hi-Fi Home branded stores, including over four in New Zealand. The Company operates approximately 190 physical stores. The Company offers various solutions, such as corporate, government and education sales of products and services, and insurance replacements. The Company also offers JB Hi-Fi Home roll-out. The Company has approximately 40 stores with small appliances.

Iron Mountain Inc. is a holding company, which stores records, primarily physical records and data backup media, and provides information management services. The Company operates through five segments: North American Records and Information Management Business, North American Data Management Business, Western European Business, Other International Business and Corporate and Other Business. The Company offers records and information management services, and data management services. The Company provides storage and information management services to legal, financial, healthcare, insurance, life sciences, energy, businesses services and government organizations. Its other services include information destruction services (primarily secure shredding), document management solutions (DMS), compliant records management and consulting services, health information storage and management solutions, entertainment services, energy data services, discovery services and other ancillary services.

JustKapital Litigation Partners Limited is a litigation funding business offering finance to corporate and third-party plaintiffs with claims. The Company provides financing solutions for litigation. The Company's solutions include case funding, disbursement funding and adverse costs insurance. The Company finances business to business claims, breaches of fiduciary duties, breaches of continuous disclosure obligations, intellectual property rights, claims by liquidators, misleading and deceptive conduct and professional negligence. The Company litigation funding involves the financing of legal claims by third parties to meet the costs of conducting such litigation. The Company intends to use capital reserves to fund protracted litigation. The Company intends to raise sufficient funds and have access to sources of funding from co-investment litigation funds to support the case work load. It operates in Australia and New Zealand. Its subsidiary is JustKapital Financing Pty Ltd.

K2fly Limited, formerly Power Resources Limited, is an enterprise asset management technology company. The Company's technology allows an organization to manage and maintain its asset data. The Company owns various asset management and asset maintenance technologies for use in vertically-integrated asset intensive industries, including DocMan Mobility Solutions, which is a task management application; TagMan, which is an asset verification application; Handover Notes Mobility Solutions, which is an electronic information sharing application, and PropertyInspector Mobility Solutions, which is an asset inspection application. It offers its services across pharmaceuticals, hospitality and tourism, healthcare, telecommunications and energy sector, among others. It offers its services across Australia, North America and South-East Asia.

iShares Global Consumer Staples ETF (the Fund), formerly The iShares S&P Global Consumer Staples Index Fund, is an exchange-traded fund (ETF). The Fund seeks investment results that correspond to the price and yield performance of the S&P Global 1200 Consumer Staples Sector Index (the Index). The Index is a subset of the Standard & Poors Global 1200 Index. Components primarily include consumer discretionary, consumer goods and consumer staples companies. The Index includes manufacturers and distributors of food, producers of non-durable household goods, and food and drug retailing companies. The Fund will concentrate its investments (that is hold 25% or more of its total assets) in a particular industry or group of industries, which may include large-, mid- or small-capitalization companies. The Funds investment advisor is BlackRock Fund Advisors (BFA).

Keybridge Capital Limited is a financial services and fund management company. The Company is focused on a diversified portfolio of listed and unlisted investments in solar, private equity, life insurance, property and funds management assets, among others. Its segments include Direct Investment and Funds Management.
