Its Direct Investment segment includes investment in the asset classes, such as Solar, which includes loan and equity investment in a renewable energy facility; Private Equity, which includes loans to an entity investing in businesses in a range of industries; Listed Equity consisting of investments in listed equities and has exposure to various types of industries; Insurance, which is an investment in Foundation Life Holdings, which holds a non-core life insurance subsidiary of Tower Limited, and Property include loans to properties, which are exposed to residential and commercial sites located in Australia. Its Funds management segment provides fund management services.

K2 Asset Management Holdings Ltd is a holding company of K2 Asset Management Ltd and KII Pty Ltd. K2 Asset Management Ltd provides investment management services to related party unit trusts- the K2 Asian Absolute Return Fund, the K2 Australian Absolute Return Fund, the K2 Select International Absolute Return Fund, the K2 Global High Alpha Fund, the K2 Australian Small Cap Fund and the K2 Global Equities Fund. KII Pty Ltd has had no operations. It has approximately six investment funds focused on Australian, Asian and International equities markets. It specializes in equity investment across global markets. Its funds are available for institutional and retail investors and can be accessed directly or through a range of investment platforms. Its funds include K2 Asian Fund, K2 Australian Fund, K2 Select International Fund, K2 Global Alpha Fund, K2 Global Equities Fund and K2 Australian Small Cap Fund.

Kasbah Resources Limited is engaged in the evaluation of its Achmmach Tin Project in Morocco through the Small Start Option Feasibility Studies. The Company operates through mineral exploration segment. The Achmmach Tin Project is located on the western edge of the El Hajeb province in Northern Morocco. The Achmmach Tin Project consists of Permis Exploitation (PE) type of exploitation permits, including 2912 and 193172, which cover an aggregate area of approximately 30 square kilometers. The Bou El Jaj Tin Project is a tin target that is located approximately 15 kilometers from the Achmmach Tin Project. Its Bou El Jaj project consists of PE type of permits, including 213172 and 193313. Its Ezzhiliga (Zaer) project consists of Permis Recherche (PR) type of permits, including 2137996 and 2137997. Its Ment project consists of PR type of permits, including 1939809 and 1939821. Its exploration program focuses on exploration on regional targets across the Ment and Zaer Granite areas.

Isentia Group Limited is a media intelligence company. The Company is engaged in the provision of media intelligence services to public and private sector clients through media database, media release distribution, media monitoring, social media monitoring, media analysis and content marketing. The Company's segments include Australia and New Zealand (ANZ) and Asia/Rest of the World (Asia/RoW). The Company has developed and hosted a range of Software as a Service (SaaS) platforms, such as its Mediaportal that provide customers access to time critical information, as well as tools to analyze and report on media intelligence. The Company provides social media insights and monitoring, quantitative and qualitative analysis, and analysis required by customers. The Company develops content marketing strategies and digital content. The Company uses Communique, a workflow management platform to handle the production process.

Kathmandu Holdings Limited is a specialist outdoor retailer. The Company is engaged in designing, marketing and retailing of clothing and equipment for travel and adventure. The Company's segments include New Zealand, Australia and the United Kingdom. It offers a range of apparels, including waterproof jackets, down jackets, thermals, fleece jackets, shirts and pants, merino apparel and thermals, and footwear and socks. It also offers equipment, including packs, bags, sleeping bags, tents, travel accessories and camping accessories. The Company operates approximately 110 stores in Australia, over 46 stores in New Zealand and approximately four in the United Kingdom. The Company's subsidiaries include Milford Group Holdings Limited, Kathmandu Limited, Kathmandu Pty Limited and Kathmandu (U.K.) Limited.

Koon Holdings Limited is a Singapore-based investment holding company. The Company's segments include Construction, Precast, Property and Electric Power Generation. The Construction segment relates to construction projects for civil engineering and infrastructure construction works, including land reclamation, roads and bridges, shore protection, terminal and port projects. The Precast segment relates to the supply and manufacturing of precast components and reinforced concrete piles. The Property segment relates to property development activities. The Electric Power Generation segment relates to the ownership and operation of electricity power generation plants. Its main operating company is Koon Construction & Transport Co. Pte. Ltd. Its subsidiaries include Koon Construction & Transport Co. Pte Ltd, Entire Engineering Pte Ltd, Entire Construction Pte Ltd, Econ Precast Pte Ltd, Koon Properties Pte Ltd and Tesla Holdings Pty Ltd.

Kina Petroleum Limited (Kina) is an Australia-based company engaged in pursuing, acquiring and developing energy related assets in Papua New Guinea and overseas. The Company's oil and gas projects include Petroleum Prospecting License (PPL) 337, PPL 338, PPL 339, PPL 340, PPL 435, PPL 436, PPL 437, Petroleum Retention Lease (PRL) 21 and PRL 38. The Company focuses on gas development options in the PRL 21 project. The PRL 38 is located offshore Gulf of Papua, and includes Pandora A and B reef gas discoveries. PPL 337 covers an area of approximately 5,500 square kilometers, and is located on shore in the Ramu Sub-Basin of the North New Guinea Basin. PPL 338 covers an area of approximately 3,160 square kilometers, and is located onshore Gulf Province within the eastern Papuan Basin. PPL 338 consists of a southern block of approximately 30 graticular blocks appended to the Uramu PRL, and approximately three blocks in the north consisting of approximately three graticulars each.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Korvest Ltd is engaged in hot dip galvanizing; sheet metal fabrication; manufacture of cable and pipe support systems and fittings; design and assembly of access systems for mobile equipment, and sale, repair and rental of high torque tools. The Company operates through two segments: Industrial Products and Production. The Industrial Products segment includes the manufacture of electrical and cable support systems, steel fabrication and access systems. It also includes the sale, hire and repair of high torque tools. It includes the businesses trading under the EzyStrut Pte. Ltd, Power Step (Australia) Pty Ltd, Power Step (Chile) SpA and Titan Technologies (SE Asia) Pty Ltd names. The Production segment represents the Korvest Galvanising business, which provides hot dip galvanizing services. Its businesses service a range of markets, including infrastructure, commercial, utilities, mining, food processing, oil and gas, power stations, health and industrial.

India Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in copper mining mineral processing and mineral exploration. The Company operates in three segments: Project Office, Expansion Project and Exploration. The Project Office segment primarily consists of the operations at the Surda mine. The Expansion Project segment consists of shaft sinking and development work at the Surda mine through the sub-contract with Shriram EPC Limited (SEPC). The Exploration segment includes the pursuit of all exploration projects in India. The Company's portfolio projects include Surda Copper Mine, Surda Expansion Project and Aravalli Project. The Surda Copper Mine, which produces copper, is located in the East Singhbhum District of Jharkhand, India. The Aravalli Project, which produces lead-zinc, is located in the state of Rajasthan.

Kollakorn Corporation Limited is a technology company. The Company is engaged in the development, marketing and commercialization of security oriented identification, authentication and information storage technologies. Its segments include Automated Vehicle Identification (AVI), Smart&Secure, and TransitVault & CertainID. The Company is also engaged in the implementation of its tamper evident radio-frequency identification (RFID) tag technology in Thailand and throughout Asia Pacific. The RFID tag is used in electronic vehicle registration (EVR) and AVI, and provides one platform for various applications, such as vehicle registration, speed monitoring, free flow and congestion tolling, parking, fleet management, e-commerce, border security and access control. Its AVR product category includes EVR, electronic tolling, average speed monitoring, public transport journey time management, access control and parking lot management. It operates in Australia, Thailand and the United States.

Ishine International Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration of mineral prospects. The Company operates through the segment of mineral exploration. The Company's projects include Glendambo Project, Mulgaria Project, Southern Cross Project and Halls Creek Project. The Glendambo Project is located in Mulga well area, approximately 110 kilometers east of Tarcoola. The Mulgaria Project is located in Mulgaria area, approximately 80 kilometers west-southwest of Marree. The Southern Cross Project's tenements include E37/1073 and E77/1786. Tenement E37/1073 is located approximately 50 kilometers northeast of Leonora and over 70 kilometers west-northeast of Laverton. Tenement E77/1786 is located approximately 60 kilometers southwest of Southern Cross, over 30 kilometers southeast of Burracoppin and approximately 20 kilometers east of the town of Muntadgin in the West Australia Wheat Belt.

Jumbo Interactive Limited is engaged in the retail of lottery tickets through the Internet and mobile devices sold both in Australia and eligible overseas jurisdictions. The Company operates in two segments: Internet Lotteries and All other segments. The Internet Lotteries segment consists of the retail of lottery tickets sold both in Australia and eligible international jurisdictions, and Internet database management/marketing. Internet Lotteries has two segments: Internet Lotteries Australia and Internet Lotteries Germany. All other segments include operating segments of non-lottery business activities. The Australian Charity Lottery business involves the sale of a number of charity-based lotteries to the established customer base in Australia. The Australian Charity Lottery business includes over four charities and the games are integrated into the OzLotteries.com Website and application. The Company offers German lottery sales online across desktop, tablet and mobile devices.

KalNorth Gold Mines Limited is a gold exploration company. The Company is engaged in gold exploration on the Lindsays, Kalpini and Kurnalpi projects near Kalgoorlie, Western Australia. It operates in two segments: mine development and mine exploration. Its Lindsays project is located approximately 65 kilometers to the north east of Kalgoorlie. Its Kurnalpi project is located approximately 85 kilometers to the north-east of Kalgoorlie, on the north-north-west trending Norseman-Wiluna greenstone belt. Its Kalpini project is located approximately 75 kilometers north-east of Kalgoorlie, approximately halfway between the Lindsay's and Kurnalpi fields. The Lindsay'd field comprises over three north-west trending structures that run through a folded sequence of dolerite, basalt and metasediments-the Eastern Structure, the Central Structure and the Western Structure. It holds tenements, including L27/0088, E28/1477, E28/2226, M28/0076, P28/1100, P28/1101, E28/2015, P28/1106 and others.

Kangaroo Island Plantation Timbers Limited is an Australia-based company, which manages a portfolio of hardwood and softwood forestry plantations, growing on former agricultural land on Kangaroo Island, South Australia. The Company operates through forestry management segment, which primarily involves the management of timber plantations and milling operations. The Company owns approximately 8,000 hectares of productive Kangaroo Island land, approximately half of which is planted with either softwood (radiata pine) or hardwood (eucalyptus globulus and eucalyptus nitens) and over half of which is either cleared or contains native vegetation. The Company also owns Kangaroo Island's only sawmill and owns land at Smith Bay, which is suitable for the development of a log or chip export facility. The Company's subsidiaries include Cineria Pty Ltd and APR Pty Ltd.

InvoCare Limited is an international provider of funeral, cemetery, crematoria and related services. The Company's segments include Australian Operations, New Zealand Operations, Singapore Operations and Other Operations. It operates over 250 funeral locations and approximately 10 cemeteries and crematoria in various markets, including Australia, New Zealand, Singapore and the United States. Its national and regional funeral brands in Australia include White Lady Funerals, Guardian Funerals, Liberty Funerals, Simplicity Funerals and Value Funerals. It has over 10 funeral home brands in New Zealand, including Academy Funeral Services, Simplicity Funerals, Resthaven Funerals and Beth Shan Funerals, among others. Its funeral home brands in Singapore include Singapore Casket and Simplicity Casket. Its Other Operations segment includes its operations in Hong Kong and the United States. Its subsidiaries include InvoCare Australia Pty Limited and Bledisloe New Zealand Limited.

Inventis Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the manufacture and sale of commercial furniture, electronic controllers and computers. The Company operates in two segments: Furniture Division and Technology Division. Its Furniture Division is engaged in the design, manufacture and sale of a range of commercial furniture, which includes office chairs, tables, lounges and workstations. Its Technology Division designs and manufactures custom control and market ready electronic systems, mobile computing solutions and emergency vehicle control systems. Its Technology Division brands address various areas, which include electronics control solutions, wireless warning solutions and rugged computer solutions. The Company's Furniture Division brands address various areas, including ergonomic furniture, designer furniture and healthcare furniture. The Company's brands include Vibe Furniture, Pluto Health Care, SafeZone, Opentec Solutions and PNE Electronics.

Konekt Limited is a provider of organizational health and risk management solutions. The Company operates in workplace health services, consulting activities of injury prevention, injury management and consulting. It provides injury prevention solutions, such as pre-employment assessments, ergonomic assessments and training, seminars and onsite worker health check. It offers return to work injury management solutions, including return to work, same employer; return to work, new employer; single assessment services; tail claims management; injury adjustment counselling, and income protection, return to work service. It also provides workplace health and safety consulting services, including workplace health and safety system audits; workplace health and safety inspections; workplace health and safety management systems, and workplace health and safety training. In addition, it offers konektiva live, which is an incident and hazard reporting and management software tool.

Japara Healthcare Limited is an owner, operator and developer of residential aged care facilities. The Company is a private sector residential aged care operator in Australia with over 47,000 resident places and approvals for places nationally across approximately 40 facilities located in Victoria, New South Wales, Queensland, South Australia and Tasmania. In conjunction with the business of providing aged care service, the Company also operates approximately 80 Independent Living Units (ILUs) across over five retirement villages, located adjacent to its aged care facilities. The Company cares for over 4,000 residents, offering a range of living arrangements, amenities, services, meal plans, social activities and care options. It offers independent living, low and high care, Dementia and Alzheimer care, respite and extra services care. Japara Retirement Living offers range of retirement property options, including independent living units/villas and apartments.

Knosys Limited is engaged in the business of computer software development and licensing. The Company offers Knosys, which is an enterprise grade knowledge management software platform for customer service and support organizations. Its features include Indexing, Business Process, Optimization, Collaboration and Integration. Its Knowledge Query Language (KwQL) is a search function that searches for knowledge, as opposed to content. Its Business Process Wizards facilitates decision making, guiding users through complex business processes by presenting information in a tiered and manageable form. Reporting and Optimization Tools, which includes the Knosys learning engine allows knowledge delivered through its workflow tools. Its Collaboration tools enable employees to share information and identify experts, and work through the task together. Knosys structures the content ensuring that deployment of the knowledge is tailored to the specifics of what is to be done and when to do it.

K&S Corporation Limited is engaged in transport and logistics, contract management, warehousing and distribution, and fuel distribution. The Company operates through three segments: Australian Transport, Fuels and New Zealand Transport. Its Australian Transport segment is engaged in the provision of logistical services to customers within Australia. The Fuels segment is engaged in the distribution of fuel to fishing, farming and retail customers within the south east of South Australia. The New Zealand Transport segment is engaged in the provision of logistical services to customers within New Zealand. The Company, through its subsidiaries, provides road, rail and coastal sea forwarding in support of full and break bulk loads; dry and liquid bulk transportation services, and offers logistical and warehousing services. Its online services include proof of delivery (POD) and consignment search, global positioning system vehicle tracking, panorama, Web mail and agency online induction.

IVE Group Limited is a vertically integrated marketing and print communications provider. The Company's principal activities include the conceptual and creative design across print, mobile and interactive media; printing of magazines, catalogues, marketing and corporate communications materials and stationery; printing of point of sale display material and large format banners for retail applications; personalized communications, including marketing mail, publication mail, e-communications and multi-channel solutions, and outsourced communications solutions for organizations, including development of customized multi-channel management models covering creative and digital services, supply chain optimization, inventory management, warehousing and logistics. The Company serves various industry sectors in Australia, including financial services, publishing, retail, communications, property, clubs and associations, not-for-profit, utilities, manufacturing, education and government.

Kingform Health Hometextile Group Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in manufacture of home textile products, such as quilt, carpet, bed sheets and mattresses. Its products include bamboo quilt cotton jacquard fabric with bamboo filling, cotton dyeing quilt and pad, guest pillow cotton fabric with ball fiber, cotton reactivate printing bedding sets, memory pillow, microfiber quilt fabric microfiber filling polyester cotton, embroidery pillow and silk jacquard bedding sets, among others. The Company's subsidiaries include Kingform Health Hometextile Pty Ltd, HongKong KangFeng Int'l Group Ltd and Zhejiang Kangbao Household Textiles Ltd Co.

Kairiki Energy Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the evaluation of new business ventures. It is engaged in exploration and evaluation of assets. It had oil and gas exploration interests.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Kalina Power Limited, formerly Enhanced Systems Technologies Limited, is a power company. The principal activities of the Company and its subsidiaries is the deployment of the Kalina Cycle technology internationally and the management of its projects and investments. It operates through two segments: Investments and Power Business. The Investment segment provides administration support and engages in investment activities of the Company. The Power Business segment located in the United States and the United Kingdom engages in the power business of the Company. The Company is focused on the industrialization of the Kalina Cycle Technology through project ownership, and Turnkey power solutions with a focus on two separate regions, being Asia and the rest of the world. The Company provides build, own and operate (BOO) and engineering, procurement, construction (EPC) power project solutions for a range of applications in industrial energy efficiency and renewable energy.

Kip McGrath Education Centres Limited is engaged in the sale of franchises and providing services to franchisees in the education field. It is engaged in helping primary and secondary school age children all over the world to improve or extend their learning. It offers KipOnline, which enables the Company to deliver face-to-face online tutoring, anywhere, in real time. KipOnline allows user's child to connect with their tutor from any location. It offers an online assessment in Maths or English by a qualified teacher. It also offers an individual learning program based around agreed personal goals. It allows the student, teachers and teacher supervisors to have access to the lessons that are delivered to students. Scores are recorded so that student results are tracked at all times and the teacher can manage their performance. It operates in Australia and overseas, principally in the United Kingdom and New Zealand.

Kabuni Limited operates an Internet-based Software-as-a-service (SaaS) and e-commerce platform for the online home design industry. The Company operates through the development of an e-commerce platform in the home design space segment. The Company's geographic segments include Australia, USA and Canada. The Company is an omni-channel marketplace, which provides interior designers, makers of home furnishings and artists with SaaS tools. The Company was originally established as a natural resource company with the purpose of acquiring, exploring and developing mineral deposits in Australia and overseas. Its principal activities were focused on mineral exploration on its Oldham Range Project located in central Western Australia, approximately 320 kilometers northeast from Wiluna. Its mobile application has a search function (called Global Search), which improves users' ability to browse its product catalogue, and search for products, inspiration boards, designers and other users.

Kingston Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company, which focuses on lithium exploration in Western Australia and the Northern Territory. The Company operates various lithium projects, including Mt Cattlin Project, Greenbushes Project, Bynoe/Wyngate Projects and North Arunta Projects, and copper projects, including Six Mile Hill Project and Cootanarina Project. Within the Mt Cattlin Project area, the Deep Purple South Prospect lies over 10 kilometers south-west of the Mt Cattlin lithium mine. Greenbushes Project operates a hard rock lithium mine, which contains a series of mineralized pegmatites. The Bynoe/Wyngate Projects are located within Litchfield Pegmatite Belt. It holds tenements within the Alcoota Pegmatite Region and the Barrow Creek Pegmatite Field within the Arunta Region. The Six Mile Hill project comprises three exploration licenses: EL 4494, EL 5498 and EL 5591. The Cootanoorina project comprises three exploration licenses: EL 5625, EL 5487 and EL 5599.

Jameson Resources Limited is an exploration company focused on the development of its Canada-based coal projects. The Company operates through two segments: Coal exploration, which includes acquisition cost of exploration licenses and all expenses related to the tenements in Canada, and Corporate. The Company's projects include Crown Mountain Coking Coal Project (Crown Mountain) and Peace River Coal Field-Dunlevy Project (Dunlevy). Crown Mountain is located within the Elk Valley coal field in south eastern British Columbia. Crown Mountain contains approximately five coal mines producing over 22 million tons per annum of coking and thermal coal. Crown Mountain contains over two coking coal mines, including Line Creek, which is over 12 kilometers to the north, and Elkview, which is approximately eight kilometers to the southwest. Dunlevy is located in the northwest extension of the Peace River coal field district of northeast British Columbia.

Onterran Limited, formerly Nomad Building Solutions Limited, is engaged in commercial and residential construction and property development; the manufacture of modular transportable buildings, and associated project management and installation, and rental of accommodation assets. Its segments include Transportable, Construction and Rental. Transportables consists of all centralized manufacturing operations. The Construction division consists of all operations where the majority of work is in situ construction. Rental consists of assets where the primary income source is rental yield. The Company operates in Australia. The Company is the parent company of a diversified group of construction, modular manufacturing and property development management businesses operating across Australia. The Company's business units offers various services, including commercial and residential construction both insitu and modular; regional and remote specialists, and project and development management.

Invigor Group Limited is a data analytics and business intelligence company. The Company is engaged in offering solutions across business (B2B) and business to consumer (B2C) platforms for retail, brands, consumers, broadcast and media. It operates through digital solutions segment in Australia and Germany. Its products include Insights Retail, Insights Visitor, Shopping Ninja and Condat Solutions. Its Insights Retail is a cloud-based software platform that collects and analyses data, and offers critical information to retailers and brand owners. Its Insights Visitor is an analytics platform that collects, aggregates and analyses mobile device usage. Insights Visitor extracts data from wireless fidelity (Wi-Fi) hotspots. Shopping Ninja is a consumer price comparison tool. Condat Solutions include digital solutions for broadcast and media sectors. Condat is provider of media solutions to public and private broadcasters in Germany.

InvestSMART Group Limited, formerly Australasian Wealth Investments Limited, is an investment company. The Company is engaged in the provision of financial services under general advice to retail investors in the area of wealth management. It is a provider of an online portfolio management platform, which offers automated investment advice. It offers a mobile application, which enables users to construct, monitor and manage their investment assets using its portfolio management tools, stock recommendations and analysis. The application users can see how their investments are performing and view news, research, alerts and insights related to their investments. The users also receive instant notifications on stock recommendations and Australian Stock Exchange (ASX) announcements. It offers a suite of investment products, which includes the Intelligent Investor portfolios. Its subsidiaries include Intelligent Investor Holdings Pty Ltd, AWI Ventures Pty Ltd and Eureka Report Pty Ltd.

Kore Potash Limited, formerly Elemental Minerals Limited, is an advanced-stage mineral exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in the exploration for potash minerals prospect. It operates through the mineral exploration in central Africa segment. Its primary asset is Sintoukola Potash Permit, which is located in the Republic of Congo. It has over three projects at varying development-stages all within approximately 1,070 square kilometers Sintoukola Permit. Its other projects include Kola Sylvinite Project (Kola), Dougou and Yangala. Kola has proven and probable reserves of approximately 150 million tons of sylvinite ore with an average grade of over 31.7% potassium chloride (KCl). The Dougou Deposit is located approximately 10 kilometers southwest of Kola and is a carnallitite deposit with a measured and indicated potash mineral resource of over 1.1 billion tons grading 20.6% KCl. The Yangala sylvinite Prospect lies immediately west of Dougou.

Invion Limited is a clinical-stage life sciences (drug development) company. The Company is engaged in the completion of clinical development programs and targeted business development programs associated with its approximately three drug assets, such as INV102 (nadolol), INV103 (ala-Cpn10) and INV104 (zafirlukast). It focuses on the development of treatments for opportunities in chronic inflammatory and respiratory disease. INV102 (nadolol) is a beta adrenergic biased ligand targeted to treat chronic inflammatory airway diseases via the reversal of mucous metaplasia in the airway epithelium. INV104 (zafirlukast) is a leukotriene receptor antagonist (LTRA) that reduces inflammation, constriction of the airways, and the build-up of mucus in the lungs. INV103 (ala-Cpn10) is a modified, naturally occurring human protein, which has been proposed as a founding member of the Resolution Associated Molecular Pattern (RAMPs) family hypothesized to maintain and restore immune homeostasis.

King River Copper Limited (King River) is engaged in exploration and development of the tenements in the East Kimberley region of Western Australia. The Company focuses on gold-silver-copper exploration, including drilling programs. The Company focuses on the geophysical basement conductor target identified in the north of the Speewah Dome. The Company holds a portfolio of tenements covering approximately 770 square kilometers. The Company's tenements contain undeveloped titanium/vanadium in magnetite deposits with combined measured, indicated and inferred resources totaling approximately five billion tons in over three deposits, which include the Central, Red Hill and Buckman deposits. The Company's tenements are located approximately 110 kilometers southwest of Kununurra and over 100 kilometers south of the port of Wyndham in the Kimberley region of Western Australia. Speewah Mining Pty Ltd is the subsidiary of the Company.

JC International Group Limited is an Australia-based company, which provides one-stop workforce subcontracting for the People's Republic of China (PRC) construction industry. The Company focuses on candidate sourcing, systematic training, screened dispatch, site deployment, engineering management, performance evaluation and talent retention. The Company provides these services for a range of workforce levels required for a construction project. The Company's clients include head contractor companies who contract with the project owners to build the projects. The head contractor companies transfer the designed building drawings, building materials and equipment to the Company. The Company utilizes workforce to complete these projects. The Company has a training school. It sources workforce candidates through networks in China. It has operating facilities in Gushu Industrial Park, Ma'anshan City, China. The Company recruits workers from countries, such as Vietnam, Indonesia and India.

Krakatoa Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the acquisition and exploration of precious and base metal projects. The Company is focused on the exploration activities at its Dalgaranga and Mac Well projects. The Company's Dalgaranga project is located approximately 80 kilometers North West of Mount Magnet in Western Australia. The Company's Mac Well project has a land area of approximately 66.9 square kilometers. It covers the pegmatite occurrence. The Mac Well project is located approximately 10 kilometers west of the Dalgaranga project. The Company's projects also include BCS project, and Bone Bay and Laeya River project. The Company's subsidiaries include PT. Bumi Pratama and PT. Bina Citra Sawita.

King Island Scheelite Limited is focused on the exploration, development and production of tungsten deposits. The Company is engaged in the development of the King Island scheelite deposit. The Company's Dolphin Project is focused on redeveloping the original scheelite mine on King Island. The King Island Scheelite project is near the town of Grassy, on the south east coast of King Island, an island in Bass Strait. The King Island Scheelite project includes the Dolphin, Bold Head and Tailings deposits. The Company intends to construct a processing plant at the Dolphin Project with annual capacity of approximately 300,000 tons. The mill will produce approximately 3,500 tons of over 65% tungsten concentrate per annum. This product will be shipped to customers in bulka bags inside conventional shipping containers. King Island is positioned mid-way between Victoria and Tasmania. The Dolphin Project Exploration area includes South Bold Head, Bold Head Mine, South Dolphin and West Dolphin.

Kaili Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration of coal and minerals. The Company is engaged in the business of investing in the coal, energy and resources industry. The Company operates through mining sector segment in Australia. The Company's projects include Queensland Projects and Western Australia Projects. The Company's Queensland coal tenements are situated approximately 30 kilometers north of Warwick within the Darling Downs region of south Queensland. The Company's Western Australia tenements are located approximately 160 kilometers east of Derby and 100 kilometers west of Fitzroy Crossing in Western Australia. The Company's Western Australia tenements are situated at the north eastern margin of the Canning Basin within Phanerozoic marine and continental sedimentary rocks adjacent to the Proterozoic granite, gneiss and metasedimentary rocks of the King Leopold Mobile Zone.

Immuron Limited is a biopharmaceutical company. The Company focuses on the research and development of bovine-colostrum enriched with antibodies of choice for the treatment and prevention of a range of infections and immune modulated diseases. The Company has three segments: Research and Development (R&D), HyperImmune Products and Corporate. The R&D segment focuses on the Company's research and development projects performed in Australia and Israel. The Company sells and licenses its product, Travelan. The HyperImmune Products segment is engaged in its Travelan product's activities, which occur in Australia, New Zealand and Canada. The Corporate segment's activities primarily occur in Australia. It also develops products for applications, including non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH), alcoholic steatohepatitis (ASH) and clostridium difficile (C-Diff), diabetes, colitis and uropathogenic escherichia coli (UPEC). The Company also offers Protectyn, IMM 124-E-NASH and IMM 529-CDI.

Kogi Iron Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in the evaluation studies at the Agbaja Plateau exploration license (EL12124) in Kogi state, Federal Republic of Nigeria. The Agbaja iron ore project is located approximately 200 kilometers from the capital city, Abuja. The Company holds six exploration licenses covering approximately 233.6 square kilometers. The Company holds a land position of approximately 400 square kilometers covering over 20 tenements. The Agbaja Plateau hosts shallow, flat-lying channel iron deposit with an Indicated and Inferred Mineral Resource of approximately 592 million tons with an in-situ iron. The mineral resource covers approximately 20% of the prospective plateau area within EL12124.

Kingsrose Mining Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in production, exploration and development of its gold and silver deposits at the Way Linggo project in south Sumatra, Indonesia. The Company operates through gold and silver segment. The Company produces gold and silver dore at its Way Linggo project in Indonesia, which is refined locally in Indonesia to produce gold and silver granules. The Way Linggo project is located on the mineralized Trans-Sumatran fault, which is part of the Pacific Rim of Fire. The Company is producing from its second mine on the project area, Talang Santo. The Talang Santo is located within a cluster of epithermal veining and is situated approximately 17 kilometers from the Way Linggo processing plant. The Talang Santo mine includes Hanging Wall vein, Mawi vein and Splay vein. The Company focuses on areas, including Talang Cluster, Mitra Jaya, Way Handa, Rowo Rejo, Sindang Jaya, Petai Kayu and Talang Tebat in the Way Linggo project.

Key Petroleum Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in oil and gas exploration. The Company is engaged in acquisition of petroleum permits and the exploration of these permits with the objective of identifying economic oil and gas reserves. It is focused on pursuing conventional and unconventional wildcat exploration programs in the North Perth and Canning basins in Western Australia. The acreage within the Canning basin portfolio consists of various development and exploration opportunities. EP448 lies over the Great Sandy Desert over structural elements known as the Willara Sub-basin, Munro Arch and Anketell Shelf in the southwestern part of the Canning basin, Western Australia. The L12-10 area is adjacent to the Company's EP448 permit in the Canning Basin, Western Australia. EP104/R1/L15 is located approximately 20 kilometers northwest of Derby within the Lennard North Province in Western Australia's Canning Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Kazakhstan Potash Corporation Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activities of the Company are the identification, acquisition, exploration and development of potash resources in the Republic of Kazakhstan to supply fertilizer products to the Chinese market and the domestic Kazakhstan market. Its Zhilyanskoye Project is located in northwestern Kazakhstan approximately 10 kilometers southwest of the city of Aktobe. The Zhilyanskoye Project has a total of approximately 119.8 million metric tons of mineral resources containing sylvinite mineralization and a total of approximately 987.7 metric tons of mineral resources containing polyhalite mineralization. The Company's other assets include the Chelkar Project. The Chelkar project is located approximately 100 kilometers south of the administrative center of Uralsk in the northwestern Kazakhstan. The deposit is secured by a sub soil license covering an area of approximately 779 square kilometers.

K2 Energy Limited is engaged three activities: oil and gas activities in the United States; solar energy activities, and interest in Atomera, Inc. The Company's segments include Atomera, Inc.-Solar; Atomera, Inc. (CMOS), and Oil and Gas. It is engaged in solar technology development and holds the rights to the Mears Silicon Technology (MST) for all solar energy applications. The MST technology addresses limiting factors for photovoltaic (PV) technology and solar power generation. The Company also holds interest in Trey Resources I, LLC (Trey Resources), which is an oil and gas producer based in Texas, the United States. The MST technology involves the production of an altered or nano-doped layer of silicon that can be inserted into the manufacture of silicon solar PV wafers. Trey Resources has operation on approximately 19,000 net acres, in Texas and Oklahoma. Trey Resources is seeking approval for water disposal wells, to enable the horizontal wells to produce optimally.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Kibaran Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of its tenements in graphite-focused mineral resources in Tanzania in East Africa, including feasibility work on the Epanko Project and marketing of graphite. Its segments include Australia and Tanzania. The Epanko Graphite Project is located over 245 kilometers south-west of Morogoro in south-east Tanzania within the Mahenge District. The Company's Merelani-Arusha Graphite Project consists of seven tenements and covers approximately 468.62 square meters in an area of over 55 kilometers south-east of Arusha, Tanzania. The Merelani East Deposit occurs within a brownfields graphite province. The Merelani-Arusha Graphite Project's mineral resource estimates approximately 17.5 metric tons (Mt) at 6.5% total graphitic carbon. The Company's Tanga license covers approximately 84 square kilometers near Tanzania's east coast.

Kimberley Diamonds Limited is engaged in mining of diamonds. The Company is engaged in exploration for minerals, including diamonds, copper and copper-gold, and in the development of mineral exploration and mining tenements. It operates through two segments: diamond mining, which is engaged in the mining, processing and marketing of diamonds, and mineral exploration, which is engaged in the acquisition and exploration of minerals and mineral tenements. Its Lerala diamond mine is located in northeast Botswana and comprises a cluster of five diamondiferous kimberlite pipes totaling approximately 6.66 hectares in size, together with a processing and recovery infrastructure. Its License 267/2013 and Prospecting License 268/2013 are located approximately 55 kilometers and 75 kilometers, respectively east of the Orapa Diamond Mine. The Lomero-Poyatos gold-silver-copper-zinc project is located over 60 kilometers north of deep-water port of Huelva in Andalucia, Spain.

Karoon Gas Australia Ltd is an independent oil and gas company. The Company is engaged in investing in hydrocarbon exploration and evaluation in Australia, Brazil and Peru. Its segments are Australia, Brazil and Peru. The Australia segment includes exploration and evaluation of hydrocarbons in two offshore permit areas: WA-314-P, which is located in Browse Basin, and WA-482-P, which is located in Carnarvon Basin. The Brazil segment includes exploration and evaluation of hydrocarbons in five offshore blocks: Block S-M-1037, Block S-M-1101, Block S-M-1102, Block S-M-1165 and Block S-M-1166, which are located in Santos Basin with gross acreage of over 550 square kilometers. These blocks are located approximately 200 kilometers from the coastline of Santa Catarina. The Peru segment includes exploration and evaluation of hydrocarbons in two blocks: Block 144 (onshore), which is located in Maranon Basin, and Block Z-38 (offshore), which is located in Tumbes Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

KNeoMedia Limited is an online games publishing company. The Company is engaged in the development of edutainment (education and entertainment) games publishing business through its United States-based entity, KNeoWORLD Inc. The Company sells games on a micro-subscription and applications basis, through the KNeoWORLD.com games portal, applications stores and through distribution agreements with direct carrier billing telecommunication company providers and education departments. The KNeoWorld is a games-based learning and edutainment portal that captures the imagination of kids aged 6 to 12. The Company's product, KNeoEd, is an in-classroom version of KNeoWorld. KNeoEd includes the adventure story and games as a learning aid for kids of any level. The Company's product, KNeoESP, is a standalone games portal to entertain, challenge and build skills for kids of all learning levels and abilities. It engages kids at their level and lets them learn at their own pace.

Kingsland Global Ltd. is an investment holding company. The Company is engaged in commercial and hospitality property development in Asia. The Company is involved in the development of residential and commercial projects, including boutique hotels and serviced apartments; mixed use retail projects, such as shopping malls and financial centers; aged care facilities, and industrial parks and office spaces. The Company's project, one18 Residences, is located in Phnom Penh. The Company's subsidiaries include Kingsland Development Sdn. Bhd., Kingsland (KH) Development Co., Ltd., Kingsland (AU) Development Pty Ltd and Kingsland Venture Co., Ltd., which are engaged in property development, and Global Investment Partners Pte. Ltd., which is engaged in providing business and management consultancy services. The Company operates in Malaysia and Cambodia. The Company's immediate and ultimate holding company is Kingsland Development Pte. Ltd.

Kogan.com Limited (Kogan.com) operates a pure play online retail Website. The principal activities of the Company were the online sale of goods and services in Australia, New Zealand and various other geographies. Kogan.com offers two verticals, which include Kogan Travel and Kogan Mobile. Kogan Travel offers travel packages, and hotel and cruise bookings online. Kogan Mobile offers prepaid mobile phone plans online. The Company's offering consists of various products released under Kogan.com's in-house brands, such as Kogan and Ovela. Kogan.com offers a range of products under various categories, which include television and video; computers and tablets; phones; cameras; audio; appliances; home and garden; office supplies; baby, kids and family; gadgets, toys and video games; health and beauty; sports, outdoors and luggage; tools and automotive, and pantry. It offers products from various brands, including Kogan, Samsung, Apple, Ovela, Canon, Komodo, Sony, Certa and Fortis.

Living Cities Development Group Limited, formerly Ferrowest Limited, is an Australia-based property and infrastructure development company. The Company was focused on the development of commercial (retail and office) and high density residential space by targeting development areas in inland China. The Company has no projects.

Kidman Resources Limited explores and develops precious and base metals deposits in New South Wales (NSW), Western Australia and Northern Territory. Its other principal activities include development of its Burbanks Gold Project located in Western Australia; acquisition of the Mt Holland asset located in Western Australia, and carrying out all requirements in relation to the acquisition of the Mt Holland Project. It operates in the exploration for base metal and rare earths industry within Australia. The Mt Holland Gold & Lithium project consists of both exploration and resource drilling. The Burbanks Gold Project is situated near Coolgardie, Western Australia. The Browns Reef Project is located close to the township of Lake Cargelligo in central NSW. The Crowl Creek Project is made up of eight exploration licenses located near the township of Condobolin in Central NSW. The Esmeralda Prospect is situated 58 kilometers southeast of the productive Croydon Goldfield in North Queensland.

Kinetiko Energy Limited is a Australia-based gas explorer focused on advanced gas and coal bed methane (CBM) opportunities in developing markets in Southern Africa. The Company is the operator of the Amersfoort Project in South Africa, which is an onshore gas project in the northern part of the Main Karoo Basin. It has approximately 49% equity in over two onshore gas licenses covering over 1,600 square kilometers in the Amersfoort area. The Afro Energy tenure consists of approximately two granted exploration rights and over five exploration right applications all covering prospective areas of gas prone coals and sandstones. The Company holds over 10 prospecting gas licenses covering a total of approximately 7,090 square kilometers in the Kalahari Basin of Botswana. The Company is developing a petroleum basin model for the Kalahari Basin. The Kalahari Basin is known to contain coal deposits.

Korab Resources Limited is an Australia-based international mining and exploration company. The principal activities of the Company consist of mineral exploration and the evaluation of mineral properties. The Company holds interests in various properties, such as the Winchester magnesite project, the Sundance gold mine, the Bobrikovo gold and silver mine, Ashburton Downs, Geolsec and Batchelor. The Ashburton Downs project focuses on copper and gold and is located in the Ashburton Basin approximately 20 kilometers south of Paraburdoo. The Ashburton Downs project covers Green Elephant Complex consisting of North Mount Elephant, Green Elephant, East Elephant and Mount Elephant. The Bobrikovo gold and silver mine is located in in the Luhansk (Lugansk) Province in Eastern Ukraine. The Sundance gold mine is located near the town of Batchelor, just south of Darwin.

LogiCamms Limited provides engineering and consulting services. The Company offers its services to owners and operators of hydrocarbons, minerals, metals and infrastructure assets. The Company's Consult offerings include competency training, competency assurance, asset performance and environmental services. The Company's Deliver services include automation and control systems, process, civil and structural, mechanical and piping, project management, consulting and support services, engineering, procurement, construction (EPC)/ design and construct, and electrical and instrumentation. The Company's Maintain business offers integrated services for implementations, maintenance, completions, testing and shutdowns for its client's brownfield assets. It offers services across Australia, Papua New Guinea and New Zealand through office locations in Brisbane, Perth, Adelaide, Melbourne and New Plymouth in New Zealand, as well as regional offices in Port Moresby, Mackay and Whyalla.

Land & Homes Group Limited, formerly MOV Corporation Limited, is a property development company. The Company is engaged in the development of medium to high-density residential apartments initially focusing on the city of Brisbane. The Company is involved the acquisition of prime sites for project development into residential, commercial and mixed-use apartments. It focuses to invest in and develop property in Australia. It focuses to develop medium to high-density residential apartments in South East Queensland. The Company focuses on the Wharf Street project in Brisbane. It focuses on the model residential project with approximately 300 apartments in 207 Wharf Street, Brisbane. It is engaged in seeking additional investment opportunities in the Brisbane market and throughout Australia. Its subsidiaries include Land & Homes Investment Pty Ltd, Brisbane Land Holdings Pty Limited and BLH Wharf Pty Ltd.

U.S. Masters Holdings Limited is an investing company. The Company focuses on becoming a mineral exploration company. The Company holds interest in exploration tenements in the Lake Lefroy, Lake Johnston and Murchison areas in Western Australia. The Company focuses on gold and nickel. The Lefroy Project is located in the heart of a gold district in the Eastern Goldfields of Western Australia, approximately 20 kilometers east of the St Ives camp and over five kilometers from the Daisy Milano underground gold mine.

LionHub Group Limited, formerly Arasor International Ltd, is an Australia-based real estate development company focusing on technology park development in China. The Company has approximately two technology park projects in Anhui Province in China. The Company's projects include Xuancheng Singapore Technology Park and Lu'An Singapore Creative Ecological and Industrial Park (Lu'an Eco-Park). The Xuancheng Singapore Technology Park has an area of approximately 2.2 square kilometers and located within Xuancheng Economic and Technology Zone. The parks will include a mix of property types, including logistics, industrial, commercial, residential and accelerator/incubator space for startups. The Company's subsidiaries include Lionhub (Xuancheng) Pte Ltd, Lionhub (Lu'An) Pte Ltd and Vanda Investment Holding Pte Ltd.

Kyckr Limited is an Australia-based company providing Know Your Bank (KYB) (Know Your Customer (KYC) for businesses) services using legally compliant information. KYB decisions supported by the Company's services include on-boarding new customers, and the cleansing and remediation of existing customer books. Its clients are banks and other sectors that require protection against money laundering, terrorism financing and tax fraud.

LBT Innovations Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in developing clinical and diagnostic technologies. The Company develops technologies for the healthcare and laboratory supply markets. It is involved in research and development activities. The Company's products include MicroStreak and Automated Plate Assessment System (APAS). MicroStreak is an automated culture plate streaking technology that performs the task of streaking (spreading) a clinical sample, such as blood or a biopsy suspension, on a small plate lined with agar gel. APAS is a platform technology for the automation of culture plate screening, evaluation and sorting. MicroStreak automates the inoculation and streaking of the agar plates and APAS streamlines the next stages of the process. The Company has a third product in development called Woundvue, an automation solution to assist in the management and treatment of chronic wounds. It has operations in Australia, Switzerland and the United States.

Lifestyle Communities Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in developing and managing communities. The Company operates through property development and management of residential accommodation segment. The Company offers community homes in Brookfield, Tarneit, Warragul, Cranbourne, Shepparton, Chelsea Heights, Hastings, Wollert, Geelong, Officer, Berwick Waters and Bittern. The Company's homes include features, such as kitchen with stainless steel appliances; reverse cycle split system heating and cooling; front deck/verandah; car accommodation; landscaping to front garden, and colorbond garden shed with concrete floor. The Company provides a specific area to store trailers, boats and caravans. The Company's community homes include Glenelg, Eildon Elite Corner, Cumberland, Mitchell Elite 2, Eildon Elite, Murray, Goulburn, Goulburn, Murray Corner, Loddon Corner, Jamieson and Mitta Mitta, Fitzroy.

Living Cell Technologies Limited is a biotechnology company, which is engaged in discovering, developing and commercializing regenerative treatments, which use naturally occurring cells to restore function. The Company operates through the segment of research and development into living cell technologies, predominantly in New Zealand. Its product pipeline consists of cell therapies developed from cells sourced from a herd of disease-free pigs breed from stock originally discovered in the remote sub-Antarctic Auckland Islands. The Company's treatments are based on cell encapsulation and implantation for human therapeutics. The Company's products are NTCELL and DIABECELL. NTCELL is an alginate-coated capsule containing clusters of neonatal porcine choroid plexus cells. DIABECELL is an insulin-producing cell product derived from pigs for the treatment of type I diabetes. It completed Phase I/IIa clinical trial for NTCELL for Parkinson's disease.

Life Corporation Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in the provision of multi-religion funeral services relating to burials or cremations, including other related ancillary services and supplies. The Company has presence in Singapore. The Company, through its subsidiary, Singapore Funeral Services Care Pte Ltd, is engaged in the business of funeral and bereavement services. Its services include embalming, caskets showroom, burials, facilitating multi-religions funerals rites and ceremonial services. It is also focused on pre-planning (pre-purchase) of bereavement services to include customized funeral events; products, such as urn-containing boxes and urns, and pre-planned rites and ceremonies upon columbarium internment for its Chinese community family clientele. Its subsidiary, Life Corporation Services (S) Pte Ltd (LFC Services), is focused on the construction of an automated columbarium, which is at a land site along Tampines Road in North-Eastern Singapore.

KBL Mining Limited is an Australia-based resource company with a focus on producing precious metals. The Company's main assets include the Mineral Hill copper-gold-silver-lead-zinc mine near Condobolin in New South Wales and Sorby Hills lead-silver-zinc project in Western Australia. The Company operates a refurbished processing plant at Mineral Hill to produce copper-gold concentrates and a gold-silver concentrate and bullion. The Company also holds Sorby Hills, a large near surface undeveloped silver-lead deposit.

Kula Gold Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the development of the Woodlark Island Gold Project located on Woodlark Island in Papua New Guinea. The Woodlark Island Gold Project contains a joint ore reserves committee (JORC) reserve of approximately 766,000 ounces of gold. The Company also has a mining lease approval for the development of 1.8 million tons per annum gold mining operation on Woodlark Island.

Legacy Iron Ore Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of iron ore and gold assets. The Company's projects include Mt Bevan Iron Ore Project, South Laverton Gold Project, Mt Celia Project, East Kimberley Project, Patricia North Project, Sunrise Bore Project, Yilgnani project, Yerilla project and Koongie Park Project. The Company holds interest in the Mt Bevan Iron Ore Project. The Mt Bevan Iron Ore Project includes Mt Bevan Magnetite project. The South Laverton project area lies along the Keith Kilkenny Tectonic Zone (KKTZ) and the southern part of the Laverton Tectonic Zone (LTZ). The East Kimberley Project tenements are located in the Halls Creek area, located to the south of Kununurra. The East Kimberley project includes Koongie Park and Mt Bradley exploration licenses. The Company holds the exploration license E80/4221 at its Koongie Park volcanic-hosted massive sulfide (VHMS) base metals deposit.

KGL Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The principal activity of the Company is the exploration and development of the Jervois multi-metal project in the Northern Territory. Its segments include Jervois Project-Northern Territory, which consists of the operations of Kentor Minerals (NT) Pty Ltd; Bashkol Projects-Kyrgyz Republic, which consists of projects that are in the process of being developed or explored, and Geothermal Energy Project-Solomon Islands, which consists of the Geothermal Energy project being conducted in the Solomon Islands. The Jervois project consists of open pit mining of several deposits followed by underground mining to feed an approximately 2.2 metric tons per annum (Mtpa) flotation plant producing 80,000 to 100,000 tons per annum (tpa) of copper concentrate plus a separate lead/zinc bulk concentrate. Its subsidiaries include Jinka Minerals Ltd, Kentor Minerals (Aust) Pty Ltd, Kentor Minerals (NT) Pty Ltd and Kentor Minerals (WA) Pty Ltd.

Legend Mining Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company's principal activities include exploration for nickel and copper, deposits in Australia. The Company's segments include Australia and West Africa. The Company's exploration focus is on its nickel-copper Rockford Project, which is located in the Fraser Range, Western Australia. The Company's Rockford Project covers a total area of approximately 2,940 square kilometers. Its tenements include E28/1718, E28/1727, E28/2188, E28/2189, E28/2190, E28/2191, E28/2192 and E28/2342. The Company's Rockford Project consists of approximately eight contiguous granted exploration licenses located approximately 120 kilometers northeast of the Nova-Bollinger nickel-copper deposit. The Company's subsidiaries include Gibson Metals Pty Ltd and Legend Cameroon Pty Ltd.

Lanka Graphite Limited is an Australia-based graphite exploration company. The Company is focused on exploring and mining vein graphite in Sri Lanka. The Company holds approximately seven exploration licenses applications in south-western and central Sri Lanka covering a total of approximately 240 square kilometers. It holds over five granted licenses and approximately three license applications. The licenses comprising EL266, EL267 and EL268 are prospective for high-grade graphite. The Company has operations in Sri Lanka where its graphite tenements are located. It operates through its subsidiary, Lanka Graphite Pte Ltd, which is engaged in exploration and feasibility studies.

Lindsay Australia Limited is an integrated transport, logistics and rural supply company. The Company is engaged in the transportation of refrigerated and general freight, merchandising of rural supplies, and export and import of horticulture goods through the Lindsay Fresh Logistics facility. The Company operates through two segments: Transport and Rural. The Company's Transport segment includes cartage of general and refrigerated products and ancillary sales. Its Rural segment is engaged in the sale and distribution of a range of agricultural supply products. The Company focuses on servicing customers in the food processing, food services, fresh produce, rural and horticultural sectors. The Company caters to growers throughout their production cycle from planting crops, through fertilizers, chemicals, supply of packaging, and transportation, fumigation and export.

Kingsgate Consolidated Limited is engaged in mining and mineral exploration in Australia, South East Asia and South America. The Company's segments include operating mines and projects, such as Chatree Mine, Thailand; Nueva Esperanza Gold/Silver Project, Chile, and Exploration, South East Asia. The Company and its Thai subsidiary, Akara Resources Public Company Limited, operate the Chatree gold mine in central Thailand, approximately 280 kilometers north of Bangkok. Chatree is an open pit gold mining operation, which produces approximately 125,090 ounces of gold and over 850,000 ounces of silver. It owns interests in Nueva Esperanza project, which is located in the Maricunga gold belt of the Atacama region of northern Chile, approximately 140 kilometers north-east of the city of copiapo. It is a silver and gold project consisting of various deposits hosted in a sulfidation epithermal (hydrothermal) system and a range of undeveloped exploration targets.

Katana Capital Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company's investment objective is to achieve a pre-tax and pre-expense return, which outperforms the Australian Stock Exchange (ASX) All Ordinaries Index, and the preservation of capital invested. The Company is engaged in investing in equity securities, debt instruments and related derivatives. It invests in listed securities; listed securities for the purpose of short selling, and warrants or options to purchase any investment and warrants or options to sell any investment. It has rights to subscribe for or convert to listed securities. Its portfolio may comprises securities in up to 80% companies from time to time, in which no investment may represent over 10% of the issued securities of a company at the time of investment. The Company's subsidiary is Kapital Investments (WA) Pty Ltd. Katana Asset Management Limited is the manager of the Fund.

Luiri Gold Limited is an Australia-based company, which was engaged in exploration and evaluation of mineral deposits. The Company was engaged in mineral exploration in Zambia. The Company is involved in evaluating investments, which focus in a resource project that is suitable for the Company's projects identified. The Company has no operations other than administration in Australia. The Company has not generated any revenues.

LifeHealthcare Group Limited provides Australian and New Zealand healthcare professionals with medical devices. The Company's product lines include Spine, Orthopaedics and Biologics, Bariatric, Surgical Instruments and Consumables, Cardio Vascular and Point-of-Care Ultrasound, Neurophysiology and Operating Room Capital. Its product categories include implantable devices, non-implantable devices and capital equipment. The implantable devices are implants that are surgically implanted to replace or support the biological structure of the body, such as screws for spine fixation and total joint prostheses, such as hips and knees. The non-implantable devices are used or consumed during surgical procedures, which includes reusable surgical instruments and suction systems. The capital equipment is used clinically either in a hospital operating or outpatient clinical setting, which includes ultrasound machines and operating theatre tables. The Company's products include Pro-Axis and Allegro.

Kresta Holdings Limited is an Australia-based manufacturer and retailer of window furnishings. The Company is engaged in the manufacturing, distribution and retailing of window coverings treatments and components. The Company operates in manufacture and sales of window coverings segment. The Company operates approximately two manufacturing plants, which are engaged in production of roller blinds, curtains, vertical blinds and awnings. The Company's manufacturing and procurement operations are centered in Western Australia and Queensland. It sells its products throughout Australia and has a presence in New Zealand. The Company's subsidiaries include Finmar Pty Ltd, Kresta Blinds (Holdings) Pty Ltd, Kresta Blinds Ltd, Kresta Blinds International Pty Ltd, Kedena Holding Holdings Pty Ltd, Sharatan Pty Ltd, Twighlight Sun Pty Ltd, Sandelle Pty Ltd, Curtain Wonderland Pty Ltd and Mardo Australia Pty Ltd.

Lake Resources N.L. is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's principal activity is to maintain its equity interest in its Pakistan exploration interests. It explores for epithermal gold and porphyry copper-gold deposits in the Chagai Project located in western Balochistan, Pakistan. The Chagai Project area is situated in the Tethyan Magmatic Arc extending from Turkey through Iran into Pakistan. The Chagai Project area hosts a range of copper gold deposits, including Saindak copper-gold mine and Reko Diq copper-gold deposits. It focuses on tenements, including Koh-i-Sultan, Dasht-i-Gauran and Amalaf. It also has lithium brine projects in over three packages of tenement applications (over 90,000 hectares) around salt lakes in North West Argentina. Its lithium brine projects include Olaroz-Cauchari and Paso Projects in Jujuy province and Kachi project in Catamarca. The tenement applications comprise over 53 mining lease applications in Jujuy and Catamarca provinces, Argentina.

Legend Corporation Limited is an engineering solutions company. The Company's principal activities include the distribution of cable accessories and tools servicing the electrical wholesale industry; the design and sale of connectors and cable assemblies to power utilities and infrastructure project contractors; the distribution of computer room accessories, distribution of gas and plumbing tools, products and spare parts to residential, commercial and industrial project, and the design and sale of integrated circuits and hybrids for consumer electrical products, medical devices and industrial electronic components. Its segments include Electrical, Power and Infrastructure; Innovative Electrical Solutions, and Gas and Plumbing. Its divisions include Cabac, Legend Performance Technology, Hendon Semiconductors, Legend Power Systems, Legend Defence, Ecco Pacific, MSS Fibre Systems and System Control Engineering. It operates in various industries, such as electrical, rail and mining.

Link Administration Holdings Limited is a technology-enabled provider of outsourced administration services for superannuation fund administration, corporate markets and related value added services, including data management analytics, digital communication and stake-holder education and advice. Its segments include Fund Administration, which provides administration services to superannuation funds; Corporate Markets, which provides an integrated corporate market offering that connects issuers with their stakeholders and offers services, including shareholder management and analytics, stakeholder engagement and company secretarial, and Information, Digital and Data Services, which provides core services of development and maintenance of information technology (IT) systems and platforms, and value-added services of data analytics, digital solutions and digital communications. It provides platform solution to its clients, covering front, middle and back office administration functions.

Lakes Oil NL is an oil and gas explorer. The principal activities of the Company consist of exploration for oil and gas within Australia. The Company operates in two segments, which include exploration for hydrocarbon reserves, principally in on-shore regions of Victoria, Australia and investment in entities engaged in the renewable energy sector. It holds 100% interest in Petroleum Retention Lease (PRL) 2 and 3. It holds interest in Petroleum Retention Permit (PRP) 166 and 169. It holds 100% interest in PRP 163, 167 and 175. It holds 100% interest the Gippsland Basin permits, which are located offshore in Victorian waters. It holds 100% interest in Queensland Petroleum Exploration Permits, ATP 642P and ATP 662P, which are located on the northern flank of the Cooper and Eromanga Basins. It holds interest in the Eagle Prospect. The Company is also focused on acquiring an interest in exploration acreage outside of Victoria.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Lend Lease Group is an integrated international property and infrastructure company. The Company consists of Lend Lease Corporation Limited and its controlled entities, including Lend Lease Trust. Its segments include Property Development, Infrastructure Development, Construction and Investment Management. It is engaged in designing, developing, constructing, funding, owning, co-investing in, operating and managing property and infrastructure assets. The Property Development business involves the development of inner and outer urban developments, apartments, commercial offices, retail centers, healthcare facilities and retirement villages. The Infrastructure Development business arranges, manages and invests in public private partnership projects. The Construction business involves project management, building, engineering and construction services. The Investment Management business involves property and infrastructure investment management, property management and asset management.

Lion One Metals Limited is engaged in the business of acquiring, exploring, and developing mineral properties. The Company has non-material exploration properties, including a tenement interest in the Olary Creek iron project in South Australia, and over two exploration properties covering over 27,490 hectares within two special prospecting licenses on the island of Vanua Levu in Fiji. Its primary asset is the Tuvatu Gold Project located near Nadi on the island of Viti Levu, Fiji. Its Mineral Resources Department (MRD) of Fiji has granted Special Mining Lease 62 (SML 62) on the Tuvatu project to the Company. The Fijian Islands are located along the Pacific Island Arc, which hosts various mineral epithermal gold deposits systems, such as the Lihir, Porgera, Ok Tedi, and Wafi-Golpu gold deposits in Papua New Guinea. The Olary Creek Project is located in South Australia over 70 kilometers (km) southwest of Broken Hill, New South Wales, and over 40 km south of the Barrier Highway.

Lincoln Minerals Limited is a mineral exploration and development company. The Company's segments include Iron Ore, Graphite and Corporate. It is focused to deliver the transition to maiden graphite mining production following the achievement of critical development and commercialization milestones for its primary graphite assets on Eyre Peninsula. It owns and is advancing a pool of second tier assets across multiple mineral commodities on Eyre Peninsula, a proven mining jurisdiction in South Australia. It has tenements totaling approximately 3,073 square kilometers on South Australia's Eyre Peninsula. It is engaged in exploring iron, graphite, copper, uranium, gold, zinc-lead-silver, vanadium, manganese and nickel-cobalt targets on Eyre Peninsula. Its projects include Kookaburra Gully Graphite Project-Southern Eyre Peninsula, Gum Flat Iron Ore Project-Southern Eyre Peninsula, Eurilla Multi-Commodity Project-Northern Eyre Peninsula and Minbrie Copper Project-Central Eyre Peninsula.

Linius Technologies Limited, formerly Firestrike Resources Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in technology business. The Company is involved in the research and development of technology products, software development, and commercialization and licensing of computer software. The Company owns method and system for providing video content on a data network connected device having a display and device controller. The Company has designed a video virtualization engine, Linius Video Virtualization Engine. Its process applies techniques, including data indexing and virtualization to the video. Using its technology, video can be indexed, spliced and edited in real-time. The Company's technology extracts and modifies index file (vStub) from a video asset allowing users to edit and manage video. It helps in video workflow by managing data within the file at the source. The Company's technology serves cable and Internet television operators.

Liquefied Natural Gas Limited is engaged in the business of developing liquefied natural gas (LNG) export terminal projects in the United States, Canada and Australia. The Company's segments are LNG Infrastructure, and Technology and Licensing. The LNG Infrastructure segment focuses on identification and progression of opportunities for the development of LNG projects. The LNG Infrastructure segment includes project development activities, construction activities, and production and sale of LNG via offtake arrangements with external parties. The LNG Infrastructure segment includes the aggregation of the Magnolia LNG project, Bear Head LNG project and Fisherman's Landing LNG project. The Technology and Licensing segment is involved in the development of LNG technology, through research and development activities. The Company's subsidiaries include LNG International Pty Ltd, Gas Link Global Limited, LNG Management services Pty Ltd and LNG Technology Pty Ltd.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Millinium's Alternatives Fund is engaged in the business of investment management within Australia. The Trust invests in accordance with the provision of the Trust constitution and the product disclosure statement. The Trust provides exposure to a diversified portfolio of alternative assets. The Trust investments include real assets, such as property related investments, unlisted equity and debt instruments; absolute return strategies, and other unlisted managed funds, cash, money market instruments, listed managed funds and other yielding investments. Millinium Capital Managers Limited is the investment manager of the Trust.

Laconia Resources Limited is an Australia-based natural resources company with a portfolio of advanced precious and base metals projects located in Peru and Western Australia. The principal activities of the Company are the exploration of its mineral tenements, and the identification and evaluation of new venture and corporate opportunities. The Company has two segments being exploration activities undertaken in Australia and Peru. The Company's projects include Kimsa Orcco Project, 701 Mile Project and Goldsworthy Project. The Kimsa Orcco copper-gold-silver development project is located in Peru, South America. The Peruvian tenement portfolio comprises the Kimsa Orcco Project: Patacancha N 1, Patacancha N 2, Patacancha N 3 and Patacancha N 4. The 701 Mile Project consists of precious and base metals and is located in Pilbara, Western Australia. The Goldsworthy Project consists of base metals and is located in Pilbara, Western Australia.

LandMark White Limited is an independent valuation and property consultancy company. The principal business activities of the Company are commercial and residential property valuations. The Company provides valuation, research and advice services in relation to property and businesses. The Company undertakes the valuation of commercial properties, including metropolitan and suburban office buildings, large and small scale industrial properties, various forms of retail shopping centers, medical centers, hotels, self-storage centers and service stations. It provides residential property valuation and advice to professional and advisory companies to assist in family law settlements, deceased estates, self-managed super funds, disputes and litigation, and forensic valuations, among others. It provides valuations for balance sheet reporting, asset valuations and portfolio valuations, among others. It offers its services in various property sectors, such as childcare and healthcare.

Matsa Resources Limited is a mining and exploration company. The Company is engaged in gold and other base metal exploration in Australia and Thailand. Its projects include Lake Carey, Symons Hill, Siam Copper, Killaloe, Dunnsville Gold Project and Phaisali Base Metals. The Lake Carey project includes the Fortitude gold deposit. The Lake Carey gold project are consists of approximately 10 tenements and covers an area of over 100 square kilometers. The Symons Hill project consists of one exploration license E69/3070, which is approximately 96 square kilometers in extent, located within the Fraser Range Tectonic zone. The Killaloe project comprises approximately 10 licenses. The Dunnsville Gold Project comprises a group of exploration licenses covering approximately 300 square kilometers located 65 kilometers west-northwest of Kalgoorlie and approximately 50 kilometers northwest of Coolgardie. Its Thailand projects cover approximately 900 square kilometers within the Loei-Ko Chang fold.

Lovisa Holdings Limited is engaged in the retail sale of fashion jewelry and accessories. The Company's segments include Australia & New Zealand, which is engaged in the retail sale of women's jewelry and accessories in Australia and New Zealand, and Rest of the World, which is engaged in the retail sale of women's jewelry and accessories in Singapore, South Africa, Malaysia and the United Kingdom.
