Its Hardware activities include the distribution of hardware supplies to retail outlets and trade customers. The Company's Food & Grocery business is supported by approximately five distribution centers delivering dry, chilled, frozen, general merchandise and hair/beauty/cosmetics. Its Independent Brands Australia (IBA) business operates four national independent retail brands: Cellarbrations, IGA Liquor, Bottle-O and Bottle-O Neighbourhood.

MaxiTRANS Industries Limited is engaged in the design, manufacture, sale, service and repair of transport equipment and related components, and spare parts. The Company operates through two segments: Trailing Solutions, and Parts & Components. The Trailing Solutions segment encompasses trailer Manufacturing, and Retail & Service divisions. The Parts & Components segment encompasses MaxiPARTS and China divisions. The Parts & Components business sells truck and trailer parts at both a wholesale and retail level in Australia. The retail business sells parts to road transport operators, as well as truck and trailer service and repair providers along the eastern seaboard of Australia. The wholesale business operates in Victoria, Queensland, New South Wales and Western Australia. Its wholesale customers are truck dealers and trailer manufacturers. Its business also includes the panel manufacturing operation in China. MaxiPARTS operates approximately 20 wholesale sites and retail stores.

Molopo Energy Limited is an Australia-based company, which is reviewing oil and gas opportunities. The Company has reviewed approximately 30 oil and gas opportunities. The Company's principal activities were selling the Fiesta asset in Texas, which was the petroleum production and exploration asset, and closing down the operations in Canada and transferring back to Australia. The Company's segments include Australia, Canada and USA. In the USA and Canada, of the segment assets, all of them were associated with oil and gas operations.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Metro Performance Glass Limited is a glass processor, distributor and glazier. The Company is engaged in operating a network of processing and retail branches for the provision and assembly of customized glass products across New Zealand. The Company supplies processed flat glass products primarily to the residential and commercial building trade. It offers range of glass products, including Low E double glazing units, deck balustrades, bathroom shower screens, splashbacks, safety glass, double glazed windows, doors and others. It also offers EzyClean protective coating and glazing services. It has approximately 17 sites across New Zealand, including over four processing sites. It delivers windows and other glass products within over three days for window frame fabricators. The Company's subsidiaries include Canterbury Glass & Glazing Limited, Christchurch Glass & Glazing Limited, Hawkes Bay Glass & Glazing Limited and Metroglass Finance Limited.

Mintails Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the processing and recovering of gold from both tailings and surface resources, which are present on the West Rand of South Africa's Witwatersrand basin. The Company's mining tenements include GP206MR, GP183PR, GP641PR and GP417PR. The Company holds these mining rights through its subsidiaries, which include Mogale Gold (Pty) Ltd, Durban Roodepoort Deep (Pty) Ltd, Witsand (Pty) Ltd and Autumn Star (Pty) Ltd. The Company processes total tons of approximately 288,530 tons. Its total gold produced was approximately 9,040 ounces. The total gold production from the Company's own resources totaled approximately 3,912.7 ounces. The Company's own resources consist of mining of 1L8 tailings, D-shaft and the screening of rock lines in the Durban Roodepoort Deep area. The Company has operations in South Africa.

Mantle Mining Corporation Limited is an Australia-based gold miner with its projects located in Queensland and Victoria. The Company holds interest in various gold projects, which include Morning Star Gold Project, Norton Gold Project, Granite Castle Project and Charters Towers Project. The Company also holds interest in various coal projects, which include Bacchus Marsh Project and Latrobe Valley Project. The Company holds interest in Morning Star Gold NL, which in turn owns the Morning Star project. The Morning Star gold mine is located near the town of Woods Point approximately 120 kilometers northeast of Melbourne. The Norton Mine is located approximately 100 kilometers south of the port city of Gladstone, Queensland. The Charters Towers Gold Project is located around the township of Charters Towers in north Queensland. Granite Castle is located approximately 260 kilometers west of Townsville and approximately 120 kilometers north of Hughenden.

Medical Developments International Limited is an Australia-based healthcare company. The Company is engaged in the manufacture and distribution of a pharmaceutical drug, and medical and veterinary equipment. The Company operates through three segments: Pharmaceuticals, Medical Devices and Veterinary products. The Pharmaceuticals segment is engaged in the sale of Penthrox primarily within Australia and the United Kingdom, and some sales in New Zealand, Eastern Europe, the Middle East and South America. The Medical Devices segment is engaged in the sale of medical devices, particularly the Space Chamber and Breath-Alert PeakFlow meters, primarily within Australia and New Zealand, and some sales in Asia, Europe, the Middle East and North America. The Veterinary Products segment is engaged in the sale of veterinary products within Australia, Europe and the United States. The Company offers a range of products in the areas of pain management, and asthma and resuscitation.

Namoi Cotton Co-operative Limited is a cotton processing and marketing company. The Company's principal activity is ginning and marketing cotton. Its segments include Ginning, Marketing and Commodities. It offers services, including cotton seed marketing and commodity packing services. The ginning business operates over 10 cotton gins located in the areas of New South Wales (NSW) and Queensland. The ginning service provided to the growers during the production process includes the separation of lint cotton from seed and other foreign matter and the conversion of cotton in module form to bale form. The marketing business involves the purchase of lint cotton from Australian growers using a range of forward contracts that offer differing combinations of price, delivery and risk characteristics. Its controlled entity, Namoi Cotton Commodities Pty Ltd, procures various grain and pulse crops from Australian growers and sells these into various domestic and international markets.

MYOB Group Limited is a provider of online business management solutions. The Company's segments include SME solutions, practice solutions and enterprise solutions. Its SME Solutions segment provides business management software and services to small and medium enterprises. Its practice solutions segment provides business software and services to accounting professionals in practice. Its enterprise solutions segment provides enterprise resource planning and human resource management software and services to medium and large enterprises. It offers accounting, payroll, tax, practice management, customer relation management, job costing and inventory for businesses across Australia and New Zealand. It provides support through various client service channels, including a network of over 40,000 accountants and other consultants. It offers products, such as MYOB PayDirect, MYOB Smart Bills, MYOB PaySuper, and MYOB Advanced, together with the MYOB Portal.

MyState Limited is a provider of banking, trustee and wealth management services. The Company's segments include Banking Division, Wealth Management Division, and Corporate and Consolidation Division. The Banking Division's product offerings include lending, encompassing home loans, personal, overdraft, line of credit and commercial products; transactional savings accounts and fixed term deposits, and insurance products. The Wealth Management Division is a provider of funds management, financial planning and trustee services. Its banking services include personal, residential and business lending; transactional and Internet banking; insurance and other alliances, and savings and investments. Its trustee services include estate planning; estate and trust administration; power of attorney, and corporate and custodial trustee. Its wealth management services include managed fund investments; financial planning; private client services, and portfolio administration services.

Metals X Limited is engaged in the operation of tin and gold mines in Australia, and exploration and development of precious and base metals projects in Australia. The Company's segments include Renison Tin Project, which includes mining, treatment and marketing of tin concentrate; Wingellina Nickel Project, which includes exploration and development of nickel assets; Higginsville Gold Operation, which includes mining, treatment, exploration and development of gold assets; South Kalgoorlie Operation, which includes mining, treatment, exploration and development of gold assets; Central Murchison Gold Project, which includes mining, treatment, exploration and development of gold assets, and Northern Territory Projects, which includes exploration and development of gold assets. The Company has over three operations in production, which include the Higginsville Gold Operations, the South Kalgoorlie Operations and the Central Murchison Gold Project, which are located in Western Australia.

Montezuma Mining Company Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in carrying out exploration on its tenements and also applies for or acquired additional tenements. Its segments include Australia and France. Its segments are engaged in the determination and assessment of the existence of commercial economic reserves, from the Company's mineral assets in its geographic location. The Company holds various multi-commodity exploration and mining tenements in Western Australia. The Company's primary focus is on its approximately 100% owned Yamarna Gold Project, as well as its over 100% owned Holleton Gold Project, which is located approximately 400 kilometers east of Perth. It also owns a manganese resource at its approximately 100% owned Butcherbird Project. It has nickel sulfide potential at the Green Dam Project and has a pipeling of business development activities ongoing in France. The Green Dam Project is located east of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia.

Myer Holdings Limited (Myer) is an Australia-based department store company. The Company's department store network includes a footprint of approximately 60 stores in retail locations across Australia. The Myer merchandise offer includes 11 product categories: Womenswear; Menswear; Miss Shop (Youth); Childrenswear; Intimate apparel; Beauty, fragrance and cosmetics; Homewares; Electrical goods; Toys; Footwear, handbags and accessories, and General merchandise. The Company also owns womenswear designer brand, sass & bide. The Company's brands include TOPSHOP TOPMAN, Seed, French Connection, Mimco, Veronika Maine, Jack & Jones and Industrie. The Company's subsidiaries include Myer Pty Ltd, NB Elizabeth Pty Ltd, NB Russell Pty Ltd, Warehouse Solutions Pty Ltd, Myer Group Finance Limited, Myer Group Pty Ltd and Myer Travel Pty Ltd. The Company also undertakes activities outside the department store retail business through its subsidiaries, sass & bide, and FSS Retail Pty Ltd.

Navigator Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which focuses on mineral exploration activities. The Company owns the Cummins Range Project. The Company's Cummins Range Project is located approximately 130 kilometers southwest of Halls Creek in Eastern Kimberly, Western Australia. The Cummins Range Project consists of an exploration license, E80/2232, which covers an area of approximately 48.5 square kilometers. The Cummins Range Project is hosted within the Cummins Range carbonatite pipe, a pipe forming part of an alkaline intrusive complex, located near the junction of the Halls Creek Orogen and the King Leopold Orogen.

NuCoal Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which operates in the coal industry in New South Wales, Australia. The Company, through its subsidiary, Dellworth Pty Ltd (Dellworth), owns over two exploration licenses. The Company owns approximately 100% interest in projects, including Savoy Hill Coal Project and Dellworth Coal Project. Its exploration licenses include exploration license (EL) 6812 (Savoy Hill tenement) and EL 6594 (Dellworth tenement). The Company's exploration licenses are located in close proximity to Bayswater Power Station. Its Savoy Hill tenement is located approximately 30 kilometers to the north-west of Singleton. The mining operations near Savoy Hill tenement include Drayton Mine, Drayton South Project, Hunter Valley Operations and Mount Arthur, which are located to the north, west, south east and north-west of the study area, respectively. The Company's subsidiaries include NuCoal Share Plan 1 Pty Ltd and Doyles Creek Mining Pty Limited.

NAOS Emerging Opportunities Company Limited is an investment company. The Company primarily invests in a concentrated portfolio of listed entities that are not included in the Standard & Poor's/Australian Securities Exchange 100 (S&P/ASX 100) Accumulation Index with the objective of providing investors with genuine exposure to emerging companies. The Company operates through Australia segment. The Company invests in securities listed on the ASX and unlisted securities. The Company is focused both on delivering an attractive fully franked yield for investors and growth in shareholder value. The Company invests in a range of industry sectors, which include consumer discretionary, telecommunication services, bulk commodities, transport and real estate. The Company's investment manager is NAOS Asset Management Limited.

New Horizon Coal Limited is engaged in investigating new projects in all business sectors for acquisition or investment. The Company operates in mining and exploration sector. Its segments include New Horizon Coal-Australia and Kinney Coal Project-USA. The Company is involved in exploration and development for coal. The Kinney Project is situated in the Eastern Wasatch Plateau, approximately 160 kilometers southeast of Salt Lake City, Utah near the town of Scofield. The Company operates in Australia and the United States.

Mitula Group Limited (Mitula Group) is an Australia-based company, which operates in the online advertising industry. The Company's platform consists of 51 vertical search Websites in 38 countries and 14 languages. Its Websites enable users to search for real estate, automotive, employment and vacation rentals classifieds. It operates a freemium model, which enables the advertisers to promote their listings. It owns two subsidiaries, including Mitula Classified, S.L., which owns and operates the Mitula branded vertical search Websites, and Lokku Limited, which owns and operates the Nestoria branded vertical search Websites. Its customers include operators of classified advertising Websites, who use the Company's Websites to drive traffic to their own Websites. Its Websites also operate various brands, including FindProperly, Bilatu and Gartoo. Its Websites also enable the users to search for holiday rental classified listings, from various advertisers, through a single search query.

Northern Mining Limited is a resources exploration and development company. The Company is engaged in the exploration of mineral tenements, such as gold, nickel and other minerals. Its geographical segments include Australia, China and Poland. Its exploration portfolio contains exploration and development potential in the East Kalgoorlie Gold and Nickel Project in Western Australia. It also holds approximately 50% interest in the Arcatamu Goldmine Project in Tuoli County in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. The Company has over 79% interest in East Kalgoorlie Gold Project. The Company's Kanowna Lights Prospect covers an area of approximately 565 hectares and is located in a gold endowment region over three kilometers north of Kanowna Belle Gold Deposit. The Company's Snake Hill Prospect consists of a range of tenements, such as P26/3705, P26/3706, P26/3707, P26/3708, P26/3709, P26/3710, P25/2071 and P25/2113. It other tenements are located at Mt Monger, Bulong and Hampton Hill.

Milton Corporation Limited is an investment company. The Company's objective is to invest in a diversified portfolio of assets, which are Australian listed companies and trusts; increase fully franked dividends paid to shareholders over time, and provide capital growth in the value of the shareholders' investment. The Company invests its assets across a range of industry sectors, such as banks, consumer staples, energy, diversified financials, insurance, commercial services, telecommunications, real estate, healthcare, retailing, utilities, capital goods, transport, media and other materials. The Company also invests in fixed interest securities, and liquid assets, such as cash and term deposits. It may also invests in hybrid securities, as well as real property development through joint ventures. Its subsidiaries are 85 Spring Street Properties Pty Ltd, Chatham Investment Co. Pty Limited, Incorporated Nominees Pty Limited and Milhunt Pty Limited.

Nkwe Platinum Limited is engaged in the mineral exploration of platinum. The Company's Garatau Project consists of three contiguous properties: Garatouw 282KT, Hoepakrantz 291KT and De Kom 252KT, located in the Eastern Limb of the Bushveld Complex, approximately 20 kilometers to the northwest of Steelpoort town.

Noni B Limited is engaged in retailing of women's apparel and accessories. The Company operates within the women's fashion retail sector in Australia through a national network of boutique stores under the brands of Noni B and Liz Jordan. It also operates Queens park and Events brands. The Company creates its products, which are manufactured under contract by third-party suppliers. It offers various types of dresses, such as day dresses, evening dresses, maxi dresses and print dresses; tops, such as T-shirts, shirts, kaftans, tanks and tunics; knitwear, such as cardigans, sweaters and jumpers, and capes and ponchos; outerwear, such as jackets, coats, shrugs and vests; bottoms, such as pants, skirts, denim and shorts; intimates, such as bras, briefs, camisoles and slips; occasions, such as mother of the bride, desk-to-dinner, travel range and the slimming range, and accessories, such as scarves, eyewear, hand bags and fascinators. It operates through a retail network over 220 stores.

Nido Petroleum Limited is an oil and gas exploration and production company. The Company is engaged in the production and sale of oil. The Company is also engaged in the development of its oil assets, and exploration for oil and gas. The Company operates in two segments: Production & Development Assets segment, and Exploration and Evaluation Assets segment. The Production & Development Assets segment includes oil producing assets and assets and activities that are in the development phase but have not yet achieved first oil and gas production. The Exploration and Evaluation Assets segment includes assets and activities that are associated with the determination and assessment of the existence of commercial economic reserves. It serves the North West Palawan Basin in the Philippines with interests in Service Contracts that have a gross acreage position of approximately 2,944,000 hectares. Its producing assets include the Galoc Oil Field, Nido A and B Fields, and Matinloc Field.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Marindi Metals Limited is engaged in the mineral exploration. The Company's projects include Newman Base Metal Project, Forrestania Lithium Project, Yalco Project, Caranbirni Project and Oakover. The Newman Zinc Project is located in Western Australia's infrastructure Pilbara District approximately 60 kilometers southwest of Newman. The project is covered by over seven exploration tenements covering over approximately 1,000 square kilometers. The Newman Base Metal Project's deposits include Prairie Deposit, Wolf Deposit, Wolf-Prairie Corridor, Titan (Anomaly B), Hyena-African Hunting Dog and Husky. Its Forrestania Lithium Project includes South Ironcap Lithium Project and Mt Hope Lithium Project. The Caranbirini Project covers approximately 10 kilometers of the prospective Batten Trough and is located over eight kilometers from the McArthur River Mine. The Oakover Manganese Project lies approximately 80 kilometers east of Newman in Western Australia's East Pilbara Manganese Province.

Namibian Copper Limited, formerly Namibian Copper NL, is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration of its Project in Namibia. The Company is engaged in the exploration, development and investment in the resources section. The Company's focus is on the Ongombo Project, which is situated in central Namibia, approximately 22 kilometers northeast of the Otjihase copper mine and over 45 kilometers northeast of the capital Windhoek. Its Ongombo Project includes an inferred resource of approximately 3.75 million tons (Mt) at over 1.70% copper (Cu), approximately nine grams-ton (g/t) silver (Ag) and over 0.32g/t gold (Au), and a measured and indicated resource of approximately 6.71 Mt at over 1.52% Cu and approximately eight g/t Ag, for a total of over 10.46Mt at approximately 1.59% Cu and over eight g/t Ag. The Company's subsidiaries include Namibian Resources Pty Ltd and Gazania Investments Thirty Two Pty Ltd. The Company has not generated revenue from its operations.

Nearmap Ltd is an online PhotoMap content provider. The Company provides geospatial map technology for business, enterprises and government customers. Its segments include Australia, which is responsible for all sales and marketing efforts in Australia; United States, which is responsible for all sales and marketing efforts in the United States, and Corporate, which holds the intellectual property (IP) and product know-how that allows the Company to deliver its product offering, being online aerial photomapping. It offers solutions for various industries, such as architecture and engineering, construction, government, insurance, rail, property, roofing and solar. It provides site information, delivered to users' desktop through high-resolution PhotoMaps technology. Nearmap Insurance provides a desktop-based risk assessment solution. Nearmap Rail delivers visual analytics to mining, port and rail infrastructure. Its property solutions include Nearmap ART and Nearmap Property Tool.

MGC Pharmaceuticals Limited, formerly Erin Resources Limited, is a medical and cosmetics cannabis company. The Company is engaged in the creating cannabidiol (CBD) and medical cannabis business that focuses on the CBD market in Europe. CBD is used for the treatment of a range of skin and health conditions, including acne, psoriasis, eczema and dry skin. The Company's business model involves in growing cannabis sativa plants from high CBD yielding seeds and extracting CBD resin from the plants grown. It sells the CBD resins as a wholesale product to cosmetic and therapeutic product manufacturers. The CBD is also used to produce the Company's line of cosmetic products in Slovenia under the Ananda Cosmetics Joint Venture. It grows, harvests, dries out, extracts and sells cannabis sativa crop to enterprise customers in bulk, individual consumers in delivery devices or other products. The Company subsidiaries include MGC Pharma (UK) Ltd and MGC Pharmaceuticals d.o.o.

N1 Holdings Limited is an Australia-based integrated financial services company. The principal activity of the Company is the provision of mortgage broking services to customers. It offers various services, which include Home Loans, Commercial Lending, Personal Insurance, Investments, Car Loans, Superannuation and N1 Centre. The Company under Personal Insurance offers Life Insurance, Total and Permanent Disability Insurance, Income Protection Insurance, Critical Illness Insurance and Business Expenses Insurance. N1 Centre is the Company's operated shop, which offers solutions for all financial and property services. The Company also operates chengdai.com.au, which is an Australian mortgage products comparison site in Mandarin. The Company is focused on mortgage broking business that uses disruptive online comparison technology to provide access to mortgage and car loan products to its clients. Its subsidiaries include N1 Loans Pty Ltd, N1 Migration Pty Ltd and N1 Reality Pty Ltd.

Southern Cross Media Group Limited is engaged in the creation and broadcasting of content on free-to-air commercial radio (amplitude modulation (AM), frequency modulation (FM) and digital), television and online media platforms across Australia. The Company offers a range of content across free to air television, approximately 80 metropolitan and regional FM and AM radio stations, digital audio and radio, social media networks, online, mobile and events. The Company's segments include Regional free-to-air commercial radio and television broadcasting segment, Metro free-to-air radio broadcasting segment and Corporate. The Company's radio stations include Buddha, kid's radio station Kinderling, music genre stations Easy, Classic Rock, Old Skool and country music favourite, Modern Rock and The Range. The Company's broadcast channels include seven, 7mate and 7two, nine, ten, life, go, gem, eleven and one.

NuEnergy Gas Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration, appraisal and development of hydrocarbons with a primary focus on unconventional gas on coal seam gas also known as coal bed methane (CBM). The Company operates in CBM exploration in Indonesia segment. The Company has approximately six Production Sharing Contracts (PSCs) covering an area of approximately 5,523 square kilometers. The Company focuses on the CBM exploration activities in Tanjung Enim PSC, South Sumatra, and Rengat PSC, Central Sumatra. It holds interest Muara Enim PSC, Muara Enim II PSC and Muralim PSC, which are located in South Sumatra, Indonesia. Muara Enim PSC and Muara Enim II PSC cover a total area of approximately 1,861 square kilometers. It holds interest in Bontang Bengalon PSC, which covers an area of approximately 411 square kilometers and is located in East Kalimantan, Indonesia. The Company holds interest in Joint Evaluation (JE) of Bungamas CBM, South Sumatra.

National Australia Bank Limited is a business bank. The Company provides personal banking and business banking services. The Company's segments include Australian Banking, NZ Banking, NAB Wealth, and Corporate Functions and Others. The Company's Australian Banking includes personal banking and business banking offering a range of banking products and services to retail and business customers, ranging from small and medium enterprises to large institutions. The Company's NZ Banking comprises the retail, business, corporate and insurance franchises in New Zealand. These franchises operate under the Bank of New Zealand (BNZ) brand. The Company's NAB Wealth provides superannuation, investment and insurance solutions to retail, corporate and institutional clients. It operates a network of financial advisors in Australia under brands, which include MLC, JBWere, JANA and Plum.

New Guinea Energy Limited is an Australia-based exploration-stage company. The Company is engaged in exploration for oil and gas in Papua New Guinea (PNG) and investment in oil and gas companies. It operates through exploration for oil and gas in Papua New Guinea segment. The Company has over two onshore Petroleum Prospecting Licenses (PPL), PPL 266 and PPL 267, covering approximately 7,490 square kilometers and a royalty right over approximately 4,000 square kilometers in a PPL running parallel to the PNG LNG project. The Company has completed subsurface mapping of the permit, PPL 265. The Company has identified a drillable prospect and over five leads on PPL 266 permit. The Macadamia Prospect in northern PPL 266 is a faulted basement drape feature identified along depositional strike from the Puk Puk 1 area to the east. The Company has identified over five prospects and leads on PPL 268.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

99 Wuxian Limited is an investment holding company. The Company offers m-commerce service platform which provides mobile value-added services in the People's Republic of China (the PRC). The platform offers its services to various sectors, including banks, financial institutions and others business partners. The Company's products include 99 Marketplace, which is m-commerce service platform; Incentive Cloud Service Platform, and Tapit, which is a near field communication provider, among others. The Company's subsidiaries include Ninety nine Trading (Shanghai) Co., Ltd., Shanghai Xinshunhui Trading Co., Ltd. and Shanghai Handpal Information Technology Co., Ltd., among others.

NetLinkz Limited, formerly iWebGate Limited, is an Australia-based company, which offers NetLinkz, a technology that provides a Software-Defined Wide Area Network (SD-WAN) solution connecting any sites to any device, anywhere, on any network. Its segments include Australia, USA, Europe and Corporate. Its technology delivers the meshed peer-to-peer SD-WAN solution. SD-WAN offers a solution for information technology (IT) to extend or replace connectivity leveraging public Internet protocol links. Offering centralized wide area network management and near-zero touch edge software, which enables IT managers to connect cloud servers and mobile users to the enterprise network. It offers a range of products, which include LaunchPad and iWebGate Workspace Suit. Its LaunchPad acts as a single point of contact for various services, and is an integrated tool set and application program interface (API). Its iWebGate Workspace Suit includes Virtual Private Network LP, Desktop LP and Proxy LP.

Niuminco Group Limited is an Australia-based company, which holds prospective exploration areas and mining leases in Papua New Guinea, through its subsidiaries. The Company has exploration licenses at May River and Bolobip, and mining leases at Edie Creek. The Company operates through three segments, including mineral exploration in Papua New Guinea and Tasmania, and mining operations in Papua New Guinea. It also has an interest in TNT Mines Limited, a tin and tungsten exploration company with assets in Tasmania. The Company holds interest in EL 1441 at May River and EL 1438 at Bolobip. The Edie Creek Project is located in Wau District of Morobe Province, approximately 210 kilometers northwest of Port Moresby and over 120 kilometers south of Lae. The mining leases in the Edie Creek Project cover over 3.92 square kilometers. The Bolobip site is located over 300 kilometers west of Mount Hagen and approximately 50 kilometers east of Tabubil in the Western Province of Papua New Guinea.

Norwood Systems Limited is engaged in the development and supply of global mobility and roaming solutions using over-the-top (OTT) technologies for organizations of all sizes. The Company operates through voice telecommunication services segment. The Company's offerings, CORONA and World Phone, deliver international fixed-line roaming solutions addressing a range of customers, from individual business travelers all the way through to enterprise and government clients. The Company's Corona Cloud is a business-focused application-based telephony offering. The Company's Corona GTS connects all office voice traffic to nearby Points of Presence in its global federated network, delivering a single-vendor solution for multi-sited multi-country organizations. The Company's World Phone is a communications application delivering sharing economy consumer access to fixed-line network service providers around the world, providing unparalleled local access to voice networks in over 90 countries.

Novarise Renewable Resources International Ltd is a producer of a range of polypropylene fiber-based products made from post-consumer polypropylene waste materials. The Company develops its own technology to utilize recycled polypropylene waste to produce polypropylene filament yarn and other finished products, such as straps and rope. Its product range includes fiber-grade recycled polypropylene pellets, which are used in the production of polypropylene filament yarn and agricultural twine; polypropylene filament yarn, which is anti-acidic, corrosion-resistant, non-toxic, wear-resistant and non-hygroscopic that is used in various applications, including consumer, agricultural, industrial and construction; polypropylene consumer webbing products, which are used for edging on beach chairs and tents, and agricultural twine. The Company expands its range of polypropylene consumer webbing products to include green shopping bags, made from recycled polypropylene filament yarn.

Netccentric Limited is an investment holding company. The Company's segments include Influencer Platform, Display Ad Network, Social Media Agency, Digital Asset production and Others. The Influencer Platform enables advertisers to engage social media influencers to promote their products and services. The Display Ad Network enables advertisers to promote their products or services. The Social Media Agency operates a digital marketing agency specializing in social media strategy and campaign management for advertisers. The Digital Asset production segment operates a boutique all-in-one digital media production house specializing in Web design and development; graphic designs, and corporate identity designs. The Others segment includes media production house and mobile blogging applications. Its subsidiaries include Nuffnang Australia Pty Ltd., which provides online advertising and management services, and Nom Nom Media Sdn. Bhd., which operates as a sales agent for advertising services.

New Hope Corporation Limited is an Australia-based diversified energy company. The Company's principal activities include coal mining, oil and gas, marketing and logistics, and investments. It operates through four segments: Coal mining in Queensland, which includes mining related exploration, development, production, processing, transportation, port operations and marketing; Coal mining in New South Wales, which includes mining production, processing, transportation and marketing; Oil and gas, which includes oil and gas related exploration, development, production and processing, and Treasury and investments, which includes cash, held to maturity investments and available for sale financial assets. The Company also has its business interests in port operation, agriculture and technologies. It has two open cut coal mines in South East Queensland that produce thermal coal: New Acland and Jeebropilly.

Neometals Ltd is a mineral project developer. The Companys segments include Lithium, Titanium and Vanadium, and Others. The Companys projects include Mount Marion Lithium Project, Lithium Hydroxide Project (ELi Process), Alphamet, Barrambie Titanium Vanadium Iron Project (Barrambie Titanium) and Forrestania Nickel Project. The Company's Mount Marion Lithium Project is located approximately 40 kilometers southwest of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia. The Company is also focused on the Mount Finnerty Project, which is located approximately 60 kilometers east of Koolyannobbing. The ELi Process has been jointly developed by the Company and Mineral Resources Limited. The Companys Barrambie Titanium project uses a technology to manage titanium, vanadium and iron compounds. The Companys Forrestania Nickel Project is located approximately seven kilometers north of the flying fox nickel sulfide mine in the Yilgarn region of Western Australia.

Nagambie Resources Limited, formerly Nagambie Mining Limited, is engaged in the investigation and development of waste handling assets. The Company is also engaged in the exploration for, and development of, gold, associated minerals, and construction materials in Australia. The Company has 100% of tenements surrounding Victorian goldfields at Nagambie, Clonbinane, Rushworth and Redcastle. The Company primarily focuses on Potential Acid Sulphate Soil (PASS) Management Project. The Company carried out a second costeaning program (four costeans totaling 313 meters in length) at the Apollo-Gladys area at Clonbinane, 60 kilometers south of the Nagambie Mine. The Gold exploration by the company is focused on the discovery of shallow, open-pit and heap-leachable oxide gold deposits. The Company has rights over a total of 551 square kilometers of prospective gold ground in the Nagambie region. It is developing all the non-gold material opportunities on the freehold land at the Nagambie Mine.

Nick Scali Limited is a furniture retailer operating in Australia. The Company is engaged in the sourcing and retailing of household furniture and related accessories. The Company operates brands, including Nick Scali brand, which consists of over 40 stores, and Sofas2Go, which consists of approximately five stores. The Company offers various products, such as lounges, including leather and fabric lounges; occasional chairs, including arm chairs and barstools; dining tables; dining chairs; buffets and cabinets; coffee tables; television and entertainment units, which are available in a range of timbers and veneers and styles, including low-line and wall mount, and rugs, which are available in range of colors and textures. The Company operates a boutique Website, www.nickscalionline.com.au, which features replica and designer furniture. The Company has stores located in New South Wales, Queensland, Victoria, South Australia, Western Australia and Australian Capital Territory (ACT).

NMG Corporation Limited, formerly Noble Mineral Resources Limited, is engaged in exploration activities in Ghana. The Company's segments include Australia and Cape Three Points. The Australia segment is engaged in mineral development and corporate activities. The Cape Three Points segment is engaged in mineral exploration activities. The Company holds an interest in Cape Three Points Concession, which is located in the Republic of Ghana. The Company's Cape Three Points (CTP) project (CTP Project) lies on the eastern margin of the Ashanti Gold Belt in Southwest Ghana. The Company's subsidiary is Noble Mineral Resources Ghana Limited.
Dotz Nano Limited, formerly Northern Iron Limited, is a technology company. The Company is focusing on the development, manufacture and commercialization of graphene quantum dots.

nib holdings limited operates as a private health insurer for Australian residents, New Zealand residents, and international visitors and students to Australia. The Company operates through the segments, including Australian Residents Health Insurance, which operates within the Australian private health insurance industry; New Zealand Residents Health Insurance, which operates within the New Zealand private health insurance industry; International (Inbound) Health Insurance, which include the Company's health insurance products for international students and workers, World Nomads Group, which is engaged in distribution of travel insurance products, and nib Options, which enables access to cosmetic and dental treatment for both overseas and also in Australia. It offers nib Travel Insurance, which include round the clock emergency assist; overseas medical and dental; medical evacuation; passport and travel documents; lost, stolen or damaged luggage, and approved medical conditions.

Nex Metals Explorations Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploring for gold, copper and nickel. The Company is involved in mineral mining and exploration in Western Australia. Its projects include Yundamindera Gold Project and Kookynie Gold Project. The Yundamindera gold mining center is located approximately 65 kilometers southeast of Leonora and over 45 kilometers north-east of the township of Kookynie, within the North-eastern Goldfields of Western Australia. The Company's Yundamindera Gold Project consists of approximately nine granted mining leases covering approximately 46.2 square kilometers. The Kookynie Gold Project is located approximately 200 kilometers north of Kalgoorlie and over 50 kilometers south of Leonora on the main gold trend. The Kookynie Gold Project is situated within the North Coolgardie Mineral field covering the Keith-Kilkenny Tectonic Zone (KKTZ). It is also involved in evaluating projects for base metals, copper, gold and diamonds.

Navarre Minerals Limited is an Australia-based resources company. The Company is a mineral exploration company in Victoria, Australia. The Company is focus on gold exploration. The Stawell Corridor Gold Project comprises two exploration licenses: Tatyoon and Ararat. It is located between 10 and 70 kilometers south of the Stawell Gold Mine. The Company focuses on exploration on the Stawell-style Irvine and Benno gold prospects. The Tandarra Gold Project is a greenfields gold discovery under shallow cover, located approximately 40 kilometers north of the Bendigo Goldfield. The Company's Western Victoria Copper Project captures multiple targets in approximately 130 kilometers of Stavely Arc volcanics, including the Eclipse, Lexington, Glenlyle and Pollockdale prospects.

Nine Entertainment Co. Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in television broadcasting and program production, and digital, Internet, subscription television and other media sectors. The Company operates in two segments: Television, which includes free to air television activities, and Digital, which includes Nine Digital Pty Limited and other digital activities. Its brands include Nine Network Television, Nine Digital and Other Businesses. Its Nine Network Television includes Channel 9 and 9HD. Channel 9's content includes a combination of international and locally produced programs with stars, events, dramas, reality and entertainment shows. Its Nine.com.au is an online source of news, sport, entertainment and lifestyle content. It also sell Microsoft's suite of advertising products across Australia and New Zealand. Its Other Businesses include CarAdvice, Literacy Planet, Pedestrain.tv and RateCity.

Neon Capital Limited, formerly Neon Energy Limited, is an Australia-based investment company. The Company operates as a listed investment company (LIC). It provides investors a managed and diversified portfolio of assets. These assets include Australian shares, international shares, fixed income securities, property with some funds offering packaged strategies.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

NSL Consolidated Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in review, assessment, exploration, development and investment in Indian iron ore and Queensland coal projects. The Company operates in two segments, which include mining and exploration for iron ore in India, and exploration for thermal coal in Queensland. Its operations under Iron Ore-India include Kurnool Iron Ore Beneficiation Plant; AP26 and AP27, which are mining leases covering approximately 100 acres located in the district of Kurnool, and AP14 Magnetite Deposit in Telangana. Its Indian Iron Ore Projects also include Kuja Project, which is located in the Andhra Pradesh Province in Southern India, and Mangal Project, which is located in the Andhra Pradesh Province in South Eastern India and is approximately five kilometers from the Kuja site. Its Australian Thermal Coal project includes exploration permits for coal, such as 2198, 2336, 2337 and 2338 covering approximately 2,585 square kilometers.

MZI Resources Ltd is an Australia-based mineral sands company, which focuses on the minerals of zircon, rutile and leucoxene. The Company's principal activities include mineral sands development, production and exploration. The Company's segments include Tiwi Island Projects, Keysbrook Project and Unallocated Corporate/Other. The Tiwi Island Projects segment includes the Company's projects located on the Tiwi Islands in the Northern Territory, including Lethbridge South, Lethbridge West and Kilimiraka. The Keysbrook Project segment includes the Keysbrook Project, which is located in the south-west of Western Australia. The Company is developing a leucoxene deposit at Keysbrook, located approximately 70 kilometers south of Perth in Western Australia. The deposit is approximately 1,406 hectares in area. The Keysbrook Project hosts zircon/leucoxene ore body. The Keysbrook Project sits within two Shires: the Shire of Murray and the Shire of Serpentine-Jarrahdale.

Noxopharm Limited is a drug development company. The Company is engaged in the research and development of NOX66 in the field of adjuvant therapy in chemotherapy and radiotherapy. The Company focuses on developing a drug to treat cancer. The Company has a primary focus on the development of drugs to treat the problem of drug- and radio-resistance in cancer cells. The Company's drug NOX66 is a dosage formulation developed to protect idronoxil from being inactivated in the human body by Phase II metabolism. Its purpose is to ensure that idronoxil administered remains in an active form. The Company has its offices in Melbourne and Sydney.

NSX Limited is an Australia-based company, which operates National Stock Exchange of Australia (NSXA) Limited. The Company provides a stock exchange facility for the listing of equity securities, corporate debt and investment scheme units. It has three common listing models, such as conventional, closed market and trading windows. The Company operates its own trader workstation terminal, as well as electronic feeds for those wishing to use their own terminals to trade or for information vendors. It sources its technology from National Association Of Securities Dealers Automated Quotations (NASDAQ). The Company's issuers by industry include property, finance, investment, life science, consumer, information technology (IT), agriculture, infrastructure, media, asset management, regional banks, health and exploration. Its participants offer services, such as raising capital, trade execution, underwriting, research, investment advice, settlement and corporate advisory services.

Northern Star Resources Limited (Northern Star) is a gold (Au) production and exploration company. The Company's principal activities include mining of gold deposits at Jundee, Kundana, Kanowna Belle and Paulsens; construction and development of extensions to existing gold mining operations at all locations; exploration at Central Tanami Project in the Northern Territory, and exploration and development of gold deposits within Western Australia. The Company's segments include Paulsens, WA Australia, which is engaged in mining and processing of gold; Kundana, WA Australia, which is engaged in gold mining; Kanowna Belle, WA Australia, which is engaged in mining and processing of gold; Jundee, WA Australia, which is engaged in mining and processing of gold; Tanami NT Australia, and Exploration, which consists of the projects in exploration, evaluation and feasibility phase, such as Mt Olympus, Fortescue JV and Electric Dingo, as well as ongoing exploration programs.

Neptune Marine Services Limited is a provider of integrated inspection, repair and maintenance solutions to the oil and gas, marine and renewable energy industries. The Company's principal activities include commercial diving services; hydrographic surveying, positioning and geophysical services; non-destructive testing (NDT), inspection and mechanical repair services; pipeline and subsea structure stabilization and grouting; remotely operated vehicle (ROV) services; subsea and pipeline engineering; manufacturing, assembly and testing services, and dry underwater welding using the NEPSYS technology. The Company operates in two divisions: Offshore Services and Engineering Services. Its primary focus is the international oil and gas, marine and renewable energy offshore industries in the regions of Australia, Asia and the United Kingdom. The Company supplies vessels, including air dive support, construction support, saturation dive support and platform support and supply vessels.
Oil Related Services and Equipment - NEC

Nickelore Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the minerals exploration and evaluation industry. The Company is evaluating investment opportunities outside the mineral exploration industry. The Company has entered into an agreement to acquire Helio Energia Holdings S.A., an end-to-end provider of distributed generation solar energy systems for commercial and industrial energy customers in Brazil. The Company will also seek either a strategic partner or commercial opportunities to divest its existing Canegrass Project mineral exploration assets and partners. The Company's tenements on Canegrass Project include P 24/4573, P 24/4574, P 24/4575, P 24/4576, P 24/4577 and P 24/4580.

Neuren Pharmaceuticals Limited (Neuren) is a biopharmaceutical company engaged in developing drugs for neurological disorders. The Company develops therapies for brain injury, neurodevelopmental and neurodegenerative disorders. Its drugs target symptoms resulting from acute traumatic brain injury, as well as symptoms of chronic conditions, such as Rett syndrome and Fragile X syndrome. Its products include NNZ-2566 and NNZ-2591. Its lead product, NNZ-2566 (Trofinetide), is in Phase II trial for the treatment of Rett syndrome, Fragile X syndrome, moderate to severe Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) and Concussion. Trofinetide is an analog of a molecule, which is derived from insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF-1) and occurs naturally in the brain. Its NNZ-2591 product is in Pre-clinical and Phase I trial for the treatment of other neurological conditions. Its subsidiaries include Hamilton Pharmaceuticals Inc. and Neuren Pharmaceuticals Inc.

Noble Metals Limited, formerly Condoto Platinum NL, is involved in the exploration of gold and platinum at its Noble Metals platinum project in Colombia. The Company's segments include Australian Exploration and Colombian Exploration. The Company's divisions include Exploration, Mineral Processing, GPS Smelting, GPS Refining and GPS Manufacturing. The Company operates as an integrated gold and precious metals company with the ability to mine, process, smelter, refine, analyze, manufacture and export gold and precious metals from Colombia to international customers. The Company also has an exploration base covering 105,975 hectares, and minerals processing facility in the township of Novita. The project in Novita lies approximately 80 kilometers east of the Pacific Ocean. The Company is focused on both carrying out exploration and assessing third party opportunities in the Novita region to establish or support alluvial precious metals mining operations.

Novatti Group Limited is a financial transaction software technology and payment services provider. The Company is engaged in the sales and deployment of the Novatti Platform, and transaction services. The Company operates through three segments: Novatti Platform, Transaction Services and Novatti Group Limited. The Novatti Platform segment develops, deploys and supports specialized mobile and alternate payment technology, primarily through the deployment of the Novatti Platform. The Transaction Services segment includes TransferBridge, which provides a global network that interconnects payment platforms, remittance operators, financial institutions, retailers, utilities and all types of telecommunication operators, and Flexewallet and Flexe Payments, which offer an alternative payment method in the form of a prepaid cash voucher, which can be used for a multitude of payment methods, such as prepaid account top-ups and for secure online payment of goods and services.

NTM Gold Limited, formerly Northern Manganese Limited, is engaged in exploration of mining tenements and investing cash assets in interest bearing bank accounts. The Company's projects include Redcliffe Gold Project, Blue Mud Bay Project, Commonwealth Waters Project (Groote Eylandt South) and Groote Eylandt Project. The Redcliffe Gold project is located in a range of 35 to 65 kilometers north east of Leonora and approximately 230 kilometers north of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia. The Company's Redcliffe Gold project holdings consist of approximately four granted mining leases and an exploration license covering approximately 120 square kilometers. The Nambi Deposit is located approximately 20 kilometers north of golden terrace south deposit. The Company holds exploration rights in over two islands near Groote Eylandt in the Northern Territory of Australia. The Company's subsidiaries include Reflective Minerals Pty Ltd, North Manganese Pty Ltd and Redcliffe Resources Limited.

Northern Minerals Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activities include the exploration and evaluation of rare earth element mineral interests. Its projects include Browns Range Project, John Galt Project and Boulder Ridge. The Browns Range Project covers an area of approximately 3,595 square kilometers and is centered on the Browns Range Dome. The Dome is located in the northern Tanami region, within both Western Australia (WA) and the Northern Territory (NT). The John Galt project consists of granted tenements, including E80/4298, E80/4671 and E80/4779, which cover a combined area of approximately 180 square kilometers. The John Galt project is situated in the East Kimberley region of Western Australia, approximately 200 kilometers south of Kununurra. The Boulder Ridge project is located in the Tanami region of the Northern Territory, approximately 100 kilometers southeast of the Browns Range Project.

NetComm Wireless Limited is engaged in the development of fixed wireless broadband, wireless machine-to-machine (M2M)/Industrial Internet of Things (IoT), and Fiber and Cable to the distribution point technologies. The Company operates through two segments: Broadband Business and Machine to Machine Business. The Broadband business segment supplies communication devices, which range from entry level gateways to high-performance devices that supports triple play services covering high-speed data transmission, multi high definition (HD)/4K Internet Protocol television (IPTV) and over-the-top video streaming, as well as voice over Internet protocol (VoIP) phone calls. The M2M business segment specializes in the development of technologies sold to telecommunications carriers, core network providers, system integrators, governments and enterprise customers around the world. The M2M business also includes network terminating devices designed to advance global network performance.

New Standard Energy Limited is engaged in the exploration for oil and gas in the Carnarvon Basin and Canning Basin in Western Australia. The Company's segments include Australia and United States. The onshore Canning Basin is situated approximately 2,000 kilometers north of Perth in the central north of Western Australia, covering an area of approximately 530,000 square kilometers. Its projects in Canning Basin include Southern Canning and Laurel Project. The Southern Canning project covers approximately 48,000 square kilometers and Laurel Project covers approximately 5,900 square kilometers. Its onshore Carnarvon Basin is located approximately 1,000 kilometers north of Perth and includes over two depo-centers. It also operates Merlinleigh Project in the onshore Carnarvon Basin in Western Australia. Its subsidiaries include New Standard Onshore Pty Ltd, New Standard Energy Inc, New Standard Energy Colorado LLC and New Standard Energy Ventures LLC.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Novogen Limited (Novogen) is an oncology biotechnology company, which is focused on developing cancer treatments. The Company is primarily engaged in pharmaceutical research and development. Novogen has two drug technology platforms (the Superbenzopyran (SBP) technology and Anti-tropomyosin (ATM)) yielding various drug candidates across a range of oncology indications. The Company's product candidates include Cantrixil (TRX-E-002-1), Anisina (ATM-3507) and Trilexium (TRX-E-009-1). The Company's target indication for Cantrixil is ovarian cancer, and Diffuse Intrinsic Pontine Glioma (DIPG) for Trilexium. The initial target pediatric indication for Anisina is neuroblastoma. Cantrixil is the lead development candidate arising from its SBP technology. Anisina is an approach to chemotherapy that targets the cancer cells' actin cytoskeleton. Trilexium (TRX-E-009-1) is its second lead SBP drug candidate. It focuses on various cancers, including melanoma and prostate cancer.

NSL Consolidated Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in review, assessment, exploration, development and investment in Indian iron ore and Queensland coal projects. The Company operates in two segments, which include mining and exploration for iron ore in India, and exploration for thermal coal in Queensland. Its operations under Iron Ore-India include Kurnool Iron Ore Beneficiation Plant; AP26 and AP27, which are mining leases covering approximately 100 acres located in the district of Kurnool, and AP14 Magnetite Deposit in Telangana. Its Indian Iron Ore Projects also include Kuja Project, which is located in the Andhra Pradesh Province in Southern India, and Mangal Project, which is located in the Andhra Pradesh Province in South Eastern India and is approximately five kilometers from the Kuja site. Its Australian Thermal Coal project includes exploration permits for coal, such as 2198, 2336, 2337 and 2338 covering approximately 2,585 square kilometers.

Nevada Iron Limited is an Australia-based resource company. The principal activities of the Company are the exploration and development of mineral assets in the United States. The Company's segments include Australia and United States. The Company's project includes Buena Vista Iron Project. The Buena Vista Iron Project is located in northern Nevada and approximately 400 kilometers northeast of San Francisco. The Company's subsidiaries include Nevada Iron LLC (the United States) and Iron Horse Transportation LLC (the United States).

New Talisman Gold Mines Limited is engaged in mine development and mineral exploration. The Company's projects include Talisman Mine Project and Rahu. The Talisman mine includes the Maria, Crown/Welcome and Mystery veins. In the Karangahake area, the Company also holds the Rahu permit, which is the northern extension of the Talisman vein system. The Company is engaged in initiating bulk sampling at Talisman and advancing the development of the mine. The Company's subsidiary, Coromandel Gold Limited, holds a portfolio of mineral interests and gold properties in the Hauraki and Northland Districts of New Zealand. Through a subsidiary company, the Company owns Broken Hill Prospecting Limited, which holds a cobalt project at Thackaringa, approximately 20 kilometers south-west of Broken Hill in Australia and a heavy mineral sands exploration portfolio. Its subsidiary also includes Northland Minerals Limited.

National Storage REIT is an internally managed and integrated owner and operator of self-storage centers in Australia. The Company has approximately 105 self-storage centers under operation or management, providing storage solutions to over 35,000 customers across Australia and New Zealand. The Company manages approximately 59,200 storage units across approximately 542,000 square meters of net lettable area around Australia and New Zealand. Approximately 60 self-storage centers are owned by National Storage Property Trust (NSPT); over 16 self-storage centers are operated as long-term leasehold centers; approximately 26 self-storage centers are managed for the Southern Cross Storage Group (Southern Cross) and over three third-party managed centers. The Company's self-storage centers are located at North Queensland, Sunshine Coast, Gold Coast, Brisbane, Sydney, Canberra, Melbourne, Geelong, Adelaide, Hobart, Perth, Darwin, Christchurch, Hamilton and Wellington.

Nuheara Limited, formerly Wild Acre Metals Limited, is an Australia-based audio wearables company. The Company is engaged in developing hardware and software to deliver multi-functional intelligent hearing technology that augments a user's hearing and facilitates cable free connection to smart devices. The Company's IQbuds is an audio wearable (hearable) device. The Company uses Focused Audio and Speech Technology (FAST) technology, which allows IQbuds to control surroundings sounds for situational awareness. The Company's IQbuds allows the consumers to augment their hearing according to their personal hearing preferences and connect hands free with their voice enabled smart devices. The Company's IQbuds has a hearing device, Bluetooth earpiece, and noise cancelling headset in approximately two wireless earbuds. The Company's IQbuds has a mobile application that allows personalizing hearing settings.

Nanosonics Limited is a medical technology company. The Company is engaged in the manufacturing and distribution of the trophon electron paramagnetic resonance (EPR) ultrasound probe disinfector and its associated consumables and accessories. It is also engaged in the research, development and commercialization of infection control and decontamination products and related technologies. It operates through healthcare equipment segment. Its product portfolio includes consumables, such as chemical indicators and NanoNebulant/Sonex-HL. Its accessories include trophon Curved Probe Positioner (CPP), which improves the positioning of approved curved probes in the trophon EPR chamber; trophon Printer, which links the probe and disinfection procedure to the patient; trophon Connect, which is a software tool that helps clinics meet documentation and audit requirements, and trophon Printer Wall Mount, which is designed for horizontal mounting of the trophon Printer to a wall.

Nvoi Limited, formerly Orrex Resources Limited, is engaged in providing cloud-based staffing platform for the contingent workforce. The Company offers platform for workers/candidates and businesses/hiring managers in the on-site, white-collar, contingent (non-permanent) workforce to find, engage, assess and contract through it with each for non-permanent work assignments. The Company focuses on the intermediation tools, such as contracts, compliance, process and payments. The Company focuses on offering a free marketplace platform to create client and candidate profiles, for hiring managers to post assignments, and for both to assess each other through video interview, and agree to commercial and compliant terms for a work assignment, on a self-service basis. The Company's Nvoi Platform allows candidates to directly present a professional profile to a Hiring Manager through the Platform, and agree terms of engagement for a work assignment.

Oakdale Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration and development of economic mineral deposits. The Company is involved in developing a graphite mining operation and graphite project located on Central Eyre Peninsula in South Australia. The Oakdale Graphite Project Area consists of approximately 6,220,000 tons at a grade of over 4.8% total graphite carbon (TGC) within an overall saprolitic graphite resource of approximately 13,450,000 tons of over 3.3% of TGC. The Company holds approximately seven exploration tenements covering over 1,810 square kilometers of central Eyre Peninsula, South Australia. The exploration tenements also contain other mineral prospects, including iron ore and base metals. The Company's projects also include Bramfield Iron Project. Bramfield Iron Project is located approximately nine kilometers from Elliston on Eyre Peninsula, approximately 170 kilometers from Port Lincoln.

Orthocell Limited is a regenerative medicine company. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of cell therapies and related technologies. The Company's products include CelGro, a collagen medical device for soft tissue repair in use as an augment to rotator cuff repair, guided bone regeneration and repair of articular cartilage, and Autologous Tenocyte Implantation (Ortho-ATI) for chronic, treatment resistant tendon regeneration. CelGro is targeted on a range of orthopedic, reconstructive and surgical applications. Ortho-ATI is a treatment that uses a minimally invasive, non-surgical approach that uses each patient's own tendon derived stem cells to stimulate tendon regeneration and is delivered through ultrasound guided injection under local anesthetic. The Company's Autologous Chondrocyte Implantation (Ortho-ACI) offers treatment for symptomatic defects of the articulating cartilage of the joints, including the knee and ankle.

OBJ Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the research and development of its dermaportation and estrogen transdermal patch (ETP) transdermal drug delivery technologies. It develops magnetic, micro-array drug and ingredient delivery technologies. It provides partnering services and product solutions for technologies in transdermal and intra-dermal drug delivery; therapeutic and dermatological skincare; cosmetic and non-medicinal active ingredient with a special focus on anti-aging and peptide delivery; oral health strips, toothbrush technologies and mouthguards; haircare solutions utilizing brushes and applicators; industrial surface interface systems; fabric and carpet cleaning technologies, and surface hygiene technologies. It operates skin labs and provides in-vivo and ex-vivo formulation profiling, skin penetration and partitioning services, including in-vivo tape stripping, accumulation and flux analysis and ex-vivo full thickness diffusion and partitioning.

Nemex Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activity is maintenance of its mineral tenements and continuing the diversification of its activities through its investment in Wavefront Biometric Technologies Pty Ltd (WBT), a security biometric technology company. It has three segments, being mineral exploration in West Africa; mineral exploration and investment activities in Australia and investment in WBT. It also holds interests in a range of resources projects, including the Telimele DSO Iron project in Guinea and the Woodley Iron project in Western Australia. Its WBT develops biometric solutions for authentication of identity utilizing the properties of the eye. Its Woodley Iron project is located in the Mid-West iron ore province of Western Australia. It has completed over 300 drill holes in the Telimele DSO Iron Project. The Company has no operating revenue.

Nufarm Limited is a crop protection and seed technologies company. The Company develops, manufactures and sells a range of crop protection products, including herbicides, insecticides and fungicides. The Company operates through two segments: crop protection and seed technologies. The crop protection segment is engaged in the manufacture and sale of crop protection products used by farmers to protect crops from damage caused by weeds, pests and disease. Its crop protection business is managed by various geographic segments, including Australia and New Zealand, Asia, Europe, North America and Latin America. The North America region includes Canada and the United States. The Latin America region includes Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Uruguay, Paraguay, Bolivia, Columbia, the Andean countries, Mexico and the Central American countries. The seed technologies segment is engaged in the sale of seeds and seed treatment products. The seed technologies business is managed on a worldwide basis.

Norwest Energy NL is engaged in exploration for hydrocarbon resources. The Company operates in the oil and gas sector. The Company holds interests in various tenements in Australia, which include EP 413, TP/15, EP492, Special Prospecting Authority (SPA)-016 AO, EP 368/EP 426, EP492 and L14 Jingemia Oilfield. The Company's the United Kingdom interests are focused on the Wessex Basin, southern England. In the United Kingdom, the Company holds interests in Promote Licence P2265-Offshore Wessex Basin. The L14 production license contains the Jingemia Oil Field and it has contained over 12 million barrels of oil in place, with a production capacity of approximately 4.6 million barrels. The Company's subsidiaries include Westranch Holdings Pty Ltd and Norwest Perth Basin Pty Ltd.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Oceania Capital Partners Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company's segments include Financial Services, which includes receivables management; Commercial Radio Broadcasting, which includes operation of frequency modulation (FM) radio stations; Digital lead generation, which includes online lead generation and marketing, and Security screens, which is engaged in supplying door and window security screens. The Company has invested in operating businesses, whether privately owned or publicly listed, with decisions being based on the fundamental investment characteristics of the business. The Company's primary focus is on investing capital in businesses, which will grow over the investment period. The Company, either directly or through subsidiary entities, has invested in various businesses, including those that operate in the financial services, commercial radio broadcasting and digital lead generation. The Company operates in the Asia Pacific region.

NRW Holdings Limited is a holding company. The Company is engaged in providing diversified services to resource and infrastructure sectors in Australia. The Company operates in three segments: NRW Civil and Mining, Action Drill & Blast, and AES Equipment Solutions. The Company's NRW Civil and Mining segment is engaged in the delivery of private and public civil infrastructure projects, mine development and contract mining, waste stripping and ore haulage supported by a mobile work force and a fleet of plant and equipment. Its Action Drill & Blast segment is engaged in providing contract drill and blast services to mining (including iron ore, gold and coal) and civil projects throughout Australia. Its AES Equipment Solutions segment is engaged in providing maintenance services to the mining and resources sectors, including the fabrication of water and service trucks. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is engaged in activities, such as plant and tire sales, and contract services.

National Veterinary Care Ltd is engaged in the provision of veterinary services throughout Australia. The Company's network of veterinary clinics offer various services, including acupuncture, blood tests, chemotherapy, dental radiography, desexing, digital radiography (X-Rays), electrocardiograph (ECG), heartworm injections, health exams, healthy nutrition programs, in-house pathology, intensive care hospitalization, microchip identification, nail trimming, orthopedic surgery, senior and palliative care, stem cell therapy, ultrasounds, vaccinations and weight loss programs. Its Best for Pet service provides optimal healthcare for pet. Its Best for Pet membership includes all the preventative care services for maintaining user's pet's health and wellbeing.

NZME Limited is a New Zealand-based company, which is principally engaged in the media and entertainment business. The Company operates in three segments: Print, Radio and Digital. The Company is focused on delivering in news, sport and entertainment to New Zealanders. GrabOne is the Company's e-commerce platform. The Company has a network of over 80 media brands. The Company's news brands include The New Zealand Herald, Herald National News, Newstalk ZB, Weekend Herald, Herald On Sunday, Herald Business, Bay of Plenty Times, Hawke's Bay Today, The Northern Advocate, Rotorua Daily Post, Wanganui Chronicle, Farming Show, Herald World News, Herald Classifieds, Heraldjobs, Northland Age, Whangarei Report and The Aucklander. The Company's sports brands include Radio Sport, Herald Sport, Herald Rugby and Dream Team. The Company's media brands include Herald Entertainment, Herald Lifestyle, Heraldhomes, Coast, Flava, Vibe and Watch Me.

Odin Energy Limited is an Australia-based company, which was engaged in the production of oil and gas in the United States. The Company is in the process of acquiring gridComm Pte Ltd. gridComm Pte Ltd is a smart city Internet of Things (IOT) sensor data communications company focused on Asian business. The Company's subsidiaries include Glory Run Pty Ltd and Jet Strike Pty Ltd.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Oil Basins Limited (OBL), through its subsidiary, Oil Basins Royalties Pty Ltd, owns over-riding royalty interests in Cyrano R3/R1 and Judith/Moby Location Vic/P47. OBL owns 100% of this retention lease and is the operator of Cyrano R3/R1. Cyrano R3/R1 is nearby to Airlie Island. The Cyrano Oil Field is defined by approximately four vintage wells and three-dimension (3D) seismic. The field contains approximately 10 meter net heavy 22.8 American Petroleum Institute (API), low sulfur oil, and 21 meter gas cap, with crude oil viscosity 3.95 centipoise (cp). The Company and its subsidiary own Vic/P47. OBL is the operator of this permit.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Nexus Minerals Limited is gold exploration company, which is engaged in mineral exploration in Australia. The Company focuses on gold production opportunities in Western Australia. The Company's projects consist of Pinnacles Joint Venture Gold project, including M28/243; Pinnacles Regional Gold project, including P28/1185, E28/2487 and E28/2526; Triumph Gold project, including E31/1088, P31/2074, P31/2075, P31/2076 and E31/819, and Mt Celia Gold project, including P39/5484, P39/5485, P39/5486 and E39/1890. It focuses on gold in the north east of Kalgoorlie in the Eastern Goldfields, Western Australia. The Pinnacles Joint Venture Gold project is located approximately 120 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie. The Pinnacles Regional Gold project is located approximately 100 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie. The Triumph project is located approximately 145 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie. The Mt Celia project is located approximately 180 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie.

Navitas Limited is an education provider. The Company is engaged in providing educational services to domestic and overseas students. The Company's segments include University Partnerships, Professional and English Programs (PEP), SAE and Corporate. Its University Partnership segment delivers education programs, through pathway colleges and managed campuses, to students requiring a university education. Its PEP segment delivers English language tuition, jobs skills training, and higher and vocational education in health, security and psychology. Its SAE segment delivers education programs in the area of creative media, including courses in audio, film and multimedia. The Company offers its educational services to approximately 80,000 students through approximately 120 colleges in over 30 countries. The Company has its operations across Australia, the United Kingdom, Europe, Asia, the United States, Canada and rest of the world.

Newfield Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company, which focuses on its diamond project in Sierra Leone and various gold projects in Western Australia. The Company's segments include Mineral Exploration Australia, Mineral Exploration Sierra Leone and Corporate. Its projects include Allotropes Diamond Project, Newfield Gold Project and Crest Yard Gold Project. It owns mineral rights to five exploration licenses (ELs) covering an area of 1,002 square kilometers within the Bo, Bonthe, Moyamba, Pujehun and Kenema Districts in the Southern Province of Sierra Leone. The Newfield Project comprises two granted mining leases and one granted prospecting license. The project is centered approximately 60 kilometers north-northwest of Bullfinch, in the Yilgarn Mineral Field. The Crest Yard Gold Project, covers 2,455 hectares, centered between the historical gold mining centers of Kintore and Dunnsville, located approximately 60 kilometers northwest of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia.

Objective Corporation Limited is a technology company. The Company is engaged in the supply of information technology software and services. Its segments include Asia Pacific and Europe. Its products include Objective enterprise content management (ECM), Objective Inform, Objective Perform, Objective Connect, Objective Keystone and Objective Trapeze. It offers professional services and managed services. Its Objective ECM combines the information governance and industry specific processes. The Objective Inform provides information picture by integrating content within line of business applications to enable user's staff to manage their content driven tasks. The Objective Perform transforms manual content driven process into a digital reality. The Objective Connect allows user to collaborate on documents, capture conversations and control tasks with anyone. The Objective Keystone manages business documents. The Objective Trapeze digitally transforms image reviews and assessments.

ORH Limited is a management consultancy that uses operational research techniques to support resource planning in the public sector. The Company operates through engineering and distribution segments. It specializes in solving locational planning problems for the emergency services, and carries out studies for health authorities, sports bodies and other public sector organizations. It delivers a service, which enables providers and commissioners of emergency services to resolve strategic and tactical planning problems. It offers a service that helps public-sector organizations to answer planning questions about the location and capacity of facilities. It provides a range of software solutions to assist emergency services in future planning and to support control-room decision-making. Its software solutions include service planning software, which is a simulation model for answering planning questions, and Dynamic Cover Tool, which provides support for emergency service control rooms.

NEXTDC Limited is a technology company, which is engaged in the development and operation of independent data centers in Australia. The Company is engaged in enabling business transformation through data center outsourcing solutions, connectivity services and infrastructure management software. Its segments include Qld, Vic, NSW, WA, ACT and Other. The Company's services categories include data center solutions, connectivity, professional services and cloud connections. The Company offers solutions, including Custom Colocation, AXONVX and ONEDC. AXONVX enables customers to activate high-speed private connections to various carries and cloud platforms on-demand, and access simplified inter-capital connectivity services. ONEDC is the Company's data center infrastructure management platform. ONEDC is engaged in managing customers entire data center infrastructure and combining their internal and colocated environments all managed through a single console.
