Its RentReports gives real-time suburb and rental market data for user's property. RentQuotes allows landlords to get proposals from local agents.

RXP Services Limited is engaged in providing information and communication technology consulting, development, support and maintenance services. The Company's practices include RXP Collective, RXP Engaged, RXP Insight, RXP Develop and RXP Optimise. The Company uses design thinking to determine the customer experience based on the behaviors and the needs of the customers. RXP Engage provides change management services ranging from small project related change to whole of enterprise change. It provides governance, risk and compliance (GRC) services to financial institutions, government departments and businesses. It provides independent oversight of projects and change programs, post implementation reviews, risk analysis and mitigation services, as well as a range of health checks, compliance testing, and penetration testing. RXP Insight solutions offer cloud hosting and managed service. RXP Develop delivers enterprise software applications for cloud and on premise environments.

Rungepincockminarco Limited is engaged in the provision and development of mining software solutions, advisory services and professional development. The Company's principal activities include software licensing, consulting, implementation and support; technical, advisory and training services to the resources industry, and laboratory gas testing. Its segments include Software Division, Advisory Division and GeoGAS. Its Software Division provides software offerings, including maintenance, training and implementation services to mining companies. The Company's Advisory Division provides consulting and advisory services, which cover technical and economic analysis, and assessment of mining activities and resources on behalf of mining companies, financial institutions, government departments, and agencies and suppliers to mining companies and projects. Its GeoGAS Division provides services to coal mining clients in respect of gas content testing and relevant consulting services.

S2 Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company operates through three segments: Scandinavian exploration activities, Australian exploration activities and Unallocated. The Scandinavian exploration activities segment includes exploration and evaluation of mineral tenements in Finland and Sweden. The Australian exploration activities segment includes exploration and evaluation of mineral tenements in Australia. The Company's projects include Polar Bear Project and Norcott Project. The Polar Bear project spans an area of approximately 150 square kilometers, located between Higginsville and Norseman. It has over 360 square kilometers of ground under application adjacent to the Polar Bear project. It holds an interest in over six exploration licenses, covering approximately 100 square kilometers of ground adjacent to the Polar Bear project (the Eundynie Joint Venture).

Southern Gold Limited is engaged in the exploration for gold, copper, nickel, and other economic mineral deposits. The Company operates through Australian geographical segment. The Company's projects include Bulong, Cannon Gold Resource, Cowarna and Cambodia. The Bulong gold project is located approximately 30 kilometers east of the Kalgoorlie Goldfield in Western Australia. The Cannon gold resource forms the center of southern gold's Bulong project, which is located approximately 30 kilometers south-east of Kalgoorlie in Western Australia. The Cowarna project covers banded iron formation (BIF) interpreted to be the equivalent of the Randalls BIF sequence, which is located approximately 50 kilometers south-east of the Bulong project. The southern gold has approximately seven granted exploration licenses prospective for gold and base metals covering over 1,500 square kilometers in northeast Cambodia.

RTG Mining Inc. is a mining and exploration company. The Company is focused on developing the high-grade copper/gold/magnetite Mabilo Project and advancing exploration on the prospective Bunawan Project, both in the Philippines, while also identifying new projects, which will allow the Company to move to production. It operates through mineral exploration and development segment. Its Mabilo Project is located in Camarines Norte Province, Eastern Luzon, Philippines. It consists of one granted Exploration Permit (EP-014-2013-V), of approximately 498 hectares and over two Exploration Permit Applications (EXPA-000188-V) of approximately 2,737 hectares and (EXPA 0000 209-V) of over 498 hectares. Its Nalesbitan Project comprises Mining Lease Contract MRD-459 of approximately 500 hectares and MPSA Application APSA-V-0002 of over 600 hectares. Its Bunawan Property is located in the east of Mindanao Island in Agusan del Sur Province, approximately 190 kilometers north-northeast of Davao.

Reliance Worldwide Corporation (Aust.) Pty Ltd is a global provider of water control systems and plumbing solutions for domestic, commercial and industrial applications. The Company develops, assembles and delivers plumbing solutions to businesses and households across Australia and New Zealand through these product lines. The Company is headquartered in Brisbane.

Ridley Corporation Limited is engaged in the production of animal nutrition solutions. The Company operates through two segments: AgriProducts segment, which is a supplier of animal nutrition solutions and Property segment, which is engaged in realization of opportunities in respect of surplus property assets and sales of residual property site assets. Its product range includes finished products in bulk or bags and in pellet form, raw materials, additives and supplements, and animal meals. Its animal meals include meat and bone meal, poultry meal, hydrolyzed feather meal, blood meal, fishmeal and animal fats. Its brands include Barastoc, Rumevite, Cobber and Primo. It provides feed rations, mineral concentrates, nutritional blocks and supplements to a range of species, such as dairy, poultry, aqua, pig, beef, horse, sheep and dog. Its services include growers, nutrition and export. It offers products in various categories, such as poultry feeds, pig feeds and aqua feed, among others.

Rewardle Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in digital customer engagement platform for local small and medium-sized enterprises (SME) merchants. The Company is involved in the development of a social network that connects approximately one million members with thousands of local businesses around Australia. Its network includes prepayment, mobile ordering, mobile payments and social media integrations. It also offers data marketing solutions to merchants. The Rewardle Platform is a marketing and transactional platform that combines membership, points, rewards, mobile ordering and payments along with social media integrations, into a single cloud based platform managed by Big Data analysis. The Company's customers include neighborhood businesses, such as cafes, yoga studios, butchers and hair dresses. Rewardle Pty Ltd is a subsidiary of the Company. The Company is a subsidiary of Rewardle Holdings Limited.

Ryder Capital Limited is engaged in investing in a concentrated portfolio of Australian Securities Exchange (ASX) and New Zealand Exchange (NZX) listed micro and small capitalization securities, bonds and cash consistent with the Company's permitted investments and stated investment objective of achieving long-term growth in capital and income. The Company operates in Australia and in the securities industry. The Company is managed by Ryder Investment Management Pty Limited, which is specializing in small to mid-cap Australasian equities.

Rox Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company has base and precious metals exploration projects in Australia, which include the Mt Fisher Gold Project, Fisher East Nickel Project, the Reward Zinc-Lead Project and the Bonya Copper Project. The Mt Fisher Gold Project and Fisher East Nickel Project are located approximately 500 kilometers north of Kalgoorile, Western Australia with tenement size of over 660 square kilometers inclusive of approximately 170 square kilometers option. The Reward Zinc-Lead Project is located approximately 700 kilometers southeast of Darwin, Northern Territory with tenement size of over 670 square kilometers. The Reward Zinc-Lead project has two areas of focus, the Teena deposit and the Myrtle deposit. The Bonya Copper Project is located approximately 350 kilometers east of Alice Springs, Northern Territory with tenement size of over 280 square kilometers. It explores the Bonya tenement for copper, lead, zinc and silver, among others.

Sky and Space Global Limited is engaged in the deployment of nano-satellite constellations for global communication infrastructure as carried out by Sky and Space Global UK Group. The Company advances its plans to deploy a nano-satellite constellation in low-earth orbit to establish voice, instant messaging and data communication infrastructure network to the telecommunications and international transport industries. The Company's business is to construct a communications infrastructure based on nano-satellite technology and develop the software systems that will deploy, maintain orbit control and handle communication code between each of the nano-satellites to give a global coverage. The Company offers services, including real-time tracking for airliners and shipping companies; service for cellular networks in Latin Americas, Asian and African regions with poor coverage, and voice and instant messaging for over four billion people without any mobile coverage.

South American Iron and Steel Corporation Limited (SAIS) is an Australia-based company engaged in mineral exploration for iron sands in South America, with an emphasis on Chile. The Company operates in four segments: Australia, Chile, Ecuador and Hong Kong. The Chile segment includes the Chilean entities, Inversiones Aconcagua Limitada, Inversiones Arenas Claras Limitada and Inversiones Arenas Maullin Limitada, which are owned by SAIS. The Ecuador segment includes the Ecuadorian exploration operation, Minera Fierro Inca Ecuador S.A., which is approximately 99.95% owned by SAIS, as well as the Ecuadorian agriculture operation, Agroindustrial Ana Julia S.A., which is over 99.95% owned by SAIS. The Hong Kong segment includes SAIS Gold Limited, which is formed to enable the Company to hold investment in Ample Success Investment Limited (Ample Success). Ample Success owns approximately 75% of the Yunnan Weishan Mineral Concession.

Rision Limited, formerly Reclaim Industries Limited, is an Australia-based cloud-based software as a service (SaaS) provider. The Company has developed a platform that enables candidates to find and manage their work, and businesses to identify, employ and roster staff, and manage timesheets. The Company is focused on providing cloud-based human resourcing solutions for organizations that manage contingent workers and their employees. The Company's platform is designed for use by job seekers, businesses and their employees, and human resources professionals. The Company's initial product offering includes JobMatch, Roster, LastMinute and TimeSheet. Its JobMatch helps businesses find employees with the right skills and experience, without trawling hundreds of job applications. Its employee management tools, including Roster, LastMinuteHire and TimeSheet simplifies human capital management, and enables mobile communications with employees.

Sundance Resources Limited is an Australia-based iron ore company. The Company is engaged in evaluation and de-risking of its Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project in the Republics of Cameroon and Congo in Central Africa, and evaluation of various development scenarios for Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project. The Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project includes iron ore deposits in the Republics of Cameroon and Congo in Central Africa. The Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project is located approximately 485 kilometers east of the coastal city of Kribi. The Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project straddles the border of Cameroon and Congo in Central Africa. The Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project includes Exploration Permit 92 (EP92) located in the East Province of Cameroon (Mbarga), and Mining Permit Nabeba-Baamegod located in the Sangha Province of the Congo (Nabeba). EP92 contains the Mbalam deposit. The Company, through its subsidiaries, Cam Iron SA and Congo Iron SA, holds interest in the Mbalam-Nabeba Iron Ore Project.

Reward Minerals Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company operates through the Potash mineral exploration within Australia segment. The Company focuses on the exploration and development of Potash resources amenable to the production of Potassium Sulfate (SOP). The Company's primary focus is the advancement of its LD Potash Project. The LD Potash Project is located in the Little Sandy Desert, Western Australia, approximately 340 kilometers east of Newman and accessed through the Talawana Track. The Project consists of over 5,000 kilometers of granted exploration licenses. Its other Projects include the Karly Project and Lake Dora Project. Its Karly Project covers the Waukarlycarly Embayment and is located approximately 200 kilometers north west of LD Potash project. Its Lake Dora is located north of LD Potash project. The Company's tenements cover approximately 10,000 square kilometers.

FeOre Limited is a Bermuda-based company, along with its subsidiaries is engaged in exploration activities in Mongolia. The Company disposed its entire interest in the Mongolian Iron projects in June 2014.

Scentre Group Trust 1 (SGT1) is an Australia-based company engaged in the ownership and improvement of shopping centers. The Trust has investments in a portfolio of shopping centers across Australia and New Zealand. SGT1's investment properties include shopping center investments, development projects and construction in progress. The Trust's shopping center investment properties represent completed centers consisting of freehold and leasehold land, buildings and leasehold improvements. The Trust has interest in approximately 40 shopping centers, which comprises over 11,260 retail outlets and approximately 3.5 million square meters of retail space. The Trust's Australian portfolio has approximately 10,690 retail outlets in approximately 3.3 million square meters of retail space. The Trust's New Zealand portfolio has over 980 retail outlets in approximately 0.3 million square meters of retail space.

Speedcast International Limited is an Australia-based satellite services provider. The Company offers a range of products and services, such as network service, value added services, equipment sales and wholesale Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP). Network service includes design, deployment, operation and maintenance of networks, including installation and configuration of equipment. Value added services include user applications (voice, video conferencing and video surveillance), network optimization (firewalls, filtering, data compression) and networking monitoring and management. The Company sells equipment directly to customers, including the very small aperture terminal (VSAT) that sends and receives transmitted data, modems, router and other types of equipment related to the provisioning of value-added services. The Company sells wholesale VoIP to telecom customers through the sale of voice minutes on a wholesale basis, which are then resold to the end user.

Rift Valley Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activity of the Company is exploration for gold in Tanzania and rare earths, gold and copper in Angola. The Company's segments include Tanzania and Angola. The Company's projects include Kitongo project, Miyabi Gold project and Ozango project. The Kitongo gold project is located approximately 90 kilometers south of Mwanza within the Lake Victoria Goldfields of Tanzania. The Miyabi Gold project is located approximately 200 kilometers southwest of the city of Mwanza in the Lake Victoria Goldfields of western Tanzania. The Miyabi property comprises a coherent block of prospecting licenses and prospecting license applications totaling over 395 square kilometers in area that covers the bulk of the Miyabi greenstone belt. The Ozango project is located approximately 520 kilometers southeast of Luanda and centered over 70 kilometers to the west of Huambo.

SIV Asset Management Limited operates Significant Investor Visa Funds in Australia. The Company is pursuing foreign investors into the two Significant Investor Visa Funds and is also seeking to design products that comply with the new investment framework for the Significant Investor Visa and Premium Investor Visa. The Company will also seek investment opportunities that are consistent with its activities and which have the potential to generate shareholder returns. The Company operates in Australia and holds all assets within Australia.

Sino Gas & Energy Holdings Limited (Sino Gas) is an Australian energy company focused on developing unconventional gas assets in China. Sino Gas holds a 49% joint venture interest in Sino Gas & Energy Limited (SGE) through a partnership with MIE Holdings Corporation (MIE), which is the operator of the Linxing and Sanjiaobei Production Sharing Contracts (PSCs) in the Ordos Basin, Shanxi province. SGE has a 64.75% interest in the Linxing PSC, partnered with CUCBM, a subsidiary of CNOOC, and a 49% interest in the Sanjiaobei PSC, partnered with PetroChina CBM, a subsidiary of CNPC. The PSCs are located in the Ordos Basin in China and cover an area of approximately 3,000 square kilometers (km2). Sino Gas holds a 31.7% working interest in the Linxing PSC and a 24% working interest in the Sanjiaobei PSC. The Linxing PSC is split into Linxing East (1,301 km2) and Linxing West (573 km2). Sanjiaobei covers 1,123.93 km2.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Sundance Energy Australia Limited is an energy exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration for and development and production of oil and natural gas in the United States, and expansion of its portfolio of oil and gas leases in the United States. The Company operates through the oil and natural gas exploration and production in North America segment. The Company's exploration and development activities are focused in the Eagle Ford formation (Texas) and the Mississippian/Woodford formations in the Greater Anadarko Basin (Oklahoma). The Company is focused on the appraisal and development of its Greater Anadarko Basin projects. The Greater Anadarko Basin includes approximately two projects, South Goltry and Mulhall, situated in Oklahoma targeting the Mississippian Lime and Woodford Formations, and a project in southern Kansas targeting the Mississippian Lime.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Rex Minerals Limited is engaged in minerals exploration and evaluation in Australia. The Company focuses on developing Hillside Project in South Australia. The Company's geographic segment is South Australia. The Company focuses on copper-gold projects. The Company's Hillside Project is situated approximately 12 kilometers south of the township of Ardrossan on the Yorke Peninsula, South Australia. The Mineral Resource of the Hillside Copper Project consists of approximately 337 million tons at 0.6% copper and 0.14 grams per ton gold (g/t) gold, equating to approximately 2.0 million tons (4.3 billion pounds) of copper, 1.4 million ounces (Moz) of gold. The Hillside Project occupies an area of approximately two square kilometers within an exploration license area of over 1,700 square kilometers. The bulk of this area is prospective for copper mineralization.

SEEK Limited is engaged in online matching of hirers and candidates with career opportunities and related services; investing in early-stage businesses and technologies, which are in or adjacent to the online employment marketplace, and distribution and provision of vocational training and higher education courses. The Company's segments include ANZ Employment, Zhaopin, SEEK Asia, Brasil Online, OCC, Education and Early Stage Ventures. Its ANZ Employment, Zhaopin, SEEK Asia, Brasil Online and OCC segments provide online employment marketplace services. Its Education segment is engaged in marketing, sale and distribution of education courses. Its Early Stage Ventures segment consists of a portfolio of Australian and international investments that either sit adjacent to the online employment and education marketplaces or provide its products or services in new geographical regions. Its operations include in Australia, New Zealand, China, South East Asia, Brazil and Mexico.

Sequoia Financial Group Limited, formerly MDS Financial Group Limited, is an integrated financial services company providing products and services to self-directed retail and wholesale clients. The Company operates through seven segments: Trading and Execution, which is engaged in provision of execution only, online trading services; Software Subscriptions, which is engaged in provision of financial market data and analysis tools for investors; Capital Markets Advisory, which is engaged in provision of capital markets advice and related services; SMSF Administration, which is engaged in provision of market solution for self-managed super funds (SMSF); Wealth Advisory, which is engaged in provision of client advisory services; Investment Solutions, which is engaged in provision of modified investment products, and Finance News Services, which is engaged in provision of financial news services. It also provides retail, wholesale and institutional trading platforms.

Sunbridge Group Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in wholesale of clothing apparel to franchised distributors and retail of clothing apparel to company owned stores. The Company operates in two segments: Wholesale of clothing apparel to franchised distributors and Retail sales of clothing apparel by company owned stores. The Company manages the Pandist brand of business and leisure clothing. The Pandist brand of products include T-shirts, wool sweaters, trousers, leather jackets, fur-lined coats, leather accessories, such as leisure bags, briefcases, wallets, traveling bags, belts, shoes scarf, tie, socks and under-garments. The Company operates in the People's Republic of China. Its subsidiaries include Mega Rich International Creation Limited, Bangdisidun (Fujian) Dress Development Co., Ltd. and Hengjiasi Dress Development Co., Ltd.

Sunland Group Limited is engaged in residential property development and construction. The Company's segments include Land and Housing, Multistorey and Other. The Land and Housing segment includes development and sale of land (urban development) and medium density housing products. The Multistorey segment includes development and sale of medium rise projects (generally between 5 and 15 stories), and high rise developments (over 15 stories). The Company has projects located in Queensland, New South Wales and Victoria in cities, including Townsville, Sunshine Coast, Brisbane, Gold Coast, Sydney and Melbourne. The Company's projects include The Heights, The Lakes, Quays Hope Island, Grace on Coronation, Concourse Villas and The Glades, Whyte Residences, Carre Residences, Ancora, Dahlia Residences, The Mariner and The Parc. The Company's development pipeline includes approximately 6,300 land, housing and multi-stored products.

Saracen Mineral Holdings Limited is engaged in gold mining and mineral exploration. The Company's segments include Saracen Gold Mines Pty Limited (SGM), which includes the exploration, production and administration relating to the Carosue Dam operations (CDO); Saracen Mineral Holdings Limited (SAR), which includes the corporate administration, and Saracen Metals Pty Limited (SME), which includes the exploration, development, production and administration relating to the Thunderbox operations (TBO). CDO tenement holdings and gold deposits are located in gold provinces, in northeast of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia. TBO is located in the Yandal Belt and the Agnew-Wiluna Belt in the North Eastern Goldfields of Western Australia. TBO includes the Thunderbox Project, including the Thunderbox and Mangilla gold deposits; the Bannockburn Project, including the Bannockburn and North Well gold deposits, and the Waterloo Project, including the Waterloo and Amorac nickel deposits.

Stemcell United Limited, formerly On Q Group Limited, is an Australia-based holding company of Stemcell United Pte Ltd. The Company is engaged in sourcing, producing, marketing and selling of Resina Draco Blume and other medicines. It is a biotechnology company, which focuses on the growth, reproduction, culture and extraction of stem cells for medicinal, health and beauty applications using its technology. The Company's products include Dendrobium Officinale and Daemonorops Draco Blume, which are two plant extracts used in many different products. The Company operates in Australia and Singapore.

Sensera Limited is an Australia-based integrated company, which is focused on research and development (R&D), design and fabrication of specialized micro-electro-mechanical systems (MEMS). The Company conducts its business through its subsidiary Sensera, Inc. The Company provides contract research, design, development, and various engineering solutions to meet requirements of its customers. The Company offers the solutions as end-to-end managed services to its customers incorporating various elements, such as R&D, Design, Prototyping and Manufacturing. The Company has a research and development process, which includes design, engineering and prototyping services to start-ups, as well as corporates customers. The Company operates Class 100 MEMS microsensors and water fabrication facility. The Company also operates a micro-fabrication facility in the United States. The Company offers its solutions to various markets, such as Healthcare, Industrial and Defense.

Royal Wolf Holdings Limited is a provider of portable container solutions to the resources, construction, logistics, retail and manufacturing industries in Australia and New Zealand. The Company specializes in the hire, sale and modification of new and refurbished container products. The Company's segments include National Accounts Group, Customer Service Center (CSC) Operations for Australia and New Zealand, and Head Office. The National Accounts Group segment includes the freight and project divisions. The CSC Operations segment includes site operations where the units are sold, modified and hired from the respective country. Its product range includes refrigerated containers; road and rail products; dangerous and hazardous goods containers; site offices, lunch rooms, change rooms, toilet and shower blocks, first aid rooms, hoardings and gantries for the construction industry; defense force containers; accommodation units, and modified shipping containers.

Scentre Group is the parent company of Scentre Group Limited, Scentre Group Trust 1 (SGT1), Scentre Group Trust 2 (SGT2) and Scentre Group Trust 3 (SGT3). The principal activity of SGT1 and SGT2 is the ownership and improvement of shopping centers. SGT1 and SGT2 operate through two segments: Australia and New Zealand. SGT1 and SGT2 have investments in a portfolio of shopping centers across Australia and New Zealand. The principal activity of SGT3 is the holding of interests in long-term brand alliance agreements with various third parties in respect of a range of properties. These agreements provide for the licensing of space in the relevant properties for the display of advertising in consideration for the payment of license fees. It also includes financing of the New Zealand equity accounted entities of SGT2. SGT3 operates through the Australasia segment. SGT1, SGT2 and SGT3 seek to manage its capital requirements through the mix of debt and equity funding.

Scottish Pacific Group Limited is engaged in providing specialized financial services. The Company provides working capital to businesses operating in Australia, New Zealand and the United Kingdom. The Company's segments include Debtor Finance and Trade Finance. The Debtor Finance credit is provided to clients through a range of options, including factoring, invoice discounting and specialized products. The Debtor Finance also offers corporate credit line, selective invoice finance, cashline, asset finance and bad debt protection. The Company offers Trade Finance cross-border transactions through trade line, and import/export finance. Its tradeline is a line of credit helping businesses purchase goods. Its import finance helps businesses improve their purchasing power and cash flow with a complete, end-to-end funding solution. Its export finance is engaged in providing business access to additional working capital and improving cash flow by advancing funds against export invoices.

Sterling Plantations Limited is engaged in oil palm plantation development through Sterling Plantations Sdn Bhd, which is the investment holding company for its oil palm plantation development business. The Company also focuses on developing an oil palm mill through SPC Palm Mills Sdn Bhd. The Company is also engaged in the sale and marketing of grower plots. The Company's oil palm and growers scheme business involve the operation of an oil palm plantation, plantation development and cultivation of fresh fruit bunches (FFB). The Company has interests in Golden Palm Growers Berhad, a Malaysian company, which is engaged in developing an approximately 11,000 acre oil palm plantation in Malaysia. Golden Palm Growers operates Golden Palm Growers Scheme. The Company's subsidiary, SPC Palm Mills Sdn Bhd, is engaged in developing an oil palm mill.

Siburan Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company's segments include Mineral Exploration, and Corporate and administrative. Its projects include Kirwan Tungsten Project and Canegrass Gold Project. It holds over three granted permits, including approximately two exploration permits and prospecting permit in an area prospective for tungsten and gold in the South Island of New Zealand. The permit areas (Kirwan Hill Tungsten Project) are located over 12 kilometers east of the township of Reefton, on the west coast of the South Island of New Zealand and cover a total area of approximately 840 square kilometers. The Canegrass Project lies in the northern half of the Menzies-Kambalda region of the Norseman-Wiluna Belt in the Archaean Yilgarn Craton of Western Australia. It consists of exploration licenses E29/789 and E24/177 located approximately 70 kilometers to the north east of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia and covers an area of over 365.4 square kilometers.

SDI Limited is engaged in the manufacture and distribution of amalgam and composite restorative materials, other dental materials, and product research and development. The Company manufactures dental restorative products, tooth whitening systems and small dental equipment for sale to dental distributors, dental dealers and dentists around the world. The Company's segments include SDI Australia segment, which includes SDI Limited; SDI Europe segment, which includes SDI Dental Limited (Ireland), SDI GmbH (Germany) and SDI Italy S.r.l (Italy); SDI USA segment, which includes SDI (North America), Inc.; SDI Brazil segment, which includes SDI Brasil Industria e Comercio Ltda, and other segments. The Company's product categories include alloys, etchants, adhesives, glass ionomers, sealants, composites, cements, tooth whitening, equipment, accessories and Riva Star. Its products are distributed through distributors and retailers in over 100 countries throughout the world.

Steadfast Group Limited is a general insurance broker network in Australia and New Zealand. The Company is engaged in the provision of services to Steadfast Network Brokers, the distribution of insurance policies through insurance brokerages and underwriting agencies and related services. It consists of approximately 345 brokerages with over 1,145 offices across metropolitan and regional areas. It is engaged in business of distributing and advising on insurance products in Australia, New Zealand, London and Singapore. It offers Steadfast Technologies, Steadfast Life, Steadfast Re, Macquarie Pacific Funding, White Outsourcing and Meridian Lawyers. It caters its services to the industries, including commercial property; education and training; health, aged care and medical services; hospitality and foodservices; manufacturing, construction and trades; marine; mining; performers and entertainers; rural and farming; sports, clubs and associations; transport, and wholesale and retail.

Shopping Centres Australasia Property Group RE Limited is an Australia-based company, which manages listed managed investment schemes that own and operate Shopping Centers in Australia and New Zealand. The Company also manages unlisted managed investment schemes that own and operate Shopping Centers in Australia. Its portfolio comprises over 82 neighborhood, sub-regional and freestanding retail shopping centers situated across Australia and New Zealand. The Company comprises two registered managed investment schemes, which include Shopping Centres Australasia Property Management Trust and Shopping Centres Australasia Property Retail Trust. The Company is a subsidiary of Shopping Centres Australasia Management Trust.

St Barbara Limited is a gold producer and explorer. The Company is engaged in mining and the sale of gold, mineral exploration and development. The Company segments include Leonora and Simberi. The Company's Leonora Operations include the Gwalia approximately 1.2 million tons per annum (Mtpa) processing plant and the Gwalia Underground mine. The Company's Simberi mine is on Simberi Island in Papua New Guinea, which includes gold and porphyry copper-gold targets. The Company's Simberi gold resources, reserves and mining operations are located in Mining Lease (ML) 136, which covers eastern half of Simberi Island, and the remainder of the island is covered by Exploration License (EL) 609, which also covers Tatau and Big Tabar Islands. Simberi focuses on epithermal gold in oxide and sulfide deposits. Simberi produced approximately 110,286 ounces of gold. The Company's Big Tabar Island is located approximately 20 kilometers south of Simberi, and over 30 kilometers north of Lihir Island.

Silver City Minerals Limited is an Australia-based base metal and lithium explorer. The Company's principal activities include exploration for the discovery and delineation of high grade base and precious metal deposits and the development of those resources. The Company focuses on discovery and development of zinc-lead-silver deposits within the Broken Hill district. It has a portfolio of highly prospective ground with drill-ready targets focused on high grade zinc-lead-silver and a pipeline of prospects moving toward the drill assessment stage. The Company controls fourteen mineral exploration tenements covering an area of 1,170 square kilometers in the district immediately surrounding the supergiant sediment-hosted Broken Hill deposit. The Company focused on its tenements close to the Broken Hill mine corridor, with main drilling activities at Balaclava, Stephens Trig and Razorback West. Its targets include Stephens Trig Corridor, Razorback West Corridor, Native Dog and Balaclava.

South32 Limited is a metals and mining company. The Company's segments include Worsley Alumina, which includes an integrated bauxite mine and alumina refinery in Western Australia; South Africa Aluminium, which includes an aluminum smelter in Richards Bay; Brazil Alumina, which includes an alumina refinery in Brazil; Mozal Aluminium, including an aluminum smelter in Mozambique; South Africa Energy Coal, including open-cut and underground energy coal mines and processing operations in South Africa; Illawarra Metallurgical Coal, which includes underground metallurgical coal mines in New South Wales; Australia Manganese, which produces manganese ore in the Northern Territory and manganese alloys in Tasmania; South Africa Manganese, which produces manganese ore and alloy in South Africa; Cerro Matoso, including an integrated laterite ferronickel mining and smelting complex in Colombia, and Cannington, including silver, lead and zinc mine in Queensland.

Senetas Corporation Limited is a developer and manufacturer of multi-certified, defense-grade data encryption hardware. The Company's principal activities include the sale of information technology security products providing network data security solutions to businesses and governments. It operates through the product division segment. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and New Zealand, the United States and Europe. Its products include CN Series Layer 2 Encryptors; Encryption Key Management; CM7 Network Encryption Management; GlobalCare Maintenance & Support, and SureDrop - Secure File Share & Sync. It manufactures encryptors for Layer 2 Carrier Ethernet, metro and wide area networks, which are used by governments, defense forces, commercial and industrial organizations, global cloud and data center service providers in approximately 35 countries. It designs, develops and manufactures in Australia.

Stream Group Limited, formerly LongReach Group Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the management of insurance claims. The Company is also engaged in the development of software and online product distribution platform. The Company's segments include Australia, New Zealand and the United Kingdom. Its Australia segment includes the main business in Australia, as well as the operating results of the Company's Australian software development entities, including Insurtech Systems Pty Ltd, Qusol Pty Ltd and Stream Connect. The Company's New Zealand segment includes the results of Stream Group N.Z. Pty Ltd. The Company's United Kingdom segment includes the results of Stream Claim Services Limited. It offers various services, including general claims services, such as building, contents and motor, and expertise services, such as construction, engineering, financial risk, major loss, marine, investigations, liability and risk services.

Segue Resources Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company is engaged in identification of potential mining assets for acquisition and development, and raising capital to fund those opportunities. Its projects include Plumridge Nickel Project, which is located in the Fraser Range Province of Western Australia. It has a 100% interest in approximately three exploration licenses in the Fraser Range, which are prospective for gold mineralization. The Company's exploration licenses are located immediately to the west of the Plumridge Nickel Project. Its Deralinya Project is in the southern portion of the Fraser Range Province. Its Gascoyne Lithium Project is located over 250 kilometers east of Carnarvon, and Pardoo Project is located 100 kilometers east of Port Hedland in the Pilbara region and is prospective for magmatic nickel-copper sulfides and a resource of over 45 metric tons at approximately 0.3% Nickel and over 0.13% copper.

Seafarms Group Limited is engaged in aquaculture project development, aquaculture operations, carbon project management, the provision of environmental services (advisory in ecosystem offsets and carbon farming projects) and trading environmental credits. The Company operates through three segments: Aquaculture, which is engaged in the development of a land-based aquaculture project in Northern Australia by Project Sea Dragon Pty Ltd and prawn aquaculture operations in North Queensland; Carbon Services, which is engaged in the establishment and management of carbon sinks and re-vegetation projects throughout Australia, including the provision of abatement certificates generated from accredited forest carbon sinks owned by the Company and its customers, and trading in environmental credits; and Other, which is the aggregation of the Company's other segments. The Company produces over two types of prawns, such as banana and black tigers, which are sold under Crystal Bay Prawns brand.

Soon Mining Limited is a mineral exploration company, which is formed to acquire and develop exploration projects. The Company's principal activity includes the contract for the acquisition of Ocean Blue International Limited and its gold mining project in Ghana, West Africa. The Company is a West African gold explorer engaged in developing the Kwahu Praso Gold Concession (Project). The Kwahu Praso Gold Project is located at the northeastern margin of the Ashanti Belt. The Kwahu Praso Gold Project is located near Kwahu Praso in the Kwahu South District in the eastern region of Ghana. The Kwahu Praso Gold Project is located approximately 130 kilometers northwest of Accra and over 20 kilometers west of Nkawkaw. The Kwahu Praso Gold Project covers an area of approximately 82.74 square kilometers, including over 60 square kilometers within the mining lease area and the surrounding approximately 19.74 square kilometers retained under a prospecting license.

Silver Chef Limited is a commercial equipment rental and financing company. The Company provides flexible equipment funding solutions to small and medium sized businesses. The Company operates through two segments, which include Silver Chef (Hospitality) and GoGetta. Silver Chef (Hospitality) provides commercial equipment rental and financing solutions to small and medium sized businesses in the hospitality industry. Silver Chef (Hospitality) caters to Hospitality business, including coffee shops, takeaway stores, independently owned restaurants and franchises, and operates in Australia, New Zealand and Canada. GoGetta provides commercial equipment rental and financing solutions to small and medium sized businesses in industries other than the hospitality industry. GoGetta provides flexible funding solutions to a range of industry sectors, including transport, light commercial vehicle and light construction sectors. GoGetta operates in Australia.

Select Harvests Limited is an almond producer and marketer. The Company's principal activities are processing, packaging, marketing and distribution of edible nuts, dried fruits, seeds, and a range of natural health foods, and the growing, processing and sale of almonds to the food industry from company owned almond orchards, the provision of management services to external owners of almond orchards, including orchard development, tree supply, farm management, land rental and irrigation infrastructure, and the marketing and selling of almonds. Its segments include Food Division, which processes, markets and distributes edible nuts, dried fruits, seeds, and a range of natural health foods, and Almond Division, which grows, processes and sells almonds to the food industry from company owned almond orchards, and provides a range of management services to external owners of almond orchards, including orchard development, land and irrigation infrastructure rental, and the sale of almonds.

Sprintex Limited manufactures and distributes a range of Sprintex superchargers. The Company focuses on developing Sprintex twin-screw supercharger and supercharger systems incorporating the Sprintex twin screw supercharger. The Company offers products for Jeeps, Dodge Challenger V6, Chrysler 300 C/S V6, RAM 1500 V6, Mini Cooper S, FT86/FRS/BRZ and Honda. The Company's products include JEEP WRANGLER JK 3.6L V6 Pentastar, JEEP WRANGLER JK 3.8L V6, JEEP WRANGLER TJ 4.0L V6, DODGE CHALLENGER 3.6L V6 Pentastar, CHRYSLER 300 3.6L V6 Pentastar, RAM 1500 3.6L V6 Pentastar, MINI COOPER S SUPERCHARGER, HONDA CRZ 1.5 L, and others. The Company's product range encompasses approximately 10 systems. The Company offers solution for V6 applications across the world. Its production facility is located in Malaysia in the Glenmarie area of Shah Alam, Selangor. Its subsidiaries include Sprintex Australasia Pty Limited, AAC Property Investments Pty Ltd and Sprintex USA, Inc.

Sabre Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company is engaged in the development and exploration of its mineral interests in Namibia. It holds interest in Otavi Mountain Land project located in northern Namibia, in southern Africa. The Otavi Mountain Land project includes two granted tenements: EPL 3540 and EPL 3542, which cover approximately 700 square kilometers. EPL 3540 covers approximately 220 square kilometers and is over 40 kilometers of the strike extents of the Kombat Copper Trend. Its exploration is focused on the area to the east of the Kombat mine around the Guchab Mining Centre. It holds interest in zinc-lead and copper targets on the Border-Toggenburg and Kombat Corridors under the Otavi Mountain Land project. The Kombat Corridor is the 40 kilometer long lineament of copper mineralization extending east west from Baltika in the west, through Gross Otavi and the Kombat copper mine. It focuses on copper exploration at the Guchab South Prospect.

Santana Minerals Limited is focused on precious metals exploration in Mexico. The Company is principally engaged in the exploration for gold, silver and base metals and the investigation of projects involving those activities with the objective of identifying, developing and exploiting economic mineral deposits. The Company holds interest in the Namiquipa Project in Chihuahua State of Mexico and Cuitaboca Project in Sinaloa State of Mexico. The Cuitaboca Project is located in the State of Sinaloa, Mexico. The Company's Cuitaboca Project is located approximately 100 kilometers north east of the city of Los Mochis and covers an area of approximately 5,500 hectares. The Company's Namiquipa silver project is located within three mineral concessions totaling approximately 2,400 hectares and is approximately 145 kilometers west-northwest of Chihuahua City in Chihuahua State.

Skydive the Beach Group Limited is an adventure tourism and leisure company. The Company is engaged in the provision of skydiving experiences to the public through its various offerings, such as tandem skydiving, night tandem skydiving, learn to skydive courses and skydive skill development camps. The Company operates through two segments: Australia and New Zealand. The Company operates approximately 10 drop zones in Australia and over two in New Zealand. In Australia, the skydiving drop zones are across New South Wales, Queensland, Victoria and Western Australia, while the two New Zealand skydiving drop zones are located in Queenstown and Glenorchy. Its subsidiaries include Aircraft Maintenance Centre Pty Ltd, Australia Skydive Pty Ltd, B & B No 2 Pty Ltd, Skydive Holdings Pty Ltd, Skydive the Beach and Beyond Airlie Beach Pty Ltd, Skydive the Beach and Beyond BB Pty Ltd, Skydive the Beach and Beyond Central Coast Pty Ltd, Skydive Queenstown Limited and Skydive Glenorchy Limited.

Sonic Healthcare Limited is a healthcare company. The Company is focused on services in medical diagnostics and multidisciplinary medical practices. The Company provides laboratory and radiology services to medical practitioners, hospitals, community health services, and their collective patients. The Company's segments include Laboratory, Imaging and Other. The Laboratory segment includes pathology/clinical laboratory services provided in Australia, New Zealand, the United Kingdom, the United States, Germany, Switzerland, Belgium and Ireland. The Imaging segment provides radiology and diagnostic imaging services in Australia. The Other segment includes the corporate office function, medical center operations and occupational health services, and other minor operations. The Company's services include laboratory medicine/pathology, radiology, medical centers/primary care, occupational and general medicine, lifescreen, clinical trials, and food and water testing.

Specialty Fashion Group Limited is a retailer of women's fashion in Australasia. The Company's brands include Millers, Crossroads, Katies, Autograph, City Chic and Rivers. Its Millers brand operates approximately 350 stores. The Katies range delivers clothing for all occasions, from key fashion pieces and work wear to loungewear and denim. Its Autograph specializes in designing, fitting and styling plus-size women in sizes 14 to 26. Crossroads' offerings include in sizes 8 to 22 for woman. Rivers is a men's, women's and children's clothing and footwear retailer with over 160 stores. The Company reaches over three million members through e-mail. It operates approximately 1,080 physical sites in Australia, New Zealand, South Africa and the United States. In addition, it operates over 15 concession locations in Myer. Its subsidiaries include Miller's Fashion Club (QLD) Pty Limited, Miller's Fashion Club (VIC) Pty Limited, Yip Eks Pty Limited and Specialty Fashion Group USA Incorporated.

Shriro Holdings Limited is a kitchen appliances and consumer products marketing and distribution company operating in Australia and New Zealand. The Company markets and distributes a range of products under its own brands, including Omega, Robinhood, Everdue and Omega Altise, and third-party brands, such as Casio, Blanco and Pioneer. The Company's segments include Kitchen Appliances and Consumer products. The Kitchen Appliance segment offers products, including ovens, cooktops, rangehoods, dishwashers, sinks, taps, ironing systems, laundry tubs, waste disposal and ducting solutions. The Consumer Products segment offers products, including watches, calculators, electronic musical instruments, projectors, point of sale terminals, cameras, barbeques, heaters, fans, air purifiers/dehumidifiers, fashion, car audio, professional disc jockey (DJ), amplifiers and high fidelity (Hi-Fi) products and speakers. The Company has over 1,000 in-store displays in retailer stores.

Shree Minerals Limited is an Australia-based exploration and development company. The Company's principal activities include mineral exploration, development and mining. The Company has a portfolio of projects within Tasmania. The Company has exploration interests in iron, gold, and base metals. The Company is focused on developing its Nelson Bay River Iron Project. The Nelson Bay River Iron Project is situated in mineral province of North West Tasmania. The Nelson Bay River Iron Project covers a license area of approximately 93 square kilometers and has a Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) resource of 12.7 Metric Ton at 36.1% iron (Fe). The Nelson Bay Iron Ore Project (ELs 41/2004 & 54/2008) covers the Nelson Bay Magnetite deposit with Inferred Mineral Resources. The Mt Sorell tenement (EL 42/2008) hosts an untested base metal soil anomaly at the southern end of the Cambrian-aged Mount Read Volcanic base metal province, which hosts the Rosebery, Hellyer and Mount Lyell mines.

Spookfish Limited, formerly White Star Resources Limited, is engaged in the development and commercialization of geospatial imagery products and services. The Company's segment operates through research, development and construction of technology for the purpose of capturing, processing and distributing geospatial imagery. The Company's Spookfish capture platform is designed to capture high-resolution imagery at higher altitudes than providers of comparable imagery. The Company's Spookfish camera system is a high-resolution ortho and oblique camera system. The Company's system is designed to provide high resolution True Orthophotos, True three-dimensional (3D) Models, Near Infra-Red imagery and terrain data all from a single capture program. The Company offers solutions to the industries, including agriculture and forestry, building and construction, defense and intelligence, energy, environment, insurance, media, resources, retail and utilities.

Sacgasco Limited (SGC), formerly Australian Oil Company Limited, is an Australia-based energy company focused on conventional oil and gas exploration, development and production onshore California. The Company is a conventional natural gas developer. The Company's segment is oil and gas exploration and appraisal. The Company has a portfolio of conventional gas prospects in the Sacramento Basin. The Company's Sacramento Basin includes Dempsey Prospect, Alvares Prospect, California AMI Prospects, Rancho-Capay Gas Field, Los Medanos Gas Field and Mankins Ranch Oil Project. It holds working interest in the Dempsey Conventional Gas Prospect, which is in appraisal/exploration-stage. Its Alvares Conventional Gas Prospect is in appraisal stage. The Alvares conventional gas prospect is located close to large natural gas pipelines and is on over 30 miles from the geologically similar multi-trillion cubic feet (Tcf) Tulainyo Project.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Sandon Capital Investments Limited is an investment company. The Company is engaged in investing activities, including cash, term deposits and equity investments. The Company also provides corporate advisory services to select wholesale clients. The Company invests its funds on behalf of wholesale clients, and advised shareholders, in a range of listed companies, funds and trusts. The Company will seek to invest in securities, which Sandon Capital Pty Ltd (the Manager) considers to be under-valued and where the Manager considers there to be opportunity to encourage changes to unlock what the Manager has identified as intrinsic value. The Manager may also invest, from time to time, in market-based investment opportunities, such as placements, merger arbitrage and other investments it considers appropriate. Sandon Capital Pty Ltd is the investment manager of the Company.

Slater and Gordon Limited is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in operating legal practices in Australia and the United Kingdom. The Company operates in three segments: Slater and Gordon Australia (AUS), Slater and Gordon UK (SGL UK), and Slater Gordon Solutions (SGS). The AUS segment includes the Company and its subsidiaries in Australia. The AUS segment conducts a range of legal services within the geographical area of Australia. The SGL UK segment conducts a range of personal injury and general law legal services in the United Kingdom. The SGS segment offers legal services relating to road traffic accidents, employee liability and noise induced hearing loss. The SGS segment also provides complementary services in health and motor services. The Company's services include personal legal services, and business and specialized litigation services, and claims, including origination, assessment and resolution of personal injury claims.

Schaffer Corporation Limited is an industrial company. The Company operates in four segments, which include Automotive Leather, Building Materials, Investment Property and Gosh Capital. The Automotive Leather segment is a manufacturer and supplier of leather in the automotive industries. The Building Materials segment consists of Delta Corporation Limited and Urbanstone Pty. Ltd., and produces and sells concrete paving, pre-cast and pre-stressed concrete elements, and natural and reconstituted limestone products. The Investment Property segment includes the Company's share of syndicated property investments and the investment property of the Company. The activities of the Investment Property segment include the leasing of office and retail properties, and the development and sale of property assets. The Gosh Capital segment manages the assets of the Gosh Leather business, and invests profits earned from those assets in investment opportunities.

SciGen Ltd is a biotechnology company. The Company, along with its subsidiaries, is involved in the sales, marketing and development of pharmaceutical and recombinant technology derived products. Its geographical segments include Singapore, involving in corporate office functions and sales and marketing; Australia, Korea, Thailand, Philippines, engaging in sales and marketing activities; China, engaging in regulatory activities, and Others, involving operations carried on in Indonesia, Pakistan, Vietnam, Hong Kong, Myanmar, Malaysia and profit sharing income on sale of insulin. Its portfolio consists of biosimilar products, such as rhuman growth hormone and rhuman insulin. The Company offers a range of products, including SciTropin A, SciBenclamide, SciLodipine, SciLosar, SciLin, SciTrozole, Heri Injection, Zinc-S, Zinc-I, Gensupen, Insupen, Zonegran, Alsense and SciLocyte. In addition, the Company in-licenses and distributes pharmaceutical products and medical devices.

Skin Elements Limited is engaged in the formulation, development, production and test marketing in Australia and internationally of the Company's Soleo Organics natural sunscreen. The Company focuses on its micronized zinc technology. Soleo is made using a range of natural and organic ingredients. Soleo sunscreen contains natural oils, botanical extracts and antioxidants. Soleo Organics All Natural Sunscreen is an alternative to synthetics based sunscreens. Soleo Organics All Natural Sunscreen protects from both ultraviolet-A (UV-A) and UV-B solar radiation. Soleo Organics All Natural Sunscreen is water resistant for over three hours. Soleo does not have chemical UV-absorbers, titanium dioxide, synthetic preservatives, paraben, Para-aminobenzoic acid (PABA), petrochemicals, benzoates, Sodium Lauryl Sulfate (SLS) and artificial colors or fragrances. The Soleo packaging material and container vessel are made from recyclable material. The contents of Soleo are biodegradable.

Spring FG Limited is engaged in the provision of financial planning and investment advice and related product sales, and accounting and taxation services. The Company's segments include Financial planning, investment advice and product sales, and Accounting and tax services. The Company's Financial planning, investment advice and product sales segment provides a range of financial services, including financial planning in self-managed superannuation funds (SMSFs), and direct and SMSF residential real estate investment. Its Accounting and tax services segment provides a range of accounting and taxation advice and solutions for investors and small to medium businesses. The Company offers various services, including financial advice, investment advice, risk management, and tax and accounting. The Company operates a range of financial technology services, including its spring around the clock personal financial management and mysuper around the clock SMSF platforms.

Silex Systems Limited is a research and development company. The Company is focused on the development and commercialization of its primary asset, the Separation of Isotopes by Laser EXcitation (SILEX) laser uranium enrichment technology. It operates in the Silex Systems segment. It is focused on the delivery of the SILEX laser enrichment technology. The SILEX Technology is a laser-based process that has the potential to separate uranium isotopes, as well as other various elements. It has licensed SILEX technology exclusively to GE-Hitachi Global Laser Enrichment LLC in the United States. It has an interest in semiconductor technology known as Rare Earth Oxide (cREO) technology, which is exclusively licensed to IQE Plc. IQE Plc is progressing the cREO technology towards commercial deployment in various semiconductor products, such as power electronics and wireless radio frequency (RF) communications chips.

Sims Metal Management Limited is a metals and electronics recycler. The Company is engaged in the buying, processing and selling of ferrous and non-ferrous recycled metals and the provision of solutions for the disposal of post-consumer electronic products, including information technology (IT) assets recycled for commercial customers. The Company operates through four segments: North America Metals, Australia/New Zealand (ANZ) Metals, Europe Metals and Global E-Recycling. The Company's product groups include ferrous secondary recycling, non-ferrous secondary recycling, recycling solutions, and secondary processing and other services. Its ferrous secondary recycling includes the collection, processing and trading of iron and steel secondary raw material. Its non-ferrous secondary recycling includes the collection, processing and trading of other metal alloys and residues, principally aluminum, lead, copper, zinc and nickel bearing materials.

St George Mining Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company holds interest in the East Laverton Project located in the North-Eastern Goldfields region of Western Australia. The East Laverton Project covers over 2,100 square kilometers. The East Laverton Project includes approximately three ultramafic-greenstone belts with a total strike length of more than 130 kilometers. The East Laverton Project is located over 230 kilometers north-east of Kalgoorlie in the eastern margin of the Yilgarn Craton. It holds interest in Mt Alexander Project, which is located approximately 120 kilometers to the south-southwest of nickel projects in the Agnew-Wiluna Belt. It also holds interest in Hawaii Project, which is located over 70 kilometers southwest of Leinster in the Agnew-Wiluna Belt. It holds interest in Lake Minigwal Project, which covers a concealed greenstone belt that is prospective for both gold and nickel sulfhides, and has a tenement area of over 300 square kilometers.

Smartgroup Corporation Ltd is an Australia-based salary packaging specialist for government, health and corporate sectors. The Company's principal activities consist of outsourced administration, primarily salary packaging, software, distribution and group services and fleet management services. The provision of salary packaging services involves the Company's holding funds in a fiduciary capacity. The Company's segments include outsourced administration; vehicle services, and software, distribution and group services (SDGS). Its outsourced administration segment consists of outsourced salary packaging services, which includes novated leasing and the marketing of salary packaging debit cards. The Company's vehicle services segment provides end-to-end fleet management services. Its SDGS segment provides salary packaging software solutions, distribution of vehicle insurances and workface management software to the healthcare industry.

Stone Resources Australia Limited (SRAL) is an Australia-based gold company. The Company operates in the mineral exploration segment. It focuses on the drilling and exploration on its Northern leases on the Ben Hur M38/339 (approximately 19,550 meters) and Cork Tree Well M38/346 (approximately 12,565 meters) areas. The Company has resources in Alpha and Beta in the Southern tenement, and Epsilon and Delta in the Northern tenements. Its Cork Tree Well project includes about 150 square kilometers of tenements around the old Cork Tree Well Mine. It owns and controls the Alpha gold deposit, which is contained in the tenement package of M38/1058, M38/1056, M38/1057, M38/968 and P38/3834, located approximately 40 kilometers East South-East of Laverton in Western Australia. Its Ben Hur deposit is situated inside the M38/339 lease, which is a northern tenement of the Company. The Company has not generated any revenues.

Sky Network Television Limited is an entertainment company. The Company delivers a range of content to its customers, including movies, television series, music, sports, documentaries and news. The Company operates as a provider of multi-channel, pay television and free-to-air television services in New Zealand. The Company's subsidiaries include SKY DMX Music Limited, which is engaged in operating the SKY DMX music business; SKY Ventures Limited, which provides investment and sponsorship in the field of information and broadcast technology; Outside Broadcasting Limited, which is engaged in providing mobile on-site broadcasting facilities and services; Screen Enterprises Limited, which is engaged in operating the FATSO digital versatile disc (DVD) and Blu-ray rental business; Igloo Limited, which is engaged in providing pay television service, and Believe It Or Not Limited, which is engaged in providing quizzes for the hotel entertainment industry.

Simonds Group Limited is engaged in the design and construction of residential dwellings, the development of residential land and providing registered training courses. The Company's segments include Residential Construction, which includes activities related to contracts for residential home construction, speculative home building and the building of display home inventory; Registered training, which includes the activities of registered training provided by House of Learning Pty Ltd, and Land development, which includes the activities related to the land developments and sales. It offers services through Simonds Homes in Victoria, Queensland, New South Wales and South Australia. Its Builders Academy Australia (BAA) is a learning company that offers nationally accredited qualifications for the building and construction industry. BAA has a range of student base, which includes pre-apprentices and apprentices; tradespeople, and non-tradespeople.

SmartTrans Holdings Limited is a technology and software company. It provides a mobile and Internet software systems and applications across China and Australia. In China, the Company operates its mobile and online business activities, including Direct Carrier Billing; Direct Subscription Billing; provision of e-commerce services, such as payment processing, digital marketing, commission-based sales, cross border payment settlement, and technical and support services for lotteries billing. Within Australia, the Company provides mobile and online software and services in the transport and logistics area. The Company is exploring opportunities to expand its services in the provision of data products in China servicing the Internet of Things market by providing connectivity to the Internet for vehicles and other machines. Sm@rtTrans Limited, E-Trans Pty Ltd, SmartTrans Technology (Beijing) Ltd, Smartrans (HK) Ltd and Digi 8 Limited are the subsidiaries of the Company.

The Star Entertainment Group Limited, formerly Echo Entertainment Group Limited, operates in the gaming, entertainment and hospitality industries. The Company owns and operates The Star Sydney (The Star Sydney); Treasury Casino and Hotel, Brisbane (Treasury Brisbane), and Jupiters Hotel and Casino, Gold Coast (Gold Coast). The Company's segments include The Star Sydney, Gold Coast and Treasury Brisbane. The Star Sydney comprises The Star Sydney's casino operations, including hotels, apartment complex, restaurants, bars and night club. The Gold Coast segment includes Jupiters' casino operations, including hotel, theatre, restaurants and bars. The Treasury Brisbane segment includes Treasury's casino operations, including hotel, restaurants and bars. The Company also manages the Gold Coast Convention and Exhibition Centre on behalf of the Queensland Government. The Company also owns Broadbeach Island on which the Gold Coast casino is located.

Stockland Corporation Limited is a diversified property company. The Company owns, manages and develops shopping centers, logistics centers, business parks, office buildings, residential communities and retirement living villages. It operates through four segments: Commercial Property, Residential, Retirement Living and Other. Its Commercial Property segment invests in, develops and manages retail, office and logistic and business park properties. Its Residential segment delivers a range of master planned and mixed use residential communities in growth areas, townhouses and apartments in general metropolitan areas. It has approximately 60 communities across New South Wales, Queensland, Victoria and Western Australia. It holds over 76,800 lots in its portfolio. Its Retirement Living segment designs, develops and manages communities for retirees. It has over 9,600 units in approximately 70 villages across over five states and the Australian Capital Territory.

Stanmore Coal Limited is a coal mining company. The Company's principal activities include the development of operation of coal mines in Queensland, Australia. The Company's segments include Isaac Plains Coal Mine, which includes the operation of the Isaac Plains Coal Mine, including the Isaac Plains East project, and All Other Segments, which includes all other exploration and development coal assets. The Company holds interests in various tenements, such as The Range, New Cambria, Belview, Tennyson, Belview North, Clifford West, Clifford East, Tennyson South, Lilyvale, Belview East and Mackenzie. The Isaac Plains project is located in Moranbah. The Belview, Mackenzie, New Cambria, Tennyson and Lilyvale projects are located in Bowen Basin. The Range and Clifford projects are located in Surat Basin.

Salmat Limited is engaged in marketing services business. The Company's segments include Media+ Digital and Contact segment. The Company's Media+ Digital segment delivers targeted and integrated communications throughout all digital and traditional channels. Its solutions enable clients to interact and engage with their customers through national letterbox distribution, digital catalogues, pre-shopping Website Lasoo, e-commerce, search, such as search engine optimization (SEO), small and medium-sized enterprises (SME) and digital advertising, e-mail and short message service (SMS) marketing. Its contact segment provides solution to customers' lifetime value using inbound and outbound voice, e-mail, Web-chat, SMS, social-media, speech technology and automation solutions. Its Subsidiaries include Salmat Contact Solutions Australia Limited, Salmat Contact Solutions New Zealand Limited, Netstarter Pty Limited, Fuse Pty Limited and Salmat Digital Pty Limited.

Synlait Milk Limited is a dairy processing company. The Company is engaged in manufacturing of nutritional solutions, value added products and specialty ingredients. It manufactures and sells milk powder and milk powder-related products. It manufactures specialized milk powders for infant formula manufacture and base pediatric powders for blending into finished infant formula, and finished infant formula products. Its products include infant and adult nutritional formulations, functional food ingredients and specialized products. The infant nutritional powder is a nutritional product. The ingredient products include whole milk powder, skim milk powder and anhydrous milk fat. The specialty product is synlait lactoferrin. The Company has 140,000 metric tons of annual production capacity and packages upto 30,000 metric tons of canned infant formula. It exports its products around the world to Asia, Middle East and Africa and other regions. Its subsidiary is Synlait Milk Finance Limited.

Strategic Energy Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration for minerals in Australia. The Company's properties include the Saxby Gold Project, the Myall Creek and Spencer copper projects, the Falcon Bridge nickel project and the Casteron nickel-copper project. The Saxby Project is located over 170 kilometers north northeast of Cloncurry in the Gulf Country of northwest Queensland. The Myall Creek and Spencer copper projects are located on the west coast of the Spencer Gulf. The Falcon Bridge nickel project covers an area of approximately 140 square kilometers in the north east of Western Australia's Archaean Yilgarn Craton. The Casteron nickel-copper project is located approximately 350 kilometers west of Melbourne, Victoria. The Myall Creek and Spencer copper projects cover approximately 700 square kilometers of the Olympic Copper Gold Province of the eastern Gawler Craton. The Saxby Project contains precious and base metal prospects.

SmartPay Holdings Limited is a provider of technology products, services and software to merchants and retailers. The Company designs, develops and implements payment solutions for customers in New Zealand and Australia. It offers a range of payment and data management solutions for retail, business payment and transactional processing requirements. The Company is the electronic funds transfer at point of sale (EFTPOS) terminal provider throughout Australia. It licenses its technologies to third parties. The Company is a supplier of taxi payment solutions in New Zealand. The Company offers wireless EFTPOS Machines that allow accepting a credit card onsite. Its stationary countertop solutions are capable of connecting through the Internet. Its EFTPOS terminals are available for hire for a trade show on a short term lease. The Company has over 45,000 EFTPOS terminals throughout Australia and New Zealand, servicing the payment needs of approximately 18,000 merchants.

Skyland Petroleum Limited, formerly MUI Corporation Limited, is an Australia-based exploration and production company that has an interest in, and is negotiating the acquisition of, a portfolio of oil and gas assets. The Company is engaged in the business of oil and gas exploration and development. The Company's primary geographical focus is on assets in the states of the former Soviet Union. The Company is engaged in developing opportunities in Tajikistan and Georgia. The Company has projects in Tajikistan, Georgia and East Siberia.

Spark Infrastructure Group is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in investment in regulated electricity distribution and transmission businesses in Australia. The Company operates through four segments: Victoria Power Networks, SA Power Networks, TransGrid and Other. Victoria Power Networks holds interest in two electricity distribution businesses in Victoria, which include CitiPower and Powercor. SA Power Networks holds interest in the electricity distribution business in South Australia and supplies energy to approximately 847,000 customers. TransGrid holds interest in the electricity transmission business in New South Wales, which include NSW Electricity Networks Assets Holdings Trust (NSW Electricity Networks Assets) and NSW Electricity Networks Operations Holdings Trust (NSW Electricity Networks Operations). Other represents the economic interest in DUET Group. The Company also invests in regulated water and sewerage assets.

Saunders International Limited is engaged in the design, construction and maintenance of steel storage tanks and the project management of ancillary facilities. The Company provides facilities maintenance and delivers asset services for customers involved in the oil and gas, mining, water infrastructure and other industrial, resource, government and commercial activities. It is also involved in design, construction and maintenance of bulk storage tanks and reservoirs in Australia. It provides a range of engineering services for bulk liquid storage facilities from front end engineering design (FEED) through to construction and commissioning. It is involved in the construction of chemical tanks, and coal bins and thickener tanks, among others. It engages in the engineering, procurement and construction of water storage facilities and petrochemical plants, and provision of facility maintenance services, including repair and maintenance of ground storage tanks, and floor replacements.

SMS Management & Technology Limited provides a range of services across business and information technology (IT) advisory, technology solutions, managed services and contract recruitment, to assist businesses to manage their use of people, processes and technology. The Company operates in two segments, which include SMS Consulting and M&T Resources. The SMS Consulting segment offers management and technology related business services, including advisory, which includes digital business strategy and agile transformation, among others; solutions, which include customer solutions, and process and productivity solutions, among others, and managed services, which include managed application services and managed infrastructure services, among others. The M&T Resources segment offers recruitment and contract labor in the IT sector, including permanent recruitment and contract recruitment. The Company provides its services in Australia and Asia Pacific.

Sigma Pharmaceuticals Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution business. The Company delivers pharmacies across Australia. The Company also manages and promotes a range of over-the-counter private and exclusive label products made available to brand member customers, as well as a generic range of private label products under the Pharmacy Care range. The Company, through its subsidiary, Central Healthcare Services (CHS), operates in the hospital pharmaceutical distribution market. The Company has pharmacy-led network in Australia, including over 700 retail brand members representing various brands, such as Amcal, Guardian, PharmaSave, Chemist King and Discount Drugstores (DDS). It offers third party logistics (3PL) and fourth party logistics (4PL) services, which include inventory management, centralized and decentralized warehousing, debtor management and customer service facilities.

SG Fleet Group Limited offers motor vehicle fleet management, vehicle leasing, consumer vehicle finance and salary packaging services. The Company's segments include Australia, New Zealand, United Kingdom and Corporate. The Company's products include driversafety intelligence, Bookingintelligence, vehicle accessories, Fleetintelligence 2.0, Roadside Assistance service, toll management service, fuel management program, and incident and accident management service. The Company's fleet management services include Maintenance plans, Registration renewal, Vehicle acquisition and disposal, Fines management and Driver training. The Company's specialist Commercial division offers truck, plant and materials handling fleet management and leasing solutions. The Company offers Fleet Management and Leasing Services for Government Organizations, Novated Leases for Government Employees and Salary Packaging for Government Employees. The Company also has an application for iPhone and Android.

Summerset Group Holdings Limited is a New Zealand-based company, which is engaged in operating retirement villages and development of villages. The Company operates through the provision of integrated retirement villages segment. The Company provides a continuum of care. Its continuum of care offers a range of living options, from independent living in a villa, apartment or townhouse, to care apartments, rest home and hospital level care. It provides both privately funded respite services and respite service funded through the Ministry of Health. It caters for people with some forms of dementia. It has approximately 2,240 total retirement units in portfolio. Its subsidiaries include Summerset Care Limited, Summerset Holdings Limited, Summerset LTI Trustees Limited, Summerset Management Group Limited, Summerset Properties Limited, Summerset Villages (Hamilton) Limited, Summerset Villages (New Plymouth) Limited and Welhom Developments Limited, among others.
