Shenhua International Limited is engaged in the manufacture and distribution of medium to high quality textiles and finished products using the same fabrics, which are suitable for internal furnishing and decorative purposes in domestic and commercial settings. It manufactures and sells curtains and bedding products. The Company operates in Benin, Brazil, France, Iran, Italy, Nigeria, Russia, South Africa, Uganda, the United Kingdom and other countries.

Sinovus Mining Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in exploration and mining in china. The Company holds interest in the Xiangguang Silver Project. The Company is evaluating new project and investment opportunities, including working capital requirements.

Stokes Limited, formerly Stokes (Australasia) Limited, is engaged in the design, distribution and installation of lighting and audio visual products. The Company provides light emitting diode (LED) lighting products, audio visual solutions and accessories to commercial electrical industry. It operates in the segment of technology products in Australia. It delivers its solutions to commercial, education, retail, finance and construction markets. Its audiovisual solutions include display and projector systems; interactive whiteboards; specialist controlled lighting; video and audio conferencing; touch panel control; collaboration technology products; service, maintenance and support contracts, and public address systems. Its lighting and building automation solutions include lighting design engineering and solutions; lighting control management; LED lighting solutions; architectural LED light panels; service, support and maintenance services, and lighting product recommendations.

Sandfire Resources NL is a mining and exploration company. The Company's principal activities are production and sale of copper, gold and silver from its DeGrussa Mine in Western Australia, and exploration and evaluation of mineral tenements and projects in Australia and overseas. It has two segments: The DeGrussa Copper Mine and Exploration and evaluation. The DeGrussa Copper Mine is a copper-gold mine located in the Bryah Basin mineral province of Western Australia, approximately 900 kilometers north-east of Perth and 150 kilometers north of Meekatharra. The DeGrussa Copper Mine generates revenue from the sale of copper-gold products to customers in Asia. The Exploration and evaluation segment includes exploration and evaluation of the mineral tenements in Australia and overseas, including exploring for repeats of DeGrussa Volcanogenic Massive Sulfide (VMS) mineralized system at the Doolgunna Project and its investment in Tintina Resources Inc and WCB Resources Ltd.

Summit Resources Limited is engaged in exploration and evaluation of uranium projects in Queensland, Australia. The Company covers approximately 2,190 square kilometers of tenements over three major project areas centered in the city of Mount Isa in northwest Queensland. The Isa North Project covers over 930 square kilometers, and hosts a number of uranium prospects, including the Valhalla, Odin, Skal and Bikini deposits. The Valhalla uranium deposit is located approximately 40 kilometers north-west of Mount Isa on Exploration Permit for Minerals (EPM) 17514. The Skal uranium deposit is located approximately 32 kilometers north of Mount Isa city on EPM 17519. The Odin uranium deposit is located approximately one kilometer north of Valhalla at EPL17514. The project also includes the Mirrioola, Watta, Warwai and Andersons uranium deposits and smaller uranium prospects. The Company's subsidiary is Summit Resources (Aust) Pty Ltd (SRA).

Supply Network Limited is engaged in the provision of aftermarket parts to the commercial vehicle industry. The Company operates in Australia and New Zealand under the Multispares brand. The Company sells truck and bus parts. It offers a range of services, including parts interpreting, procurement, supply management and problem solving. The Company's subsidiaries include Multispares N.Z. Limited, Multispares Limited, Globac Limited and Supply Network Services Limited.

SECOS Group Limited is engaged in the development of the bioplastics business. The Company has two segments: Manufacturing Division and Distribution Division. The manufacturing segment develops and manufactures sustainable resins derived from renewable resources for the global packaging and plastic products industries and also manufactures cast films for the personal care, hygiene, pet care and medical product industries. The manufacturing segment comprises manufacturing units in China, Malaysia and Australia, which are responsible for distribution and sales of products locally and overseas. The distribution segment develops and distributes the Company's products both locally and overseas. The manufacturing segment also sells products to the distribution segment. The Company is also focused on the waste management solutions market. The Company offers Compostable and Biohybrid product ranges, including Cardia Bioproducts Compostable and Biohybrid bag range.

Syndicated Metals Limited is engaged in mineral exploration and evaluation in relation to its copper mineral resources. The Company holds interests in approximately 1,700 square kilometers of tenement package in the Mount Isa region of North Queensland. Its tenements are located to the northeast and southeast of Mount Isa, namely Northern Hub and Southern Hub areas. The Northern Project Hub includes Barbara Copper Project, which is located approximately 60 kilometers northeast of Mount Isa in North Queensland. The Barbara Project straddles EPM19733 and EPM16112. The Company also focuses on Mt Remarkable Project, which is located between 20 kilometers and 100 kilometers northeast of Mount Isa in North Queensland. Its Blue Star Copper-Gold Project is located over 60 kilometers northeast of Mount Isa in North Queensland. The Company's Southern Hub includes the Fountain Range tenure, which consists of multiple exploration targets, including Dronfield, Duke and Nil Desperandum.

Silver Lake Resources Limited is a gold producing and exploration company. The Company's principal activities include gold mining and processing from the Mount Monger Operation, gold exploration and evaluation projects. Its projects include Mount Monger operation, Murchison operation and Great Southern Gold project. The Mount Monger goldfield is located approximately 50 kilometers southeast of Kalgoorlie, Western Australia. Its operations include Daisy Complex, Cock-eyed Bob, Santa and Imperial/Majestic. The Murchison operation is located southeast of the town of Cue, over 600 kilometers northeast of Perth. Its assets consist of the Tuckabianna, Comet, Moyagee and Eelya projects. The Great Southern Gold Project is a gold exploration project located in the Ravensthorpe region of Western Australia, approximately 200 kilometers west of the Port of Esperance. The Great Southern Project consists of a package of tenements, gold and base metal mineral resources and ore reserves.

Sipa Resources Limited is a gold, base metals and nickel exploration company. The Company is engaged in acquisitions and exploration of mineral tenements. The Company's projects include Kitgum-Pader Project and Paterson North Project. The Kitgum-Pader Project is located in northern Uganda on the north-east margin of the Congo super-craton. The Kitgum-Pader Project includes Akelikongo Nickel prospect, Goma Nickel prospect, and Pamwa Zinc and Lead prospect. The Paterson North Project is located in the northern part of the Paterson Province. The Company's subsidiaries include Sipa Gold Limited, Sipa Copper Pty Ltd, Sipa Exploration NL, Sipa Management Pty Ltd, Ashling Resources NL, Topjest Pty Limited and Sipa Resources (1987) Limited.

Strategic Minerals Corporation NL is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in gold and mineral exploration. The Company's Woolgar Project consists of exploration permits and mining leases in central north Queensland over a window of basement rocks within younger sedimentary cover. The Company has identified over three styles of mineralization at Woolgar Project, including epithermal vein deposits at Sandy Creek, mesothermal veins along the Woolgar Fault Zone and intrusive related mineralization (IRGS) in the Upper Camp, as well as associated alluvial gold. The Company focuses on the mesothermal veins in the Lower Camp area, and reappraises the epithermal and IRGS, as well as mesothermal veining.

Sealink Travel Group Limited is a tourism and transport company. The Company's principal activities include ferry services; tourism cruises, charter cruises and accommodated cruising; coach tours; packaged holidays; travel agency services; tug and barge services, and accommodation and restaurant services at Vivonne Bay. Its segments include Kangaroo Island Sealink, which offers ferry services, retail travel services and accommodation facilities at Vivonne Bay; Captain Cook Cruises, which runs tourist cruises, charter cruises, ferry passenger services on Sydney Harbor; Sealink Queensland, which includes and manages the operations of Sealink Northern Territory, and provides ferry passenger services in Townsville and Darwin; Captain Cook Cruises WA, which includes tourist cruises and ferry operations in Perth; Sealink Gladstone and Sealink SEQ (TSM), which includes ferry and barging operations, and Corporate, which provides finance, administration and risk management support.

Site Group International Limited provides training and education services in Australia and internationally. The Company operates through four business segments: Site Skills Training-Domestic, Site Skills Training-International, Energy Services and Tertiary Education. The Site Skills Training-Domestic segment delivers vocational training and assessment services through approximately five training facilities located at Perth, Gladstone, Darwin, Landsborough and Logan. The Site Skills Training-International segment operates an approximately 300,000 square meter facility at Clark Freeport Zone in the Philippines, allowing the Company to deliver Australian standard training. The Energy Services segment refers to the establishment of specialized energy training and services delivered to the oil and gas industry. The Tertiary Education segment delivers Diploma level courses at various campuses around Australia through complementary brands, such as Captain Cook College and Site Institute.

Sihayo Gold Limited is a mineral exploration company with gold exploration projects in Indonesia. The Company is engaged in the development of the Sihayo Pungkut Gold project (Sihayo Pungkut). Its geographical segments include Australia, Africa, South East Asia, India and Other foreign countries. It holds an interest in the project through 100% ownership of Aberfoyle Pungkut Investments Pte Ltd (API). The Sihayo Pungkut is located in Mandailing Natal, North Sumatra, Indonesia. The Hutabargot Julu prospect is located on the south eastern portion of approximately 11.5 kilometers long Sihayo-Hutabargot mineralized trend. The prospect is over 10 kilometers southeast from the Sihayo-Sambung Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) Compliant Mineral Resource. It has identified combined mineral resources of measured, indicated and inferred approximately 1.4 million ounces of gold, which contains a combined proved and probable ore reserve of over 544,000 ounces at its Sihayo Pungkut project.

Success Global Media Limited (SGM), formerly Success Resources Global Limited, is a seminar company. The Company's principal activity is that it organizes seminars, which promote the business and personal development programs of speakers across Australia, the United States, Singapore, Malaysia and other parts of Asia. The Company operates in one business and five geographical segments, being the provision of personal development seminars and related products and services, covering individual personal, financial, career, health and relationship goals throughout Australia, United States of America, United Kingdom, Singapore and Malaysia. SGM offers a range of educational services and products, including three-dimension (3D) Holograms, Video on Demand (VOD), Virtual Reality, Live Streaming and Augmented Reality. The Company's subsidiaries include Success Resources Australia Pty Ltd, Success Resources Singapore Pte Ltd and Success Resources Malaysia Group Sdn Bhd, among others.

Saferoads Holdings Limited is engaged in the provision of road safety products and solutions primarily to end users. The Company provides products and services, including flexible guide posts and signage; rubber-based traffic calming products, including separation kerbing and wheel stops; variable messaging sign boards; decorative and standard street and major road light poles, and permanent and temporary crash cushions, including bollards and safety barriers. The Company provides safety products to the road users, such as motorists, road construction workers and pedestrians. The Company provides state government departments, local councils, road construction companies and equipment hire companies with a range of products and services designed to direct, protect, inform and illuminate for the public's safety. The Company offers solar lighting solution. It provides light duration of 23-30 hours without charge. It also offers Ironman Hybrid product.

SKYCITY Entertainment Group Limited operates in gaming/entertainment, hotel and convention, hospitality, recreation, and tourism sectors. The Company's segments are SKYCITY Auckland that includes casino operations, hotels and convention, food and beverage, carparking, Sky Tower and other related activities, and excludes international business customers; Rest of New Zealand, which includes its operations at SKYCITY Hamilton, SKYCITY Queenstown and SKYCITY Wharf, and excludes international business customers; Adelaide Casino that includes casino operations and food and beverage, and excludes international business customers; SKYCITY Darwin, which includes casino operations, food and beverage and hotel, and excludes international business customers; International Business, which is made up of international customers sourced mainly from Asia, and Corporate/Group, which includes its interest in the New Zealand international convention Center. It has operations in New Zealand and Australia.

SkyFii Limited (SkyFii) is engaged in the provision of data analytics services. The Company focuses on the development and commercialization of data analytics, marketing and advertisement services to its customers in Australia. It provides analytics and data driven marketing products for bricks and mortar businesses. It focuses on various channels, including analytics, advertising and data services. It offers subscription to services, including guest wireless fidelity (Wi-Fi), analytics and content delivery platform modules. It delivers consultancy engagements on a project-by-project basis to solve objectives, such as Precinct analysis, Competitor impact analysis and impact of new tenants on customer behavior. It focuses on venue deployments within its core retail vertical with a focus on its shopping center penetration in Australia and internationally. It focuses on verticals, including education (universities), councils, hospitals and transit (airports).

Search Party Group Limited, formerly Applabs Technologies Limited, operates an online recruitment marketplace. The Company offers Search Party, which is a recruitment platform that allows employers to find candidates for any role. For employers, the Company allows them to hire staff using the skills and experience of recruiters. For recruiters, the Company offers customer base and improves using the existing database of candidates by focusing on the leads generated through the marketplace. For job seekers, the Company allows them to find the job. The Company allows the employers to shortlist, schedule interviews and even make employment offers. The Company offers STARTER and PROFESSIONAL packs. Search Party supports every stage of the recruitment process online, such as Publishing Candidates, Searching for new hires and Shortlisting candidates. It owns JobAdvisor, which is an Australian employer review site. The Company has offices in Sydney, London and Toronto.

Salt Lake Potash Limited, formerly Wildhorse Energy Limited, is a mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activities include exploration and development of resource projects. Its segments include United States of America and Australia Potash. It holds a range of salt lake brine projects (Projects) in Western Australia, South Australia and the Northern Territory. Its primary focus is the advancement of the Lake Wells' Project, which is located approximately 80 kilometers north of the Great Central Road and over 180 kilometers northeast of Laverton in the West Australian Goldfields. The Project consists of over 1,130 square kilometers of exploration licenses, covering the Lake Wells Playa and the area immediately contiguous to the Lake. It also holds exploration licenses or applications covering all or parts of Lake Irwin and Lake Minigwal and Lake Ballard in Western Australia; Lake Lewis in the Northern Territory, and Lake Macfarlane and Island Lagoon in South Australia.

SRG Limited is a complex services company. The principal activities of the Company are drilling and ground control services, engineering, remedial and construction contracting, and manufacture of post-tensioning components. The Company operates through three segments, which include Construction segment, Mining segment and Corporate segment. The construction segment delivers specialist construction services, specifically post-tensioning, concrete placement and remedial operations. The mining segment services mining clients and specializes in production drilling. Its products include SureLok, Refobar, Macalloy, Concrete Canvas, Rock Mesha, Ground Support Products, Geotechnical Equipment, Ducting and Duct Chairs, and Barrels and Wedges. It offers an array of services, including post-tensioning, bar stressing, cable stays, strand jacking, flat jacks, cylinder jacking, synchronized lifting, bearing inspection and bearing replacement.

Spotless Group Holdings Limited is engaged in the provision of outsourced facility services, laundry and linen services, technical and engineering services, maintenance and asset management services, and refrigeration solutions to various industries in Australia and New Zealand. The Company's segments include facility services, which provides multi-faceted facilities management, cleaning, and catering and food services to a range of industries across Australia and New Zealand, and laundry services, which provides linen and uniform laundry services to a range of customers across Australia and New Zealand. Its geographical segments include Australia and New Zealand. It serves industries, including business and industry, education, defense, leisure, sport and entertainment, health, infrastructure, and laundries among others. It offers services, such as catering and hospitality, grounds and gardens, and cleaning, among others. Its brands include Spotless, AE Smith, EPICURE and MUSTARD.

SurfStitch Group Limited is an online global action sports and youth culture network and online retailer. The principal activities of the Company are online retail and online advertising and publication. The Company's segments include Asia-Pacific Retail, an action sports and youth culture apparel retailer in Australia and New Zealand; Europe Retail, an action sports and youth culture apparel retailer in Europe; North America Retail, an action sports and youth culture apparel retailer in the United States; Media & Production, which includes action sports media, production and utilities platforms, and Surf Hardware, a designer, marketer and distributor of water board sports products and accessories. The Company's e-commerce platforms include SurfStitch.com (Gold Coast, Australia), Surfdome.com (London, the United Kingdom) and SWELL.com (California, the United States). The Company's media platforms include Magicseaweed.com, Stabmag.com and Garageentertainment.com.au.

Shark Mitigation Systems Limited, formerly Sena Resources Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in the design and development of shark mitigation and ocean technology. The Company's segments include SAMS and Clever Buoy. The SAMS is a visual deterrent technology. The SAMS technology is focused on the visual systems of large predatory sharks. The Company licenses the SAMS technology to surfing and ocean apparel brands. The Clever Buoy is a shark detection technology and consumer warning system. The Clever Buoy is a near shore shark detection system that utilizes sonar and a software to identify sharks. It provides alerts to beach safety authorities. The Clever Buoy technology has global application in providing beach users and researchers with critical location and environmental information. The Clever Buoy system uses a non-invasive technology solution to create a virtual shark net to detect sharks and alert the appropriate authorities and/or beach users.

Smart Parking Limited is engaged in the design, development and management of parking technology. The Company operates through the segments, including technology, which consists of car parking technology products sold globally, and parking management, which operates in the United Kingdom and consists of the provision of car parking management services on behalf of third party car park owners and on sites leased by the Company and managed its own behalf. Its SmartApp is a mobile application, which enables drivers to locate vacant parking spaces. Its SmartEye is a sensor technology that gathers and transmits information for management, payment and compliance monitoring. It offers radio-frequency identification (RFID) solutions for payment, enforcement and management, including parking permits. Its SmartRep is a parking management software for both daily administration and long term planning. It offers SmartGuide, which identifies special status parking areas.

SubZero Group Limited, formerly SVC Group Ltd, is engaged in providing mining services. The Company's services include mechanical support (on and offsite heavy machinery repairs and light vehicle maintenance), structural support (on and offsite engineering and fabrication), mining support (mining project support, equipment hire and labor hire), and electrical harnessing and hydraulic isolator safety systems. Its Mechanical Support division provides complete machine rebuild and diagnostic monitoring of heavy and light machinery in the heavy construction and mining industries. The mechanical Support division focuses on designing and fabricating safety solutions for equipment, from MDG15 fit out of light vehicles to hydraulic isolation devices. Its Structural Support division provides structural repair and fabrication services to mining equipment, components and machinery. Its Production Support division provides bulk earthworks, poly and infrastructure services, among others.

SomnoMed Limited is engaged in the business of producing and selling devices for the oral treatment of sleep related disorders primarily in the Asia Pacific region, North America and Europe. The Company's products include SomnoDent Fusion, SomnoDent Flex, SomnoDent Classic, Somnodent SUAD, Somnodent SUAD Ultra, SomnoDent Herbst Advance, SomnoDent AIR & AIR+ and Morning Repositioner. The SomnoDent Herbst Advance is an intraoral device featuring a visual calibration indicator for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea (OSA). The Company manufactures custom fit acrylic occlusal splints (dental guards), the SomnoBrux, to protect patient's teeth against heaving grinding and bruxism. Its SomnoBrux products include Gelb, Tanner and Michigan. It offers SOMGauge, which is an autoclavable instrument that can be used to construct reliable bite records. The Company provides medical reimbursement services to assist dental offices with submitting a medical claim for their patients' OSA treatment.

Shaw River Manganese Limited (Shaw River) is engaged in the exploration for and evaluation of manganese deposits. The Company focuses on the development of an open cut mining operation at its Otjozondu project (Otjo) in Namibia. It operates through two geographical segments: Australia and Africa. Its projects include Otjozondu project, which is located approximately 150 kilometers north-east Windhoek in Namibia, and Butre Project, which is located in the Republic of Ghana in West Africa. The Butre Project is located approximately 30 kilometers on sealed roads from the bulk port of Takoradi and around 200 kilometers west of the capital, Accra. The Butre Project contains manganese occurrences at Jimra Bepo, consisting of multiple in-siti manganese oxide seams up to 12 meters thick. In addition, Shaw River holds interest in the manganese and iron rights in around three Pilbara tenements at Baramine, which is located approximately 80 kilometers north-west of Woodie Woodie Manganese mine.

Spitfire Materials Limited, formerly Spitfire Resources Limited, is engaged in the minerals exploration. The Company's segments include the South Woodie Woodie Manganese Segment with these activities forming the Australian manganese exploration segment, and Treasury and unallocated. Its types of exploration by project segment include Australia-Manganese Exploration, which includes the maintenance of the Manganese project at South Woodie in the East Pilbara; Zambia-Limestone Exploration, which includes the limestone exploration project based in Zambia, and Australia-Treasury. The South Woodie Woodie Manganese Project comprises approximately three granted Exploration Licenses in Western Australia's East Pilbara Manganese Province. The White Lion limestone project is located approximately 100 kilometers North West from the Zambian capital Lusaka. The White Lion limestone project sits on a granted Large Scale Mining License (14948-HQ-LML) and covers an area of over 240 square kilometers.

Structural Monitoring Systems Plc is a holding company. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of its intellectual property for products used in testing and monitoring the structural integrity of materials that are subject to operational stress and fatigue in structures, such as aircraft, ships, transportation infrastructure and power plants. Its Comparative Vacuum Monitoring (CVM) is a measure of the differential pressure between fine galleries containing a low vacuum alternating with galleries at atmosphere in a simple manifold. The CVM system consists of a sensor that is applied to the area requiring testing or inspection; a vacuum source to control and apply a partial vacuum to the sensor; a differential pressure flow meter device with output options that interface with the control systems, and software management systems that process the data. The CVM technology has been developed for use in both a laboratory environment or on operating equipment.

Strike Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company's principal activity includes the examination of a range of strategies and the investigation of alternative value-add strategies in relation to the development of its iron ore projects in Peru. The Company's segments include Peru and Australia. The Company holds approximately 15 Apurimac and Cusco project mineral concessions. The Apurimac Magnetite Iron Ore project is located in the Southern Highlands of Peru. The Cusco Magnetite Iron Ore Project consists of approximately three concessions totaling approximately 3,000 hectares, and located approximately 150 kilometers to the east of the Apurimac Project area and approximately 80 kilometers south of Cusco. In addition, the Company has applied for a range of exploration licenses in North Pilbara, Western Australia and exploration concessions in northern Chile considered prospective for lithium.

SML Corporation Limited is a holding company. The Company is focused on opportunities through investments, mergers and acquisitions. The Company, through its subsidiary, holds a mining lease covering approximately 240 hectares in eastern Victoria, Australia. Its mining lease includes Glen Wills-Sunnyside gold project. The Company operates as an explorer for base precious metals. The Company focuses on gold, silver, zinc and lead mineralization within Australia. Its subsidiaries include Synergy Metals Pty Limited, Australian Gold Mines Pty Limited, Mt. Wills Gold Mines Pty Limited and Mitta Omeo Metals Pty Ltd. Australian Gold Mines Pty Limited and Mt Wills Gold Mines Pty Limited collectively hold interests in the Glen Wills and Sunnyside gold project, which is located in the East Gippsland region in Victoria.

SmartPay Holdings Limited is a provider of technology products, services and software to merchants and retailers. The Company designs, develops and implements payment solutions for customers in New Zealand and Australia. It offers a range of payment and data management solutions for retail, business payment and transactional processing requirements. The Company is the electronic funds transfer at point of sale (EFTPOS) terminal provider throughout Australia. It licenses its technologies to third parties. The Company is a supplier of taxi payment solutions in New Zealand. The Company offers wireless EFTPOS Machines that allow accepting a credit card onsite. Its stationary countertop solutions are capable of connecting through the Internet. Its EFTPOS terminals are available for hire for a trade show on a short term lease. The Company has over 45,000 EFTPOS terminals throughout Australia and New Zealand, servicing the payment needs of approximately 18,000 merchants.

Shine Corporate Ltd is engaged in the provision of legal services across Queensland, Victoria, Western Australia and New South Wales. The Company has interest in an insurance recovery consulting business in New Zealand. It operates in two segments: personal injury and emerging practice areas. The Personal injury segment is its core business in damaged-based plaintiff litigation. Services offered in the Personal injury segment include medical negligence, public liability, catastrophic injuries, workers' compensation, and motor vehicle accidents. It has diversified to include emerging practice areas, which include disability insurance and superannuation claims, professional negligence, social justice, class actions, first party insurance recovery claims, landowners' rights, aviation, product liability, family law and asbestos compensation. The Company specializes primarily in damages-based plaintiff litigation legal services, primarily relating to personal injury.

Strategic Elements Limited is a Pooled Development Fund (PDF). The Company invests into small and medium sized Australian companies to assist in the development or expansion of the company. The Company's segments are Metals and Materials, and Research & Development. The Company owns Australian Advanced Materials Pty Ltd, which is engaged in developing a memory technology. The technology consists of tiny cube-shaped memory cells with potential to enable memory to be printed in an ink onto a range of materials, such as flexible plastic and glass. The Company also holds investments in Maria Resources Pty Ltd (Maria Resources) and Strategic Materials Pty Ltd (Strategic Materials). Maria Resources owns the Officer project. Strategic Materials owns the Golden Blocks Project in New Zealand. The Company also licensed new Ultraviolet (UV) light transistor-memory combination technology (UVTM), which enables a transistor to have non-volatile memory capacity.

Starpharma Holdings Limited is engaged in development of dendrimer products for pharmaceutical, life science and other applications. The Company utilizes dendrimers, which is a type of synthetic nanoscale polymer that is regular in size and structure and suited to pharmaceutical and medical uses. It has approximately three development programs, including VivaGel portfolio, DEP drug delivery and agrochemicals. It develops and commercializes dendrimer nanotechnology across various applications, including sexual health, drug delivery for pharmaceuticals, animal health, coatings and inks, crop protection and agrochemicals, diagnostics and research reagents, cosmetics and water treatment. Its products are based on VivaGel (SPL7013, astodrimer sodium), a dendrimer, which has antimicrobial properties. It has both partnered and internal programs in drug delivery. In agrochemicals, it has partnerships with Adama, as well as internal programs, including an enhanced version of glyphosate.

Swick Mining Services Ltd is engaged in the provision of mineral drilling services to the mining industry in the Asia Pacific and other international regions, primarily in the areas of underground diamond drilling, underground production drilling and surface reverse circulation drilling. The Company also carries out research and development activities in mineral analysis. The Company's segments are Drilling Services in Asia Pacific and Drilling Services International. Its Swick RC Drill consists of a modular configuration, automated rod handling system and remote controlled air support truck. It utilizes Tamrock Solo 1020 top head hammer longhole rigs to provide underground production drilling services, which include grade control, blast hole, ground support and rise/slot drilling. The Company also provides tailored management services for underground production drilling, offering crews to operate, manage and maintain production drill rigs that are owned by the client.

Story-I Limited is a reseller and retailer of Apple and information technology (IT) life style products across Indonesia and Vietnam. The Company's segments include Australia, Singapore and Republic of Indonesia. Its divisions include Retail division, Education division, E-commerce division and Enterprise Solutions. The Retail division includes its retail network, including the Authorized Apple Resellers under the Story-I branded stores and the Iconnect retail outlets carrying its other brands, such as Samsung, Lenovo and Huawei, as well as a range of accessories. The Education division offers mobile learning solutions to schools and educational institutions in Indonesia. The E-commerce division operates an online E-Commerce platform that retails devices and accessories, and hosts an online community of users and buyers. The Enterprise Solutions division focuses on opening an infrastructure as a service market to Indonesian corporates and multi-national companies entering Indonesia.

Suncorp Group Limited is engaged in the provision of general insurance, banking, life insurance, superannuation products and related services to the retail, corporate and commercial sectors in Australia and New Zealand. The Company's segments include Personal Insurance, which provides home and contents, motor, boat and travel insurance products; Commercial Insurance, which provides commercial motor, commercial property, marine, industrial special risks, loan protection insurance products and others; General Insurance New Zealand, which provides motor, marine, business, rural, travel insurance products and others; Bank, which provides personal and commercial banking, property and equipment finance, home, personal and small business loans and others; Life, which provides superannuation administration services, financial planning and funds administration services, and Corporate, which includes investment of the Company's capital, business strategy activities and its shared services.

Surefire Resources NL, formerly Black Ridge Mining NL, is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company is also engaged in the exploration and evaluation of opportunities located domestically and internationally. The Company holds interest in Unaly Hill Project (E57/420), which is located approximately 500 kilometers north east of Perth, Western Australia and is a single tenement covering over 13 kilometers of the strike length of the regionally Youanmi Fault. The Company's project contains multi-element anomalies, notably gold, nickel and vanadium iron-titanium. Other prospective anomalies present at the project include nickel-cobalt in an area with a high magnesium response and various target zones where iron, vanadium and titanium are coincident. The Company' subsidiaries include Unaly Hill Pty Ltd, Sandstone Holdings Pty Ltd and Oil and Gas SE Pty Ltd.

Swala Energy Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas company. The Company's principal activities are the exploration for hydrocarbons in Tanzania and Kenya with the completion of its operated seismic acquisition program onshore Tanzania, technical review and processing of the seismic data in Kenya and preparation of the drilling program in Tanzania. The Company's segment is the exploration of oil and gas in Africa. The Company's holding are in the East African Rift System with a total net land package of approximately 9,000 square kilometers in Tanzania and Kenya. The Company, through its subsidiary, Swala Oil and Gas (Tanzania) Plc, holds a participating interest in the Pangani license and the Kilosa-Kilombero license in Tanzania. The Company also has a participating interest in its Kenyan joint operations arrangements for the Block 12B license.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Sayona Mining Limited is a resource company, which is engaged in identification, acquisition and evaluation of mineral exploration assets, focusing on lithium and graphite. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and Overseas. It holds interest in the East Kimberley project, which is located within the East Kimberley region of Western Australia, approximately 240 kilometers south of Wyndham Port and over 220 kilometers south-south-west of the regional center, Kununurra. It has an option-to-purchase contract for Itabela graphite project in Brazil. It undertakes exploration activity on a range of projects, including Cooglegong project; approximately two lithium project areas covering a total over 1,065 square kilometers in Western Australia; Pilbara Lithium project in Pilgangoora district; Tabba Tabba project, which is located north of Pilgangoora; Red rock project, which is located to the east of Tabba Tabba, and Friendly Creek and West Wodgina.

Service Stream Limited is a provider of essential network services, including access, design, build, installation and maintenance across copper, fiber and wireless telecommunications networks, as well as to private and public energy, and water entities. The Company's segments include Fixed Communications, Mobile Communications, and Energy & Water. The Fixed Communications segment provides design, construction, maintenance and customer connection services to the owners of telecommunications network infrastructure in connection with the roll-out of the National Broadband Network in Australia. The Mobile Communications segment provides program management and turnkey services for infrastructure projects in the telecommunications sector. The Energy & Water segment provides a range of metering and energy services to electricity, gas and water networks, and through the Customer Care business provides contact center services and workforce management support for contracts.

333D Limited, formerly Oz Brewing Limited, is engaged in carrying out legal and technical due diligence on the acquisition of 333D Pty Ltd. The Company is a three dimension (3D) technology company focused on upstream and downstream opportunities associated with additive manufacturing, also referred to as 3D printing. Having designed and manufactured fused filament fabrication printer on the market in Melbourne, Australia, the Company is developing a number of ancillary and complementary lines of business and services, including further development of industrial grade multi-application printers, a print bureau service, an online 3D print file market place, an at school education initiative and a retail kiosk concept.

ShareRoot Limited, formerly Monto Minerals Limited, is an information technology company. The Company operates through the segment of SaaS platform that allows for brand to search and source user generated content for their own marketing purposes. The Company offers Premium Tier, which allows users to purchase products directly that appear within a shop-able gallery. The Company also offers Hootsuite integration, which gives users an access across social media channels. The Company's subsidiaries include ShareRoot Inc and ShareRoot (Australian Ops) Pty Ltd.

Super Retail Group Limited is primarily involved in the retail industry. The Company's principal activities include retailing of auto parts and accessories, tools and equipment; retailing of boating, camping, outdoor equipment, fishing equipment and apparel, and retailing of sporting equipment, bicycles, bicycle accessories and apparel. The Company's segments include Auto, which is engaged in retailing of auto parts and accessories, tools and equipment; Leisure, which is engaged in retailing of boating, camping, outdoor equipment, fishing equipment and apparel, and Sports, which is engaged in retailing of sporting equipment, bicycles, bicycle accessories and apparel. The Company's brands include Amart Sports, which provides leisure sports products; BCF, an outdoor retailer; Rays, an outdoor entertainment and camping leisure retailer; Rebel, which provides branded sporting and leisure goods, and Supercheap Auto, a specialty retail business.
Auto Vehicles, Parts & Service Retailers - NEC

Washington H. Soul Pattinson and Company Limited is engaged in ownership of shares, coal mining, gold and copper mining and refining, property investment and consulting. It has five segments: investing activities, energy, copper and gold operations, corporate advisory and property. Its investment segment is engaged in investing in cash, term deposits and equity investments. Its energy segment is engaged in coal, oil and gas activities, which include exploration, development, production, processing, associated transport infrastructure and ancillary activities. Its copper and gold operations segment is engaged in copper and gold mining activities, including exploration, mining and processing of ore into copper concentrate, copper sulfide and gold. Its corporate advisory segment is engaged in providing corporate advisory services. Its property segment is engaged in property investment activities, including the identification and management of real estate to be held, sold or developed.

Silver Mines Limited is engaged in acquiring the Bowdens Silver Project and maintaining the Webbs Silver Project in New South Wales Australia. The Company is engaged in exploration operations. Its projects also include Conrad Project (silver/polymetallic) and Tuena Project (gold/silver). The Bowdens Silver Project (Bowdens Silver) is located in central New South Wales, approximately 26 kilometers east of Mudgee. The Company holds approximately 100% of Bowdens Silver comprising EL5920, EL6354, EL8159, EL8160, EL8160, EL8268, EL5674, EL8403, EL8405 and ELA5235. The Webbs Silver Project (EL 5674) is located in the New England region of northern New South Wales approximately 45 kilometers north of Glen Innes. The Conrad Silver Project (EPL1050, EL5977, ML6040, ML6041 and ML 5992) is located in the New England region of northern New South Wales approximately 25 kilometers south of Inverell. The Tuena Project tenement application is located to the south of Orange, New South Wales.

Tabcorp Holdings Limited is engaged in the provision of gambling and entertainment services. The Company operates through three segments: Wagering and Media, Keno and Gaming Services. It manages customer brands, including TAB, tab.com.au, Luxbet, Sky Racing, Sky Sports Radio, Tabcorp Gaming Solutions (TGS), Keno and Trackside animated racing game. It conducts wagering activities under the TAB brand in Victoria, New South Wales and the Australian Capital Territory through a network of agencies, hotels and clubs; provides on-course totalisators at thoroughbred, harness and greyhound metropolitan and country race meetings; and via the Internet, mobile devices, phone and pay television. Its Gaming services segment is engaged in the supply of electronic gaming machines and specialized services to licensed gaming venues. Its Keno segment includes Keno operations in licensed venues and TABs in Victoria, Queensland and Australian Capital Territory, and in licensed venues in New South Wales.

South Pacific Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration and development of oil and gas licenses. The Company is also engaged in investment management activities. The Company operates and holds an approximately 100% working interest in over five petroleum prospecting licenses (PPL) in Papua New Guinea (PNG). The Company's licenses include PPL 356, PPL 357, PPL 366, PPL 367 and PPL 358. These licenses cover an area of approximately 11, 970 square kilometers in both onshore and offshore settings. Its Dibiri & Hiri (PPL 356 and 357) licenses are located in the prospective offshore segment of the Papuan Basin close to the Pandora and Pasca gas discoveries. The Company's Biwai & Turama (PPL 366 and 367) licenses are located in the onshore Papuan Basin close to oil and gas discoveries and production infrastructure. Its PPL 358 license is in the underexplored offshore frontier Cape Vogel Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Sietel Limited is an Australia-based company, which invests in industrial, commercial, retail real estate and listed company securities. The Company is also engaged in the provision of finance and lease facilities, and plant and management services to its controlled entities and management, evaluation and expansion of these and other business opportunities. The Company's segments include Investments and Operations. The Investments segment includes its listed share and property investment activities. The Operations segment includes the Company's manufacturing, importation and services activities. Its subsidiaries include Cook's Body Works Pty Ltd, which is a commercial vehicle body builder; The Cylinder Company Pty Ltd, which is a property maintenance company, mainly servicing the Company's properties, as well as investigating new product, importation, and research and development opportunities, and Alliance Appliances Australia Pty Ltd (AAA).

Tanami Gold NL is an Australia-based company engaged in gold exploration. The Company's segments include Gold Production and Exploration. Its exploration centers are situated in the Tanami Desert straddling the Western Australia and Northern Territory border. The Company owns approximately 100% interest in Coyote Gold Project, which is an underground mining operation. The Coyote Gold Project is located in Western Australia and consists of over 350,000 tons per annum carbon-in-leach treatment plant. Its principal asset, Central Tanami Project in the Northern Territory is located adjacent to the Tanami Track and approximately 90 kilometers east of the Coyote Gold Project. The Company's principal focus of activity is Groundrush deposit (mineral leases (ML) 22934). Its exploration programs are also focused on the extensions of known deposits within MLs, such as MLS153, MLS167, MLS168 and MLS180. The Company's subsidiaries include Tanami Exploration NL and Tanami (NT) Pty Ltd.

Spark New Zealand Limited is a supplier of telecommunications and digital services in New Zealand. The Company operates through three segments: Spark Home, Mobile & Business; Spark Digital, and Spark Connect. The Spark Home, Mobile & Business segment provides fixed line, mobile and Internet services to consumers and the small medium business market, and includes Spark Ventures. The Spark Digital segment integrates information technology (IT) and telecommunications services to provide converged information and communications technology (ICT) solutions for clients. The Spark Connect segment includes its network and IT operations, shared business operations and servicing of wholesale and international customers. The Company provides a range of telecommunications, and ICT products and services, including local, national, international and telephone services; data networks, broadband services and Internet television; IT services and procurement; equipment sales, and installation services.

Samson Oil & Gas Limited an oil and gas company focusing on oil production in the Niobrara and Bakken formations in the United States. The Company's principal activities are oil and gas exploration, development and production in the United States. Its geographic segments include United States of America and Other segments. All revenue from the United States of America segment is from customers based in the United States. The Other Segments revenue relates principally to interest income earned on cash balances in Australia. Its projects include Foreman Butte project, Roosevelt Project, North Stockyard Project, Rainbow Project, Hawk Springs Project, South Prairie Project and Cane Creek Project. Its Foreman Butte project includes various producing and non-producing, operated and non-operated wells in the Ratcliffe and Madison formations in Montana and North Dakota. The Company has an interest in over 3,303 acres adjacent to the North Stockyard Oil Field.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Topbetta Holdings Limited is engaged in digital fantasy wagering, wagering and content services. The Company's segments include Fantasy wagering and wagering, Content Services and Corporate. It operates an online wagering platform, which utilizes technology across risk management systems, odds management, content delivery and consumer facing platforms. Online fantasy wagering tournaments platform is integrated into the groups online wagering platforms and enable sports fans to compete against each other through fantasy wagering on real sports events, with the focus on the social engagement. It operates a content platform, which enables customers to access a range of sporting and racing content. In addition to the TopBetta Platform, it also has other technology platforms, including the TopTippa Platform and the 12Follow Platform. The platforms provide third-party Websites engagement tools for their audience and the opportunity to turn their traffic into a database for the Company.

Strike Energy Limited is engaged in the evaluation and development of energy projects, and the production of oil and gas in Australia. The Company's segments are Australia and the United States. It focuses on the development of a gas resource in the Southern Cooper Basin. Its Southern Cooper Basin Gas Project is centered in and around its PEL 96 permit area. The Company holds working interests in the Eagle Landing joint venture. The Eagle Landing joint venture includes the Bigham 1 H Unit in Fayette County, Texas, which consists of approximately 850.32 acres. It holds working interests in the Eaglewood joint venture. It also holds working interests in various wells and units producing from the Clearfork Formation in Martin County, Texas. The Company also holds interests in PEL 515 and PELA 640 in the Cooper-Eromanga Basin in Australia. The Company also has exploration permits in the Carnarvon Basin and rights over a 578-million ton lignite resource in South Australia.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Sydney Airport Holdings Limited the ownership of Sydney Airport. The Companys investment policy is to invest funds in accordance with the provisions of the governing documents of the individual entities within the Company. The Company is consists of Sydney Airport Limited (SAL) and Sydney Airport Trust 1 (SAT1).The Trust Company (Sydney Airport) Limited (TCSAL) is the responsible entity of SAT1.

South East Asia Resources Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company is engaged in the process of acquiring interests in resource deposits in South East Asia. The Company has a 95% interest in the Malala Molybdenum project and is finalizing a 27.5% interest to production with Molybdenum mining group China Guangshou Group Co., Ltd. The Company is the owner and operator of 287.5 square kilometers of granted tenure in six claim blocks forming the Malala Molybdenum Project. The Companys project is PAR Coking Coal project. In addition, the Company is maintaining its rights to exploration and exploitation of the Malala Molybdenum deposit in Sulawesi, Indonesia.

Sirtex Medical Limited is a medical device company with primary objective of manufacturing and distributing liver cancer treatments utilizing small particle technology to markets in Asia-Pacific; Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA), and North and South America. The Company's segments include Asia Pacific, Americas and EMEA. Its lead product is SIR-Spheres Y-90 resin microspheres, which is a targeted radioactive treatment for liver cancer. The treatment is called Selective Internal Radiation Therapy (SIRT) and consists of a minimally invasive surgical procedure performed by an interventional radiologist. The SIR-Spheres microspheres lodge in the small blood vessels of the tumor where they destroy it from the inside while sparing the surrounding healthy tissue. The Company is also engaged in conducting other studies, which include SIRFLOX and FOXFIRE Global for liver metastases, and RESIRT for primary renal cell carcinoma. SIR-Spheres is available in over 40 countries.

Suda Limited is a drug delivery company. The Company is engaged in pharmaceutical development of drug delivery technology, and medical devices and consumables distribution. Its segments are Suda, Westcoast Surgical & Medical Supplies (Westcoast), Malaria Research Company (MRC) and Other. The Suda segment is engaged in research and development to create new human pharmaceutical products by combining drugs with delivery technologies. The Westcoast segment is engaged in sales and logistics operation for medical devices and consumables. The MRC segment is pharmaceutical development segment for the treatment of malaria, including ArTiMist project. ArTiMist is a sublingual spray for the treatment of Plasmodium falciparum severe pediatric malaria. Its other pipeline of products includes Zolpimist, SUD-001, SUD-002, SUD-003, SUD-004 and SUD-005. Its development stage products include orals sprays for the treatment of migraine headache, erectile dysfunction and chemotherapy-induced nausea.

Sunvest Corporation Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company is engaged in investing in shares in other companies, which are quoted or are intended to be quoted on a recognized exchange, in Australia and the United Kingdom. The Company predominantly operates in the business segment of investing in listed equities and other securities in Australia, the United Kingdom and Canada. The Company's geographical segments include Australia, the United Kingdom and Canada. The majority of the Company's investments are in companies that are quoted on the Alternative Investment Market (AIM) stock exchange in the United Kingdom. Adelaide Securities Pty Ltd is the Company's subsidiary.

Syngas Limited is an Australia-based company, which operates in the resource and energy sector. The Company is involved in the exploration and development of mining tenements for minerals. The Company is seeking investment opportunities in the resource and energy sector. The Company had interests in MEL 4185 (north-west of Adeliade in the Northern St Vincent Basin Coalfields) located in South Australia. The Company operates in Australia. Syngas Energy Pty Ltd is the Company's subsidiary. The Company has not generated any revenues.

Tawana Resources NL is an Australia-based company engaged in mineral exploration, evaluation and development of iron ore. The Company operates through the mineral exploration in Liberia segment. The Company's project includes the Mofe Creek Iron Ore Project (Mofe Creek Project), which is located in Liberia, West Africa. The Mofe Creek Project covers an area of approximately 475 square kilometers of tenements in the Grand Cape Mount County. The Mofe Creek Project hosts friable itabirite mineralization, which can be upgraded to an iron ore product in the 64 to 68% iron grade range. The Mofe Creek deposits consist of a series of 1 to 3 kilometer strike length semi-contiguous hills with coincident magnetic anomalies within an approximate 65 kilometer strike length of magnetic anomalies interpreted. The Company's subsidiary, Tawana Liberia Inc., holds exploration licenses, which include MEL 1223/14 and MEL 12029.

Seven West Media Limited is a multiple platform media company. The Company's principal activities are free to air television broadcasting, newspaper and magazine publishing, online and radio broadcasting, and a subscription video on demand service (Presto TV). Its segments include Television, Newspapers, Pacific, and Other Business and New Ventures. The Television segment produces and operates commercial television programming and stations. The Newspapers segment publishes newspapers and insert magazines in West Australia and includes Quokka, Colourpress, Digital Publishing and West Australian publishers. The Pacific segment publishes magazines in print and digital editions, as well as social and e-commerce business. The Other Business and New Ventures segment consists of equity accounted investees, including Yahoo7, Presto, Australian news channel and Community Newspapers; radio (radio stations broadcasting in regional areas of Western Australia), and RED Live.

Tasman Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company's principal activities include mineral exploration, and through Eden Energy Ltd, the sale of high performance concrete admixture, EdenCrete and retrofit dual fuel technology, OptiBlend, developed for diesel generator sets. Its segments include Tasman Resources Ltd and Eden Energy Ltd. The Tasman Resources Ltd segment is engaged in mineral exploration in South Australia. The Eden Energy Ltd segment includes EdenCrete production and sales in the United States, and Optiblend sales and manufacturing in India and the United States. It focuses on mineral exploration for a range of commodities within the Company's tenements in South Australia. Its principal exploration projects are Lake Torrens Iron-Oxide Copper-Gold-Uranium (IOCGU)-base metal project and the Parkinson Dam epithermal gold-silver (lead-zinc) project in South Australia. Its Lake Torrens IOCGU Project is located approximately 15 kilometers north of Olympic Dam.

Stavely Minerals Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company's assets located in western Victoria and in northern Queensland are prospective for copper-gold mineralization with existing volcanic massive sulfide (VMS)-style and porphyry deposits. Its projects, Ararat and Stavely, host Inferred Mineral Resources that contain over 130 kilotons of copper and over 19,000 ounces of gold, as well as accessory zinc and silver. Its other projects include Mortlake Project, Yarram Park Project, Ravenswood Project, Dreghorn and Kirk North. The Stavely Project is located in western Victoria on the Stavely tablelands approximately 250 kilometers to the west of Melbourne. The Ararat Project is hosted in the Stawell -Bendigo zone of the Lachlan Fold Belt. The Mortlake Project straddles the boundary between the Delamerian and Lachlan Orogens. The Ravenswood Project is located over 90 kilometers south of Townsville and approximately 10 kilometers southwest of Ravenswood in North Queensland.

Superior Resources Limited is a junior minerals explorer. The Company is engaged in exploration for base metals and gold in northern Queensland, Australia. It holds various exploration permits, exploration permit applications and a granted mining lease in northern Queensland for base metals exploration. The Company is also a party to a farm-in agreement for gold over three granted mining leases at Tick Hill in northwest Queensland. It focuses on areas with potential for high-grade deposits of copper, lead-zinc-silver and gold. These include the Mount Isa style deposits in northwest Queensland, the volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) deposits in northeast Queensland and the Proterozoic Tick Hill gold deposits in northwest Queensland. The Company's projects include Tick Hill Gold Project, Tick Hill Tailings Project, Victor Project, Nicholson Project, Riesling Project, Dajarra Project, and Greenvale Project, which includes VMS and Porphyry Copper.

Trustees Australia Limited is engaged in providing financial services, tourism and hospitality, and property activities. The Company segments are Financial Services, Tourism & Hospitality and Property. The financial services segment includes custodial and responsible entity services; fixed income broking and advisory through Rim Securities Limited, and its portfolio holding of listed investments that includes interest in the Australian Dairy Farms Group. The tourism & hospitality segment includes ownership and operation of Magnums Airlie Beach Backpackers, offering various grades of backpacker hostel style accommodation and services. The tourism and hospitality segment operations are located at Airlie Beach in the Whitsundays, Queensland. The property segment includes development land and buildings at Airlie Beach, suitable for providing retail shopping facilities, accommodation or held for resale in the Company, and interest in Whitsunday Village Retail Property Trust No 1.

Stonewall Resources Limited is an Australia-based gold mining company. The principal activities of the Company are the consolidation of costs in the South African entities, as well as a review of the Pre Mined Residue Project with a view to bringing it into operation. The Company's operating segments include TGME, Bosveld and Sabie. The Company's projects include Transvaal Gold Mining Estates Limited (TGME) Project and Sabie. The TGME project is located around the towns of Pilgrims Rest. The TGME Project consists of two mining operations: Central/Northern (near and to the north of town Pilgrim's Rest) and Southern (town Sabie to the south). The Sabie project is located in the Mpumalanga Province of South Africa. The Company owns Lucky Draw Gold Project, which is located in Australia, near the township of Burraga in New South Wales. The Company's projects also include Bosveld Project, which is located in South Africa's KwaZulu-Natal Province.

Sayona Mining Limited is a resource company, which is engaged in identification, acquisition and evaluation of mineral exploration assets, focusing on lithium and graphite. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and Overseas. It holds interest in the East Kimberley project, which is located within the East Kimberley region of Western Australia, approximately 240 kilometers south of Wyndham Port and over 220 kilometers south-south-west of the regional center, Kununurra. It has an option-to-purchase contract for Itabela graphite project in Brazil. It undertakes exploration activity on a range of projects, including Cooglegong project; approximately two lithium project areas covering a total over 1,065 square kilometers in Western Australia; Pilbara Lithium project in Pilgangoora district; Tabba Tabba project, which is located north of Pilgangoora; Red rock project, which is located to the east of Tabba Tabba, and Friendly Creek and West Wodgina.

Syrah Resources Limited is an Australia-based resource company. The Company is engaged in the development and construction of the Balama Graphite Project in Mozambique; assessment of the use of graphite from the Balama Graphite Project as an input into the production of spherical graphite and recarburizer products, and exploration and evaluation studies, including technical investigations into the potential to extract and produce vanadium from the Balama Graphite Project ore body. The Company's segments include Australia and Mozambique. The Company's Australia segment is engaged in investing activities and corporate management. Its Mozambique segment is engaged in mining, mineral exploration, evaluation and development activities. The Balama Project is situated in the Cabo Delgado province of northern Mozambique, approximately 200 kilometers west of the port town of Pemba. It also operates Sasare North project.

Spicers Limited, formerly PaperlinX Limited, is engaged in the merchanting of paper, communication materials and diversified materials, including packaging, and sign and display. The Company's segments include merchanting and unallocated. Its merchanting segment includes three businesses: merchanting Australia, merchanting New Zealand and merchanting Asia, which involves international merchant supplying the printing and publishing industry and office supplies. It offers a suite of solutions to the printing and graphic arts industry, incorporating sign and display, commercial print products, industrial packaging, hardware, digital media, label and packaging products. From point-of-sale and vehicle graphics, through to exhibition stand construction and shop fit out, its range of sign and display substrates includes banners, papers and boards, synthetics, self-adhesives and rigid materials. Its line-up of industrial supplies and packaging materials include cartons and adhesive tapes.

Spectrum Rare Earths Limited (Spectrum) is a resource development company, which focuses on the commercialization of mineral assets. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of rare earths. The Company holds approximately 12,000 square kilometers of tenements (approximately 11 granted and approximately 19 application tenements) across the Northern Territory of Australia. The Company's rare earth projects include Skyfall magnetic end use rare earth exploration target and Quantum and Pine Creek projects. The Company's uranium projects include Pine Creek, Arnhem, MacArthur and Litchfield. The Company's other commodity projects and potentials include Tennant creek copper gold project, Litchfield coal and PB-ZN project, MacArthur base metals, Ne Arnhem bauxite and Calvert base metals and gold. The Company's Litchfield Uranium Project consists of the license application, ELA25221.

Tag Pacific Limited is an investment company that invests in the power sector. The Company's segments include Power investments and Property investments. The Power investments segment provides power solutions for use in various manners of emergency, back-up, generated and renewable power situations in Australia, New Zealand and the Pacific Islands. The Power investments segment includes the operations of MPower Group Pty Limited, MPower Pacific Ltd, MPower Samoa Limited and MPower Nominees Pty Ltd. The Property investments segment consists of its investments in the Power Property Unit Trust, which owns a property occupied by MPower Group in Melbourne, Victoria. The investment in the power sector has business segments across Australia, which includes branches in Victoria, Queensland, Western Australia and South Australia, and includes overseas projects (including Samoa) managed in Australia and New Zealand, which includes branches in Auckland, Wellington, Christchurch and Suva.

Southern Cross Electrical Engineering Limited (SCEE) is engaged in the provision of specialized electrical, control and instrumentation installation and testing services for the resources, infrastructure and heavy industrial sectors. The Company operates through three divisions: SCEE Construction, SCEE Infrastructure and SCEE Services. SCEE Construction division installs and commissions greenfield and brownfield upgrade projects. SCEE Infrastructure division delivers overhead powerline design and construction services. SCEE Infrastructure division provides a range of electrical infrastructure works, including high voltage, underground and overhead powerlines, substations, switchyards and site-wide distribution and reticulation systems. SCEE Services division provides electrical and instrumentation operational support, maintenance and shutdowns, as well as sustaining capital programs of work to various locations across Australia and to the offshore industry across the globe.

Strandline Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company engages in evaluation in Australia and Tanzania, with a focus on mineral sands. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and Tanzania. The Company's projects include Tanzania mineral sands project, Coburn heavy mineral sands project and Fowlers bay gold-base metal project. The Tanzanian project covers Tanga Project in the northern region, Fungoni Project in the central region and Madimba Project in the southern region. The Coburn project is located approximately 250 kilometers north of the regional center and port of Geraldton, immediately south of Shark Bay and just outside the eastern boundary of the Shark Bay World Heritage Property. The Coburn project has zircon, ilmenite and hiti. The Fowlers bay project comprises approximately 700 square kilometer exploration license located approximately 150 kilometers west of Ceduna.

Tap Oil Limited is an oil and gas exploration and production company. The Company's principal activities include oil and gas exploration, development and production and gas marketing. The Company's segments include oil & gas production and development; oil & gas exploration, and Third party gas. The oil & gas production and development segment includes the assets moved from the exploration phase to the development phase. This segment also includes producing assets, such as The Manora (G1/48). The oil & gas exploration segment includes all the areas of interest still in their exploration phase. The Third party gas segment includes the purchases and sale of gas. The gas purchases are based on contracted quantities and sales are done through agreements with customers or in certain instances through market sales. The Company has interest in Manora Oil field, Block M-07 Moatamma Basin, WA-351-P, WA-290-P and WA-49-R, WA-320-P and WA-155-P (Part II), TL/2 and TP/7, and Vic/P67-Otway Basin.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Seven Group Holdings Limited is a diversified operating and investment company. The Company's segments include WesTrac Australia, which is the authorized Caterpillar dealer in Western Australia, New South Wales and the Australian Capital Territory; WesTrac China, which is the authorized Caterpillar dealer in the North Eastern China provinces of Hebei, Liaoning, Heilongjiang, Jilin, Shanxi, Inner Mongolia and the municipalities of Beijing and Tianjin; AllightSykes, which operates in the manufacture, assembly, sales and support of lighting, power generation and dewatering equipment, as well as distribution of Perkins engines; Coates Hire, which represents its equity accounted investment in Coates Group Holdings Pty Limited; Media investments, which relates to investments in listed and unlisted media organizations; Energy, which relates to its working interest in Bivins Ranch area and in SGH Energy Pty Ltd, and Other investments, which incorporates listed investments and property.

Sumatra Copper & Gold plc is a holding company and a gold and silver producer and precious metals explorer. The Company's principal activity is to acquire, explore, develop and mine gold-silver and other metal deposits in Sumatra, Indonesia. The Company's asset, Tembang gold-silver mine (Tembang), is in production. The Company also has an exploration portfolio with projects ranging from brownfield, near-production opportunities to strategically located greenfield holdings. Tembang is located in the Bengkulu district in central Sumatra and covers an area of approximately 850 square kilometers. Tembang has proven and probable ore reserves of over 2.01 million tons at 2.8 grams per ton gold (g/t Au) and over 32.9 grams per ton silver (g/t Ag) for a total of approximately 181,000 ounces of gold and over 2.12 million ounces silver. Its Tandai Project is located approximately 100 kilometers north of Bengkulu in the Kabupaten area of Bengkulu Utara in central Sumatra Indonesia.

Southern Hemisphere Mining Limited is an Australia-based exploration-stage company. The Company is engaged in the acquisition and exploration of mineral properties, principally located in Chile, South America. The Company is focused on the Coquimbo Region of Chile, South America where it owns a Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) resource at the Llahuin Copper-Gold Project and has a joint venture on the Los Rulos Copper-Gold Project. The Company holds prospective copper/gold project areas in Chile, South America. The Company's portfolio includes the Llahuin Copper-Gold Project and the Rincon Copper-Gold Project. The Llahuin Project is located approximately 17 kilometers south of Combarbala and over 56 kilometers from the coast and Pan American Highway, on the lower Coastal Cordillera (1,300 meters elevation). The Rincon Project is a copper opportunity. The Company's other projects include Mantos Grandes Copper-Gold Project, which is located approximately 80 kilometers from Ovalle.

Southern Cross Exploration N.L. is engaged in the exploration for uranium, gold and other minerals, as well as examining projects for possible acquisition. The Company's segments include Exploration and Other. The Exploration segment includes the exploration for metals and other minerals, primarily for oil, gas and other energy resources, either directly and/or through equity investment in exploration companies. The Other segment relates to an investment with a company involved in the development of property. The Company has interests in Batangas Gold Project and Gold Cross Gold project in the Philippines. The Company also has an interest in a uranium project in Tanzania. The Company has an investment in the Bigrlyi Uranium Joint Venture, which is located in the Ngalia Basin, Northern Territory. The Batangas Gold Project is located approximately 100 kilometers from Manila.

Sun Resources NL is engaged in oil and gas exploration and investment. The Company is engaged in the exploration, development and production of oil and gas projects. The Company's segments include Australia and the United States of America (USA). The Company focuses on the exploration and development of unconventional oil and gas within over two onshore unconventional resource plays in Texas. It has an interest in approximately 4,087 net acres across over five projects, over four of these projects are located in the Woodbine Tight Oil Play (Eaglebine) approximately 150 kilometers north of Houston. Its Normangee Oil Project is located in the Leon County-Madison County border, Texas, the United States and includes over 690 acres net to the Company. The SW Leona Oil Project, Delta Oil Project and the Southern Woodbine Oil Project are located in the Leon County, Texas. The Badger Oil Project is located in Bastrop County, on trend with the Eagle Ford Shale unconventional oil play.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Senex Energy Limited (Senex) is an oil and gas exploration and production company. The Company's segments include SURAT/BOWEN BASIN and COOPER/EROMANGA BASINS. The Company produces over one million barrels of oil annually from over 10 Senex-operated oil fields. The Company holds an acreage position across the South Australian and Queensland Cooper Basin, with approximately 15,000 square kilometers considered prospective for conventional and unconventional (tight) oil. The Company holds various interests, including the western flank of the Cooper Basin, as well as north, south and east of the Moomba processing and transportation hub. In the northern Cooper Basin, Senex is developing its Vanessa conventional gas field. Its Western Surat Gas Project is involved in the extraction of natural gas from coal seams over approximately 910 square kilometers of Senex permits, north of Roma in Queensland.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Southern Cross Media Group Limited is engaged in the creation and broadcasting of content on free-to-air commercial radio (amplitude modulation (AM), frequency modulation (FM) and digital), television and online media platforms across Australia. The Company offers a range of content across free to air television, approximately 80 metropolitan and regional FM and AM radio stations, digital audio and radio, social media networks, online, mobile and events. The Company's segments include Regional free-to-air commercial radio and television broadcasting segment, Metro free-to-air radio broadcasting segment and Corporate. The Company's radio stations include Buddha, kid's radio station Kinderling, music genre stations Easy, Classic Rock, Old Skool and country music favourite, Modern Rock and The Range. The Company's broadcast channels include seven, 7mate and 7two, nine, ten, life, go, gem, eleven and one.

Swift Networks Group Limited, formerly Stanfield Funds Management Limited, is a diversified telecommunications and digital entertainment business providing fully integrated solutions for the resources, hospitality, lifestyle village and aged care accommodation sectors. These solutions include free-to-air television, pay television, telecommunications, Internet, data, wireless networks and streaming video on demand with content from Hollywood studios. The Company offers a digital entertainment system, which consists of television gateway technology, middleware, applications, an internal management system, and a monitoring and control system. Its digital entertainment system comprises four main components: entertainment, communication, information and administration.

Spirit Telecom Limited, formerly Arunta Resources Limited, is engaged in the provision of telecommunications services. The Company offers high-speed Internet and telecommunications services to commercial and residential customers within Australia. It owns and operates its own national voice and data network. Its services are fiber broadband, business services, student accommodation Internet, national broadcasting network (nbn) activations and communities. Its Ultra-Fast Internet Apartment Fiber plan offers upto 200/200 megabytes per second of unlimited bandwidth or power for all the entertainment, research and downloading. Its business services include business broadband, business phone systems and other data services. The student accommodation Internet service provides wireless fidelity. It delivers Internet to connected communities using own fiber technologies. The community service includes ultra-fast speed, symmetrical uploading and downloading.

Sietel Limited is an Australia-based company, which invests in industrial, commercial, retail real estate and listed company securities. The Company is also engaged in the provision of finance and lease facilities, and plant and management services to its controlled entities and management, evaluation and expansion of these and other business opportunities. The Company's segments include Investments and Operations. The Investments segment includes its listed share and property investment activities. The Operations segment includes the Company's manufacturing, importation and services activities.
