Its subsidiaries include Cook's Body Works Pty Ltd, which is a commercial vehicle body builder; The Cylinder Company Pty Ltd, which is a property maintenance company, mainly servicing the Company's properties, as well as investigating new product, importation, and research and development opportunities, and Alliance Appliances Australia Pty Ltd (AAA).

Servcorp Limited is engaged in the provision of executive serviced and virtual offices, and information technology (IT), communications and secretarial services. The Company's segments include Australia, New Zealand and Southeast Asia; USA; Europe and Middle East (EME); North Asia, and other. Its Servcorp Online allows users to manage call diversion, call answering and messages online; book meeting rooms, boardrooms, facilities and resources; manage and change bookings online; manage their business services, book a courier, stationery and translation services, and download and view their invoices. Its Servcorp Online also enables to share and distribute electronic files, host a Web conference via WebEx, convert computer into a voice over Internet protocol (VoIP) phone and reserve multilingual administrative assistance. It offers its services in various countries, such as the United States, Europe, China, Japan, Saudi Arabia, India, Lebanon, France and Australia, among others.

Sovereign Metals Limited is engaged in the mineral exploration, identification and appraisal of resource projects. The Company's segments include exploration in Queensland, Australia (Tate River Project and the Carpentaria Joint Venture) and Malawi (Central Malawi Graphite Project). The Company is focused on exploration and development of the Central Malawi Graphite Project located in Malawi, near the capital city, Lilongwe. Its projects in Queensland, Australia include Mt Marathon, Mt Avarice, Fountain Range, Corella River and Saint Andrews Extended. It also controls approximately 3,790 square kilometers tenement package in central Malawi that contains a number of other flake graphite prospects. These include the Malingunde deposit, which is hosted in saprolite (clay). Its graphite project is Duwi Flake Graphite Project, which is located within its exclusive prospecting license (EPL) 0372 in Malawi, near the capital city of Lilongwe.

Total Face Group Limited is engaged in providing non-invasive cosmetic treatments. The Company provides non-invasive, non-surgical cosmetic procedures throughout its clinic network. The Company has over 14 clinics across Victoria, New South Wales, Queens Land and Australian Capital Territory, which offers approximately three treatment modalities, including Cosmetic Injectables, Skin Solutions and CoolSculpting body fat reduction. Its Cosmetic Injectables include Anti-wrinkle injections, dermal filler treatments and lip enhancements. Its Skin Solutions include Laser skin rejuvenation, Intense pulsed light (IPL), medical grade skin peels, microdermabrasion and skin care. Its face treatment includes microdermabrasion treatment, acne scarring treatment, nose bridge, frown line, jaw slimming and peels. Its body treatment includes hair removal, skin analysis, scar reduction and vein treatment. Its laser treatment includes photo rejuvenation, laser hair treatment and tattoo removal.

Transmetro Corporation Limited is primarily involved in the hospitality sector. The Company's principal activities include the operation of hotels, inns, serviced apartments and theme pubs. Its segments include Hotels, Inns and Apartments, and Theme Pubs. The Metro Hospitality Group is the trading division of the Company, which oversees Metro Hotels, the accommodation arm, and two pubs. Its Metro Hotels comprises over 15 hotels, apartments, resorts and inns through-out Australia. Its Metro Hotels, including Metro Hotel on Pitt, Metro Hotel Tower Mill, Metro Hotel Perth and Metro Hotel Ipswich International are located in Sydney, Brisbane, Perth and Ipswich. Its Metro Apartments are located in Sydney, Melbourne and Gladstone. Its Metro Inn Ryde is located in Sydney. The Metro Hospitality Group operates two pubs-The Elephant Adelaide and Palace Hotel Sydney in Sydney and Adelaide, which offers a range of traditional the United Kingdom, Australian and international beverages and meals.

3D Oil Limited is principally engaged in the exploration and development of upstream oil and gas assets. The Company operates in the development of oil and gas segment within Australia. The Company holds interests in exploration permits in the offshore Gippsland and Otway Basins of South East Australia. The Company's project includes VIC/P57 and T/49P. The VIC/P57 Exploration Permit is located in the north-west offshore Gippsland Basin. The Company holds VIC/P57 exploration permit, which consists the Sea Lion Prospect. VICP/57 also consists of the Felix Prospect, which lies between Esso's Moonfish and Wirrah oil fields. The Company also focuses on exploration on the South East coast of Australia, which is the T/49P exploration permit located in the offshore Otway Basin of Tasmania. T/49P covers an area of approximately 4,960 square kilometers in water depths. 3D Oil T49P Pty Ltd is the Company's subsidiary.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Taruga Gold Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the mineral exploration in West Africa. The Company's exploration assets consist of the Kossa project in Niger and the Mankono project in Cote d'Ivoire. The Kossa Project is located in northwest Niger, approximately 230 kilometers northwest of the capital city Niamey. The Kossa Project is adjacent to the Burkina Faso border and lies approximately 15 kilometers east of the Essakane Gold Mine, located in Burkina Faso. The Borobon prospect is located at the south end of the Kossa-Borobon trend, approximately 10 kilometers strike length of gold mineralization. Its Kossa area consists of over four concessions, such as Kossa 1, Kossa 2, Ouanzerbie and Kouriki. The Cote d'Ivoire licenses are located in areas, including the Tengrela-Tongon area, the Korhogo region, as well as the extensions of the Bonikro and Hounde greenstone belt. Its concession in Cote d'Ivoire consists of the Mankono concession.

Stargroup Limited is engaged in operating banking technology business. The Company is engaged in the sale, deployment and operation of automatic teller machines (ATMs), cash handling and other banking equipment in Australia. The Company is engaged in design, manufacture, sale and operating of ATMs and other banking equipment. The Company has three operational areas: Star Payment Systems (ATM deployment), StarATM (ATM sales, ATM software and support sales) and StarPOS (electronic funds transfer at point of sale (EFTPOS) deployment). It offers basic EFTPOS terminal, full service integrated terminal for detailed reporting, or a portable terminal for payments on the go. It also offers pre-authorization, customer preferred currency, extra services, tipping and pay at table functionality. Its subsidiaries include CashPod ATM Pty Ltd, iCash Asia Pty Ltd, Stargroup Investments Limited, Star Payment Systems Pty Ltd, StarPOS Pty Ltd, StarATM Pty Ltd, StarApps Pty Ltd and StarLabs Pty Ltd.

TBG Diagnostics Limited, formerly Progen Pharmaceuticals Limited, is a biotechnology company. The Company's principal activities include the discovery, research and development of pharmaceutical therapeutics for the treatment of human diseases, and the provision of contract services related to the process development, manufacture and quality assurance of biopharmaceutical products. The Company's segments include Research & Development, and Manufacturing. The Company is primarily engaged in the discovery and development of small molecule-based cancer therapeutics. The Company is focused on the development of the anti-angiogenesis and anti-metastatic oncology products pipeline. The Company's offerings include Muparfostat (PI-88) and PG545. Muparfostat (PI-88) is an anti-angiogenesis and anti-metastatic compound. Muparfostat (PI-88) is a dual angiogenesis and heparanase inhibitor. PG545 is an agent designed to target the tumor microenvironment.

Steamships Trading Company Limited (Steamships) is engaged in shipping, transport, property, manufacturing, hotels and information technology in Papua New Guinea. The Company operates through four segments: Commercial, Hotels and property, Logistics, and Finance and investment. The Commercial segment is involved in the manufacture and distribution of consumer products. The Hotels and property segment owns and operates hotels, and includes the property leasing division. The Logistics segment consists of shipping and land-based freight transport and related services divisions. The Finance and investment segment consists of the head office administration function. The Company operates its hotel division through Coral Sea Hotels, which operates approximately nine hotel and apartment complexes offering hotel facilities and serviced apartments, as well as meeting, conference and banqueting facilities.

Tribune Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the development of exploration, development and production activities at its East Kundana Joint Venture (EKJV) tenements. The Company's EKJV is located approximately 20 kilometers west northwest of Kalgoorlie and approximately 50 kilometers northeast of Coolgardie. Its Japa Concession is located in the Western Region of Ghana, approximately 110 kilometers southwest of Kumasi and approximately 50 kilometers north of Tarkwa, and the concession covers approximately 27.52 square kilometers within the Akropong Belt within the Birimian Supergroup that hosts the Ashanti type lode-gold deposits of West Africa. The Company also operates West Kundana Joint Venture, Mt Celia Project and Seven Mile Hill in Western Australia. The Company's subsidiaries include Tribune Resources (Ghana) Limited, Mount Manning Resources Limited, Melville Parade Pty Ltd and Rand Mining Limited.

T.F.S. Corporation Ltd is principally engaged in the manufacture, sale, distribution, management, ownership and promotion of sandalwood plantations. The Company's segments include Plantation Management, Finance, Sandalwood Products and Pharmaceutical. The Plantation Management segment is responsible for the promotion and sales of Indian sandalwood lots to investors, called growers. The Plantation Management segment is also responsible for the establishment, maintenance and harvesting of Indian sandalwood plantations on behalf of the growers and group owned plantations. The Finance segment is responsible for providing finance to growers to purchase sandalwood lots. The Sandalwood Products segment is responsible for the manufacture of sandalwood oil and products for resale both domestic and internationally. The Pharmaceutical segment is located in the United States and is responsible for research and development of pharmaceutical and biopharmaceutical products for commercializing.
Forest Nurseries & Gathering of Forest Products

Tungsten Mining NL is a resource company. The Company is focused on the exploration and development of tungsten projects in Australia. The Company has three advanced projects in Australia: the Mt Mulgine Project, which is located within the Murchison Region of Western Australia, approximately 350 kilometers north northeast of Perth; Big Hill Project, which is located approximately 30 kilometers northeast of the Nullagine township in the Eastern Pilbara of Western Australia, and Kilba Project, which is located within the Ashburton Region of Western Australia, approximately 250 kilometers southwest of Karratha. Its other projects include Loves Find in the Ashburton region and the Koolyanobbing Project. It has an agreement with Lithium Australia NL to explore for lithium and other metals, on the shores of Lake Seabrook, approximately 60 kilometers north-east of Southern Cross, Western Australia.

Triangle Energy (Global) Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas production and exploration company. The Company is engaged in the divestment of its interests in the Company's Indonesia assets, the continued assessment (and acquisition of additional interest) of the Reid's Dome exploration asset in Queensland and the completion of the Cliff's Head Acquisition in Western Australia. The Company's segments include Held for sale-Indonesian exploration, WA Oil Production and Australian corporate. The Cliff Head oil field is located approximately 10 kilometers off the coast of Western Australia at a water depth of 15 to 20 meters. The field covers approximately six square kilometers in the Commonwealth exploration permit WA-286-P. The Reid's Dome Tenement covers an area of approximately 181 square kilometers on the western flank of the Bowen Basin in Queensland. The Reid's Dome Gas Field is situated within Reid's Dome Tenement.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Silver Heritage Group Limited is engaged in the operation and management of casinos in Nepal and Vietnam, and management of electronic gaming operations in casinos in Laos and Cambodia. The Company's business is divided in two business lines: Operation of casinos, and Provision and operation of electronic gaming machines (EGMs). The Company operates The Millionaire's Club & Casino (TMC) in Kathmandu, Nepal, under its own license, and provides management services to the Phoenix International Club casino (the Phoenix International Club) in Bac Ninh, Vietnam. It provides EGMs to casinos and licensed gaming clubs in Laos and Cambodia. The Company's geographic segments include Laos, Vietnam, Nepal, Cambodia, Macau, Tinian and Other. The Company is focused on development of its casino resort in close proximity to the India-Nepal border, and it seeks to offer its shareholders exposure to Asian gaming, Asian consumers and the outbound tourism markets of India and China.

Santos Limited is an oil and gas producer. The Company's principal activities are the exploration for, and development, production, transportation and marketing of, hydrocarbons. The Company's segments include Eastern Australia, Western Australia and Northern Territory (WA&NT), Asia Pacific and Gladstone LNG (GLNG). It is a producer of natural gas, gas liquids and crude oil in eastern Australia. It sells gas primarily to domestic retailers, industry and for the production of liquefied natural gas. It sells gas liquids and crude oil in the domestic and export markets. Its WA&NT operations include domestic gas and oil production in the Carnarvon Basin, exploration activity in the Browse and Bonaparte basins and its liquefied natural gas (LNG) project, Darwin LNG. It has producing assets in Papua New Guinea, Indonesia and Vietnam and exploration assets in Malaysia, Papua New Guinea, Indonesia and Bangladesh. It has interests in GLNG project, which produces LNG.

Stellar Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration with the objective of identifying and developing economic reserves. The Company's segments include Corporate, Tin/Nickel, Copper/Gold and Other. It operates in the Australian mineral exploration sector where it is pursuing opportunities for a range of mineral targets through various tenements all of which are at exploration-stage. It owns 100% interest in Heemskirk Tin Project, which is located in northwest Tasmania, Australia. The Heemskirk Tin Project consists of over three tin deposits, Queen Hill, Severn and Montana located on the northwestern boundary of Zeehan. It also holds a portfolio of tenements in Tasmania and South Australia that are prospective for base metals, uranium and iron ore. Its exploration portfolio includes EL 46/2003 Heemskirk Tasmania; EL 49/2004 Rayne Tasmania; ELs 5125, 5126 near Coober Pedy and ELs 4573 and 4882 near Kingoonya South Australia, and EL 40/2010 Heazlewood Hill Tasmania.

Templeton Global Growth Fund Limited is an investment company. The Company provides Australian residents with an investment vehicle, which provides them with an access to equity markets across the world. The Company's investment objective is to achieve long-term capital growth from a globally diversified portfolio of investment securities. The Company focuses on long-term appreciation from a globally diversified portfolio, consisting primarily of international securities. The Company invests in various sectors, such as consumer discretionary, consumer staples, energy, financials, healthcare, industrials, information technology, materials and telecommunications services. The Company's primary form of investment is in common equity stocks traded on global stock markets. The Company's investment manager is Franklin Templeton Investments Australia Ltd (FTIAL), a subsidiary of Franklin Resources, Inc.

Thorney Technologies Ltd, formerly Australian Renewable Fuels Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the production and sale of biodiesel. The Company focuses on transforming and recapitalizing itself into a managed listed investment company with special focus on technology investments.

Tegel Group Holdings Limited is involved in breeding, hatching, processing, marketing and distribution of poultry products. The Company also manufactures and markets a range of sausages and other processed meat products. It produces a range of products across its business (such as fresh and frozen whole chickens, fillets and portions), and convenience products (such as cooked and smoked smallgoods, and frozen further processed products). The Company's brands include Tegel, Rangitikei and Top Hat. Its offerings include Tegel Meal Maker Shredded Roast Chicken, Honey Roast Sliced Turkey and Cheese Fresh Chicken Sausages. Domestically, the Company's products are supplied to supermarkets, other retail outlets, processors, hotels, restaurants, distributors and fast food customers. The Company's international markets include Australia, the Pacific Islands, the United Arab Emirates and Hong Kong. Its operations include processing facilities in Auckland, New Plymouth and Christchurch.

Touchcorp Limited is engaged in the development, operation and commercialization of the Touch System Platform, a cloud-based software platform. The Company's segments include Retail Services, which enables transactions in retail stores; Health & Government, enables a range of electronic claiming solutions designed to streamline processing and payments of health insurance claims and entitlement claims at the point of service, and Mobility Services, which enable businesses, such as mobile telecommunications network operators and mobile virtual telecommunications network operators to accept payments and facilitate purchases of electronic products by consumers through self-service methods. The Touch System Platform enables electronic delivery of non-physical products and entitlements through multiple consumer service points. Its other Service Modules include Perimeter Protection, Identification and Activation Systems, Transaction Integrity Systems and Fraud Protection Systems.

TasFoods Limited, formerly OnCard International Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in offering branded food products. The Company offers food products primarily sourced from Tasmania. The Company operates the Meander Valley Dairy business. The Company operates the MarketSmart payment solutions business in Australia.

WPP AUNZ Limited, formerly STW Communications Group Limited, is engaged in advertising and diversified communications operations. The Company provides advertising and communications services for clients through various channels, including television, radio, print, outdoor and electronic forms. Its segments include Advertising, Production and Media, and Diversified Communications. The Advertising, Production and Media segment provides advertising services, television and print production services and media investments for Australia, New Zealand and other countries. The Diversified Communications segment covers a range of marketing communications services. Through its operating companies, it provides a range of services, including advertising and media investment management; data investment management; public relations and public affairs; branding and identity; healthcare communications; direct, digital, promotion and relationship marketing, and specialist communications.

Tiger Resources Limited is engaged in mineral exploration, development, mining and sale of copper cathode and concentrate. The Company operates in minerals exploration, development and production in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) segment. It owns interests in Kipoi Copper Project, Lupoto Copper Project and La Patience Permit project. The Kipoi Copper Project is located approximately 70 kilometers north-northwest of Lubumbashi in the Katanga Province of the DRC. The Kipoi Mining License covers an area of approximately 50 square kilometers and contains over 10 kilometers long copper-cobalt mineralized segment of Upper Roan sediments. The Kipoi Copper project hosts over five copper deposits. The Lupoto Project has a surface area of approximately 140 square kilometers and is located over 10 kilometers to the south of the Kipoi Project area. The La Patience permit has an area of approximately 30 square kilometers and is located over 10 kilometers southeast of the Kipoi Project.

Shaver Shop Group Limited, formerly Lavomer Riah Holdings Pty Ltd, is engaged in the retailing of specialist grooming products through its corporate owned store and franchise store networks. The Company offers its products under various categories, such as electric shavers, including electric shavers and replacement parts; beard trimmers, including beard trimmers, grooming kits, nose and ear trimmers, and beard care; hair clippers; body groomers, including body groomers and long term hair removal, and manual shavers, including men's blades, men's razors, shave brushes, shave sets and accessories, and cut throat razors. It also offers oral care, such as electric toothbrushes, oral irrigation and toothbrush refills; ladies hair removal, including epilators and ladies blades; hair styling, including curlers and stylers; massage, including back massage, circulation boosters, feet massage, hand held massage and neck massage, and well being, including air purifiers, skin care and mirrors.

Thorn Group Limited is a financial services company. The Company provides financial solutions to consumers and businesses. The Company operates through four segments: Consumer Leasing, Business Finance, Receivable Management and Consumer Finance. The Consumer Leasing division is engaged in the leasing of household products. Business Finance division provides financial products to small and medium enterprises, including equipment leasing, trade finance and invoice discounting. Receivable Management division provides receivables management, debt recovery, credit information services, debt purchasing and other financial services. The Consumer Finance division provides personal loans. The Company's subsidiaries include Thorn Australia Pty Ltd, Eclipse Retail Rental Pty Ltd, Rent Try Buy Pty Ltd, CashFirst Pty Ltd, Thorn Equipment Finance Pty Ltd, Votraint No 1537 Pty Ltd, Hudson Legal Pty Ltd and Cash Resource Australia Pty Ltd, among others.

Techniche Limited is engaged in investment in and management of global technology companies. The Company's segments include Urgent Technology, ERST and Corporate/Techniche Ltd. The Urgent Technology business segment supplies contractor management solutions using its e-maintenance software and other data consultancy services conducted by Urgent Technology Limited in the United Kingdom and Europe; Urgent Technology USA LLC in North America, and Urgent Technology Australasia Pty Ltd in Australia and New Zealand. Urgent Technology Limited provides configurable facilities management infrastructure and field service management software to over 30,000 sites around the world. The ERST segment conducts a discrete business supplying data transfer and processing services to European customers through its Hamburg office. The Corporate/Techniche Ltd. segment undertakes a role in managing investments and undertakes overall direction of strategy, including acquisitions and divestments.

TTE Petroleum Ltd is an oil and gas exploration and production company with interests in Australia and the United States. The Company's principal activities include exploration, development and production for oil and gas, and investment in the resources industry. Its segments include Oil and Gas Australia, and Oil and Gas USA. The Company's projects in Texas Gulf Coast include Allen Dome, Boling Dome, Blue Ridge and Markham Dome. The Allen Dome is a piercement salt dome located 50 miles south of Houston in Brazoria County, Texas. The Company owns approximately 360 net acres on the Blue Ridge salt dome. The Company's acreage, known as the Occidental Fee lease, represents a portion of the south-western corner of the Blue Ridge field in Fort Bend County, Texas, approximately 20 miles south of Houston. The Company holds approximately 1,500 net acres in the Markham Dome Field, located in Matagorda County, Texas. Its petroleum tenements in Australia include EP 455.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

TerraCom Limited, formerly Guildford Coal Limited, is resource company with a portfolio of assets in Mongolia and Queensland. The Company is engaged in mineral exploration of mining tenements held across Australia. Its segments include Australia, which is engaged in coal exploration and development activities within Australia, and Mongolia, which is engaged in coal exploration and extraction activities within Mongolia, including the transition from developer to producer. The Company's tenements cover an area of approximately 11,100 square kilometers. Its projects include Northern Galilee Project, Springsure Project, Sierra Project, and Kolan Project (Maryborough Basin). The Company controls both thermal and coking control tenements located in the coal bearing basins of the South and Middle Gobi. It owns and operates the Baruun Noyon Uul (BNU) coking coal mine in Noyon Soum, South Gobi province. The Dund (Mid) Gobi Project consists of two exploration licenses: 12929X and 15466X.

360 Capital Group Limited, formerly Trafalgar Corporate Group Limited, is a property investment and funds management company concentrating on strategic investment and active investment management of property assets. The Company invests in direct property assets, property securities and various corporate real estate acquisitions within Australian real estate markets on a private equity basis. It manages approximately nine investment vehicles holding assets. Its investment philosophy is based around a business plan focused on over three areas of property in Australia: property investment, property funds management, and special situations and opportunistic investment activities. It is focused solely on actively managing Australian-based real estate portfolios across the commercial, retail and industrial sectors. It also has an investment philosophy of co-investing with its clients, aligning its interests and sharing the benefits that property investment provides with its clients.

Tlou Energy Limited is an exploration-stage company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of assets in southern Africa to identify and develop Coalbed Methane (CBM) resources. The CBM tenements are located at Botswana. The Company's Lesedi CBM project has a certified contingent resource of approximately 3.3 trillion cubic feet (TCF). The Lesedi CBM project's prospecting licenses extend for approximately 8,500 square kilometers in the Karoo Kalahari Basin, southeastern Botswana. The Company holds over five prospecting licenses (PLs) in Mamba Area. These permits cover an area of approximately 4,500 square kilometers. The Company has not generated any revenues.

Syntonic Limited, formerly Pacific Ore Limited, is engaged in the provision of mobile technology services to business and consumers. The Company offers sponsored content services, and enables consumers and businesses to access applications and content across the mobile Internet. The Company allows user to access the mobile Internet with approximately two technology solutions, such as Freeway by Syntonic and Syntonic DataFlex. The Company's Freeway by Syntonic allows mobile Internet access on smartphones by having advertisers pay for the data. The Company's Syntonic DataFlex provides mobile split billing solution to separate personal from business use on employee smartphones. It focuses on offering its Syntonic DataFlex solution in the United States, and its Freeway by Syntonic solution in the Southeast Asia, Latin America and the United States. Its subsidiaries include PSF Merger Subsidiary, Inc., Pacific Ore (UK) Limited, Pacific Ore (WA) Pyt Ltd and Pacific Ore Exploration Pyt Ltd.

Tomizone Limited is a provider of connectivity, analytics and location-based services and software to enterprises, brands and public venues. The Company offers enterprise-grade solutions, focusing on accommodation, transportation and hubs, retail, metro and campus, and hospitality verticals. The Company is engaged in the development and commercialization of wireless fidelity (Wi-Fi) software. The Company operates in Australia and New Zealand. The Company offers a range of technology products and services that enable enterprises, venues and brands to connect with their customers. The Company's product, Lightswitch Connect, represents a connectivity, analytics and location-based services solutions. The Company's Concierge 3 Series hotspot-in-a-box provides Wi-Fi in a small environment, such as a cafe, office lobby or floor plan of approximately 200 square meters. Its Chauffeur series provides access to anyone on any backhaul type.

Transurban Group is engaged in the development, financing, operation and maintenance of toll roads networks, as well as management of the associated customer and client relationships. The Company's segments include Victoria (VIC), New South Wales (NSW), Queensland (QLD) and the Greater Washington Area (GWA). Its VIC segment's operations include CityLink operations and development of CityLink Tulla Widening and Western Distributor. Its NSW segment's operations include GLIDe tolling system and the development of NorthConnex. Its QLD segment's operations include AirportlinkM7 and the development of Inner City Bypass (ICB), Gateway Upgrade North and Logan Enhancement Project. Its GWA segment's operations include 95 Express Lanes and the development of I-66, I-395 and Southern Extensions to 95 Express Lanes. The Company manages and develops urban toll road networks in Australia and the United States. Its subsidiaries include Transurban Holdings Limited and Transurban Holdings Trust.

Think Childcare Limited, formerly Think Childcare and Education Limited, is engaged in operating childcare centers. The Company seeks to provide a professional and nurturing family type environment that supports its children through their emotional, social and physical development. It also prepares children for their transition to the school system through government approved Kindergarten programs, providing them with the foundational skills they need for school readiness. It owns, manages and operates over 40 long day childcare facilities in Australia for children between the ages of six weeks and six years old. Its subsidiaries include Baker Street Childcare Education Pty Ltd, Edhod Greensborough Pty Ltd, Edhod Macleod Pty Ltd, Edhod Newcomb Pty Ltd, Edhod Trafalgar Pty Ltd, LEA Childcare Pty Ltd, LEA Cranbourne Pty Ltd, LEA Georges Pty Ltd, LEA Landsdale Pty Ltd, LEA Superior Pty Ltd, Think 2 Georges Hall Geor Pty Ltd and Think Childcare Belmont Pty Ltd. It operates in Australia.

Ten Network Holdings Limited is an entertainment and news content company, with free-to-air television and digital media assets. The Company is engaged in the investment in The Ten Group Pty Limited (Ten Group) and controlled entities, whose principal activities are the operation of multi-channel commercial television licenses in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Adelaide and Perth, and a national online media platform. It operates through two segments: Television and Out-of-Home (Roads and Maritime Services contract (RMS) and Eye US operations). It owns and operates Network Ten, which includes three free-to-air television channels: TEN, ELEVEN and ONE in Australia's five metropolitan markets of Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, Adelaide and Perth, plus the digital platform tenplay. tenplay is a multi-platform catch up television (TV) and video portal that includes all TEN, ONE and ELEVEN shows, plus news, sport and its TV Guide. It covers over 177 different social media channels and accounts.

Tanga Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the identification of suitable gold, copper and base metal exploration and production opportunities in Tanzania. The Company has two exploration focuses in Tanzania: the Singida project and the Geita project. The Singida project covers approximately 985 square kilometers and the Geita project covers approximately 58 square kilometers. In the Singida project area, the Company is developing the Winston gold discovery. At Geita, the Company holds prospecting licenses covering the Mabale Hills gold camp, and holds prospective ground at the Mimbili gold discovery, approximately 20 kilometers east of Bulyanhulu (Acacia Mining). The Singida project consists of over 12 prospecting licenses, covering over 410 square kilometers of Archaean greenstones in Central North Tanzania, approximately 60 kilometers north of Londoni gold resource. The Geita project consists of over 10 prospecting licenses.

Terrain Minerals Limited is an Australia-based minerals exploration company. The Company is engaged in exploration for gold and other mineral resources. The Company is focused on the mineral province, the Eastern Goldfields of Western Australia. The Company's Great Western Project is located approximately 70 kilometers north of Leonora on Weebo pastoral leases and forms part of the Wilsons Patch mining area. The Company's Gimlet Project is located approximately 20 kilometers east of Salmon Gums. It is located in the Fraser Range nickel province in the southeastern extent of Western Australia. The Project area covers a total land area of approximately 470 square kilometers. The Company also operates Rembrandt Gold Project.

Tamaska Oil and Gas Limited is engaged in the acquisition, exploration and production of petroleum and gas properties. The Company's segments include USA and Australia. The Company has interests in several tenements in the West Klondike Prospect, located in Iberville Parish, Louisiana. The West Klondike project includes an area of approximately 640 acres. The Company also operates Fusselman Well, Clayton Johnson #3F. The Fusselman Project is located in the Borden County, Texas. Its subsidiaries include Tamaska Energy LLC, Tamaska Oil and Gas Inc, Tamaska Oil and Gas Illinois LLC and Tamaska Oil and Gas Texas LLC.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Thorney Opportunities Ltd is an investment company. The Company's principal activity is making investments in listed securities. The Company is focused on producing absolute returns for shareholders over the medium to long-term. Its primary focus is on the selection of investments, which enable it to be a catalyst towards unlocking the value in the companies that it identifies. The Company's investment manager is Thorney Management Services Pty Ltd.

Takoradi Limited is an Australian-based minerals explorer and in advanced copper, gold and molybdenum projects in minerals rich areas of Africa and South America. The company explores, defines and advances the projects in Namibia and Ghana and in Chile and Peru. Takoradi has interest in a portfolio of two majorly owned projects and a further interest, through the investment in Metminco Limited in another seven projects. The Mollacas project is located approximately southeast of the town La Serena, North of Santiaga. The Company also maintains an exposure to mineral resource activities in Chile, Peru and South America, through the companys investment held in Metminco Limited (Metminco). The Vallecillo gold-zinc project covers an area approximate of 54 square kilometers of La Serena.

Target Energy Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas exploration and production company. The Company is principally engaged in the development, production and exploration for oil and gas in the United States. The Company's segments include USA Subsidiaries and Australian operations. The Company's portfolio includes Fairway Project and East Chalkley Project. The Company's Fairway Project consists of approximately 4,500 acres, and is part of Wolfberry oil resource play in West Texas. The Company has over 115 well locations on a 40-acre well spacing. The Company's East Chalkley Project is located approximately 33 kilometers southeast of the town of Lake Charles in Cameron Parish in southern Louisiana. The Company operates through its USA subsidiaries, which include TELA Garwood Limited LP, TELA Louisiana Limited Inc and TELA USA Inc.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Traka Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The principal activity of the Company is the exploration of Traka's mineral tenements. The Company's Western Australian exploration interests consist of the Musgrave, Yallalong and Ravensthorpe Projects. The Company has interests in approximately 30 exploration licenses extending over 9,000 square kilometers. The Company's interests consist of approximately 20 exploration license applications. The Yallalong Antimony Project centers on over four exploration tenements covering antimony mineralization in a quartz veined shear zone, which strikes over 10's on kilometers. The Company's interests at Ravensthorpe are in over three separate areas within the Ravensthorpe Greenstone Belt, including Mt Short, Mt Cattlin and Bandalup Gossan. It also maintains a program of project generation both in Australia and overseas.

Talisman Mining Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the exploration for, and development of, base metals and other minerals, including copper, copper-gold, gold and nickel. The Company's operations include Doolgunna Cu-Au Projects, Springfield Project, Monty deposit, Halloween West, Sinclair Nickel Project, Delphi Prospect and Cody Well Prospect. The Doolgunna Cu-Au Projects Joint Venture is between the Company and Sandfire Resources NL (Sandfire), with Sandfire acting as Joint Venture Manager. The Springfield Project comprises approximately 174 square kilometers ground package located approximately 150 kilometers north-east of Meekatharra in the northern Murchison Goldfields region of Western Australia. The Monty deposit is located approximately 10 kilometers from Sandfire's DeGrussa Copper-Gold Mine. The Halloween Project is located approximately 17 kilometers west south-west of Sandfire's DeGrussa Copper-Gold Mine.

Torian Resources Limited (Torian) is an Australia-based gold company. The Company is engaged in exploration and development of mineral interests. The Company's operations consist of exploring and developing gold assets in Western Australia segment. The Company's gold projects include Zuleika JV, Mt Stirling and Malcolm, which are located in the Goldfields region of Western Australia. The Zuleika JV project consists of approximately 120 tenements covering approximately 210 square kilometers located over 50 kilometers northwest of Kalgoorlia. The Mt Stirling Project is located approximately 40 kilometers north west of Leonora in Western Australia. The Malcolm Project is located approximately 20 kilometers east of Leonora. The Company's subsidiaries include Cluff Minerals (Australia) Pty Limited, NSW Gold NL and Torian Exploration Pty Ltd.

Trade Me Group Limited provides online marketplaces that connect people to undertake a transaction or form a relationship. The Company's businesses include providing a new and used goods marketplace, classified advertising for motor vehicles, real estate and employment, online advertising services and other ancillary online businesses. Its segments include General Items, Classifieds and Other. The General Items segment is its online marketplace business. The Classifieds segment represents advertising revenue from each of its three classified advertising sites: Motors, Property and Jobs. Its revenue is generated from basic and premium listing fees. The Other segment reflects all other businesses, including advertising, travel, dating, life and health insurance comparison and general insurance.

Tasmania Mines Limited is a resources company. The Company's principal activities consist of mining and production of magnetite and scheelite, including operation of crushing and concentrating mill at Kara Mine, south of Burnie, Tasmania and sale of its products, and exploration and development of mining tenements. Its primary product, dense medium magnetite, is used for coal washery purposes. Its secondary products, such as scheelite and iron ore fines are used for steelmaking. It operates in Australia and International segments. Its operations consist of exploration, production and sale of magnetite and its scheelite by-product primarily in Australia. It sells scheelite to customers in Europe for use in production of specialty steel, and in the United States for use in lighting industry. It sells magnetite to Australian coal industry, where it is used as a dense medium to wash coal. It has an interest in an exploration license in the Upper Hunter Region of New South Wales.

Talon Petroleum Limited is an Australia-based exploration and appraisal company. The principal activity of the Company is to develop and produce petroleum resources in the United States. The Company operates through the petroleum exploration and production industry segment. The Company's principal asset is its Mosman Rockingham (MR) Olmos Project, which is located in McMullen County, Texas. The project consists of approximately 3,600 acres. The target reservoir is the Olmos tight sandstone. The Company operates approximately one MR Olmos horizontal producing well (Quintanilla OL-1H, working interest 10%), and over two vertical producing wells (approximately 95% working interest).
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Tikforce Limited is an Australia-based regulatory technology company. The Company is engaged in the acquisition and operation of individual identification application developer Misto Pty Ltd and its subsidiary Tikforce Operations Pty Ltd. The TikForce Platform is a cloud-based suite of browser and application-based tools that work together to establish and utilize verified identities and credentials to build certainty in its clients' workforce. It offers Real.id, which is an online login for its credential management, onboarding, and training verification systems. Real.id connects its clients' photo identity with their name and e-mail, and performs an identity check, and also performs bank account verification to verify their online identity. It offers Tik.me, which is a single-point solution that lets its clients upload, store, verify, manage and share their qualifications, licenses and insurances. It also offers Right-to-Work package.

Tassal Group Limited is engaged in hatching, farming, processing, sale and marketing of Atlantic salmon. The Company is an integrated Salmon grower and Salmon and Seafood processor, seller and marketer. The Company's segments include Domestic market and Export market. The Company produces smoked, canned and frozen Tasmanian grown Atlantic salmon products for distribution in retail and wholesale channels throughout Australia and export markets. Its range of brands includes Tassal, Superior Gold and Tasmanian Smokehouse. It operates over three hatcheries that have the capacity to produce approximately 10 million smelt annually. It has approximately six marine regions, where the standard pen has a volume of approximately 11,600 cubic meters and holds salmon to produce over 120 tons once harvested. It has approximately three processing sites, including a smokehouse that produces an average of over 15.4 kilograms of finished product per minute or approximately 3,050 tons every year.

Tian Poh Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration of minerals in Mongolia. The Company focuses on advancing its coal and copper assets in Mongolia. Its projects include Amulet, Mandal-Urgukh, Khangailand and Huabei Kuangye projects. The Amulet project area, which is located across the Umnugovi and Govi-Altai regions of southern Mongolia, is prospective for copper and coal, and covers over 56,354 hectares. The Mandal-Urghukh project, consisting of over five concessions covering approximately 56,668 hectares, is located in the Umnugovi region of southern Mongolia. The concessions are prospective for gold, copper and coal mineralization. The Umnugovi region hosts the Khangailand project area, which covers approximately 12,418 hectares, and is prospective for gold and coal mineralization. The Huabei Kuangye is located in close proximity to the Shinejinst coking coal operation, which contains over 229 metric tons (mt) of Joint Ore Reserves Committee resources and 95mt reserves.

Temple & Webster Group Ltd is an online retailer of furniture and homewares. The Company is engaged in selling of third-party produced furniture and homewares to residential and commercial customers. It is also engaged in the sale of lifestyle products. The Company is a holding company of various operating companies. The Company operates through over two brands, including Temple & Webster, which is an online retailer for the home, and Milan Direct, which is an online retailer of furniture. The Milan Direct business sources private label products under the Milan Direct brand. Temple & Webster has a catalogue of approximately 140,000 products. The Company's subsidiaries include Temple & Webster Pty Ltd, Zizo Home Pty Ltd, TPW Group Services Pty Ltd, Milan Direct Group Investments Pty Ltd, Milan Direct Pty Ltd and Milan Direct UK Pty Ltd.

Seymour Whyte Limited is an engineering and construction company. The Company is engaged in the construction activities in civil and utilities infrastructure across a range of industries. The Company operates through two segments: Civil Infrastructure and Utilities Infrastructure. The Company's Civil Infrastructure segment is responsible for construction projects in transport infrastructure, including roads and bridges. It offers civil infrastructure solutions for rail, aviation, roads, bridges and marine projects. The Utilities Infrastructure segment is responsible for micro tunneling and pipeline infrastructure projects in the water and energy utilities market. It provides multidisciplinary utilities service offering to water, energy, power and resources businesses. The Company has projects in Queensland, New South Wales, Western Australia and Victoria. Its projects include the Townsville Ring Road Project in north Queensland and the Great Western Highway in New South Wales.

Top End Minerals Limited is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company controls exploration tenements in the Northern Territory, Australia. The Company's primary focus is on exploration of base metal project, in the Northern Territory, Australia. The Company's base metal project is located in Arnhem Land and comprises granted tenements EL26206 and EL30051. The Company has mineral rights other than diamonds for the farm-in tenements and holds all mineral rights for two tenements held in its own name. The Company's residual gravity anomaly is associated with an area defined by surface rock chip mineralization. The Company's exploration licenses are held under application and are located on Aboriginal Land. The Company holds various licenses located in western Arnhem Land closer to the East Alligator River uranium deposits (Ranger, Jabiluka, Koongarra, and Nabarlek).

Tanga Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the identification of suitable gold, copper and base metal exploration and production opportunities in Tanzania. The Company has two exploration focuses in Tanzania: the Singida project and the Geita project. The Singida project covers approximately 985 square kilometers and the Geita project covers approximately 58 square kilometers. In the Singida project area, the Company is developing the Winston gold discovery. At Geita, the Company holds prospecting licenses covering the Mabale Hills gold camp, and holds prospective ground at the Mimbili gold discovery, approximately 20 kilometers east of Bulyanhulu (Acacia Mining). The Singida project consists of over 12 prospecting licenses, covering over 410 square kilometers of Archaean greenstones in Central North Tanzania, approximately 60 kilometers north of Londoni gold resource. The Geita project consists of over 10 prospecting licenses.

360 Capital Office Fund is an office sector Australian-real estate investment trust (A-REIT). The principal activity of the Fund is making investments in commercial office properties within Australia. The Fund's objective is to provide consistent and growing income returns and capital growth from a diverse portfolio of office assets owned within a simple capital structure. The Fund focuses on acquiring assets in suburban A and CBD B grade rent collecting properties in Australia. The Fund's property portfolio includes 154 Melbourne Street, Brisbane, Queensland; 438-517 Kingsford Smith Drive, Brisbane, Queensland, and 576 Swan Street, Richmond, Melbourne Victoria. Its 154 Melbourne Street property has a net lettable area of approximately 11,301 square meters. Its 438-517 Kingsford Smith Drive property has a net lettable area of over 9,322 square meters. Its 576 Swan Street property has a net lettable area of approximately 8,331 square meters. 360 Capital Group is the Fund's manager.

Tox Free Solutions Limited offers specialist industrial and waste management services. The Company operates through three segments: Waste Services, Industrial Services, and Technical and Environmental Services. The Waste Services segment includes the collection, resource recovery, recycling and disposal of solid, industrial, municipal and commercial wastes. The Industrial Services segment provides onsite industrial cleaning services, such as tank and drain cleaning, high pressure water jetting, vacuum loading, and liquid and industrial waste collection, to the oil and gas, mining, heavy manufacturing, civil infrastructure, municipal and utilities sector. The Technical and Environmental Services segment includes its network of liquid and hazardous waste management facilities across Australia. The Company provides waste services primarily in regional areas of Australia, including the Kimberley, Pilbara and South West regions of Western Australia, Tasmania and across regional Queensland.

Tigers Realm Coal Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in identification, exploration and development of coal deposits in the Far East of the Russian Federation and the operation of Ugolny Port in Beringovsky. The Company's segments include Amaam Project and Amaam North Project. The Amaam Project is located in the Bering Basin in Chukotka province, Russia and consists of Amaam tenement. The Amaam North Project is located in the Bering Basin in Chukotka province, Russia and consists of Amaam North tenement. It also includes transport and infrastructure assets associated with the Beringovsky port and coal terminal. The Amaam North tenement is located approximately 30 kilometers to the north of the Amaam tenement. The Beringovsky Port and Coal Terminal is located over 35 kilometers to the north east of the Amaam North tenement. The Company's subsidiaries include TR Coal International Limited, Tigers Realm Coal (Cyprus) Pty Ltd and Eastshore Coal Holding Limited.

Troy Resources Limited is engaged in gold and silver production. The Company is engaged in exploration activities principally for gold, at Karouni gold project in Guyana. The Company at its Karouni Block has outlined an inferred resources of approximately 1.6 million ounces (Moz) at the smarts deposit and hicks deposits. The Andorinhas Mine is located in the state of Para in northern Brazil approximately 45 kilometers from the town of Rio Maria, approximately 17 kilometers from the town of Floresta do Araguaia and approximately 310 kilometers from the town of Maraba. The Karouni gold project produced approximately 34,740 ounces of gold and approximately 356,770 tons of ore. The Andorinhas mine produced approximately 8,789 ounces of gold. The Casposo mine operation comprises an open pit, underground mine and a processing plant. The Casposo mine produced approximately 17,210 ounces of gold.

Thred Limited is engaged in the development of Thred, which is a messaging platform, and Web and mobile application specializing in cross platform communication systems. The Company's segments include Hong Kong and Australia. The Company's Thred will be a platform that unifies and centralizes the user's contacts whilst simultaneously providing a centralized communication hub. Thred offers unified social messaging and a private way to share content across multiple networks. Thred combines instant messenger (IM) with e-mail to create a communication experience. The Company's Thred platform consists of Social Microblogging, including reading posts; Group Chats, including creating and managing groups; Global Search; Multi Device, including portable connectivity; Secured Accounts, and Move Forward. Thred offers features, such as cross platform, Office 365 integration, social media integration, user data security, in-application search and multiple conversations.

Traffic Technologies Limited is a traffic solutions company. The Company is engaged in the designing, manufacturing and installation of traffic signals, traffic controllers, pedestrian countdown timers, electronic road signs, emergency telephones, portable roadside technology and road lighting products. It provides directional and regulatory traffic signs and traffic control products to road traffic authorities, municipal councils and construction companies. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is a supplier to the road signage market across Australia. Its portfolio of products and services include technical products, such as Aldridge Traffic Systems, Clearsonics and QTC Traffic Solutions, and signage and safety products, such as De Neefe, Norsign, Sunny Signs and Bob Panich Traffic. It is also involved in the manufacture of traffic controllers. Its manufacturing facility for traffic signals, lighting and intelligent transport systems equipment is based in Rhodes, New South Wales.

Trilogy International Limited is a manufacturer and wholesaler of products in the home fragrance, body care and natural skincare categories. The Company is a distributer of personal fragrance and beauty products. Its segments include Home Fragrance, Bodycare (the Ecoya brand), Natural Products (the Trilogy and Goodness brands) and Distribution (CS&Co Company). Its Home Fragrance & Bodycare segment offers products, including Soy-based home fragrance (candles, diffusers, bodycare). The Natural Products segment offers products, including natural and organic rosehip oil-based and organic chia seed oil skincare range. The Distribution segment is engaged in the third party premium beauty products distribution. The Company provides natural skin care and home fragrance products through the brands, including Trilogy, Goodness and Ecoya in New Zealand and around the world. Its subsidiary, CS&Co, distributes international cosmetics, fragrances, skincare and haircare brands in New Zealand.

Timah Resources Limited is an iron ore mineral exploration company. The Company operates through renewal energy power generation segment. The Company's subsidiary, Mistral Engineering Sdn. Bhd. (Mistral), is a biogas energy company. Mistral is engaged in the business of renewable energy generation. Mistral produces green power from palm oil mill effluent (POME). It operates a Biogas Renewable Energy Plant (Plant) in Malaysia, with nominal capacity of approximately three megawatt. The Plant is located at approximately Km 63 Jalan Sandakan, Lahad Datu, Sandakan in the State of Sabah, Malaysia. The Company operates in Australia and Malaysia.

Titanium Sands Limited, formerly Windimurra Vanadium Limited, is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's segments include Australia and Sri Lanka. Under the Sri Lankan Mineral Sands Project, the Company has an interest in Srinel Holdings Limited (Srinel). Srinel, through its subsidiaries, owns approximately 10 exploration licenses (EL) over 350 square kilometers in various coastal districts of Sri Lanka. The Company focuses on the Mannar Island project in Sri Lanka, comprising the 180 and 182 exploration licenses.

Tian An Australia Limited, formerly PBD Developments Limited, is engaged in the development and sale of residential land and built-form products. It is engaged in property development in Australia. The Company has interests in developments on the east coast of Australia and developments in the Mandurah or peel Region of Western Australia. Its projects include Oceanique, which is located in Port Bouvard, Western Australia; Point Grey, which is located on the peninsula setting on the eastern shores of the Peel Inlet and the Harvey Estuary in the Shire of Murray, Western Australia; Bridgeview, which is located approximately five kilometers from the Sydney central business district (CBD); Burwood Square, which is located within the city center of Burwood; The Milton, which is located within the suburb of Milton and approximately two kilometers from the Brisbane CBD, and SeaSpray, which is located within the suburb of Point Cook and approximately 19 kilometers from the Melbourne CBD.

Transerv Energy Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in oil and gas exploration, development and production. The Company's principal activities include the evaluation of oil and gas exploration projects in Western Australia. The Company's geographic segments include Australia and Canada. The Company has a joint venture held through Latent Petroleum Pty Ltd (Western Australia). The Company holds interest in Warro Gas Project. The Warro field lies 200 kilometers north of Perth in the Perth Basin. The field is located 31 kilometers east of both the Dampier-to-Bunbury Natural Gas Pipeline and the Dongara-to-Perth Parmelia Pipeline. The Warro field is located in RL-7 and RL-6 and covers an area of approximately 7,000 hectares. The Warro Gas Project wells include Warro-5 and Warro-6. The Warro-5 is located approximately 3.5 kilometers south from the previous Warro wells. The Warro-6 is located approximately three kilometers to the northwest of Warro-5. The Warro-4 well was retested.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

360 Capital Industrial Fund is engaged in investment in industrial properties within Australia. The Fund's portfolio comprises approximately 37 industrial assets. The Company has tenants in various sectors, including automotive, real estate, construction, transport logistics, manufacturing, consumer staples, consumer discretionary, and health and pharmaceutical. Its property portfolio consists of 2 Woolworths Way, Warnervale New South Wales; 92-98 Cosgrove Road, Enfield, New South Wales; 29 Glendenning Road, Glendenning, New South Wales; 12 Williamson Road, Ingleburn, New South Wales; 37-51 Scrivener Street, Warwick Farm, New South Wales; 74-94 Newton Road, Wetherill Park, New South Wales; 60 Marple Avenue, Villawood, New South Wales; 6 Macdonald Road, Ingleburn, New South Wales; 30 Clay Place, Eastern Creek, New South Wales; 324-332 Frankston-Dandenong Road, Dandenong South, Victoria; 49 Temple Drive, Thomastown, Victoria, and 8 Penelope Crescent, Arndell Park, New South Wales.

Tech Mpire Limited is a digital performance-based marketing company, which offers performance-based online and mobile marketing solutions. The Company uses its global network of online media partners to enable brands to advertise to their audiences online. The Company also offers nxus, the cloud-based software platform. Its segments include Technology and Performance Marketing. The Technology segment is engaged in the development and maintenance of the nxus platform. The Performance Marketing segment includes its performance marketing operations. The nxus platform provides real-time attribution tracking, analytics and reporting data for online advertising. The Company acts as an intermediary between its advertiser clients and its network of affiliates that deploy digital advertising marketing campaigns to consumers. It provides strategic management of advertising campaigns and selective sourcing of affiliates to develop customer acquisition solutions for advertiser clients.

Transaction Solutions International Limited is an Australia-based company that holds a non-controlling interest in Transaction Solutions International (India) Private Limited (TSI India). The Company is engaged in installing and managing a network of automated teller machines (ATMs) and bill payment systems in India. The Company focuses on identifying and evaluating the other investment opportunities. TSI India holds equity investment in TSI India. TSI India has created an in-house intellectual property (I.P.), and offers products, including electronic surveillance offering (remote security monitoring of an offsite asset, such as an ATM site) and power management solutions (remote electronic monitoring and control of power to offsite assets, such as an ATM site). The Company's subsidiaries include Transaction Solutions International Pty Ltd and Transaction Solutions International (Mauritius) Pty Limited.

TNG Limited is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of its Mount Peake project and Mount Hardy projects; the review of projects for potential acquisition; the management of its other exploration properties, and management of its interest, such as in the Manbarrum and Cawse Extended Projects. The Company operates in mineral exploration in Australia segment. The Mount Peake Vanadium-Titanium-Iron project is located over 230 kilometers north-west of Alice Springs in the Northern Territory. The Mount Hardy Project is located within the Mount Hardy Copper Field, approximately 300 kilometers north-west of Alice Springs. The Mount Hardy project comprises approximately three granted exploration licenses, including EL27892, EL28694 and EL29219, covering an area of approximately 411.36 square kilometers. The Manbarrum project comprises over four tenements, including EL24395, EL 25646, MA24518 and MA26581; over two resources, and various prospects.

Thomson Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration for the discovery and delineation of base and precious metal deposits particularly within New South Wales and the development of those resources into cash flow generating businesses. The Company is exploring in New South Wales for mineral deposits containing gold, tin and copper. The Company is focused on its Bygoo tin discovery in the Ardlethan Tin Field, central New South Wales. Its projects include Byrock and Havilah Projects, Mt Paynter Project, Mt Jacob Project, Achillies-Tooroonga Project Joint Venture and Thomson Fold Belt. The exploration license (EL) covers a significant tin-tungsten (Sn-W) occurrence at Mt Paynter in southern New South Wales. Its tenements include EL 6224, EL 6631, EL 7391, EL 7746, EL 7891, EL 7931, EL 8011, EL 8102, EL 8136, EL 8163, EL 8256, EL 8260, EL 8392, exploration license application (ELA) 5302 and ELA 5350. Its subsidiaries include Lassiter Resources Pty Ltd and Riverston Tin Pty Ltd.

Toro Energy Limited is an Australia-based uranium company with project development and exploration portfolio. The Company's principal activities include advancing the development of the Wiluna Uranium project; expansion and improvement of its Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) resource base; exploration and assessment of its tenement portfolio, and review and execution of value-adding uranium acquisitions at corporate and project level. The Company's segments include Project Evaluation, Exploration and Reconciling. The Company's primary focus is on the development of Wiluna uranium project, which is located approximately 30 kilometers south of the town of Wiluna in the northern goldfields of Western Australia. The Wiluna regional resource contains approximately 80.5 million pounds of Triuranium octoxide (U3O8). Its Theseus project is located near Lake Mackay on the Western Australian/Northern Territory border. It also holds exploration interests in Namibia, Africa.

TPI Enterprises Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the manufacture and supply of alkaloids to international markets. The Company's segment is supplying narcotic raw materials (NRM), including morphine and thebaine to the active pharmaceutical ingredient sector. The Company uses its technology for solvent free extraction of alkaloids from opium poppies. The Company sources its raw materials from Australian poppy growers in Tasmania and Victoria. The Company assists customers with NRM conversions, such as methylation and oxidiation reactions. The Company sells and exports culinary poppy seed throughout Australia and around the world. The Company focuses on manufacture and supply of the products, including concentrate of poppy straw (oripavine), concentrate of poppy straw (thebaine), concentrate of poppy straw (morphine), concentrate of poppy straw (codeine), technical oripavine, technical codeine, noscapine and certified alkaloid impurities.

TTA Holdings Limited is engaged in the distribution of TEAC branded audio and visual consumer electronics products in Australia. The Company's segment is distribution of electronic goods to retailers in the Australian market. The Company's audio products include sound systems, potable digital/analog audio, iPod/iPhone docking systems and clock radios. The Company's visual products are light-emitting diode (LED) flat panel televisions, television combo with built in digital versatile disc (DVD) players, ultra-high-definition (UHD) Smart television, set up boxes and DVD players. The Company's TEAC products are distributed through retailers, including Harvey Norman, JB Hi Fi, Good Guys, Betta Home Living Stores and other state-based retailers. The Company's subsidiary includes TEAC Australia Pty Ltd.

Triton Minerals Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activity is to acquire, explore and develop areas that are prospective for graphite, vanadium, gold, and other precious and base metals and minerals in Australia and Mozambique, Africa. Its segments include Australia, Africa and Treasury. It has graphite projects in Mozambique, Africa. The Company, through its joint venture interest in Grafex Limitada, holds approximately eight exploration licenses, of which six have been granted and two are in application, in the Cabo Delgado Province of northern Mozambique. The licenses include approximately three project areas, such as Balama North Project, Balama South Project and Ancuabe Project. The Balama North and Ancuabe projects are located approximately 230 kilometers and 60 kilometers, respectively, west of Pemba, in northern Mozambique. The Balama South project is located over 35 kilometers south of the Balama township.

Thundelarra Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company operates in the exploration of minerals in Australia segment. The Company has active projects in Western Australia and the Northern Territory. Its main commodity focus is on copper, gold and uranium, although its projects also have potential for the discovery of base metal (lead, zinc, silver and nickel) and graphite mineralization. The Company's projects include Doolgunna project, East Kimberley project, Pine Creek project and Ngalia project. The Doolgunna project in Western Australia hosts the Red Bore and Curara Well projects. The Pine Creek in Northern Territory hosts the Allamber and Copperfield projects. The East Kimberley in Western Australia hosts the Sophie Downs (zinc and copper), Frank Hill (copper) and Keller Creek (nickel) project interests. The Ngalia Basin in Northern Territory is a greenfields uranium prospect that may host in situ leach uranium mineralization.

Tempo Australia Limited is engaged in the construction, maintenance and personal management activities, which include the supply of project management, procurement and site execution services. The Company operates through resources services segment. It serves minerals and metals, oil and gas, and tank farms sectors. It offers structural, mechanical and piping (SMP), electrical and instrumentation maintenance solutions, including maintenance management and execution services; sustaining and minor capital works; shutdowns, and fabrication. It offers construction solutions, including vertical construction packages, turn-key construct services, plant commissioning, and front line workers productivity tools and consultancy. It offers front-end services, including site productivity reviews, productivity tools and consultancy, and constructability reviews. Its subsidiaries include Tempo Engineering Services Pty Ltd, Tempo Personnel Management Pty Ltd and Tempo Global Pty Ltd.

The Reject Shop Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the retailing of discount variety merchandise. The Company offers a range of general consumer merchandise. The Company offers various products, such as toiletries, cosmetics, home wares, personal care products, hardware, basic furniture, household cleaning products, kitchenware, confectionery and snack food, and lifestyle and seasonal merchandise, such as seasonal gifts, cards and wrap, toys, leisure items and home decorations. The Company operates approximately 340 leasehold stores in Australia. The Company's stores are located in metropolitan areas, regional centers and Country towns in shopping centers and standalone sites. The Company's stores are located in various states, including Australian Capital Territory, New South Wales, Queensland, Southern Australia, Tasmania, Victoria and Western Australia.

Talga Resources Ltd is engaged in graphite exploration and development, including trial mining, in Sweden and graphite/graphene research and development through its pilot plant test facility in Germany. The Company operates through three segments: graphite exploration and development in Sweden; gold exploration and evaluation in Australia, and graphite/graphene research and development in Germany. Its graphite projects include Vittangi, Raitajarvi, Pitea, Jalkunen and Pajala. It owns over two iron ore projects, Masugnsbyn and Vittangi, located in Norrbotten County, north Sweden. It owns approximately four gold exploration projects in Western Australia. The Bullfinch project is located in the Yilgarn region, approximately 50 kilometers north of the town of Southern Cross. The other three projects, including Talga Talga, Warrawoona and Mosquito Creek projects are located in the East Pilbara gold region, near the towns of Marble Bar and Nullagine.

Thor Mining PLC is an exploration and development company. The Company's principal activities include the exploration for and potential development of tungsten deposits and exploration for, and potential development of, gold projects. Its segments include Australia and the United States. It has a portfolio of properties in Australia in the Northern Territory and in Western Australia. Its projects include Molyhil tungsten project, Pilot Mountain Tungsten Project, Dundas Gold Project and Spring Hill Gold Project. Its Molyhil tungsten project is located 220 kilometers (km) north-east of Alice Springs within the prospective polymetallic province of the Proterozoic Eastern Arunta Block in the Northern Territory. Its Pilot Mountain Tungsten Project is located approximately 200 kilometers south of the city of Reno and 20 km east of the town of Mina. It holds interest in Dundas Gold Project. The Spring Hill project is located approximately 150 km south of Darwin in the Northern Territory.

Timpetra Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in identifying, assessing and investing in gold and other business opportunities. The Company makes investment in exploration of gold resources. The Company is assessing and developing an exploration program over the Jillewarra joint venture Project.

Truscott Mining Corporation Limited is engaged in the exploration and development of gold and base metal projects in the Northern Territory. The Company manages an exploration program over mineral projects. Its projects include Westminster Project, Ewan Edward Project, Arcadia Project and Olympus Project. The Westminster project area is located west of the Tennant Creek Township in the center of the Tennant Creek Goldfield and encompasses an area of approximately 5.96 square kilometers. The Ewan Edward Project is located over 20 kilometers east of Tennant Creek, which contains the primary exploration nodes Lyall and Hera, and covers approximately two interpreted trends of mineralized lodes. The Arcadia Project are shallow historical gold workings associated with ironstones, located within granted mineral leases central (MLC) 621 and MLC622. The Olympus Project is located over 25 kilometers to the West of the Tennant Creek Township within tenement exploration license (EL) EL27145.

TZ Limited is engaged in the development of intelligent devices and smart device systems that enable the commercialization of hardware and software solutions for the management, control and monitoring of business assets and the provision of associated value added services through its subsidiaries globally. The Company operates in the United States, Australian and Asian markets. It fuses software control, remote locking and fastening, environmental sensing and real time dynamic analysis to enable devices to sense, act, lock and audit activity based on secure instructions delivered over the Internet. Its enablers include addressability, integrated sensing, processing power and shape memory alloy (SMA) actuation. Its applications include data center cabinet security, smart lockers and aero asset locking systems. Its installations include Packaged Asset Delivery, SingPost POP Station Lockers, POS Indonesia Parcel Lockers, UTS Housing Parcel Lockers and Poste Italiane Parcel Lockers.

Technology One Limited is engaged in the development, marketing, sales, implementation and support of enterprise business software solutions. The Company's segments include Sales and Marketing, which includes sales of license fees and customer support; Consulting, which offers implementation and consulting services; Plus, which offers software development services for purpose built applications; Research and development, which includes the research, development and support of its products; Cloud, which includes delivery of cloud hosting services, and Corporate. Its enterprise business software solutions include TechnologyOne Financials, TechnologyOne Spatial, TechnologyOne Enterprise Asset Management, TechnologyOne Student Management, TechnologyOne Stakeholder Management and TechnologyOne Supply Chain. Its corporate performance management software solutions include TechnologyOne Business Intelligence, TechnologyOne Budgeting & Forecasting, and TechnologyOne Performance Planning.

Tesserent Limited is an Australia-based company, which provides Internet security-as-a-service to a range of Australian and international customers, including education providers, corporate enterprises, and government customers. Its Security-as-a-service packages security services for a customer's computer infrastructure, including firewall, authentication, anti-virus, antimalware/spyware, intrusion detection, and security event management, amongst other services. The Company operates in two segments, which include IT Security Managed Services and Software Licensing. The Company offers various security services, which include firewall; fiber Internet; Web filtering; e-mail filtering, and data center and cloud. The Company offers fiber Internet for schools. The Company also offers Internet management platform, which is an integrated, identity-based appliance that enables educational institutions to secure and manage their Internet connections.

Threat Protect Australia Limited provides monitored security solutions. The Company operates as a security agency. The Company offers round the clock safety of Australian homes and businesses. The Company offers a Grade A1 security control room. The Company offers security personnel and corporate risk consultancy. The Company offers a range of security systems, including Evacuation Systems, closed circuit television (CCTV) and Access Control. The Company offers guarding services, including on-site security, executive protection, concierge services and secure transport. The Company provides investigation services, including risk management consultancy, such as surveillance, counter surveillance, security audits, threat assessments, corporate investigations and due diligence. It offers a range of intercoms in audio or video, color or black or white, which can be integrated with an access control system to open doors and gates. It also offers alarm products.

360 Capital Total Return Fund is an opportunistic fund. The Fund invests in various forms of Australian real estate assets. Its objective is to deliver a total return of over 12% plus per annum through disciplined investment in a range of real estate opportunities, including repositioning assets, including short term re-leasing positions and refurbishment projects; investing in investment properties that generate rental income; underwriting potential capital raisings in the real estate sector, including syndicates and both unlisted and listed funds; taking strategic positions in unlisted funds; capitalizing on mispriced trading opportunities within Ascendas Real Estate Investment Trust (AREIT) sector; participating in mergers and acquisition activities occurring within the Australian real estate markets, and participating in special situations, which arise within Australian real estate markets, including distressed sales, investments with restructuring potential, and providing loans.

Triple Energy Limited is engaged in the exploration for natural resources. The Company is focused on the oil and gas sector. The Company is focused on investing in oil and gas projects in both the conventional and unconventional (coal seam gas and shale oil and gas) sectors, along with power generation. The Company has a Joint Venture (JV) interest in a coalmine gas project in the Heilongjiang province of the People's Republic of China. Under the JV agreement, it has rights to approximately four other coal bed methane (CBM) areas in the Heilongjiang Province in the People's Republic of China, including the Jixi area. The Company is also focused on acquiring interests in CBM blocks in Shaanxi Province, China. The Company's subsidiaries include Tango Energy, Inc, which holds interests in oil and gas exploration; CFT Heilongjiang (HK) Ltd, which is engaged in oil and gas investment, and Heilongjiang Aolong Energy Co.
