Ltd., which is engaged in coal mine gas exploration.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Tamawood Limited (Tamawood) is engaged in offering home design, project management services and associated activities, including home contract construction activities in various markets, and franchising and licensing operations, among others. The Company operates through four segments: Construction QLD, Construction NSW, Franchises and Renewable Energy. The Construction QLD segment offers services in Queensland markets. The Construction NSW segment offers services in New South Wales. The Franchises segment offers franchising and licensing operations in Queensland, New South Wales, Australian Capital Territory (ACT) and New Zealand. The Renewable Energy segment is engaged in generating and trading renewable energy certificates associated with solar projects. The Company's subsidiaries include Dixon Build Pty Ltd, Dixon NSW Pty Ltd, DixonRes Pty Ltd, Dixon Systems Pty Ltd, SolarpowerRex Pty Ltd and SolarRex Pty Ltd.

TPG Telecom Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the provision of consumer, wholesale and corporate telecommunications services. The Company conducts its operations through three segments: TPG Consumer, TPG Corporate and iiNet. The TPG Consumer segment provides retail telecommunications services to residential and small business consumers. The TPG Corporate segment provides telecommunications services to corporate, government and wholesale customers. The iiNet segment provides telecommunications and technology services to residential and business customers. The Company's telecommunications services include the provision of data, Internet, voice, telehousing, network capacity and other services to consumers and corporate customers. The Company provides a range of National Broadband Network (NBN) services. The Company also provides broadband services over its fiber to the building network.

Telstra Corporation Limited (Telstra) is a telecommunications and technology company. Its principal activity is to provide telecommunications and information services for domestic and international customers. The Company operates through four segments. The Telstra Retail segment provides telecommunication products, services and solutions across mobiles, fixed and mobile broadband, telephony and Pay television/Internet Protocol television and digital content. The Global Enterprise and Services segment provides sales and contract management for business and government customers. The Telstra Operations segment offers overall planning, design, engineering and architecture and construction of Telstra networks, technology and information technology solution. The Telstra Wholesale segment provides a range of telecommunication products and services delivered over Telstra networks and associated support systems to other carriers, carriage service providers and Internet service providers.

Urbanise.com Limited develops software that enables building operators to automate, streamline, simplify and optimize building operations and performance. The software is complemented by remote sensors that monitor various assets to provide visibility and response. The Company's segments include Urbanise and Mystrata. The Urbanise segment includes platform licensing and professional services. The Mystrata segment includes a building financial management platform. The Company offers the Urbanise platform, which includes various functionalities, such as community and property management, asset maintenance, mobile workforce, operation center, asset monitoring, utility reporting, e-commerce for services and customer portal. The Company through its subsidiary, Mystrata Holdings Pty Limited, offers a technology, which allows customers to manage portfolios of apartment buildings, condominiums, co-ops, housing estates and commercial towers.

TTG Fintech Limited is an investment holding company. The Company is a financial technology service provider. The Company's subsidiaries are engaged in provision of system development and information technology services and information technology services, sale of point-of-sale machines and licensing for sale and installation of an internally generated smart cloud-supported point-of-sale system Tlinx in the People's Republic of China (the PRC). The Company has developed Financial Electronic Authentication (FEA) technology. By combining bank-card and non-bank-card accounts, FEA technology allows clearing and settlement of digital currencies and payment of commissions. Its Tlinx accommodates varying payment methodologies, such as cash, bank card, debit card, Quick Response (QR) code, Near field communication (NFC), mobile payments and payments by royalty points. Tlinx also allows for data transmission and supports various customer relationship management (CRM) functions.

Tyranna Resources Limited is a resource company. The Company is engaged in mineral exploration and project development. The Company's segments include exploration international, exploration WA, shipping and exploration. The Company's primary focus is on the Jumbuck Gold Project, which comprises over 8,000 square kilometers of contiguous tenements surrounding one million-ounce challenger gold mine in the Gawler Craton of South Australia. The Jumbuck Gold Project is located in north-western South Australia, on the western edge of the Gawler Craton. The Golf Bore Prospect is one of seven advanced prospects at Jumbuck, all of which are located within approximately 50 kilometers from the Challenger minesite. The Wilcherry Hill Project consists of four tenements and covers an area of approximately 976 square kilometers. The Wilcherry Hill Project is located in South Australia, approximately 30 kilometers north of the township of Kimba.

Terramin Australia Limited (Terramin) is an Australia-based company engaged in the development of and exploration for base and precious metals (in particular zinc, lead and gold) and other economic mineral deposits. The Company operates in two segments: Australia and Northern Africa. The Australia segment is engaged in exploring, developing and mining zinc, lead and gold deposits. The Northern Africa segment is engaged in developing a zinc deposit. The Company's projects include the Oued Amizour Zinc Project, which includes the Tala Hamza zinc deposit; Bird-in-Hand Gold Project, which is located approximately 30 kilometers north of Terramin's mining and processing facilities at the Angas Zinc Mine; Angas Zinc Mine, which is located approximately two kilometers outside the town of Strathalbyn; Adelaide Hills Project, which consists of over 10 contiguous exploration tenements; Gawler Ranges Project, which hosts the Menninnie Dam deposit.

TV2U International Limited, formerly Galicia Energy Corporation Limited, is a wholesale television provider to business-to-business clients. The Company's services include systems integration and solution delivery, managed service content hub for Internet video, and customization and localization. Its platforms include encoder, which encodes and transcodes both live and file-based content into the desired playout and mezzanine formats for operators for distribution into direct to home, cable and over-the-top content networks; iVan, which is an intelligent origin server; iVAN CMS, which is a modular, end-to-end platform for the management and delivery of live and on-demand video-based content services to set-top box, personal computer, wireless and consumer electronics devices, and analytics platform, which provides feedback on all the customer data that is required in order to operate, manage and market a television platform. It also offers iVan Traffic management and application.

Traditional Therapy Clinics Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in providing healthcare services in the People's Republic of China. The Company's segments include Franchise Clinics and Owned Clinics. The Franchise Clinics include approximately 310 Franchise Clinics located in over 27 administrative divisions in China. The Owned Clinics segment includes approximately 20 Owned Clinics in Chongqing, Zhejiang, Sichuan, Jiangsu, Yunnan, Fujian, Guangxi, Guangdong and Hainan. The Company operates under Fuqiao brand and is a franchisor and owner of traditional therapeutic health and wellness clinics in China. The Company operates through its network of approximately 330 franchised and owned clinics.

Tatts Group Limited is engaged in the operation of regulated lotteries, conducting wagering and sports betting, conducting game machine monitoring and supply of jackpot, and provision of third party installation and maintenance services for gaming, wagering, lottery and other transactional equipment and systems. The Company's segments include Lotteries, which includes the operation of lottery licenses, the operation of a Lottery Operator Agreement in Queensland, South Australia, and an agreement in Northern Territory to conduct lotteries; Wagering, which includes totalisator and fixed odds betting on thoroughbred, harness, greyhounds and other sporting events; Maxgaming, which includes gaming machine monitoring and services in Queensland, New South Wales and the Northern Territory, and Bytecraft Systems, which includes warehousing, installation, relocation and maintenance of gaming machines, lottery and wagering terminals, and other transaction devices in Australia and New Zealand.

Treasury Wine Estates Limited is engaged in grape growing and sourcing; wine production, and wine marketing, selling and distribution. The Company's segments include Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), which is engaged in the manufacture, sale and marketing of wine within Australia and New Zealand, and distribution of beer and cider under license in New Zealand; Americas, which is engaged in the manufacture, sale and marketing of wine within the Americas region; Asia, which is engaged in the sale and marketing of wine within the Asia (including the Middle East and Africa), and Europe, which is engaged in the manufacture, sale and marketing of wine within Europe and Latin America. It is also engaged in the sale of branded wines, principally as a finished, bottle product. The Company's wine portfolio includes Commercial, Masstige and luxury wine brands, such as Penfolds, Beringer, Lindeman's, Wolf Blass, Stag's Leap, Chateau St Jean, Beaulieu Vineyard and Sterling Vineyards.

Tower Limited is a New Zealand-based company, which is engaged in the provision of general insurance. The Company's geographical segments include New Zealand and the Pacific region. The New Zealand segment comprises general insurance business written in New Zealand. The Pacific Islands segment includes general insurance business with customers in the Pacific Islands written by Tower Insurance Limited's subsidiaries and branch operations. It offers a mobile application, SmartDriver, which can help users manage their driving by giving them tips along the way. SmartDriver application collects basic driving information through the numerous sensors within users' smartphone, including the accelerometer and the global positioning system (GPS). Its Claim4Car is an application that lets users pre-load details about their vehicle and any drivers, and then walks them through the information they need for their insurance claim. It offers premium contents, plus contents and standard contents.

Tychean Resources Limited is engaged in the natural resources exploration and development. The Company's segments include Spargoville, Suplejack and Valley Floor Resources. Its projects include Spargoville Project, Valley Floor Project and Tanami Project. Its Spargoville project is located in Eastern Goldfields in Western Australia. It has exploration tenement package of approximately 30 granted mining leases, over two granted exploration licenses, approximately five prospecting licenses and over two miscellaneous licenses. The total exploration area is approximately 11,440 hectares. The Valley Floor Project is located in the Eastern Goldfields directly south of Kambalda, Western Australia and covers an exploration area of approximately 40 square kilometers. It consists of the granted exploration licenses, including E15/1399, E15/1434, E15/1249 and E15/1249. The Tanami Project has over 1,700 square kilometers prospective land package within the Tanami Complex, Northern Territory.

TW Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in evaluating investment opportunities and identifying acquisition targets. The Company intends to hold interests in AusCann Group Holdings Limited (AusCann). AusCann is a medical cannabis company. AusCann is engaged in the cultivation and manufacture of medical cannabis products.

TPC Consolidated Limited, formerly Tel.Pacific Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the provision of retail electricity and gas services to residential and businesses, and the provision of pre-paid mobile and related services in Australia. The Company operates through the segments, including Energy Services and Telecommunication Services. The Company's core business is around the Mobile Real Time Monitoring platform (MRTM), which is an intelligent network connected to a mobile network. The Company is a Mobile Virtual Network Operator (MVNO) and Mobile Virtual Network Enabler (MVNE). The Company's product line consists of Hello Mobile and Gotalk Mobile, which are sold to consumers. The Company also has wholesale customers on its MRTM platform. The Company's subsidiary, CovaU Pty Limited (CovaU), is engaged in the reselling of electricity and gas services. The CovaU services are also sold to both business and residential consumers.

TopTung Limited is engaged in acquisition of exploration tenements and carrying out mineral exploration activities on those tenements, and assessing other business development and research opportunities in the minerals industry. The Company focuses on Torrington Tungsten and Topaz Project. The Company holds EL 8258 and EL 8355, which comprise the Torrington Tungsten and Topaz Project in northeastern New South Wales. Its tenements, which are contiguous, cover an area of approximately 50 square kilometers. The Torrington project is located in northern New South Wales, approximately 240 kilometers south-west of Brisbane, Queensland, and over 400 kilometers north of Newcastle, New South Wales, in proximity to the Torrington Township approximately 45 kilometers south-west of the local Shire town of Tenterfield. The Torrington region and the area of the Torrington Pendant, within which Torrington Project is located, contain concentrations of tungsten, topaz, bismuth and gold mineralization.

UIL Energy Ltd (UIL Energy) is engaged in oil and gas exploration. The Company's principal activity is the exploration for reserves of both conventional and unconventional natural oil and gas. The Company is focused on gas and liquids plays with a portfolio across the Perth basin. Its exploration portfolio also has pipeline infrastructure in place to UIL Energy's permits. Its focus is on the Perth Basin where its targets gas and liquids plays and prospects in over two separate project areas where the Company has over 700,000 acres. Its projects in perth basin include north perth-multiple stacked plays for gas and liquids having approximately 250,000 net acres, and central perth-conventional and basin centered gas play having approximately 250,000 net acres. It also holds additional permit interests in the Perth Basin, including the Ocean Hill prospect. UIL Energy's petroleum tenements include EP 447, EP 488, EP 489, EP 495, EPA 82, EPA 98 and EPA 99.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

US Residential Fund is an Australia-based fund, which operates through the United States single-family home residential property market segment. The Fund's investment objective is to create and deliver long-term shareholder value through investment in the United States residential property market. The Fund provides investors with an opportunity to gain an investment exposure to the United States residential property market. The Fund has a portfolio of established rental houses in over three states, such as Texas, Georgia and Ohio. The investment objective also includes expanding and diversifying in the United States residential market through direct and indirect property investments, utilizing both debt and equity instruments to facilitate the transactions. Its investments include single-family homes, apartment complexes (multifamily) and strategic positioning of single-family homes.

USCOM Limited is engaged in the development, design, manufacture and marketing of premium non-invasive cardiovascular and pulmonary medical devices. The Company manages a network of distribution partners across the world for the sale of its equipment to hospitals and other medical care locations. Its geographic segments include Australia, Asia, the Americas, Europe and Mid East and Africa, and Other Regions. The Company has approximately three practice suites of devices in the field of cardiac, vascular and pulmonary monitoring, including the USCOM 1A, which is an advanced hemodynamic monitor that measures cardiovascular function, detects irregularities and is used to guide treatment; USCOM BP+, which is a supra systolic oscillometric Central Blood Pressure monitor that measures blood pressure and blood pressure waveforms only previously available using cardiac catheterization, and the Uscom SpiroSonic spirometers, which is a digital pulmonary testing device.

Viking Mines Limited is engaged in investing in mineral exploration projects. The Company's geographical segments include the resources sector in Ghana and Mongolia. The Company's mineral licenses are located in southern Ghana, West Africa, in the Ashanti Gold Belt. The Company's projects in Ghana include the Akoase Gold Project and the West Star/Blue River Joint Venture Project. The Akoase Gold Project is located approximately 130 kilometers north-northwest of Accra in southern Ghana. The West Star/Blue River Joint Venture Project is located approximately 190 kilometers west of Accra. The Company's projects in Mongolia include the Berkh Uul Coal Project and the Khonkhor Zag Coal Project. The Berkh Uul Coal Project is located approximately 400 kilometers north of Ulaanbaatar in northern Mongolia within the Orkhon-Selege coal district. The Khonkhor Zag Coal Project is an anthracitic coal project located approximately 1,400 kilometers southwest of Ulaanbaatar in Western Mongolia.

Ultima United Limited is a property development company. The Company focuses on developing residential houses and apartment units in Western Australia. The Company's segments include Property Development and Corporate. The Company's projects include Bentley Development, Cannington Development and Como Development. The Bentley development consists of approximately two sites, which cover a total area of over 1,622 square meters. The Cannington Property consists of approximately 1,260 square meters of vacant land. The Bentley development is located at 19-21 Tate Street, Bentley. The Cannington development is located at 3 Oak Street, Cannington. The Como development is located at 295 Canning Highway, Como. The Company intends to construct approximately 10 apartments on the Bentley development. The Company intends to construct approximately 10 apartments on the Cannington Property.

US Residential Fund is an Australia-based fund, which operates through the United States single-family home residential property market segment. The Fund's investment objective is to create and deliver long-term shareholder value through investment in the United States residential property market. The Fund provides investors with an opportunity to gain an investment exposure to the United States residential property market. The Fund has a portfolio of established rental houses in over three states, such as Texas, Georgia and Ohio. The investment objective also includes expanding and diversifying in the United States residential market through direct and indirect property investments, utilizing both debt and equity instruments to facilitate the transactions. Its investments include single-family homes, apartment complexes (multifamily) and strategic positioning of single-family homes.

Venture Minerals Limited is engaged in the exploration for mineral reserves within Australia and Thailand. The Company's prospects named Pak Yang and Thali are located in the Loei Belt, which hosts copper and gold deposits, including Kingsgate's Chatree deposit and PanAust's Phu Kham deposit. Its Tasmanian Operations are located in northwest Tasmania approximately 125 kilometers south from the Port of Burnie. Its Tasmanian tenement exploration area covers over 186 square kilometers encompassing the south and eastern margins and metamorphic aureole of the Meredith Granite. Its Riley DSO Project is located approximately 10 kilometers from the Mt Lindsay Tin-Tungsten Deposit and occurs as a hematite rich pisolitic and cemented laterite. The Company's Livingstone DSO Hematite deposit is located approximately 3.5 kilometers from the Company's Mt Lindsay Tin-Tungsten deposit.

US Masters Residential Property Fund (the Fund) is an Australia-based property trust. The Fund is primarily involved in investing in the United States residential property market. It is a provider of urban single-family home rentals focused on New York metropolitan area single-family housing. The Fund seeks to invest in undervalued neighborhoods experiencing growth and gentrification specifically Hudson County, New Jersey, and Brooklyn, Manhattan, and Queens, New York. The Fund's portfolio of New York metropolitan area residential housing and apartments consists of approximately 1,950 housing units across approximately 570 freestanding houses and approximately 30 apartment buildings. URF Investment Management Pty Limited is its investment manager. Walsh & Company Investments Limited is the responsible entity of the Fund.

Vealls Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the business of agriculture, real estate, investment and negotiable securities. The Company's segments include Investments and Agriculture. The Investment segment consists of interest bearing deposits, listed shares and freehold land at Mt Martha Vic. The Agriculture segment consists of forestry business, which is conducted at Foret de Leyde near Moulins, France. The Company's subsidiaries include VL Investments Pty Ltd, Cardrona Ski Resort Ltd and Vealls (Singapore) Pte Ltd.

Viento Group Limited (Viento) is an Australia-based company specialized in Civil Contracting, Switchroom Services, and Land Subdivisions. Viento Group operates the following divisions: Viento Contracting Services (VCS) provides construction services to the civil and mining industries; Mineworks, another subsidiary of Viento Group, supplies a comprehensive range of mining support services and products through its operational areas  equipment hire and sales, maintenance services, agency support, and labour hire; HVLV delivers robust, reliable and durable switchrooms to clients all across Australia. Power Infastructure Services (Powins) is 55% owned by HVLV is electrical switchgear and service solution company that provides electrical services to the mining and heavy industry sectors. Viento undertakes residential land sub-divisions for investors.

Volpara Health Technologies Limited is a New Zealand-based research, development and manufacturing company. The Company operates through the sale of a single suite of medical device software products segment. Its geographic segments include America and South America, Europe, Asia and Middle East, and Australia and New Zealand. The Company provides breast imaging analytics and analysis products that help in clinical decision-making and the early detection of breast cancer. Its offerings include VolparaEnterprise, which enables breast imaging providers to perform control checks; VolparaDensity, which provides objective assessment of a woman's breast density; VolparaAnalytics, which includes a reporting dashboard for breast imaging centers, and VolparaDoseRT, which provides clinicians with patient-specific x-ray dose and applied compression pressure based on a woman's breast composition. Its subsidiaries include Volpara Solutions Limited, Volpara Solutions Inc and Matakina UK Limited.

Universal Biosensors, Inc. is a specialist medical diagnostics company. The Company is focused on the research, development and manufacture of in vitro diagnostic test devices for consumer and professional point-of-care use. The Company's subsidiary, Universal Biosensors Pty Ltd, conducts its research, development and manufacturing activities. The Company uses its electrochemical cell technology platform to develop point-of-care testing systems for a range of different markets. The Company is engaged in the development of its own Prothrombin Time International Normalized Ratio (PT-INR) test for use in decentralized settings, including the patient self-test market. It is engaged in demonstrating the various applications of its technology platform, including its application to diagnostic tests based on enzymatic, immunoassay and molecular diagnostic methods. It has developed a blood glucose test with LifeScan, Inc. and a coagulation PT-INR test with Siemens Healthcare Diagnostics Inc.

Victor Group Holdings Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in conducting enterprise management training programs. The Company's consultation and advisory services are offered to entrepreneurs for the management and strategic planning of their companies. The Company's segments include training and consulting services, and Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS). The training and consulting services segment includes management consulting service. The IaaS segment includes system maintenance, backup, resiliery and computing resources services over Internet. IaaS is a form of cloud computing that provides virtualized computing resources over the Internet. The Company's operating model focuses on carrying out seminars and specific enterprise management consulting courses. The Company's business involves providing Enterprise Management Consulting Services (EMCS), which include marketing management training and consulting courses that are delivered offline and face to face.

Variscan Mines Limited is engaged in the exploration for economic base and precious metals, and tin and tungsten deposits. The Company's segments include exploration projects funded directly by the Company operating in France and Australia, and Investments in other companies. The Company's geographical segments are Australia and France. The Company's primary targets are base metal (copper, lead, zinc and nickel), precious metal (gold and silver), and tin and tungsten deposits. The Company's projects in Europe include Merleac zinc project, St Pierre gold project, Beaulieu tin project, Tennie base metal project, Silfiac base metal project and Loc Envel tungsten project. The Company has projects in Curnamona craton region, including Mundi Plains (Teck Australia), Junction Dam (Teck Australia, Marmota Energy and Eaglehawk), Callabonna and Quinyambie (Red Metal) and Hillston (Perilya).

Venus Metals Corporation Limited is engaged in exploration of mineral tenements in Western Australia. The Company is focused on the exploration and development of its base metal projects, which are prospective for copper and zinc, as well as its precious and specialty metals. It has license applications over five strategic lithium-tantalum project areas in Western Australia, which include the Pilgangoora Northeast; Wodgina South projects in the Pilbara; the Nardoo Well project in the Capricorn; the Poona Project in the Murchison, and the Greenbushes project in the southwest of Western Australia. It also holds two granted tenements (E52/3068 and E52/3069) and an application (ELA 52/3320) covering its Doolgunna project. Its tenements covering the southern Manindi Trend (E 57/983 and E 57/986) are located over 600 kilometers north northeast of Perth and form part of the Company's Youanmi base and precious metals project covering over 524 square kilometers of the Youanmi greenstone belt.

United Overseas Australia Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the land development and resale, and investment properties. The Company's land development and resale is focused on residential and commercial development in Asia. The Company's segments include Land development and Sale, Investment and Other. The Company's developments include Vertical Office Suites (commercial) and Scenaria@North Kiara Hills (residential).

Victory Mines Limited is an Australia-based exploration company. The Company's principal activities include project acquisition. The Company's segments include mineral exploration and development, and treasury. Its geographical segments include Australia and Bolivia. The Company holds interest in the Bolivian projects. The Company focuses on other opportunities in the resources sector. The Company's subsidiaries include Victory Exploration Pty Ltd and South American Tin Limited (SAT). SAT's Bolivian subsidiary, Compania Minera Gondwanaland S.A., holds contractual rights to several mining projects prospective for tin and other metals in Bolivia. Its Siglo XX Tin Mine includes San Pedrito Project to the immediate south of Siglo XX and various tailings stockpiles associated with the Siglo XX Mine.

Vealls Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the business of agriculture, real estate, investment and negotiable securities. The Company's segments include Investments and Agriculture. The Investment segment consists of interest bearing deposits, listed shares and freehold land at Mt Martha Vic. The Agriculture segment consists of forestry business, which is conducted at Foret de Leyde near Moulins, France. The Company's subsidiaries include VL Investments Pty Ltd, Cardrona Ski Resort Ltd and Vealls (Singapore) Pte Ltd.

Vietnam Industrial Investments Limited is an Australia-based investment holding company. The Company has various investments in Vietnam through its operating subsidiaries. It operates through two segments: Steel Making and Steel Products. The Steel Making segment includes the manufacturing and selling of wire rod and rebar activities of Vinausteel Limited and SSESTEEL Ltd (SSESTEEL). The Steel Products segment includes the operations of Austnam Joint Stock Corporation (Austnam), Total Building Systems Ltd (TBS) and VRC Weldmesh (Vietnam) Limited, which are engaged in manufacturing and trading of steel roofing and steel frames; engineering and project management services, and manufacturing and trading welded wire mesh. Austnam produces metal roofing and cladding from its factory in Hanoi. SSESTEEL owns and operates an automated rolling mill located in Hai Phong, Vietnam. TBS supplies engineering/construction services, commercial and industrial buildings, and civic works in Vietnam.

Vicinity Centres RE Ltd, formerly Federation Centres Limited, is a real estate investment trust (REIT), which focuses on owning, managing and developing Australian assets across the retail range. The Company's principal activities are property investment, property management, property development, leasing and funds management. The Company's segments include Property Investment and Strategic Partnerships. The Property Investment segment consists of net property income derived from investment in retail property. The Strategic Partnerships segment consists of fee income from property management, development, leasing and management of wholesale property funds. The Company's portfolio consists of approximately 90 retail assets that it owns and manages. The Company's portfolio of properties includes Bankstown Central, Bayside Shopping Centre, Chatswood Chase Sydney, Galleria, Northland Shopping Centre, Roselands, The Glen and Chadstone Shopping Centre.

Villa World Limited is a property developer and housing provider. The Company's principal activities include the development and sale of residential land, and the development, construction and sale of house and land packages. It operates through two segments: Property development and construction - Queensland and New South Wales, and Property development and construction - Victoria. It develops and sells residential land and buildings in Queensland, New South Wales and Victoria. Its portfolio includes approximately 5,940 lots. Its properties in Brisbane include AFFINITY-THORNLANDS, EMINENCE-BRIDGEMAN DOWNS, RIVA-JOYNER, SEASCAPE-REDLAND BAY, THE SANCTUARY-WOODLANDS and WATERLINE-THORNLANDS. Its properties in Gold Coast include ARUNDEL SPRINGS-ARUNDEL, PARKSIDE-COOMERA and SEABRIGHT-JACOBS WELL. Its properties in North Queensland include AUGUSTUS-HERVEY BAY and LITTLE CREEK-GLADSTONE. Its properties in Victoria include CARDINIA VIEWS-PAKENHAM, LAVINIA-GREENVALE and SIENNA-PLUMPTON.

Uranium Equities Limited is engaged in the mineral exploration and evaluation. The Company operates through exploration and evaluation, and corporate segments. The Company's Nabarlek Project covers approximately 500 square kilometers in the heart of the Alligator Rivers Uranium Field, Northern Territory. In the West Arnhem joint venture, the Company has identified various intercepts, which include U40 Prospect, Coopers Prospect, N147 Prospect and Nabarlek Mineral Lease. The brownfields opportunity has Uranium Equities Rudall River Project, which covers approximately 175 square kilometers of exploration licenses, which adjoin the Kintyre Uranium Deposit in the East Pilbara, Western Australia. The greenfields opportunity has Alligator Rivers Uranium Field (ARUF), which is analogous to the Athabasca Uranium Province in Canada.

Ultracharge Ltd, formerly Lithex Resources Limited, is engaged in mineral exploration and identification of potential mining assets for acquisition and development. It holds a set of over four lithium, tin, tantalum and rare earths tenements, covering a total of approximately 40 square kilometers located in the Pilbara and Southern Regions of Western Australia. Its projects include Moolyella Project and Furniss East. The Moolyella Project is located in the East Pilbara Goldfield region, within the mineralized Achaean Pilbara Craton. It is located approximately 20 kilometers east-north-east of the township of Marble Bar. The Furniss East project is located approximately 10 kilometers to the east of the Furniss graphite mine, east of Albany, in southern Western Australia. The Moolyella tenements cover the Moolyella Tin Field, which contains deposits of rare metals (tin, tantalum and lithium) and rare earths (lanthanides). Its tenements include P45/2845, P45/2846, P45/2847 and E70/4212.

ViaGOLD Capital Limited is a Macau-based investment holding Company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, is engaged in investment holdings, leasing, mineral trading business, as well as consultancy and management services to educational institutions. The Company operates through four segments, which include investment holdings and administration, trading of minerals, leasing and capital financing and provision of consultancy and management services to educational institutions. The Company operates its businesses in Hong Kong and Macau and the People's Republic of China (PRC), in which the Company is engaged in leasing financing consultancy and management services to educational institutions. Its subsidiaries include ViaGOLD Technology Limited, ViaGOLD Inc. Limited and ViaGOLD International Education Management Group Limited, Beijing Hua Bao Times International Leasing Company Limited, Zhuhai ViaGOLD Education Consulting Limited and Goldwin Century Limited, among others.

Transcendence Technologies Limited, formerly GRP Corporation Limited, is an Australia-based technology company. The Company is engaged in the development of the E-Collate software system for sharing and organizing business documentation and messaging for decision making and compliance. The E-Collate application is a cross-platform messaging and financials management tool that enables users to collate and analyze short message service (SMS), e-mail, instant messages and bank data, as well as attachments and documents added into the system. The E-Collate self-managed superannuation funds (SMSF) application allows users to automatically generate reports for compliance management and designate items for secure sharing with trusted third parties, such as accountants, auditors, financial advisors and legal representatives. The Company is commercializing its compliance technology via roll-out of the E-Collate SMSF application.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

UCW Limited, formerly UnderCoverWear Limited, is an Australia-based education provider. The Company is engaged in building a fee-for-service private education business in the Vocational Education and Training (VET) sector, with a focus on the international student market. The Company focuses on acquiring campus-based businesses that offer accredited courses, that it can add value to and grow through strategies, including product expansion, geographic expansion, broadening distribution and the addition of new learning modes, such as online.

Unilife Corporation is engaged in the designing, development and manufacturing of injectable drug delivery systems. The Company has a portfolio of product platforms, including pre-filled syringes, disposable and reusable auto-injectors, drug reconstitution delivery systems, ocular delivery systems, and other systems for the targeted delivery of injectable therapies. The majority of its products are designed for sale directly to pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies supplying them as drug-device combination products, pre-filled and ready for administration by end-users, such as health-care providers or patients. Its other products, such as reusable auto-injectors and certain systems for targeted drug delivery are designed either to be sold to pharmaceutical or biotechnology companies for use as combination products or to be sold directly to a health care provider or end user without having the device pre-filled by a pharmaceutical company.

VDM Group Limited is an Australia-based company, which is organized within the three business divisions of VDM Construction, VDM Trading and VDM Mining. The Company operates through segments, including Construction, Trading and Mining. The VDM Construction division is engaged in providing engineering, procurement and construction (EPC) services for a range of projects. The VDM Trading division is engaged in the import and export of goods to and from Asia. The VDM Mining division is engaged in mining exploration, development and operation in Africa and Latin America. The Company offers solutions in customized modular buildings and steel buildings and infrastructure. The Company provides Australian customers with a procurement and import service for custom designed or ready-made products from Chinese markets. The Company provides its Chinese customers with delivery of the Australian products, including foods and wine.

Universal Coal Plc is engaged in coal mining, coal beneficiation, and mineral exploration and development of coal interests in South Africa. The Company's segments include Exploration and development of coal; Mining and sale of coal, and Corporate. The Company's thermal coal projects include Kangala Mine, NCC Roodekop Coal Project and Brakfontein Coal Project. Its Coking Coal Projects include Berenice/Cygnus and Somerville. The Kangala Mine produces approximately 2.1 million tons of saleable coal per annum and is located approximately 65 kilometers east of Johannesburg. The NCC Roodekop Coal Project is located over 35 kilometers south of the town Witbank and is in development. The Brakfontein Coal Project is located in the Delmas District approximately 20 kilometers south of Kangala Mine. The Berenice-Cygnus Coking Coal Project is located in the Soutpansberg coalfield. The Somerville Project is located in the Tuli coalfield, northwest of the Soutpansberg coalfield.

Vealls Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the business of agriculture, real estate, investment and negotiable securities. The Company's segments include Investments and Agriculture. The Investment segment consists of interest bearing deposits, listed shares and freehold land at Mt Martha Vic. The Agriculture segment consists of forestry business, which is conducted at Foret de Leyde near Moulins, France. The Company's subsidiaries include VL Investments Pty Ltd, Cardrona Ski Resort Ltd and Vealls (Singapore) Pte Ltd.
Vector Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company focuses on identifying and evaluating new venture and corporate opportunities.

Viralytics Limited is a biotechnology company. The Company focuses on the development and commercialization of oncolytic immunotherapies that harness the power of certain viruses to preferentially infect and kill cancer cells. The principal activity of the Company is clinical and preclinical development of its lead product, CAVATAK. CAVATAK is a formulation of the common cold Coxsackievirus Type A21. CAVATAK binds to specific receptor proteins expressed on a range of tumor cell types, and acts to destroy local, as well as metastatic cancer cells through cell lysis and the generation of a specific immune response against the cancer cells. CAVATAK is a naturally occurring, genetically unaltered virus with activity in a range of cancer types, including, but not limited to melanoma, prostate, lung, and bladder cancers. CAVATAK is being evaluated in Phase I and II clinical trials, both as an intratumoural and intravenous agent.

Uranium Resources, Inc. is a uranium exploration, development and production company. The Company has approximately 190,000 acres of mineral holdings in the prolific Grants Mineral Belt of the State of New Mexico and approximately 14,000 acres in the South Texas uranium province. Its uranium exploration and development activities are focused principally in the United States and the Republic of Turkey. The Company's properties include Temrezli Project, Kingsville Dome Project, Rosita Project, Vasquez Project, Butler Ranch Project, Churchrock Project, Crownpoint Project, Cebolleta Project and Juan Tafoya Project. The Kingsville Dome property is located in Kleberg County. The Juan Tafoya Project is located approximately 45 miles west-northwest of Albuquerque. The Cebolleta project is located in west-central New Mexico. The Sejita Dome exploration project is located in southern Duval County, Texas. The Vasquez project is located in southwestern Duval County, Texas.

Vango Mining Limited is engaged in gold exploration and the development of its Plutonic Dome Gold Project in Western Australia. The Company operates through Australia and Laos segments. The Company's projects include K2 Road Completed, Keillor Deposits, Trident and Bolaven Plateau Baux. The Trident deposit is located approximately 25 kilometers north east of Plutonic Main Pit. The Company is focused on a core project in proven bauxite deposit in southern Laos located across approximately 487 square kilometers in southern Laos. The Archaean Plutonic-Marymia greenstone belt is approximately 60 kilometers long by approximately 10 kilometers and hosts gold mineralization. The Bauxite Project working area is approximately 140 kilometers and is located on the Bolaven Plateau. The Plutonic Dome project covers the Plutonic-Marymia greenstone belt and a portion of the smaller Baumgarten greenstone belt to the east.

UraniumSA Limited is engaged in the exploration for uranium and other minerals. The Company is an Adelaide-based explorer with a portfolio of properties in South Australia's Gawler Craton and Eyre Peninsula. The Company's projects include Muckanippie-Ela 2016/00011 (El 4694 renewal), Whymlet- Ela 2015/00126 and Sheoak Hill and Lock-Ela's 2015/00113 and 2015/00114. The Muckanippie-EL 4694 tenure covers the Wigetty prospect, which is an ilmenite-magnetite-apatite deposit, the Malbooma gold working and other un-named gold prospects, and various base metal and rare earth element prospects. The Company also has exploration on prospects referred to as Satisfaction Bore and White Nose Bore. The Whymlet- Ela 2015/00126 area covers basement complex and cover sequence targets that are prospective for black-shale hosted and unconformity styles of mineralization, among others. Its subsidiaries include Samphire Uranium Limited, Angus Resources Pty Ltd, Fatjack Pty Ltd and Boston Minerals Pty Ltd.

Voltage IP Limited is an investment company with a focus on investments in the technology sector. The Company is engaged in evaluating potential acquisition opportunities. The Company has not held any active investments in active businesses. The Company owns KLE Products Sdn. Bhd. (KLE), which is a Malaysian manufacturer of conveyor chain systems and components that service the rubber glove manufacturing industry. KLE manufactures a range of roller conveyor chains and former holder sets according to customer specifications. KLE supplies to various glove manufacturers in Malaysia and overseas with its product set. Some of the KLE's customers are also based in China. VIP Glove Sdn. Bhd. is a subsidiary the Company, which is formed as a special purpose vehicle to implement its strategy of expansion into the rubber glove manufacturing industry. It is also focused on the procurement, installation and commissioning of over two glove manufacturing lines.

Valence Industries Limited is an industrial manufacturing company, which is engaged in producing flake graphite products for distribution and sale to global markets. The Company owns processing facilities and infrastructure to manufacture a range of graphite product lines for multiple applications and multiple industries. It produces and sells its graphite products from its Uley Graphite facilities in regional South Australia for delivery to markets for graphite in the Asia Pacific, Europe and North America. Its graphite product lines include HEATPROGraff, which includes refractories, crucibles, forging and billet coatings; StratGraff, which includes lubricants, ceramics, foils and dispersions; GraffPlus, which includes power cables and fire retardants; PowerGraff, which includes lead acid battery and fuel cells; GraffTEX, which includes construction materials, nuclear and electronics, and GraffMED, which includes medical consumables, pathology, hematology and oncology products.

West African Resources Limited is a gold exploration company. The Company's principal activity is mineral exploration and feasibility study work focusing primarily on the Boulsa Gold project within Burkina Faso and Niger. The Company has approximately 100% interest in the Tanlouka gold exploration permit in Burkina Faso. The Company is targeting gold production at its Mankarga 5 project in Burkina Faso. The project includes M1 South Prospect and M1 North Prospect. The Company also has over 100% interest in the Sartenga Permit. The Sartenga copper-gold-molybdenum project is a porphyry system. The inferred mineral resources contain approximately 174,000 tons of copper and over 651,000 ounces of gold. The Moktedu prospect is located in the southwestern part of the Boulsa Project. The prospect covers approximately 10 kilometers of strike and it is confined within a northeast trending regional shear. The Company's subsidiaries include Wura Resources Pty Ltd SARL and Swan Resources SARL.

Vista Group International Limited is a New Zealand-based company, engaged in the sale, support and associated development of software for the film industry. The Company's segment operates through single vertical film/cinema market. It consists of seven businesses, including Vista Entertainment Solutions (VES), Veezi, BookMyShow, MACCS, Movio, Numero and Share Dimension. VES offers software suite for cinema management. Veezi offers cinema management software, which is a cloud-based Software as a Service (SaaS) product for the small circuit market. BookMyShow is a cinema ticketing Website operated in New Zealand. MACCS International designs and develops film distribution software. Movio is also a SaaS solution providing marketing data analysis and a campaign management platform for cinema exhibitors and distributors. Numero provides an aggregated box office reporting platform. Share Dimension specializes in business intelligence and predictive analytics software for the cinema industry.

WAM Active Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company is engaged in investing activities, including cash, term deposits and equity investments. The Company is engaged in investing in equities listed on the Australian Securities Exchange (ASX). The Company's investment objectives are to deliver a regular income stream of fully franked dividends; to provide a positive return with low volatility, and preserve capital. The Company manages the market for various opportunities, including initial public offerings, capital raisings, take overs, listed investment companies (LICs) trading at a discount to their net tangible assets (NTA) and short selling. The Company invests in various sectors, including financials, consumer discretionary, industrials, healthcare, telecommunication services, consumer staples, materials and information technology. The Company's investment manager is MAM Pty Limited.

Vocus Communications Limited is an integrated telecommunications provider. The Company is engaged in providing telecommunications and other services to customers across Australia and New Zealand. Its segments include Australia and New Zealand. It supplies broadband, fixed voice, mobile, data center, cloud and energy services to consumer and business segments through the Commander, Dodo and iPrimus brands in Australia, and Slingshot, CallPlus and Orcon in New Zealand. It offers data network solutions, including Dark Fiber, which is a fiber-optic point-to-point connection; Ethernet services; Ethernet Multipoint, which simplifies layer 2 connectivity across multiple offices or data centers, and Internet Protocol Wide Area Network (IP WAN), which converges information and communications technology services, such as Internet or Cloud Connect. It offers unified communication services, and also the cloud services, including cloud computer, backup and archive, and disaster recovery services.

Wavenet International Limited is engaged in the mineral resource exploration. The Company has coal mining tenements in the Bowen Basin, Rockhampton and Gayndah districts in Queensland and is in the process of acquiring more coal tenements within the same regions. Its portfolio consists of approximately four granted tenements and over six tenement applications situated in Bowen, Hillsborough, Surat and Eromanga coal basins of Queensland. Its projects include Dysart Coking Coal Project, Blackwater Coking Coal Project, Waterpark Coal Project, Gayndah Coal Project, Proserpine Project, Isisford Coal Project and Quilpie Coal Project. Its tenements include exploration permit for coal (EPC) 1067, EPC 1958, EPC 1897, EPC 2264, EPC 2265, EPC 2204, EPC 2530, EPC 2525 and EPC 2526. In addition, it has interest in polymetallic project at Putussibau in West Kalimantan, Indonesia. These tenements are located within a region that contains copper and lead occurrences, and artisanal gold workings.

National Veterinary Care Ltd is engaged in the provision of veterinary services throughout Australia. The Company's network of veterinary clinics offer various services, including acupuncture, blood tests, chemotherapy, dental radiography, desexing, digital radiography (X-Rays), electrocardiograph (ECG), heartworm injections, health exams, healthy nutrition programs, in-house pathology, intensive care hospitalization, microchip identification, nail trimming, orthopedic surgery, senior and palliative care, stem cell therapy, ultrasounds, vaccinations and weight loss programs. Its Best for Pet service provides optimal healthcare for pet. Its Best for Pet membership includes all the preventative care services for maintaining user's pet's health and wellbeing.

Venturex Resources Limited is a resource exploration company focused in base metals. The Company's projects are Panorama Project and Whim Creek Project. The Panorama Project is located approximately 160 kilometers to the south east of Port Hedland, which includes the Sulphur Springs and Kangaroo Caves mines together with tenements covering approximately 30 kilometers of the Panorama trend. The Whim Creek Project is located approximately 120 kilometers to the west of Port Hedland, which includes the Whim Creek, Mons Cupri and Salt Creek mines. The Sulphur Springs Project is located approximately 140 kilometers by road southeast of Port Hedland. The Company holds granted exploration and mining tenements covering approximately 27 kilometers of strike along the Panorama Trend, which is a known VMS mineralized horizon. The Company's subsidiaries include Jutt Resources Pty. Ltd., Juranium Pty. Ltd., CMG Gold Ltd., Venturex Pilbara Pty. Ltd. and Venturex Sulphur Springs Pty. Ltd.

Velpic Limited, formerly International Coal Limited, is engaged in the business of provision of a cloud-based video e-learning software platform and a brand technology agency. The Company's segments are Software-as-a-Service, Consultancy Services and Other. The Company's e-learning platform consists of a multimedia video authoring tool, learning management system (LMS), and Internet-responsive video streaming portal. The Company's technology allows businesses to embrace video e-learning, allowing an organization to create, customize and publish training videos. Its online induction system allows users to follow-up anytime from your smartphone, tablet, laptop or desktop computer. It allows to track lesson statuses and send automated reminders for overdue ones. Its onboarding software can also be used for product training; customer service; mandatory compliance training; technology, tools and systems training; processes, procedures and business practices, and soft skills training.

Updater Inc. (Updater) is a technology company. The Company develops and markets tools for consumers to complete their move-related tasks. The Company partners with companies in the relocation services industry, such as real estate agents and brokers, property managers, moving companies, and title insurance companies to provide a co-branded version of its product to consumers. The Company offers a Mover product, which provides Movers in the United States with a centralized online service to organize and complete relocation-related tasks and logistics. Its Real Estate Products enable Real Estate Companies to provide their clients with the invite only Mover Product, and to brand, customize and personalize the Mover Product experience for their Clients. Updater focuses to develop Businesses Products that enable Businesses to customize the Mover Product experience for their existing customers. The Company also offers an Integration Platform.

Vmoto Limited is a scooter manufacturing and distribution company. The Company is engaged in the development, manufacture, and international marketing and distribution of electric powered two-wheel vehicles, petrol two-wheel vehicles and all-terrain vehicles. The Company's geographical segments include Australia and China. The Company offers green electric powered two-wheel vehicles and manufactures a range of western designed electric two-wheel vehicles from its manufacturing facilities located in Nanjing, China. It sells its products on an original equipment manufacturer basis. The Company operates through two brands: Vmoto, which is aimed at the value market in Asia, and Emax, which targets the western markets with a premium end product. The Company has a total capacity of approximately 450,000 two wheel units per annum. The Company consists of approximately 40 outlets through a combination of its own retail outlets and third party distributors across China.

Veem Limited is a marine technology company. The Company is engaged in the manufacturing of propellers and industrial products and the provision of engineering services. The Company specializes in propulsion and stabilization systems. It also manufactures products and services for the marine, defense and mining industries. Its business units include VEEM Propellers, VEEM Gyro, Timcast, VEEM 24-7 and VEEM Defence. VEEM Propellers offers commercial and recreational fixed pitch propeller technology. VEEM Gyro is a ship roll stabilizing technology that uses gyrostabilizers with control technology. Timcast is a range of centrifugally cast bi-metal pipes. VEEM 24/7 provides a range of manufactured products and repair services to a range of customers within the Western Australian mining industry. VEEM Defence provides manufacturing and service work for the Australian Defense Force and key defense force contractors.

Vimy Resources Limited is an Australia-based exploration and evaluation company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and evaluation on the Mulga Rock Project. The Mulga Rock Project includes undeveloped uranium resources. The project is located approximately 240 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie in the Great Victoria Desert of Western Australia. The Company has 17 tenements that relate to the Mulga Rock Project, of which two are mining leases, six are exploration licenses, six are prospecting licenses and three are miscellaneous licenses. The Mulga Rock Project ore reserves include Princess and Ambassador at Mulga Rock East, and Emperor and Shogun at Mulga Rock West.

Vault Intelligence Limited (Vault), formerly Credo Resources Limited, provides cloud-based and mobile environmental health and safety (EHS) software. The Company's software streamlines a corporation's EHS processes. The Vault software offers features, such as combining all EHS related work in an end-to-end enterprise system; providing access to audit, inspection and incident reporting at any time from any location; asset management and integrating with existing enterprise systems, and mobile applications that can standalone or work with existing systems. The software is available across various devices and is accessible for a range of varied user purposes, including non-desk bound users through its applications. Its software includes components, such as Risk Management, Contractor Management, Incident Management, Mobility, Compliance, Claims Management and Governance. It offers Vault Business EHS solution for smaller companies and Vault EHS Enterprise Solution for larger corporations.

Vita Life Sciences Limited (Vita Life) is a healthcare company. The Company is involved in the formulating, packaging, sales and distribution of vitamins and supplements. The Company's segments include health, including sale of vitamins and supplements, and investment, including general investments. It offers products under the brands, such as Vita Health, Herbs of Gold and VitaScience, throughout the Asia-Pacific region. The Company has presence in Australia, Singapore, Malaysia and others. The Company's over the counter (OTC) products are mainly sold at pharmacies and health food stores. Its subsidiaries include Tetley Research Pty Limited, Tetley Treadmills Pty Limited, Tetley Manufacturing Pty Limited, Vimed BioSciences Pty Limited, Lovin Pharma International Limited, Herbs of Gold Pty Limited, Herbs of Gold (Shanghai) Co. Limited, Vita Life Science (S) Pte Limited and Sino Metro Developments Limited.
Wakenby Limited, formerly ILH Group Limited, is engaged in the provision of legal services, wealth management and advice and online legal document services. The Company operates in Australia.

Veriluma Limited, formerly Parmelia Resources Limited, is engaged in product development, marketing and commercialization of software, products and services. The Company's subsidiaries include Toro Mining Pty Ltd, Sentosa Mining (Philippines) Inc., St Nicholas Mines Pty Ltd and Niquaero LLC. The Company was involved in the exploration of its Jaurdi Hills Project in Western Australia.

White Energy Company Limited is engaged in the ongoing development and exploitation of the Binderless Coal Briquetting (BCB) technology; the operation of coal mines in Kentucky, the United States, operated by Mountainside Coal Company, Inc. (MCC), and the evaluation of mining exploration assets. The Company operates through four segments: coal technology, coal mining, mining exploration and property. The coal technology segment has the exclusive license to BCB technology developed by a consortia. The coal mining segment includes MCC, which operates a series of coal mines in the United States. The mining exploration segment holds tenements near Cooper Pedy, South Australia. The property segment is engaged in the agricultural activities of Ingomar Station, which operates as a working cattle and sheep property. The Company's sectors operate in over five main geographical areas, which include Australia, Asia, South Africa and Mauritius, the United States and the United Kingdom.

Wealth Defender Equities Limited is engaged in making investments mainly in listed large, mid and small cap Australian companies. The Company is also engaged in deriving revenue and investment income from listed securities in Australia. The Company aims to outperform the Standard & Poor's/Australian Securities Exchange 300 (S&P/ASX 300) Accumulation Index by investing in a diversified portfolio of Australian shares while using protection strategies, including derivatives and cash to dynamically protect the portfolio through market cycles, thereby cushioning the magnitude of negative returns when equity markets fall significantly. Perennial Value Management Limited is the investment manager of the Company.

Waterco Limited is engaged in the business of manufacture and wholesale of swimming pool chemicals, accessories and equipment, and manufacture and sale of solar pool heating systems. The Company is also a franchisor of swimming pool outlets retailing swimming pool accessories and equipment. The Company manufactures water treatment solutions suitable for commercial environments, including public swimming pools, aquaculture installations and industrial water treatment. Its water treatment products include Drinking Water Purifiers, Residential Water Filters, Residential Water Softeners, Fibreglass filters, Cartridge and Bag Filters, MultiCyclone Centrifugal Filters, Cooling water filtration, Koi Pond Systems, Electronic flocculation and Residential Pressure Pumps. Its pool and spa products include Filters, Cleaners, Infloor Cleaning Systems, Lights, Recirculation, Valves, Blowers, Spa Equipment, Commercial Pumps, Commercial Filters, Commercial Accessories, Ozone Generators and Test Kits.

Whitefield Limited is an investment company. The Company is engaged in investing in companies and trusts. The Company invests in shares and securities listed on the Australian Stock Exchange. The Company's investment objective is to provide investors with capital growth and franked income from investment in a diversified portfolio of industrial shares listed on the Australian Stock Exchange, and an investment return exceeding the ASX200 Industrials Accumulation Index over the long term. The Company invests in sectors, such as utilities, banks, consumer discretionary, consumer staple, healthcare, information technology, materials, non-bank financials, property, industrials and telecoms. The Company provides shareholders with exposure to a diversified portfolio of listed Australian industrial shares.

Vectus Biosystems Limited is engaged in medical Research and Development. The Company's drug candidates can be orally administered. The Company's primary lead compound, VB0004, has been shown to be both anti-hypertensive and anti-fibrotic in the heart and kidneys. Using its platform technology, the Company has constructed a library of more than 200 small molecules with varying degrees of anti-hypertensive and/or anti-fibrotic properties. It also focuses on developing candidates for the treatment of fibrotic liver diseases, including non-alcoholic steatohepatitis (NASH), as well as pulmonary fibrotic diseases. Accugen is a platform, developed by the Company's subsidiary, Accugen Pty Limited. Accugen comprises reagents and software that quantitate quantitative polymerase chain reaction (qPCR) reactions, which measures the amount of Deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA) or ribonucleic acid (RNA) in a sample. It identifies drug targets with specific activity in the heart, kidneys, lungs and liver.

Virgin Australia Holdings Limited is engaged in the operation of a domestic and international airline business, and the operation of a frequent flyer program. The Company's segments include Virgin Australia Domestic, which includes operations using the fleet of Boeing B737 aircraft, Airbus A320 and A330 aircraft, and Fokker F50 and F100 aircraft, and comprises Australian domestic flying, including regional network and cargo operations; Virgin Australia International, which includes operations using a mix of Airbus A330, Boeing B777 and B737 aircraft, and comprises Trans-Pacific, Abu Dhabi, Trans-Tasman, Pacific Island and South East Asia flying, including international cargo operations; Velocity, which includes operations of its loyalty program, and Tigerair Australia, which includes operations using a narrow body fleet of Airbus A320 and Boeing B737 aircraft, and comprises Australian domestic flying targeting the budget leisure market and international flying to Denpasar.

Vita Group Limited is a communications, computing and electronics provider. The Company is engaged in selling and marketing of technology and communication products and services through its retail store brands. The Company offers its products and services through its retail store brands, which include Telstra, Fone Zone and One Zero, and through its small to medium business (SMB), and government and enterprise channels in Australia. Fone Zone provides products and services, such as mobiles, accessories and national broadband network (NBN). Its One Zero brand serves business needs, such as mobiles, Internet, home phones, business plans and accessories, among others. Telstra is a telecommunications and information services provider. Telstra provides a range of communications services in the telecommunications markets. Its subsidiaries include Next Byte Holdings Pty Ltd, Vita People Pty Ltd and The Learning Academy Pty Ltd.

Volt Resources Limited, formerly Mozambi Resources Limited, is a graphite exploration company. The Company is focused on the exploration and development of its existing Namangale Graphite Project in Tanzania and the identification of further assets globally. Its segments include Mineral Exploration-Tanzania and Mineral Exploration-Australia. The Namangale project is located 10 kilometers away from sealed roads, then 130 kilometers direct to the deep-water port of Mtwara. Its graphite projects are located in the Balama Region of Mozambique and the Nachingwea region of Tanzania. The Nachingwea Project consists of 18 tenements in South Eastern Tanzania within the prospective Mozambique Mobile Belt; 10 of the tenements are located in the Lindi Province with the remaining eight being located in the adjacent Mtwara Province bordering Mozambique. It owns a 70% interest in Dugal Resources Lda, a Mozambican entity that holds a 100% interest in licenses, including 3245L and 3246L.

Wesfarmers Limited is engaged in various business operations, such as supermarkets, liquor, hotels and convenience stores; home improvement; office supplies, and an industrials division with businesses in chemicals, energy and fertilizers, industrial and safety products and coal. The Company's segments include Coles; Home Improvement; Department Stores, which includes Kmart and Target; Office Works; Industrials, which includes Resources, WIS and WesCEF, and Other. Coles is a supermarket retailer, which operates over 770 supermarkets. Bunnings is a retailer of home improvement and outdoor living products in Australia and New Zealand. Kmart is a retailer with approximately 210 stores throughout Australia and New Zealand. Target operates a network of over 300 stores and sells a range of products for the contemporary family, including apparel, homewares and general merchandise. Officeworks is a retailer and supplier of office products and solutions for home, business and education.

White Rock Minerals Limited is an Australia-based minerals exploration and development company with activities focused in the New England Fold Belt of northern New South Wales and the Bonnifield district in central Alaska. The Company operates through two segments: Mt Carrington, Australia and Red Mountain, Alaska. It owns the Mt Carrington project, which is located approximately five kilometers from the township of Drake in northern New South Wales. The Mt Carrington project contains an Indicated and Inferred Mineral Resource estimate of approximately 338,000 ounces gold and over 23.5 million ounces silver. The Red Mountain Project is located in central Alaska, approximately 100 kilometers south of Fairbanks, in the Bonnifield Mining District. The tenement package comprises over 124 mining claims over a total area of approximately 140 square kilometers. The Red Mountain Project contains polymetallic volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) mineralization rich in zinc, silver and lead.

Virtus Health Limited is an assisted reproductive services provider engaged in the provision of healthcare services, including fertility services, medical day procedure services and medical diagnostic services. The Company has six operating segments: New South Wales, Queensland, Victoria, Tasmania, Australian Diagnostics and International. It has consolidated its operations into two segments, being an Australian aggregated healthcare services segment (Healthcare Services Australia) and an International healthcare services segment (Healthcare Services International). Its fertility clinics include IVFAustralia, Melbourne IVF, Queensland Fertility Group, Rotunda IVF and Virtus Fertility Centre. Its day hospitals include North Shore Specialist Day Hospital, Spring Hill Specialist Day Hospital, Mackay Specialist Day Hospital, City East Specialist Day Hospital and City West Specialist Day Hospital. It offers general pathology services, as well as specialist fertility and genetic testing.

Webster Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the production, processing and marketing of walnuts, cotton, crops and livestock. The Company operates through two segments: Agriculture and Horticulture. The Agriculture segment products are primarily annual row crops, including cotton, wheat and maize, as well as livestock. The Horticulture segment pertains to tree crops, which are primarily walnuts. The Company produces in-shell and kernel walnuts. The Company has approximately 40,000 irrigable hectares of land holdings across southern Queensland and New South Wales focusing on cotton, corn and other cereals and livestock. It owns a portfolio of over 200,000 mega liters of water entitlement. Its orchard portfolio is located in Tasmania and New South Wales. These productive orchards span over 2,000 hectares and include cultivars, including Chandler, Howard, Tulare and other walnut varieties. It produces over 200,000 bales of cotton annually. It also owns grazing farmland.

Westpac Banking Corporation is a banking organization. The Company provides a range of banking and financial services in markets, including consumer, business and institutional banking and wealth management services. The Company is engaged in the provision of financial services, including lending, deposit taking, payments services, investment portfolio management and advice, superannuation and funds management, insurance services, leasing finance, general finance, interest rate risk management and foreign exchange services. The Company's segments include Consumer Bank, Business Bank, BT Financial Group (BTFG), Westpac Institutional Bank (WIB) and Westpac New Zealand. The Company has branches throughout Australia, New Zealand, Asia and in the Pacific region. The Company through its division offers its services under various brands, such as Westpac, St.George, BankSA, Bank of Melbourne and RAMS brands.

WAM Capital Limited (WAM) is an Australia-based investment company, which is primarily an investor in equities listed on the Australian Securities Exchange. The Company's investment objectives are to deliver a rising stream of fully franked dividends; to provide capital growth, and to preserve capital of the Company. It invests in various sectors, such as financials, consumer discretionary, industrials, healthcare, information technology, telecommunication services, consumer staples, utilities and materials. The Company's trading opportunities are derived from initial public offerings, placements, block trades, rights issues, corporate transactions (such as takeovers, mergers, schemes of arrangements, corporate spin-offs and restructures), arbitrage opportunities, life insurance corporation (LIC) discount arbitrages, short-selling and trading market themes and trends. Wilson Asset Management (International) Pty Ltd is the Company's investment manager.

Whitefield Limited is an investment company. The Company is engaged in investing in companies and trusts. The Company invests in shares and securities listed on the Australian Stock Exchange. The Company's investment objective is to provide investors with capital growth and franked income from investment in a diversified portfolio of industrial shares listed on the Australian Stock Exchange, and an investment return exceeding the ASX200 Industrials Accumulation Index over the long term. The Company invests in sectors, such as utilities, banks, consumer discretionary, consumer staple, healthcare, information technology, materials, non-bank financials, property, industrials and telecoms. The Company provides shareholders with exposure to a diversified portfolio of listed Australian industrial shares.

Wellcom Group Limited is an independent production company. The Company is engaged in the provision of advertising and marketing content production and content management services in Australia, the United Kingdom, New Zealand, Asia and the United States. The Company's segments include Australasia, the United Kingdom (UK) and in the United States of America (US). The Company offers a range of services, including Advertising and Marketing Content Production Services; Design, Artwork and Retouching; Content Management Services; Digital Photography; Television Production; Digital Print, and Computer to Plate (CTP) Production. It specializes in producing volumes of advertising production collateral and its solutions address the brand management needs. The Company's Knowedgewell marketing platform provides scale, functionality and security. It provides a central repository for all stakeholders involved in the marketing process to collaborate and execute volumes of marketing collateral.

Western Areas Limited is an Australia-based mining company. The Company's principal activities include mining, processing and sale of nickel sulfide concentrate, the continued assessment of development feasibility of the high-grade nickel mines, and the exploration for nickel sulfides, other base metals and platinum group metals. The Company has nickel production assets in Australia and base metals development projects across Australia, Canada and Finland. The Company's Forrestania project includes two nickel mines, Flying Fox and Spotted Quoll; the Cosmic Boy Concentrator, which treats the ore and produces nickel concentrate for sale; a regional tenement package, and site infrastructure, including a 450-bed accommodation village, grid connected power, water management network, airstrip and nickel concentrate export facilities.

World Reach Limited is a satellite telecommunications company that designs, develops, manufactures and distributes satellite phone equipment and related services. The Company manufactures and distributes satellite communication terminals, handheld phone accessories and original equipment manufacturer (OEM) for the Iridium GO! wireless fidelity (wifi) device that provides global voice/text/data services for smartphones. It has operations in Australia, China, the United Kingdom, the United States, the Netherlands and Japan. Its businesses include Beam Communications Pty Ltd (Beam), SatPhone Shop Pty Ltd (SPS), SatPhonerental Pty Ltd (SPR) and Beam Communications USA Inc. Beam is a designer and manufacturer of satellite communication equipment. SPS operates online store for Telstra's range of mobile satellite products. SPR offers rental service for satellite equipment for personal or enterprise needs. Beam Communications USA Inc. offers technical support on Beam products and services.

Verdant Minerals Ltd, formerly Rum Jungle Resources Limited, is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of fertilizer minerals (in particular phosphate and sulfate of potash). The Company is engaged in the exploration of other minerals in northern and central Australia. It has a portfolio of projects that includes the Ammaroo Phosphate Project, a portfolio of Sulphate of Potash projects and the Dingo Hill Silica Project. The Ammaroo Phosphate Project is located in the southern Georgina Basin. The Brunchilly Project consists of over three contiguous phosphate ELs east of Bootu Creek Manganese Mine near Tennant Creek. The Patanella Phosphate Project on EL 24716 is a rock phosphate deposit on the opposite side of the Georgina Basin. Its projects also include Burge Bore Phosphate Project, Karinga Lakes Project, Lake Mackay South Potash Project, Weedens Phosphate Project, Lake Amadeus Potash Project, Lake MacDonald Potash Project, Lake Frome Potash Project and Dingo Hole Silica Project.

WCP Resources Limited is engaged in the identification, acquisition, exploration and development of resource projects. The Company's projects include mineral exploration in Western Australia (Yalgoo Project) and mineral exploration in the Republic of Yemen (Al Hariqah Project). The Yalgoo Project includes a prospective tenement located in the Yalgoo Mineral Field in Western Australia and close to a range of gold and base metal operations. The Al Hariqah Project is a near-surface gold deposit located in the Republic of Yemen and within the Arabian-Nubian Shield (ANS), a gold mining region that contains a range of gold deposits. The Al Hariqah Gold Project is located approximately 130 kilometers northwest of Sana'a, Yemen. The project includes a granted exploration license covering an area of approximately 960 square kilometers. The Company's Piedmont Lithium Project is a lithium project. It includes landholding in the Carolina Lithium Belt.

Woolworths Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in retail operations. The Company's segments include Australian Food and Petrol, New Zealand Supermarkets, Endeavour Drinks Group, BIGW and Hotels. The Australian Food and Petrol segment is engaged in the procurement of food and petroleum products for resale to customers in Australia.
