The New Zealand Supermarkets segment is engaged in the procurement of food and liquor products for resale to customers in New Zealand. The Endeavour Drinks Group segment is involved in the procurement of liquor products for resale to customers in Australia. The BIGW segment is engaged in the procurement of discount general merchandise products for resale to customers in Australia. The Hotels segment is engaged in the provision of a range of leisure and hospitality services, including food and alcohol, accommodation, entertainment and gaming in Australia. The Company's brands include Essentials, Woolworths, Dan Murphy's and BWS.

Westfield Corporation is an Australia-based shopping center company. The Company is engaged in ownership, development, design, construction, asset management, leasing and marketing activities with respect to the United States and the United Kingdom portfolio. The Company's segments include Property investments, Property and project management, and Corporate. The Property investments segment includes net property income from shopping centers and completed developments, and other operational expenses. The Property and project management segment includes external fee income from third parties, primarily property management and development fees, and associated business expenses. Its shopping center portfolio includes over 30 centers in the United States, the United Kingdom and Europe encompassing approximately 6,480 retail outlets. Its portfolio of shopping centers includes Westfield London, Westfield Stratford City, Old Orchard, Brandon, Broward and Citrus Park, among others.

WONHE Multimedia Commerce Ltd is an Australia-based company, which focuses on the research, development, manufacturing and sale of home media center, domestic routers and the commercial routers. The Company's subsidiary includes Shenzhen WONHE Technology Co., Ltd (Shenzhen WONHE), which has a research and development department that designs its own software and hardware products. Shenzhen WONHE outsources the manufacturing of its products to a third party contract manufacturer.

Walkabout Resources Limited is an Australia-based mineral exploration company. The Company is principally engaged in the exploration and development of resources and energy assets located in Botswana, Tanzania and Namibia. The Company's operating segments include Graphite, Coal, Lithium and Copper. The Company's geographical segments include Australia, Botswana and Tanzania and Namibia. The Company's projects include Takatokwane Coal Project, Lindi Jumbo Graphite Project and Kigoma Copper Project. The Takatokwane Coal Project is located approximately 195 kilometers from the Botswana capital, Gaborone, in the southern belt of the Central Kalahari Sub-Basin. The Lindi Jumbo Graphite Project is located within the emerging graphite province in southeastern Tanzania approximately 200 kilometers by road from the port of Mtwara. The Kigoma Copper Project is located approximately 80 kilometers south of the town of Kigoma on the shores of Lake Tanganyika in western Tanzania.

Village Roadshow Limited is engaged in theme park and water park operations, cinema exhibition operations, film and digital versatile disc (DVD) distribution operations, and sales promotion and loyalty program operations. The Company's segments include Theme Parks, Cinema Exhibition, Film Distribution, Marketing Solutions and Other. The Theme Parks segment is engaged in theme park and water park operations. The Cinema Exhibition segment is engaged in cinema exhibition operations. The Film Distribution segment is engaged in film and DVD distribution operations. The Marketing Solutions segment is engaged in sales promotion and loyalty program operations. In addition, the Company has an equity interest in Village Roadshow Entertainment Group Limited, which is engaged in film production activities. The Company's other activities include corporate overheads, financing activities, and digital and information technology development.

Waratah Resource Limited is engaged in the ongoing development of the Australian Commodities Trading Division. The Company is engaged in identifying and acquiring resource projects that have discovery and development potential. It is also engaged in global trading of commodities. Its segments include Mineral Exploration, Australian Commodities Division and Information Technology. The Australian Commodities Division focuses on developing Australian and international assets. It is involved in evaluation and assessment of its exploration assets in Gabon, which include the Mekambo-Est Iron Ore Project, the Tchibanga License, the Waka License and the Makokou License. The Mekambo-Est iron ore project is located on the Ivindo Massif in the north east of the Republic of Gabon. It supplies thermal and coking coal from its Indonesian mining partners to its end user customers in China, India and Korea. It is also investigating investment opportunities in the tech sector.

Wingara AG Limited, formerly Biron Apparel Limited, is an Australia-based company, which acts as a product processor and marketer of agricultural products. The Company's subsidiaries include Elect Performance Group Pty Ltd (Elect) and Superion Property Pty Ltd (Superion), which are engaged in product processing and marketing of agricultural products.

XTEK Limited is an Australia-based company, which focuses on the supply of Homeland Security products and services to Defense and Law Enforcement agencies throughout Australasia; the continued development and commercialization of XTclave isostatic Composite Consolidation Technology (armor) and XTatlas contextual video and mosaic mapping technology; securing a range of products to assist Government in countering the terror threat, and the acquisition of the business and assets of Simmersion Holdings Pty Ltd. The Company's homeland security agency business includes the supply of homeland security equipment and services to predominantly government customers in the Australasian region. The XTEK Agency business covers a range of products and equipment, operating under various portfolios, including Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS), Weapons and Ancillaries, Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) equipment, Protective Security equipment and Forensics products.

Yellow Brick Road Holdings Limited is a full service wealth management company. The Company is engaged in providing investment and wealth management services; general insurance services; accounting services, and mortgage broking, aggregation and management services. The Company operates through the segments, including Branch network, Professional services and Other segments. The Company's home loans include Rate Smasher, Empower, Empower Package and Empower Line of Credit. The Company offers financial advice. The Company's subsidiaries include Yellow Brick Road Group Pty Ltd Australia, Skasgard Pty Ltd Australia, Gessle Pty Ltd Australia, Carithas Pty Ltd Australia, Boreanaz Pty Ltd Australia, Yellow Brick Road Investment Partners Pty Ltd Australia.

Winchester Energy Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas exploration company. The Company is engaged in acquiring oil and gas leases, and working interests in areas situated on the Eastern Shelf of the Permian Basin in Texas and exploring for oil and gas on those oil and gas leases and working interests (WI). The Company's geographical segments are Australia and USA. The Company focuses on Thomas 119-1H well. The Company has WI in White Hat 21#1, White Hat 20#1, White Hat 20#2 and White Hat 21#2, among others. The Company holds WI in the oil and gas mineral rights of approximately 8,062 gross acres in separate leases, including Mcleod and Arlege. The Company also holds WI in the deep oil and gas rights of approximately 505-acre Cisco Sand oil field located in Coke country, Texas. The Company's subsidiaries include Winchester Energy Limited LLC and Winchester Energy Holding Inc.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Wellard Limited is engaged in agribusiness that connects primary producers of cattle, sheep and other livestock to customers across the globe through a vertically integrated supply chain. Its segments include Livestock Marketing, Export and Transportation, and Other Segments. The Livestock Marketing, Export and Transportation segment is engaged in the business of buying livestock from multiple sources for export to international markets and includes all the logistics and transport required to supply livestock to its customers. The Company's Other Segments segment consists of Processing and Distribution, as well as Corporate Services. Its Processing and Distribution is in the business of operating abattoirs, as well as marketing of processed meat for export to international markets. Its Corporate Services consists of a centralized support function, which provides services, including human resources, finance and payroll, information technology and communication, and legal services.

World.Net Services Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the development, provision and sale of information technology products and services. The Company's segments include Australia and Malaysia. The Australia segment represents the holding company operations only. The Malaysia segment develops, provides and sells information technology products and services. The Malaysia segment also provides services in connection with the implementation, hosting and maintenance and support of its core product Travel.World.Net (TWN), which is an integrated multi-user reservations and distributions system for use by suppliers and buyers of travel and tourism products. The Company, through its partnership with PYO Travel, is also developing and managing online travel solutions, servicing the Asian market. Its subsidiaries include World.Net Services (UK) Limited and World Net Services Sdn Bhd.

WPG Resources Limited is an Australia-based resource company. The Company's principal activities include mining, exploration, evaluation and development of its precious metal, base metal, iron ore and coal projects located in South Australia, as well as the pursuit of new mining opportunities in any jurisdiction. Its segments include exploration and production. It holds its gold prospects through three subsidiaries: Challenger Gold Operations Pty Ltd (CGO), Tarcoola Gold Pty Ltd and Tunkillia Gold Pty Ltd. The Company focuses on its three South Australian gold projects (Challenger, Tarcoola and Tunkillia). CGO holds mineral lease (ML) 6103, and miscellaneous purpose leases (MPL) 63, 65 and 66 on which the Challenger Mine is located. The Tarcoola project is located on ML 6455, which is surrounded by EL 5355, both of which are owned by Tarcoola Gold Pty Ltd. It has four mineral leases at Tarcoola. The Tunkillia 223 deposit lies in the north western part of the Tunkillia tenement block.

Water Resources Group Limited is an Australia-based company focused on water treatment solutions within Australia, specifically using ozone within a water treatment facility. The Company is principally engaged in the ongoing analysis of the technical and economic viability of the AiR2O3 technology specific to its uses in water; seeking out and consideration alternative opportunities in the water sector, and consideration of alternative, non-water related opportunities utilizing the AiR2O3 generator. The Company is conducting research into various water treatment technologies and services, including ground water treatment, desalination and ozone production technology. The Company is also focused on the other uses of ozone within Australia.

Westoz Investment Company Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company's primary objective of the capital management is to produce positive return on funds, regardless of the general direction of the listed share market and that is consistent with acceptable risk parameters in order to maximize the shareholder value. The Company invests mainly in the listed securities. The Company also invests in equity securities on the Australian Stock Exchange. The Company has made investments in approximately 31 companies. Westoz Funds Management Pty Ltd serves as the manager for the Company that manages portfolio of assets. Westoz Funds Management Pty Ltd is a subsidiary of Euroz Limited.

Warrnambool Cheese and Butter Factory Company Holdings Limited (WCB) is engaged in the manufacture, processing and sale of cheese, milk powder, butter, cream, whey protein concentrate, lactoferrin, and bulk and processed milk. The Company operates through three segments: Commodities, Consumer Goods and Other. The Commodities segment consists of dairy products, cheese, skim milk powder, butter, cream, lactoferrin and whey protein concentrate, which are manufactured in Australia and sold in domestic and export markets to wholesale customers. The Consumer goods segment consists of branded products sold for retail sale, including Sungold and Great Ocean Road, the packaged milk; Enprocal, the nutritional products, and Warrnambool and Great Ocean Road, the cheese products. The Company's subsidiaries include Warrnambool Cheese and Butter Factory Company Limited, Australian Dairy Products Pty Ltd, Warrnambool Milk Products Pty Limited and Protein Technology Victoria Pty Ltd.

Ventnor Resources Limited is an exploration company. The Company's segments include Development assets, and Exploration and evaluation assets, which includes assets that are associated with the determination and assessment of the existence of commercial economic reserves. Its assets include Thaduna/Green Dragon Copper Project Joint Venture with Sandfire Resources NL in the Doolgunna district of Western Australia. The Thaduna/Green Dragon Copper Project is an advanced copper exploration project located approximately 210 kilometers northeast of Meekatharra in Western Australia. Its other projects include Warrawanda Project and Black Dragon Project. The Warrawanda Project is an advanced nickel exploration project located approximately 40 kilometers south of Newman in Western Australia. The Black Dragon Project is located over 370 kilometers north-east of Kalgoorlie, and approximately 22 kilometers north-east of AngloGold Ashanti (70%) and Independence Group's (30%) Tropicana Gold mine.

Whitehaven Coal Limited is engaged in exploration, project evaluation, project development and coal mining activities in New South Wales' Gunnedah Basin. The Company operates through two segments: Open Cut Operations and Underground Operations. It owns four open cut mines (Maules Creek, Werris Creek, Tarrawonga and Rocglen), one underground mine (Narrabri) and operates a coal handling and processing plant at Gunnedah. The Maules Creek Mine is located over 45 kilometers southeast of Narrabri and approximately 17 kilometers northeast of Boggabri in the Gunnedah Basin of New South Wales, Australia. The Werris Creek Mine is located over four kilometers south of Werris Creek on the Quirindi Road. The Tarrawonga Mine is located approximately 16 kilometers east of Boggabri. The Rocglen Mine is located over 28 kilometers north of Gunnedah on the Wean road. The Narrabri North Mine is located approximately 17 kilometers southeast of Narrabri and over 70 kilometers northwest of Gunnedah.

Webster Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the production, processing and marketing of walnuts, cotton, crops and livestock. The Company operates through two segments: Agriculture and Horticulture. The Agriculture segment products are primarily annual row crops, including cotton, wheat and maize, as well as livestock. The Horticulture segment pertains to tree crops, which are primarily walnuts. The Company produces in-shell and kernel walnuts. The Company has approximately 40,000 irrigable hectares of land holdings across southern Queensland and New South Wales focusing on cotton, corn and other cereals and livestock. It owns a portfolio of over 200,000 mega liters of water entitlement. Its orchard portfolio is located in Tasmania and New South Wales. These productive orchards span over 2,000 hectares and include cultivars, including Chandler, Howard, Tulare and other walnut varieties. It produces over 200,000 bales of cotton annually. It also owns grazing farmland.

WolfStrike Rentals Group Limited is focused on the financing and management of rental contracts for technology solutions. The Company's main business is rental of technology products to retailers, business and merchants, with a principal focus on the hospitality sector. The Company operates through technology rentals segment. The Company provides a range of financial and operational services to small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs). The Company's network includes WolfStrike Rental Services, WolfStrike Distributors NZ, WolfStrike Distributors AU, Eftpos Warehouse, Settle, XCR POS, Wolfstrike Rentals, WolfstrikePOS, PayCafe and CashCow Technologies. WolfStrike Rental Services is a provider of merchant finance solutions for New Zealand-based SMEs. Eftpos Warehouse is a business technology provider for SMEs. Wolfstrike Rentals is a provider of merchant finance solutions for Australia-based SMEs. The Company also manages its own direct and agent-based sales network.

XRF Scientific Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in the business of manufacturing and marketing precious metal products, specialized chemicals and instruments for the scientific, analytical and mining industries. The Company operates through three segments: Capital Equipment, Precious Metals and Consumables. The Capital Equipment segment designs, manufactures and services organization, specializing in automated fusion equipment, high temperature test and production furnaces, as well as general laboratory equipment. The Precious Metals segment manufactures products for the laboratory and platinum alloy markets. The Consumables segment produces and distributes consumables, chemicals and other supplies for analytical laboratories. Its products include fusion equipment, flux, platinum labware, precision products and lab equipment. Its fusion equipment includes electric fusion machines and gas fusion machines. Its flux products include fusion flux and flux weighing.

Wolf Minerals Limited is an Australia-based specialty metals producer. The Company is engaged in tungsten and tin mining, which is conducted through the subsidiary, Wolf Minerals (UK) Limited. The Company operates in the tungsten and tin industry of the mining and materials sector in the United Kingdom. The Company has the Drakelands open pit mine (Drakelands) at the Hemerdon tungsten and tin project. Its project is located near Plymouth in the south-west United Kingdom county of Devon. Drakelands is located near the village of Hemerdon in the United Kingdom in a mining area and adjacent to the China clay mines. The tungsten deposit at the Drakelands is hosted within and around a dyke-like body of porphyritic granite, which is known as the Hemerdon Granite. The Company's processing plant at Drakelands produces approximately 57,458 metric ton units (mtu) of tungsten in concentrate and over 48 tons of tin in concentrate.

Veris Limited, formerly OTOC Limited, is a planning, design, survey and spatial solutions company. The Company operates two business lines: Veris, which is engaged in providing surveying and infrastructure services to the property, civil infrastructure, government and resources sectors, and OTOC Australia Infrastructure Services, which operates as infrastructure construction contractor. The Company's services include Surveying, Sensing, Geospatial Data Management, Town Planning, Urban Design and Infrastructure Services. It provides scanning and sensing services for a variety of project applications where precise data extraction and delivery are needed. Its scanning and sensing capabilities include High Definition Surveys, Aerial Surveys and Underground Service Detection Surveys. It offers a range of spatial services, and utilizes advanced systems to provide specialized imagery and analysis, cartographic plans, geographic information system (GIS) products and custom graphics.

Xanadu Mines Limited is an exploration company. The Company is engaged in the exploration and development of its various mineral exploration projects in Mongolia. The Company focuses on the exploration for copper and gold. The Company operates through the Mongolian exploration projects segment. The Company's projects include Kharmagtai Copper-gold Project, Oyut Ulaan Project and Sharchuluut Project. The Kharmagtai project is located within the Omnogovi Province, approximately 420 kilometers southeast of Ulaanbaatar and approximately 120 kilometers north of the Oyu Tolgoi deposit. The Oyut Ulaan copper-gold project is located in the Dornogovi Province of southern Mongolia, approximately 70 kilometers west of the industrial center of Sainshand. The Sharchuluut project is an early-stage project focused on an advanced argillic (high-sulfidation lithocap) alteration above a deeper porphyry center.

WAM Research Limited is an Australia-based investment company. The Company makes investments in listed companies. The Company's investment objectives are to provide investors a rising stream of fully franked dividends, and achieve a high real rate of return, comprising both income and capital growth, within the risk parameters acceptable to the Directors. The Company engages in investing activities, including cash, term deposits and equity investments. The Company invests in equities listed on the Australian Securities Exchange. The Company provides investors with exposure to a diversified portfolio of undervalued growth companies, which are small-to-medium sized industrial companies listed on the Australian Securities Exchange. The Company provides investors with access to Wilson Asset Management's research-driven process, which focuses on identifying undervalued growth companies. MAM Pty Limited is the investment manager of the Company.

Yojee Limited (Yojee), formerly Southern Crown Resources Limited, is engaged in developing a sharing economy-based logistics technology through the creation of the Yojee delivery network and blockchain technology platform. The Company is engaged in the development of a logistics technology platform to enable mass participation in a sharing economy network to help both carrier and sender. The Company's collaborative economy technology platform focuses to provide on-demand movement of goods and services. The Company's platform aggregates and optimizes logistics businesses. Yojee implements real-time tracking and a blockchain technology payment system. Yojee will connect and enable logistics providers with limited geographical capability. Yojee will also help e-commerce companies. The Company focuses on developing a logistics software to serve small and medium businesses. The Company focuses on the Asia-Pacific region.

Yancoal Australia Limited is a coal miner. The Company is a provider of mine management, marketing, infrastructure and other corporate support services. The Company's segments are New South Wales (NSW) and Queensland (QLD). It produces over 15.5 million tons of saleable thermal and metallurgical coal per annum for export into international markets. It operates over four sites and manages over five others across New South Wales, Queensland and Western Australia. It also manages the Cameby Downs and Premier coal mines in Queensland and Western Australia, respectively on behalf of Yanzhou Coal Mining Company Limited. Its New South Wales region includes the mines of Moolarben and Stratford Duralie, with the Queensland region comprising Yarrabee and the Middlemount Joint Venture. Its measured, indicated and inferred resources are over 2,890 million tons (Mt); recoverable proved and probable reserves are over 600 Mt, and marketable proved and probable reserves are approximately 430 Mt.

West Wits Mining Limited is a mining and exploration company. The Company's principal activities include exploring for gold at the mining tenements situated in South Africa and Papua Province, Indonesia. The Company's segments include South Africa, Indonesia and Australia. The Company is focused on developing its Soweto Cluster Gold Project, located near Johannesburg. The Soweto Cluster project consists of approximately two mining centers, which include the Durban Roodepoort Deep and the Rand Leases on the Northern Edge of the Witwatersrand Basin in the Central Rand Goldfield immediately southwest of the city of Johannesburg. Its Derewo River Gold Project is situated on the Derewo River within the central mountains of the Papua Province, Indonesia. The project is located approximately 110 kilometers north west of Freeport McMoRan's Grasberg complex. The Company's subsidiaries include West Wits Mining SA (Pty) Ltd, West Wits Monarch (Pty) Ltd and PT. NuGold Indonesia.

Xstate Resources Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in oil and natural gas exploration in the United States. The Company operates through oil and gas exploration and evaluation segment. The Company has working interest (WI) in Alvares Prospect, Dempsey Prospect, California AMI Prospects, Rancho-Capay Gas Field and Los Medanos Gas Field, all of which are located in Sacramento Basin onshore Northern California. In addition, the Company holds leases covering oil prospects in the Santa Maria basin. The Company also has an interest in King Brown gold tenement. The Dempsey Prospect's proposed drilling depth is approximately 3,200 meters. The Company's subsidiaries include Bombora Energy Pty Ltd and Calog LLC, which are engaged in oil and gas exploration.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Xped Limited, formerly Raya Group Limited, is engaged in developing and operating an Internet of Things (IoT) technology business. The Company has developed a technology that enables devices to wirelessly communicate with each other. Its Auto Discover Remote Control (ADRC) technology platform facilitates connection of smart phones to electronic devices, enabling users to control all of their electronic devices remotely from an application. It has developed a mini peripheral component interconnect (PCI)-express card that provides the near field communication (NFC) and 802.15.4 communications hardware required by ADRC. It addresses both the consumer and industrial global IoT markets. It offers ADRC technology for Intel IoT Gateway, ADRC Shields for Arduino, Umbo, Equinox and UltraPlug. It holds interests in the Penola Trough and Limestone Coast tenements located in the southeast of South Australia and an interest in the Sokoria Geothermal project located in Flores Island, Indonesia.

Watpac Limited is a construction and civil and mining services company. The Company's segments include Construction, Mining & Civil, and Property. The Construction segment provides building, refurbishment, project management and construction management services across various eastern states in Australia and South Australia. The Mining & Civil segment is engaged in providing contract mining services and civil infrastructure activities for small to medium projects throughout Australia. The Property segment is engaged in development and trading of commercial, residential and industrial properties. Its projects include Mount Magnet Gold Mine, Gold Coast Private Hospital, Ryde Garden, Axehandle Gold Mine, Summer Hill Flour Mill, Cockatoo Island Iron Ore Mining and Kathleen Valley Gold Project. The Company undertakes technical refurbishment projects across a range of areas, including aged care, health, commercial, education, food-related facilities and other construction disciplines.

Wisetech Global Limited is a provider of software solutions to the logistics industry globally. The Company develops, sells and implements software solutions that enable logistics service providers to facilitate the movement and storage of goods and information domestically and internationally. The Company's technology, CargoWise One, is an integrated software solution for logistics service providers that enables its customers to execute logistics transactions and manage their operations on a single database across multiple users, functions, offices, countries and languages. The Company operates its own data centers and delivers its CargoWise One software principally through the cloud. It provides its software as a service, which is accessed by customers. The Company provides its solutions to approximately 6,000 customers across over 125 countries through offices in Australia, New Zealand, China, Singapore, South Africa, the United Kingdom and the United States.

Yanghao International Limited is an Australia-based company, which is focused on the provision of management services to related party entities. The Company is focusing on rebuilding its business operations. The Company's subsidiary is Millenarianism Tower Limited.

Titanium Sands Limited, formerly Windimurra Vanadium Limited, is engaged in mineral exploration. The Company's segments include Australia and Sri Lanka. Under the Sri Lankan Mineral Sands Project, the Company has an interest in Srinel Holdings Limited (Srinel). Srinel, through its subsidiaries, owns approximately 10 exploration licenses (EL) over 350 square kilometers in various coastal districts of Sri Lanka. The Company focuses on the Mannar Island project in Sri Lanka, comprising the 180 and 182 exploration licenses.

Energy World Corporation Ltd (EWC) is an independent energy company engaged in the production and sale of power and natural gas. The Company's principal activities include development, design, construction, operation and maintenance of power stations; development of liquefied natural gas (LNG), design, construction, operation and maintenance of LNG plants and road transport of LNG, and design and development of LNG receiving terminals, and exploration, development and production of gas and oil, design, construction, operation and maintenance of gas, processing plants and gas pipelines. The Company's segments include Oil & Gas, and Power. The Company operates in Australia and Indonesia. The Company is focused on the development of LNG facilities using mid-sized modular LNG trains and regasification facilities. The Company has primary gas and power operations located at Sengkang, South Sulawesi in Indonesia and it also produces gas, power and LNG in Australia.

Wolf Petroleum Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in mineral exploration and examination of new resource opportunities. The Company is a petroleum acreage holder with over 18,000,000 acres in Mongolia. The Company's projects include Sukhbaatar Block (SB), Baruun Urt Block and Jinst Block. The Sukhbaatar Block, which covers approximately 23,074 square kilometers consists of sub-basins, Toson Tolgoi and Talbulag, with an area covering over 3,500 square kilometers. The Baruun Urt (BU) Block, which covers an area of over 10,287 square kilometers is located in a region with proven and producing petroleum systems and is adjoining the Company's SB Block. The Jinst Block covers an area of approximately 41,000 square kilometers and consists of over 12 sub basins. The Jinst Block consists of target basins with over 1,500 square kilometers. The Company's subsidiaries include Wolf Operations Limited, Wolf Investments Pte Limited and MME Iron LLC.

Webjet Limited is engaged in the provision of online travel booking. The Company is engaged in digital travel business providing services in regional consumer markets, as well as global wholesale markets via the online channel. It operates through the segments, including Business to Consumer Travel (B2C Travel) and Business to Business Travel (B2B Travel). The Company's B2C division consists of Webjet, ZUJI and online republic brands. Its B2B division consists of Lots of Hotels and Sunhotels brands. Lots of Hotels brand operates in approximately 25 markets, providing coverage across the Middle East and Africa. Sunhotels brand has over 6,000 directly contracted hotels. It offers its services through the Website, www.webjet.com.au. Its products include cheap flights, hotels, holiday packages, car hire, cruises, exclusives, and travel insurance. It offers cruises, such as P&O Cruises, Princess Cruises, Carnival Cruises, Royal Caribbean Cruises, Celebrity Cruises and Norwegian Cruise Line.

White Cliff Minerals Limited is a mineral exploration company. The Company controls tenement packages in Western Australia's Yilgarn Craton and the Pilbara region, as well as a gold-copper project in Central Asia. The Company's geographic segments include Australia and Kyrgyz. It holds interests in Aucu Gold Project, Merolia Gold and Nickel Gold Project, Chanach copper and gold exploration tenement, Laverton Project, Mt Remarkable Project, Ghan Well Project, Ironstone Range Project, Lake Johnson Project, Irwin Hills Project and Red Flag project. The Aucu Gold project is located in the central Asian Kyrgyz Republic. The Laverton Gold Project consists of 100 square kilometers in the Laverton Greenstone belt. The Merolia nickel and copper project consists of a section of the Merolia greenstone belt southeast of Laverton in the Eastern Goldfield of Western Australia. The Ironstone Gold Project is located in the heart of the Northeastern goldfields of Western Australia.

WPP AUNZ Limited, formerly STW Communications Group Limited, is engaged in advertising and diversified communications operations. The Company provides advertising and communications services for clients through various channels, including television, radio, print, outdoor and electronic forms. Its segments include Advertising, Production and Media, and Diversified Communications. The Advertising, Production and Media segment provides advertising services, television and print production services and media investments for Australia, New Zealand and other countries. The Diversified Communications segment covers a range of marketing communications services. Through its operating companies, it provides a range of services, including advertising and media investment management; data investment management; public relations and public affairs; branding and identity; healthcare communications; direct, digital, promotion and relationship marketing, and specialist communications.

Winmar Resources Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the investment in exploration assets in the Pilbara region of Western Australia and the conduct of exploration activities on those assets and the identification and evaluation of new commercial opportunities. The Hamersley Iron Project is located approximately 50 kilometers northeast of Tom Price in the Pilbara region of Western Australia and contains a channel iron deposit (CID) called the Winmar Iron deposit. The project includes Exploration License E47/1617 and Mining Lease M47/1450. The Lomero gold-copper-silver-zinc project is an advanced exploration project. It is located approximately 60 kilometers north of the deep-water port of Huelva in Andalucia, Spain, within Spain's mineral district, the Iberian Pyrite Belt. It is a tabular volcanogenic massive sulfide (VMS) deposit with the gold grade of any mineral deposit within the Iberian Pyrite Belt.

Yowie Group Limited is a brand licensing company. The Company specializes in the development of consumer products designed to promote learning, understanding and engagement by exploiting its over six Yowie characters. The Company operates through confectionery business segment. The Company employs its rights in the outsourcing of the manufacturing and distribution of the Yowie chocolate confectionery product; in the development of a Yowie digital platform, and Yowie branded licensed consumer products. Yowie confectionery is a character-molded, 28-gram chocolate inclusion product. The Company operates Yowieworld.com, which consists of applications, three-dimensional (3D) games and other fun activities. Yowieworld.com is a multiplatform experience, which lets users build their own virtual sticker book that enables to keep track of their Playmate collection. The Company is focused on distribution of Yowie product in North America, Australia, New Zealand and throughout Asia.

YPB Group Limited offers brand protection and anti-counterfeiting solutions to protect, detect, and connect brands and consumers. The principal activity of the Company is selling, marketing and developing anti-counterfeiting, product authentication and consumer engagement solutions to brand owners across the globe. Its segments include Covert Forensic Products, Digital Solutions and Print Solutions. The Covert Forensic Products are hidden, invisible particles fused into a product or packaging during or after the manufacturing process. The Digital Solutions is an application-based platform designed for governments, brands and consumers to identify, manage, track and report counterfeit or diverted products within supply chains or at point-of sale. The Print Solutions segment is engaged in the provision of anti-counterfeiting solutions to brands and resellers in packaging and labelling. It operates in Australia, People's Republic of China and Hong Kong, Thailand and the United States.

Xero Limited is a software as a service (SaaS) company. The Company is engaged in the provision of a platform for online accounting and business services to small businesses and their advisors. The Company operates through two operating segments: Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), and International. The Company's small business cloud accounting software, Xero, is provided in Australia, New Zealand and the United Kingdom. Xero integrates with over 400 add-on applications allowing people to customize Xero to their needs. Xero includes various features, which include cash flow, invoicing, payments, pay runs, reports, contacts, security, support and mobile. Through its various features, Xero offers online accounting, automatic bank reconciliation, quotes and online training for small businesses. Xero allows access to real-time account information and business tools from any device.

XPD Soccer Gear Group Limited is engaged the designing, developing, manufacturing, distributing and marketing sportswear with a focus on soccer wear under the XPD brand. The Company operates through two segments: Own-brand sales (XPD brand) and Contract third-party sales (OEM). It offers a range of products, consisting of sports footwear, sports apparel, soccer kits and soccer accessories. It also manufactures sports footwear on an original equipment manufacturer (OEM) or original design manufacturer (ODM) basis for international footwear brands. It sells its XPD brand products to independent third-party distributors on a wholesale basis. Through distributors, its distribution network reaches over 1,900 retail outlets throughout China. These retail outlets are either specialty stores, such as shoe stores and sporting goods stores, or concessions in department stores and shopping malls. Its products are also sold through online platforms. It operates in People's Republic of China.

Xref Limited, formerly King Solomon Mines Limited, is engaged in software development for the human resource (HR) industry. The Company is engaged in online candidate referencing. The Company is engaged in leveraging its database to provide predictive analytics, which enable human resource directors to make data-driven decisions. It is also developing products tailored for the United Kingdom market and managing trials for clients in Canada. It automates the practice of obtaining and verifying references that job candidates provide. It transforms phone-based, manual procedure into a cloud-based, electronic process. It allows the users to request references via the Company. The Company requests referee information from candidate. It gathers background information from referees. It analyses candidate and provides report. It offers data governance, fraud prevention, comparable metrics and customized reports.

Zamanco Minerals Limited is an Australia-based company, which continues to seek a transaction of merit capable of becoming the primary undertaking of the Company. The Company focuses on identifying and evaluating a business opportunity. It has undertaken evaluation of a range of prospects in various industries.

WorleyParsons Limited is a professional services business company. The principal activities of the Company consist of providing engineering design and project delivery services, including providing maintenance, support services and advisory services to sectors, which include hydrocarbons; minerals, metals and chemicals, and infrastructure. Its segments include Services, Major Projects, Improve and Advisian. Its geographic segments include Australia, Pacific, Asia and China; Europe, Middle East and Africa, and Americas. It offers a range of services from small studies to the delivery of mega projects. Its OneWay is an integrity management framework. Its EcoNomics is a framework, which includes Sustainable Decisions, Sustainable Project Delivery and Sustainable Operations. It serves multi-national oil and gas, resources and chemicals companies, as well as regionally and locally focused companies, national oil companies and government owned utilities. It operates in over 40 countries.

Yonder & Beyond Group Limited is an Australia-based company, which operates in the information technology industry as a global incubation company. The Company has a portfolio of technology assets with a focus on mobile businesses. The Company's segments include the United Kingdom, United States of America, Australia and All other regions segments. The Company has developed Beyond Media platform. The Company's Beyond Media is a virtual reality and multimedia solution, delivering entertainment and virtual reality experience platforms. Its Beyond Media processes, meets and exceeds the digital rights management (DRM) requirements of content partners in delivering high definition content through its secure platform. The Company's portfolio also includes Boppl application, which is engaged in mobile payments and hospitality technologies, and Gophr, which is an on-demand courier application, which allows users to order a courier, watch its delivery in real time and pay with a single tap.

Weebit Nano Limited, formerly Radar Iron Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in technology development. The Company is involved in developing silicon oxide (SiOx) resistive random access memory (ReRAM) technology. The focus of ReRAM technology is to replace flash memory and is viewed as the flash replacement. The Company's products are used in various applications, such as in computers, consumer electronics, smartphones, tablets, enterprise storage, automotive infotainment and navigation systems, healthcare, wearables and Internet of Things (IoT). The Company's ReRAM technology is also used in data centers, banking and stock exchange transactions, as well as cloud computing. The Company's subsidiaries include Radar Resources Pty Ltd and Radar Uruara Pty Ltd.

World Titanium Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration and evaluation of the Ranobe mineral sands deposit in Madagascar. The Company's mineral sands segment includes its projects in Madagascar, including the Toliara Sands Project and other projects at a less advanced-stage at Ankililoaka, Basibasy and Morombe. The Big Dune area at Morombe contains titanium dioxide (TiO2) ilmenite and zircon. Ankililoaka is located approximately 20 kilometers north of Ranobe mineral sands deposit. Basibasy is located approximately 60 kilometers north of Ranobe mineral sands deposit. The Ranobe deposit is located approximately 40 kilometers north of the port of Toliara in southwestern Madagascar. The mineralized zone at Ranobe is approximately 20 kilometers long, 1 to 2 kilometers wide and includes three mineralized sand units: the upper sand, intermediate sand and lower sand units.

Zeta Resources Limited is a closed end investment company. The Company is engaged in investing in listed and unlisted resource focused investments. Its objective is to maximize total returns for shareholders by identifying and investing in assets and companies where the underlying value is not reflected in the market price. It operates through four segments: Gold, Oil & Gas, Mineral Exploration and Other segments. The Gold segment includes investments in companies, which mine gold. The Oil & Gas segment includes investments in companies, which extract or prospect for oil or gas. The Mineral Exploration segment includes investments in companies, which explore or mine for nickel, copper and other minerals. It invests in a range of resources entities, including those focused on oil and gas, gold and base metals exploration and production. Its subsidiaries include Zeta Energy Pte. Ltd. and Zeta Investments Limited. ICM Limited serves as investment manager for the Company.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Zamia Metals Limited is an Australia-based company engaged in the mineral exploration, primarily for gold, copper and molybdenum within the Clermont region of Central Queensland. The Company's targets at the central Queensland area include Epithermal gold deposits and Porphyry copper-gold deposits. The Company is focused on the exploration of the Belyando gold deposit, in exploration permit for minerals (EPM) 15145 Mazeppa Extended. The Belyando gold deposit is located approximately 2.5 kilometers northeast of the Company's Anthony molybdenum project. It also has interests in Anthony Molybdenum deposit. The Company has porphyry copper-gold targets and has conducted a review of the Mistake Creek, Mount McLaren and Hill 271 targets. Its projects also include Logan Creek, Disney, Amaroo South and Dingo Range.

Zeus Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration for uranium and other metal resources, and the assessment of options for investment in multi-commodity mining assets. The Company has interests in approximately 17 tenements covering approximately 2,400 square kilometers over six project areas in Western Australia. The Company's project areas are prospective for three styles of uranium mineralization: surficial, sandstone and basement-hosted. Its projects include Lake Way Project, Yeelirrie South Project, Narnoo Project, North Musgrave Project, Mortimer Hills Project and Red Rock Project. The Kukabubba Palaeochannel Sub-Project includes tenements E53/1601, 1603 and 1604. The North Musgrave Project comprises a tenement (E69/2362) located in the north Musgrave region in central-eastern Western Australia. The Narnoo Project consists of tenements (E39/1683 and E39/1401, E28/2096 and E28/2097, and E39/1687 and E39/1689) located on the margins of the Eucla Basin.

Zicom Group Limited is engaged in manufacturing deck machinery, offshore structures, gas metering stations, concrete mixers and precision engineered machinery, rental of foundation equipment, supply of medical technology equipment and products, medical technology translation services and services, among others to the offshore marine, oil and gas, electronics, biomedical and agriculture industries. The Company's segments include Offshore Marine, Oil & Gas Machinery, which manufactures and supplies deck machinery, offshore structures for underwater robots and related equipment, parts and services; Construction Equipment, which manufactures and supplies concrete mixers and foundation equipment, including equipment rental, parts and related services; Precision Engineering & Technologies, which manufactures precision and automation equipment, and products and engineering services, among others, and Industrial & Mobile Hydraulics, which supplies hydraulic drive systems, parts and services.

Zeta Petroleum plc (Zeta) is engaged in oil and gas exploration, development and production. The Company has a portfolio of oil and gas assets, which includes various production, development, appraisal and exploration projects in Romania, including Bobocu Gas Field license, Jimbolia Oil Field license, Suceava Concession license and non-exclusive Prospecting Permits. The Bobocu Gas Field is located to the north of the Buzau valley, approximately 20 kilometers northeast of Buzau and over 110 kilometers northeast of Bucharest. The Jimbolia license is located in eastern part of the Pannonian Basin, approximately 40 kilometers west of Timisoara on the Romanian-Serbian border and covers an area of approximately 23.9 square kilometers. The Suceava concession is located on the Moldovian platform, approximately 370 kilometers north of Bucharest and covers an area of over 2,403 square kilometers. It holds over 6,000 square kilometers of non-exclusive prospecting permits.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Zenith Minerals Limited is engaged in mineral exploration in Australia and Turkey (Europe), and the United States. The Company has hard rock pegmatite lithium projects in Australia and the United States, in addition to the gold projects in Australia and Turkey, and the Develin Creek copper-zinc-gold-silver massive sulfide project in Queensland. The Company's San Domingo project covers lithium-bearing pegmatite dyke swarm that intrudes Proterozoic mafic gneiss host rocks that are in turn locally overlain by Tertiary age volcanic and sedimentary rocks. The 1,000-meter long Guney (South) Zone gold-in-soil anomaly is located approximately 500 meters southeast of the Kuzey Zone. The Mt Minnie project consists of an exploration license. Its projects also include Red Lake Manganese Mineral Resource, Lockeridge Manganese Mineral Resource, Mt Alexander Iron Mineral Resource and Mt Alexander West Iron Mineral Resource. The Mt Alexander Project is located in Western Australia.

ZipTel Limited, formerly Skywards Limited, is a telecommunications company. The Company focuses on providing international roaming and calling solutions to the consumer. The Company operates through two segments: prepaid travel sim card services (AussieSim) and mobile based VOIP communication services (Zipt). Its AussieSim segment offers prepaid travel subscriber identity module (sim) card to the overseas travel market. AussieSim offers consumers discounted roaming rates for talk, text and data usage. AussieSim offers short message services (SMS) based top up technology, along with a call forwarding platform and an online trading platform. The Company's Zipt segment offers ZipT, a mobile-based voice over Internet protocol (VOIP) communication application that allows consumers to SMS and to make international calls from their mobile. ZipT can be installed on any smartphone and enables consumers to retain their existing phone number and service provider.

WestStar Industrial Limited, formerly Antares Mining Limited, is an Australia-based company, which is principally engaged in the mineral exploration and examination of new opportunities, which resulted in the acquisition of Precast Australian Pty Ltd. The Company operates in the mining exploration for phosphate, iron ore and copper segment. Icon Gold Pty Limited is the Company's subsidiary.

Zenitas Healthcare Ltd, formerly BGD Corporation Ltd, is engaged in the acquisition and operation of medical clinics in Melbourne, Victoria. The Company is planning for further acquisitions in the healthcare sector. The Company is engaged in the disposal of all interests in the Euroa Steel Plant Project Joint Venture in Gladstone, Queensland. The Company's subsidiaries include BGD Medical Centres Pty Ltd., Modern Medical Group Pty Ltd and Modern Medical Administration Trust.

zipMoney Limited offers point-of-sale credit and digital payment services to consumers and merchants. The Company provides a range of integrated Retail Finance solutions to small, medium and enterprise businesses across various industries, both online and in-store. The Company offers its services primarily to the retail, education, health and travel industries. Its products include zipMoney and zipPay. zipMoney is classified as a continuing line of credit and generally applied to various ticket purchases where a promotional interest-free period is applied, between 6 to 24 months. zipPay is a no interest ever digital shopping account and generally applied to various ticket purchases, such as fashion, accessories, food and hospitality. It supports prime, near prime and emerging prime borrowers by providing those customers with a revolving unsecured line of credit to finance their transactions. Its platform utilizes a range of variables to deliver real-time consumer credit responses.

Zimplats Holdings Limited is engaged in the business of producing platinum group metals (PGMs) and associated metals, which include nickel, gold, copper, cobalt and silver mined from the Great Dyke in Zimbabwe. Its segments include Platinum, Palladium, Gold, Rhodium, Nickel, Ruthenium, Iridium, Silver, Copper and Cobalt. The Company, through its subsidiary Zimbabwe Platinum Mines (Private) Limited, a producer of PGMs, is engaged in exploiting the ore bodies located on the Great Dyke in Zimbabwe. The Company has a Mineral Resource base of approximately 223.6 million ounces 4E. The Company operates approximately four underground mines and an open pit mine, which supply ore to three concentrator modules (two at Ngezi and the third one at Selous). Three of the four underground mines are operating at full production while the fourth one is under re-development. The Company sells white matte (a concentrate of metals), which consists of platinum, palladium, rhodium, gold and nickel.

ZYL Limited is a metallurgical coal exploration and development company with two projects in South Africa. The Companys flagship projects are the Mbila and Kangwane projects in South Africa, located close to rail, port, power and water infrastructure. The Mbila Project is located approximately 150 kilometer north west of the Richards Bay Coal Terminal. The Mbila Project consists of a Mining Right covering 19,180ha (Mbila Mining Right Area) and a Prospecting Right covering 52,946 hectares (Msebe Prospecting Right Area). The Kangwane Central Project is located in South Africas Mpumalanga province. The Kangwane Central Project also has a Joint Ore Reserves Committee (JORC) Code compliant probable reserves of 26.7 metric tons. The Kangwane South Project is located in the Mpumalanga Province of South Africa, approximately 150 kilometers from the coast to the Matola Terminal at Maputo Port in Mozambique and approximately 25 kilometers to the south of the Companys Kangwane Central Project

Zinc of Ireland NL, formerly Global Metals Exploration NL, is a mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activities include mineral exploration and project evaluation. The Company's projects include Kildare Project, which is located in County Kildare, approximately 40 kilometers south-west of Dublin; Ballinasloe Project, which is located in County Galway, over 50 kilometers east of Galway/Carnmore on the Glentaun-Cloonark Regional Structure; Navan Project, which is located approximately 15 kilometers south-east of the Navan Tara mine; Sligo Project, which is located over four kilometers north of Sligo in the western province of Connacht; Monaghan Project, which is located approximately 20 kilometers south-east of Monaghan in the eastern portion of the Longford-Down Inlier; Cork Project, which is located over 15 kilometers south-west of Cork, and Galway Project, which is located approximately 25 kilometers north-west of Galway in the Neoproterozoic Dalradian Supergroup.

Zyber Holdings Limited, formerly Dourado Resources Limited, is engaged in the development and sale of computer hardware, software and services of secure file synchronization and sharing solution in Canada. The Company enables businesses to transact, share data and collaborate across multiple devices and operating systems all within a centralized platform. The Company provides a platform to share and collaborate on sensitive data over open networks with anyone, on any device while eliminating the negligent end user as a threat. The files are accessed by end users through encrypted streaming. The end user can edit file/collaborate with others. The Company's subsidiaries include Zyber Secure Mobile Solutions Inc. and 1050494 B.C. Ltd.

Zambezi Resources Limited is engaged in the exploration for minerals. The Company is engaged in the exploration for copper and gold in sub-Saharan Africa. It is engaged in developing its large scale Kangaluwi Copper Project and the continued exploration for commercially and economically viable copper in Zambia for profit. Its Kangaluwi Copper Project is covered by approximately 245 square kilometers Mining license area ML 15547. Its Kangaluwi Copper Project consists of the Kangaluwi, Chisawa and Kalulu prospects. Its subsidiaries include Mwembeshi Resources (Bermuda) Limited, Mwembeshi Resources Limited, Zambezi Resources (Australia) Pty Ltd and Makoma Resources Limited.

Z Energy Limited is a New Zealand-based company engaged in supplying fuel to retail and commercial customers. For motorists, the Company offers fuels, such as ZX Premium Unleaded, Z91 Unleaded, Z Bio D Biodiesel and Z Diesel. The Company also operates Z shop at approximately 200 locations across New Zealand. The Z shop offers food, Z Espress coffee, gift cards, discount vouchers and bathrooms. For business, the Company offers fuels, such as Z Diesel Emission Cleaner, diesel, aviation fuel, marine fuel and Z Bio D biodiesel. The Company also supplies bulk fuel to trucking companies, airlines, transport firms, construction companies, power generators, farmers, loggers and mining operations. The Company also supplies bitumen to roading companies. The Company also offers Z Card for business customers. The Company's subsidiaries include Harbour City Property Investments Limited, Z Energy ESPP Trustee Limited and Z Energy LTI Trustee Limited.

Zinc of Ireland NL, formerly Global Metals Exploration NL, is a mineral exploration company. The Company's principal activities include mineral exploration and project evaluation. The Company's projects include Kildare Project, which is located in County Kildare, approximately 40 kilometers south-west of Dublin; Ballinasloe Project, which is located in County Galway, over 50 kilometers east of Galway/Carnmore on the Glentaun-Cloonark Regional Structure; Navan Project, which is located approximately 15 kilometers south-east of the Navan Tara mine; Sligo Project, which is located over four kilometers north of Sligo in the western province of Connacht; Monaghan Project, which is located approximately 20 kilometers south-east of Monaghan in the eastern portion of the Longford-Down Inlier; Cork Project, which is located over 15 kilometers south-west of Cork, and Galway Project, which is located approximately 25 kilometers north-west of Galway in the Neoproterozoic Dalradian Supergroup.

WPG Resources Limited is an Australia-based resource company. The Company's principal activities include mining, exploration, evaluation and development of its precious metal, base metal, iron ore and coal projects located in South Australia, as well as the pursuit of new mining opportunities in any jurisdiction. Its segments include exploration and production. It holds its gold prospects through three subsidiaries: Challenger Gold Operations Pty Ltd (CGO), Tarcoola Gold Pty Ltd and Tunkillia Gold Pty Ltd. The Company focuses on its three South Australian gold projects (Challenger, Tarcoola and Tunkillia). CGO holds mineral lease (ML) 6103, and miscellaneous purpose leases (MPL) 63, 65 and 66 on which the Challenger Mine is located. The Tarcoola project is located on ML 6455, which is surrounded by EL 5355, both of which are owned by Tarcoola Gold Pty Ltd. It has four mineral leases at Tarcoola. The Tunkillia 223 deposit lies in the north western part of the Tunkillia tenement block.

Vital Metals Limited is an Australia-based company, which is engaged in mineral exploration in Australia and Burkina Faso, West Africa. The Company has two segments being mineral exploration and prospecting for minerals in Australia and Burkina Faso. The Company holds interest in Watershed Tungsten Project, which is located in Queensland. The Watershed Tungsten Project is approximately 115 kilometers northwest of Cairns, together with over seven prospective exploration tenements covering an area of approximately 870 square kilometers. The Company's Doulnia Gold Project is located in southern Burkina Faso, West Africa. Its Kollo Gold Project is located on the Doulnia tenement. Its Boungou South Gold Prospect is located approximately six kilometers to the southeast of Kollo Gold Prospect. Its Nabenia Zinc Prospect is located on the southeast margin of the Tiebele Dome. Its Loubel Zinc Prospects are located on the southern side of the Tiebele Dome.

Valmec Limited is an energy and infrastructure services company providing equipment, construction, commissioning and maintenance services to oil and gas, resources and infrastructure sectors throughout Australia. The Company's principal activities include process services engineering, procurement and construction; mining services multi-discipline construction; gas turbine compression and metering; petrochemical and mining fabrication; electrical and underground services; earthworks and civil engineering, and asset preservation, service and maintenance. It provides services across a range of infrastructure sectors, including urban development, water, transport and industrial maintenance. Its offerings include structural mechanical piping; gas compression products; gas processing products, and completions and commissioning. Its subsidiaries include Valmec Australia Pty Ltd, Core Plant and Equipment Pty Ltd and Valmec Services Pty Ltd.

Westfield America Trust is engaged in the ownership, development, design, construction, asset management, leasing and marketing activities undertaken with respect to its the United States portfolio of retail properties. The Company's segments include Property Investments, Property and Project Management, and Corporate. The Property investments segment includes net property income from existing shopping centers and completed developments, revaluation of existing centers and other operational expenses. The Property and Project Management segment includes external fee income from third parties, primarily property management and development fees, and associated business expenses. The Corporate segment includes unallocated corporate entity expenses.

WHL Energy Limited is an Australia-based oil and gas company. The principal activities of the Company are oil and gas exploration and the assessment of new investment opportunities. The Company's asset portfolio consists of conventional oil and gas projects, focusing specifically on opportunities within offshore Australia. The Company's segments include Oil and Gas Exploration Australia, and Corporate Entity. The Company holds interest in VIC/P67 (La Bella). VIC/P67 lies in the offshore Otway Basin, approximately 200 kilometers west-southwest of Melbourne, Victoria. The Company discovers and commercializes the gas resources in VIC/P67, including the undeveloped La Bella gas discovery. The Company's subsidiaries include PetroQuest International Seychelles Limited, PetroQuest International Incorporated and Indian Ocean Petroleum Holdings Pty Limited.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Woodside Petroleum Ltd (Woodside) is an oil and gas company. The Company is engaged in hydrocarbon exploration, evaluation, development, production and marketing. It operates in three segments: Producing comprising North West Shelf (NWS) Project, Pluto Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG) and Australia Oil; Development comprising Browse floating liquefied natural gas (FLNG) and Wheatstone LNG, and Other. Its Other segment comprises the activities undertaken by trading and shipping, the United States, Exploration, International, Canada and Sunrise Business Units. Its North West Shelf Project is engaged in the exploration, evaluation, development, production and sale of liquefied natural gas, pipeline natural gas, condensate, liquefied petroleum gas and crude oil from the North West Shelf ventures. Its Pluto LNG project is engaged in exploration, evaluation, development, production and sale of liquefied natural gas and condensate in assigned permit areas.
Oil & Gas Exploration and Production - NEC

Wangle Technologies Limited, formerly VTX Holdings Limited, is an Australia-based company engaged in development of Web optimization technology. The Company is involved in the development and commercialization of the ShieldLiner System technology. The Company is focused on the commercialization of its consumer offering, mobile application Wangle, and enterprise offerings. The Company has developed a virtual software technology, which optimizes data usage on Web platforms, delivering data savings and enhanced speed to the end user on any mobile, tablet or desktop device. The Company's Wangle technology combines a range of advanced subsystems to deliver unparalleled acceleration and data optimization. Its technology optimizes, rebuilds and compresses data. VTX Holdings (Singapore) Pte. Ltd is the Company's subsidiary.

Wollongong Coal Limited is a mining company, which owns and operates the Russell Vale Colliery and Wongawilli Colliery in the Southern Coalfields Region of New South Wales. The Company is engaged in expanding and developing Russell Vale colliery; mining and producing coal, and selling and exporting coal. The Company operates through the segment of coal mining, coal preparation and export of coal. The Russell Vale Colliery is located approximately 10 kilometers north of Wollongong and approximately 60 kilometers south of Sydney. The Russell Vale Colliery mine is spread over approximately 6,420 hectares and comprises over three coal seams, including the Bulli, Balgownie and Wongawilli seams. Wongawilli Colliery is located approximately 15 kilometers south-west of Wollongong and 80 kilometers south-west of Sydney. Its mines are situated in close proximity to the Port Kembla Coal Terminal. Jindal Steel and Power Limited (JSPL) is its ultimate parent company.

xTV Networks Limited is a media network company. The Company is engaged in developing technologies for online networks, deploying xTV online networks for enterprises and managing interactive online television (TV) networks for enterprises. The Company allows businesses to set up multi-channel online networks that integrate branded video and user-generated content with other real-time feeds. Its products include Cloud TV Networks, Digital Signage and Premium Channels. Its Cloud TV Networks aggregate and organize video, Web and social media feeds into a single destination and displays them on any device that supports a Web browser, such as high-definition televisions (HDTVs), computers, tablets or smartphones. Digital Signage delivers xTV Cloud TV Networks wirelessly (or wired) to any HDTV, monitor, projector, kiosk, or screen with an available high-definition multimedia interface (HDMI) port. Its Premium Channels are ready-to-use, regularly-curated video content from major sources.

Zelda Therapeutics Limited, formerly Gleneagle Gold Limited, is engaged in mineral exploration of gold and base metals, and the assessment of investment opportunities. Its projects include Milly Well, Berring Pool, Chester North and Chester South. It operates over four leases on its projects, which are located in the Cue Mineral Field. Three of the leases are contiguous being E20/742 and P20/2095 and P20/2096. The fourth lease, EL20/833, is situated to the north west of Milly Bore. The Milly Bore project is situated within the Archaean Meekatharra-Wydgee Greenstone Belt. The principal deposits in Milly Bore are Black Swan, Black Swan South, Golden Gate, Chieftain and Rheingold. The Berring Pool project covers an area of approximately 16 square Kms and is also situated within the Archaean Meekatharra-Wydgee Greenstone Belt. The Chester North project covers an area of over 154 hectares and Chester South covers an area of over 131 hectares.

Xenith IP Group Limited is an Australia-based holding company. The Company's principal activities are the protection, management, commercialization and enforcement of intellectual property (IP) rights on behalf of its clients. It comprises the Shelston IP business, which include Shelston IP Pty Limited, a specialist IP practice; Shelston IP Lawyers Pty Limited, a specialist IP Law practice, and Xenith IP Services Pty Limited, an entity providing shared services to the Company. It provides a range of IP services for a spectrum of clients in Australia, New Zealand and the rest of the world. It provides IP services relating to patents, trademarks, copyrights, circuit layouts, trade secrets and industrial designs. The Company serves over 3,000 clients across the globe. The Company serves national and multinational corporations and research institutes; foreign associates, including offshore IP and law firms; small to medium enterprises (SMEs); start-up companies, and entrepreneurs.

Western Mining Network Limited is engaged in the acquisition and exploration, and evaluation of resource-based projects within Indonesia. The Company operates through two segments: mineral exploration and treasury. Its geographical segments include Australia and Indonesia. It focuses on projects, including coal, base metals and gold. It holds interest in an on-going project, Persada Gold Project, in Central Sulawesi for gold. The Persada Gold Project covers an area of approximately 5,000 hectares in Central Sulawesi, Indonesia. Its projects also include over three gold prospective projects, which include Defiance, Mt Howe and Unknown. Its Defiance project is located on the east limb of the regional southeast-plunging Margaret Anticline. Its Mt Howe project lies within the S extension of the Laverton Tectonic Zone, approximately 160 kilometers northeast of Kalgoorlie. Its Unknown project is located over 30 kilometers east of Kalgoorlie in the Bulong District of the Eastern Goldfields.

XTD Limited is a service provider to Out-of-Home Advertising (OOH Advertising) sector. The Company focuses on operating in cross track digital media installation and service provision. Its cross track digital media installation uses billboard-sized light-emitting diode (LED) coupled to various forms of content to metro train commuters. It operates approximately 30 XTD digital screens across over three underground rail stations in Melbourne. Through its XTD system, Lunalite designed a solution, which gives the advertising market to provide digital advertising to rail commuters from a cross track location. It installs home screens to help EMBARK, which is a smartphone application that allows commuters to plan their journey across various forms of public transport and interact with content on network of digital out of home screens. Its cross track digital media installations provide information for rail commuters, by station, including local weather, event details and news.
